product_title: Zinus 14 Inch Elite SmartBase Mattress Foundation / for Big & Tall / Extra Strong Support / Platform Bed Frame / Box Spring Replacement / Sturdy / Quiet Noise Free / Non-Slip, Twin
review_headline: A solid VICTORY for an over-crowded apartment!
review_body:
I've been looking for ways to increase storage space. I live in a 2 bed 1 bath apartment with my girlfriend, and our two Siberian Huskies, and another couple. Needless to say, we are all packed in there like sardines! Now, let's be honest here... 50% of the space is for the other couple, 60% of the space is for the pups, and the other 30% is my girlfriends. The numbers don't lie... we definitely have no more space at this point! I bought this for me, in hopes that I can re-claim a percentage of space for myself. Bed risers just weren't going to do the trick, and wooden framed with built-in drawers are much out of my price range. For me, this was a solid meet-me-in-the-middle solution.

FIRST IMPRESSIONS:
The actual storage space of each of the two "cavities" from floor to the under-bars measures at about 12-1/2"tall x 30"wide x 60"deep. I've very pleased to say that I was able to fit EIGHT (count em'), EIGHT large 12" storage tubs under the bed! The tubs were about 8 bucks each at our local "w-mart". We have gotten rid of the box spring completely, without any issues so far, and we feel no difference in comfort without it. Our mattress is an old 8" coil spring with a separate 3" memory foam mattress topper on the mattress. I could see how some may say a solid 8" memory foam mattress might sag through the spaces. Some have put down cardboard for that, but I didn't find it necessary with our mattress. So far, we've been sleeping on this bed for a few weeks and it seems very solid, give or take a husky and some horseplay. It's very quiet, and I have not hears and creeks or squeaks from the frame as of yet.

My worries were put aside when we finally received it in the mail. I was reading others reviews and was initially concerned about the frame arriving damaged during shipping as others have stated. Although, the box did arrive with a few minor bumps and bruises, there was zero damage and no rust to actual frame. I LOVE that this frame folds up, that's a really nice convenience. It took me all of 20 minutes to un-box and setup this frame where the old one used to be. There was very little assembly that I actually had to do. I was surprised that I did not need any tools what-so-ever. The only thing that confused me for a moment was the brackets that lock the outer legs in place. Those needed to be rotated PRIOR to fully folding out the legs, and then they lined up just fine. The cross-bars are not flush with the other length-wise support bars, and that is a bit of a pet peeve for me, but not that big of a deal. I'm definitely satisfied, and I would recommend this product.ctual frame. I LOVE that this frame folds up, that's a really nice convenience. It took me all of 20 minutes to un-box and setup this frame where the old one used to be. There was very little assembly that I actually had to do. I was surprised that I did not need any tools what-so-ever. The only thing that confused me for a moment was the brackets that lock the outer legs in place. Those needed to be rotated PRIOR to fully folding out the legs, and then they lined up just fine. The cross-bars are not flush with the other length-wise support bars, and that is a bit of a pet peeve for me, but not that big of a deal. I'm definitely satisfied, and I would recommend this product.

product_title: Sauder Carson Forge Desk - Washington Cherry
review_headline: I swear by Sauder -- this is my 30th piece (no kidding)
review_body:
I love Sauder pieces. This desk was my 30th piece, and I just ordered my 31st. I call Sauder the Cadillac of Walmart. Their attention to detail is astonishing. It is par for the course to have a few pieces arrive damaged in shipping, and yes Sauder, obviously damaged in the factory BEFORE packaging. But Sauder makes it right (usually, see below). Just hop on their website and order the replacement pieces you need, free of charge. Set aside the project for a week. My parts' orders arrive within a week.

This particular desk is intricately designed and looks fabulous. It took more time than usual. It is a solid, well-designed desk which has a lot of pieces. It astounds me to see people criticize Sauder for furniture that does not come out well -- it is THEMSELVES who are the poor assemblers! I have assembled three or four other companies' furniture, and all fared poorly, and we were careful and conscientious.

The Carson Forge collection is a family's dream furniture. When I get a knick in it, I take a black magic marker to it, then fast smudge the black using Kleenex. That is all you do to make an imperfection disappear, presto chango. Plus, before assembly, take Carson Forge pieces and with a magic marker, blacken all the edges, smudging with Kleenex.

Sauder is now middle-class furniture. It is what people can afford. Sauder, for the most part, cares about its customers. Only one time did I have a bad experience -- for an armoire, more than six pieces came damaged. Sauder balks when the number of pieces to send out free is over their quota. A customer service rep \\"Tanya\\" contacted me saying that she felt, in couched terminology, that I was lying about how many pieces arrived to me damaged (number of replacement pieces), and that I had to send them photos. I told her no (and in no uncertain terms, that she could shove it). She did not like that and threw it back in my face, refusing to send replacements, more than willing to let a several hundred dollar unassembled armoire ([[ASIN:B001DKTKDO Sauder Harbor View Armoire - Antiqued White]]) rot in my hallway. My husband intervened, complied, and emailed pictures. It was humiliating and degrading -- overall a bad experience. But that was unusual. I hope to not have a repeat of that. If it happens again, I will be contacting their Chairman of the Board and President, and scream bloody murder. It may be that people abuse their free replacement service, but why the heck does Sauder not take note when I contact them that I had (at the time) over 25 pieces of their furniture in my home, and I am not a crank. Jeez and criminy!

Take a trip to any furniture store. Bring a flashlight. Go up to a wall unit, open a cabinet, tap on side walls, bottoms of drawers, very top of the unit. Much of the woods there are 1/4\\" thick. And for the 9X less, you can buy Sauder, and to tell you the truth, Sauder looks just as nice, and you won't go broke. What costs $5,000 at a furniture store could only be $500 buying Sauder. Price out wall units, and you will see what I mean.

Anyway, Sauder is a super company, most of the time.al hundred dollar unassembled armoire ([[ASIN:B001DKTKDO Sauder Harbor View Armoire - Antiqued White]]) rot in my hallway. My husband intervened, complied, and emailed pictures. It was humiliating and degrading -- overall a bad experience. But that was unusual. I hope to not have a repeat of that. If it happens again, I will be contacting their Chairman of the Board and President, and scream bloody murder. It may be that people abuse their free replacement service, but why the heck does Sauder not take note when I contact them that I had (at the time) over 25 pieces of their furniture in my home, and I am not a crank. Jeez and criminy!

Take a trip to any furniture store. Bring a flashlight. Go up to a wall unit, open a cabinet, tap on side walls, bottoms of drawers, very top of the unit. Much of the woods there are 1/4\\" thick. And for the 9X less, you can buy Sauder, and to tell you the truth, Sauder looks just as nice, and you won't go broke. What costs $5,000 at a furniture store could only be $500 buying Sauder. Price out wall units, and you will see what I mean.

Anyway, Sauder is a super company, most of the time.

product_title: 8" Night Therapy Spring Mattress & Bi-Fold® Box Spring Set
review_body:
A full size mattress is approximately 72-inches long by 54-inches wide, and this set was advertised as being 8-inches thick. When this set arrived, in two boxes, I went back to the listing thinking that I had misunderstood the listing.

The box for the spring was only 54-inches by 47-inches by 5-inches. I felt that there was no way an 8-inch spring could fit in it. I was certainly surprised when we unfolded the spring and it expanded itself to a full size and 8-inch thickness. I did not look closely to see how this transformation was accomplished, but just looked at it in wonder.

Similarly, the mattress box measured 18-inches by 18-inches by 39-inches. Again, certainly not large enough for a full size mattress of 8-inches thickness. Once again I was totally surprised. The mattress was rolled into a tight roll. When we removed it from the box and unrolled it on the bed, it self-expanded to its full size.

I have been sleeping on it for about two weeks now, and this is my impression. As advertised, it is a firm mattress set, but with enough "give" to make it very comfortable. The 8-inch thickness of the springs and the mattress mean that the top is 18-inches from the bed frame. For some shorter people, it may make getting into bed a bit more challenging. As arthritis is destroying my joints and spine, this may become a problem for me.

Over all, I recommend this set.

product_title: East West Furniture VANC7-OAK-C 7-Piece Dining Table Set
review_headline: Instead of embedding a bolt or connector into the bottom of the seat body like it is in the body of the chair
review_body: The construction of the table is solid. All the components fit together correctly. However, the chairs pose a problem. Connecting the seat onto the chair is a total disaster. Instead of embedding a bolt or connector into the bottom of the seat body like it is in the body of the chair, there is only a set of wood screws to work with. The screws are screwed in less than 1/16th of an inch into the seat which is not enough length to hold the seat in place securely.  Also, there is a tremendous problem positioning the seat onto the structure of the chair. You are left to guess at where to position the seat and where ever you position the seat it still does not line up correctly. East West definitely dropped the ball on this one. Fitting the seat onto the chair is total guess work and it can never be positioned correctly. East West put all the burden on the assembler. This problem could have been solved if East West had  embedded bolts or connectors into the body of the seat bottom.

product_title: Winsome Trading Hamilton Double Drop Leaf Dining Table
review_body:
I live in a small apartment, and like many small apartments, this one doesn't have a separate dining area. I have a tiny corner of the living room with which to place a dining table – so I really needed one that was nice and compact. However, I also wanted one that was big enough to serve as extra table space for when I'm working on prepping a larger meal (because, yes, the kitchen is tiny, too). This was a bit of dilemma before I struck on the idea of getting a table with drop leaves. Unfortunately, it seems that smaller tables with drop leaves are somewhat hard to find, but after much searching, I came across this table, the "Winsome Wood Hamilton Double Drop Leaf Dining Table."

The first thing I love about it is its smaller footprint – it measures just 30" by 26" across with the leaves down, and 30" by 42" across with the leaves fully extended (do keep in mind, though, if you happen to be trying to jam this into some tiny niche, that when the leaves are down they still take up some space while hanging, so the table is more like 30" by 28" wide). Also, I like the tiny drawer. It's not really big enough to hold much, but I appreciate the effort at putting in a bit of storage. Plus, it kinda makes the desk look almost like a writing desk, so I could see this table serving multiple functions, making it a nice multi-purpose piece. Speaking of versatility, I also like how the table keeps to a simple, classic style without being too boring (the tapered legs give it some visual interest), to where it could look equally well with a contemporary decorating scheme or a more traditional one.

In terms of quality, I should mention that the leaves are sturdy and stable (very much so) when extended. What's also awesome is the fact that the table is made out of actual solid wood (with the exception of the interior of the drawer, which I'm pretty sure is made of some sort of composite. Color-wise, it's pretty spot-on to the online picture, and I'd describe it as a walnut color (just like the listing does). The finish is also pretty good, at least on the top and legs. The underside of the table isn't very well-sanded (feels rough), and I can tell that they put a thinner coat of varnish on it. So, that's clearly where they cheaped out. Still, for a table that's made of real wood for this price point, I'm not going to complain.

Overall I'd have to say this table is a fantastic value for what you're getting. It's solid wood, has a reasonably decent finish, is sturdy, and is attractive, all for the price of $120 (as of the time of writing this review). You really can't beat that, and if you are desperately searching for a tiny dining table for a small space that still looks nice, then this really is a great choice.

Update: Well, a few days have past, and I've noticed that it now has a couple scratches in the top finish (despite treating my new table carefully). They are relatively small, but this is still disappointing. It means that the top coat of varnish/polyurethane/whatever is rather thin and not very protective. As such, I'm downgrading my original rating to four stars. It's still a decent table for the price, but I'm not sure how it will hold up over a couple years (if it gets super scratched up but is still a functional table, I may choose to refinish it). I'll certainly update if things get worse. For now, though, I'm still reasonably pleased with it.icture, and I'd describe it as a walnut color (just like the listing does). Overall I'd have to say this table is a fantastic value for what you're getting. It's solid wood, has a reasonably decent finish, is sturdy, and is attractive, all for the price of $120 (as of the time of writing this review). product_title: Arctic Dreams 10" Cooling Gel Mattress Made in the USA
review_body:
I decided to get the arctic dreams 10 inch cooling gel foam mattress by DreamFoam Bedding. Here's what I think about it.

* Queen mattress
* 10 inch
* made in the USA
* cooling gel foam
* 3 inches of gel foam

When this box was delivered I was highly skeptical. It honestly didn't look at the size of a large twin. We unleashed it from its packaging. With in two minutes it had expanded to be a 10 inch mattress. It was truly amazing. I'm still scratching my head over that one.

Some people are going to doubt buying a mattress over the Internet. I had the same thoughts myself. This mattress is made in the USA that's some reassurance in itself. It is absolutely everything it advertises to be with no doubts. It consists of high quality materials. If I was to need a mattress in the future I will definitely purchase from this company again.

I have been sleeping on it now for 10 days. I wanted to wait a bit to ensure I had enough experience to write this review. In my entire life this is the best mattress I have ever purchased. My job entails standing on concrete floor. I tend to have lower back problems. Quickly within two days I realized I was not having those pains. I was no longer contorting my legs to sleep comfortably in my old traditional mattress. It's as simple as this my pain was gone. This mattress cradles you. My old mattress was simply flat and firm. There is a vast difference from the two. I am now enjoying a relaxing quality sleep.

I understand that gel foam mattresses can get quite hot. I have in no way experienced that with this mattress. You can see I purchased it in August. That is the hottest weather month we experience in Kentucky. I have slept cool and comfortably every night.

Don't wait until you're 43 to find out what a good nights sleep can do for you. You deserve to be comfortable and have quality sleep. I highly recommend this for everyone. It is absolutely worth every penny. This company is able to provide a higher quality mattress for a reasonable price because of using Amazon.

***** It is January 19, 2016 currently. I am still in love with this mattress. I have the same quality of comfort today as when it arrived. I was a bit skeptical about the gel foam flattening. It is a lofty as ever. This mattress still amazes me.

I purchased this mattress at a discount in exchange for my honest unbiased review. product_title: SmartMotion Executive SwingChair (black)
review_headline: The only chair I can use for long periods at a desk due to spinal problems
review_body:
I've used this chair for 8 years now. Mine is starting to wear out (nothing that is irreplaceable, the material on the arm rests wore down, and I'd like a taller gas lift, etc).

I've been looking around for parts for the chair for awhile and am not having much luck. It appears the older model (the one pictured) was discontinued awhile back. Luckily the 2 things that need work are not too hard to do without the official parts. I will just re-upholster the arms and I believe I can find a compatible generic gas lift.

So why bother to review? Because this chair is solid (I weigh 250-275, varied throughout the years) and will last you a long time. And NO ONE else seems to offer this swinging seat base. Understandable as it requires a lot of metal to make it that strong and design companies don't want to deal with a lot of heavy shipping (and it isn't the prettiest thing in the world). However this seat literally makes the difference for me to be able to sit at my computer or not after many spinal surgeries and some really ugly spinal complications.

For my specifics, I've got 4 fused levels in my lumbar spine, 2 in my cervical spine, as well as a condition called Adhesive Arachnoiditis (complication from a surgery).

If you have a bad back, you'll be amazed what allowing your legs to adjust regularly does for your ability to stay comfortable. Do you ever ride in a car with power seats and find yourself adjusting the tilt of the seat throughout the drive due to back aches? That is what you get to do here, but easily and as many times as you'd like.

And the chair back is shaped well and has LOTS of height and depth (distance from the chair center) adjustability.

They still make the newer version (which I found less comfortable), but even that is becoming harder to find. If you are on the fence, get it. Don't wait too long.

product_title: Coaster Home Furnishings 201991KE Country King Bed, Cappuccino
review_headline: I'll start by saying I love the bed frame and the look!
review_body: I'll start by saying I love the bed frame and the look!  The reason for 4 stars instead of 5 is the matter of a railing reinforcement that is needed before placing a split king 9" foundation and 14 " heavy new beauty rest mattress on the railing.  Be advise one may want to reinforce the rails and footing under the rails with heavier wood if you have purchased the king version of this bed frame and if you intend to use a split king foundation.  The bed frame came in three boxes, was packed well, not damaged and fairly easy to put together.  The average person should not have a problem putting this bed frame together in a three or four hours.  You will be able to see once you put the bed together that the support railings and support feet that go across the side bed frame rails at the bottom of the bed to support the foundation and mattress look very lite and flimsy; go with your instinct....they are lite and flimsy and the support feet that are visible from the side underneath look funny and do not match the bed frame.  The rest of the bed frame, headboard, footboard, side bed rails, and the actual bed frame legs are extremely sturdy!  The support railings are made of pine wood and measure approximately 3/4" x 2".  I did not count them; but I believe there are eight horizontal rails.  My suggestion, replace these rails with 1" x 2" or 2" x 4" boards and replace the support feet with 4"x4" posts cut off and stained to match the finish of your frame.  We did this after the first night we set up and put the new bed mattress and split foundation on it collapsed with the lite and flimsy support rails and support feet.  After replacing the support rails and support feet with sturdier rails and feet, it is great...and does not move a bit (solid as a rock)!  Again, overall, I love the bed frame for the look and the price and the quality.  The only downfall is the lite and flimsy support rails and support feet under rails.

review_headline: Don't expect to disassemble this bed for your next move.
review_body: Got the right bed with the right color and arrived on time in great condition.  One wooden pin was missing, so I had to make a trip to the local hardware store and spend $2 for a replacement.  Overall, it looks like the advertised picture and I got the product I ordered.  However, the setup was painful.  There was over 50 screws and little parts.  Most of the screws were to be screwed directly into the wood (no pre-drilled holes).  The sheer number of small screws and no pre-drilled holes means good luck trying to disassemble this bed.  Even the bed slat is screwed down (with 26 small screws omg).  I can't help feel disappointed because we will be moving in less than a year.  Setup took no less than 4 hours.  I still give this three stars because at the end of the day, the bed arrived as advertised, with the exception of the missing wooden pin.

product_title: South Shore Zach Storage Bed
review_headline: GREAT customer service from this company!
review_body:
This product is exactly as pictured. It is made out of a laminate over pressed particle board. Was not difficult to assemble. Assembly time was approximately 2 hours. There are two sheets of pressed particle board that support the top for your mattress (not included). Because this product is made of laminate, we have had the laminate chip from the particle board on one side of the bed (side opposite of drawers), and we have had two drawers catch on each other and the laminate separate. It stinks, but we don't feel like it's the end of the world.

HERE'S why we 100% recommend this company : We had a sheet of pressed particle board (one that supported the mattress) break about a year after our purchase. We called their customer service and although we didn't have an original receipt, they were able to look up our amazon order and sent us a replacement for free with fast shipping. Great customer service! We will definitely come back for future purchases.

review_headline: Bought 2 chairs, well made, love the style.
review_body:
We bought two of these chairs. They are beautiful and comfortable. The chair is absolutely great. The back is tall enough, seat comfortable enough, main foot rest is just right. The Mission style fits in well with our other furniture. It is well made.

Look at the little "foot rest" that comes out when you lean back. That little strip is hard and hurts the back of my ankles. Probably just my height. That little strip could really use some padding.

Shipping was a challenge. The company responds to email and wants to make sure you inspect the shipment before accepting it. This was our first experience with UPS Freight. The driver was excellent and was able to use a device to bring the shipment from the road to the house.

Even with the time it took to actually receive the chairs, we would buy these again.

review_headline: Beautiful set but bad shipping with damage
review_body: The table is beautiful and the chairs look very well also.  It is tall, but expected, wish just a little shorter version was available.  My problem was in shipping or prior to shipping don't know which but the table was damaged on the upper outer edge with 2 large scratches and indents where scratches are at.  One of the stools arms did not line up properly when assembling but manage to get it to work.  First put the stool seat together, the first one went very smooth no issues, no damage but time consuming.  Then the 2nd stool, had the arm issue and a missing plastic piece used to line up holes, found a piece of stuff to use of my own so it worked.  Then assemble the table, had entire table together with only top piece to put on, then found the very noticeable damage.  After all the time in assembling all of it, no way did want to take back apart to ship back!!  So I am just living with the damaged table, and trying to find out how to contact Amazon and ask for a 30% refund on what I paid because of the damage. Does any one know how to contact them for this request?  All items came packed separately, I guess I should have opened and inspected each piece before assembling.  Recommend you do this if you purchase.  Shipping material was not adequate for the weight, very then Styrofoam that had all crumbled in the box.  This was too nice to not pack properly.

product_title: VIVA OFFICE High Back Mesh Executive Chair,with Adjustable Armrests,Headrest and Lumbar Pad
review_headline: Very ergonomic chair for a great price!
review_body:
I was looking for a comfortable chair to do a lot of freelance work from at home. I have bought a few chairs in my life and it's always been kind of a spontaneous decision that I later regret because I didn't actually look into all the features and comfort level of bought chairs.
I bought this chair after a lot of research and reading reviews. I liked the idea of so many adjustable parts and the fact that a lot of people seem to be very happy with it. It's much better than just looking at a random chair in a store and buying it without knowing anything about it.
As I have a lot of back issues I was very happy to see that the chair actually has a very good back support system. The back has a very nice curve to it and you can adjust the position of the headrest and armrests-a lot of office chairs don't have that option.
It's also great how much you can adjust the chair to fit your or your desk's height. No matter how high or low the desk is the chair will fit to work from it.
Overall I'm very happy with this chair. From a pleasant and discreet look to a very comfortable feeling, this chair will definitely stay with me for years.

Folds down small enough to be simple to store. I'm absolutely happy with it!

product_title: DHP Over Futon Metal Bunk Bed, Silver
review_headline: Sturdy Construction with Some Minor Flaws. Great for Fort Building!
review_body: Came quickly with all pieces. Was able to assemble within a few hours-- I think about 3 or 4 actually. Directions were good as long as you pay attention to the pictures. The bed is sturdy, but is quite squeaky-- WD40, maybe? We ended up attaching it to the wall to be safe. The ladders are rough on the feet-- get some pipe insulation wrap and place it around the rungs. The front catch on the futon level didn't seem to line up quite right, even though everything else did, but that could've been my putting something together incorrectly. The bars that support the upper bunk don't look very strong, but my 190# has been able to climb up there with my son and not fall through. No mattresses are included, so don't trust the picture. Overall, I would buy this again, if given the option. My son LOVES IT and that's what matters most.

product_title: Milliard Contoured Cooling Gel and Memory Foam Bed Pillow, 24 by 15 by 4-Inch
review_body:
Yayyyyy I received my cooling gel contour pillow. It comes in it's own zippered plastic bag and it has a removable cover that can be washed. The washing instructions are easy to read and easy to understand. I love that the pillow is hypoallergenic because I am allergic to certain materials. Since this pillow is made from memory foam I can also use it for my back. It definitely helps support and relieve pain because it adjusts and very comfortable. I am glad I got this pillow no more neck pains in the mornings. I wouldn't of thought by simply replacing a pillow for a memory foam pillow would be the solution to my neck and back problem. Now I know the plan pillows are not for me. Glad I was able to give this pillow a try.

I recieved this item in exchange for an honest review. It's my own and honest opinion.

product_title: DHP Emily Chrome Legs
review_body:
Assembly involves attaching the legs, an easy task. (Note: screws and Allen key are taped to box containing legs. I had to retrieve from the trash as i had not noticed they were attached to the box.)

I was surprised at how comfortable it is to lounge and sleep on.

It is not ideal to sit on using for example a wall as back support. My personal preference would have been for it to be a bit narrower and two inches higher to sit on. There is little room for flexibility regarding it being narrower. Being higher, however, could be accommodated by making it an option to have longer legs at time of purchase or by offering the ability to buy longer spare legs . It is 15 inches high, which is low and uncomfortable for people with long legs. Even 16 inches would be a good compromise.

product_title: Santa Fe - Chocolate High Leg Recliner
review_body: This is a nice chair.  I am enjoying it very much.  It is exactly as advertised.  I work from home as a customer support person for a dot com company and I have everything set up to work from this chair with my laptop and table.  The straight wooden arms are great for mouse device use and with the over-the-arm remote holders with many pockets.  I am quite satisfied with the chair.  The delivery was great.  I was notified of the approximate delivery time.  I met the driver at the front of the house and directed him to the garage street (we live on a corner) and he was able to unload the chair with little difficulty.  I had a dolly he used to put the chair into the garage and waited while we inspected the box all over for any damage (there was none) before he left.  So - great chair, great price, wonderful delivery.  We recommend the company and the chair to anyone wanting this type chair.

product_title: Prepac Monterey Cherry Queen Wood Platform Storage Bed 3 Piece Bedroom Set
review_body:
We bought this set for our guest bedroom and for when our older son decides he wants his own room. I love the color of the wood and the style that it can be used as an good looking guest bedroom and is still nice for young teenager growing up just by changing decor and a comforter. It was easy to put together with an electric screwdriver, power drill, and hammer for my husband (probably would have been a nightmare for me). Being a cheaper bedroom set, which is what we wanted, it still has some particle board and I am not sure how this set will do when we move.
Pros: Great bedroom suit for the money
Should last a while, especially if you are not moving around.
Wood feels solid
Drawers slide in and out well
Does not need box springs (platform bed)

Cons: May not move move well (but if your movers are gentle, who knows).

product_title: Tuft & Needle Mattress
review_headline: Most painful mattress I've ever slept on
review_body: This product was a complete disappointment. I ordered on Amazon to get expedited shipping and was excited to watch the vacuum-packed mattress unroll and inflate...  BUT the mattress is way too firm. I would say 8.5/10 firmness where 10 is a bare floor. On my back it hurts my back, neck and even hips. On my side it hurts my ribs and shoulders. On my stomach it hurts my ribs too. We're talking a stabbing pain that leads to lingering tension and wakes me up at night, if I even can fall asleep.  I tried to pair it with a thin-ish  memory foam topper; this didn't help. I'll try a more expensive one even though that kind of defeats the purpose of shelling out $500 for a non-IKEA mattress and if that doesn't work I will be returning ASAP.  About me: I am a 105 lbs 5'1" Asian female. I suspect this product is good for a narrow band of white people near average weight and is NOT good for anyone more than 1.5 standard deviations from that average. My partner likes it and he is 140 lbs 5'9".   Ironically, I am not hard to please with mattresses. I've slept on primarily IKEA--spring and foam--for the past few years without problems (got this new one because of moving). Before that slept on used spring mattresses that I picked up for between $10 and $100, and family ones likely purchased from a department store. No mattress has ever caused me pain like this one.  I write this while sleeping on a folded up egg crate pad plus thin pillows on the floor at 5AM because I woke up in back pain at 3:30.

product_title: Split King Size Leggett & Platt S-Cape Adjustable Beds
review_headline: This is by far the best bed purchase we've ever made
review_body:
This is by far the best bed purchase we've ever made.

Our California King set had already given out on us (brand new, lasted 3 years, wasn't cheap) and was causing us both back pain. Considering people spend around a third of their lifetime in bed, and that we both work hard and need to be well-rested and ready to go in the AM- we decided to splurge on this bed. We have this base plus two Tempur-Pedic mattresses. If a memory foam mattress isn't your thing, they make spring and half-half mattresses to fit this style of bed also.

I am writing this review after approximately 18 months of use. The assembly is straightforward and easy. We have the wireless remote, which I would highly recommend. Quiet enough not to wake up my husband sleeping next to me. I can have my bed the way I want, even with a completely different mattress then him- whatever makes ME and HIM comfortable (although we did purchase matching mattresses as well). Perfect to position for reading in bed, etc. Extremely comfortable and makes you feel like you're royalty.

A couple things people might want to be aware of:
This base + mattress = the top of the bed is on the higher side. You can't take the wheels off to lower the bed as the mechanism is there. So for elderly people, this might be a little hard to get into, and out of. Of course, that depends on the height of your mattress- but overall, it seems the adjustable type mattresses run thicker then the normal ones. I'm a nurse and I think about mechanics with elderly movement. I think a tempur-pedic mattress and this frame would be ideal for a frail elderly person with fragile skin who needs an adjustable, almost hospital-like bed- but perhaps a wide platform on one side of the bed might be useful, if that is the purpose you're looking at this bed.

Second is that adjustable mattresses are quite a bit heavier then their non-adjustable counterparts. This thing is quite heavy to move, and 1 XL Twin mattress alone takes 2 people to move. I'd estimate the bed to weigh around 350 lbs.

Sometimes the top mattress can become ever so slightly misaligned with the base. You don't notice it when you're sleeping, but like above, it takes quite a powerful shove to get them lined up again.

Also, these are essentially two twin beds, shoved side-by side. The frames do not "lock" together; rather the caster wheels lock in place on the frames side-by-side. I think (not sure) they might sell some sort of locking clamp; although you don't really need it. If you needed two twin beds in place of a king, easy- just pop the locks up on the casters and push a bed to wherever you need it.

A lot of people will tell you they fit into existing King frames. Although this is true (we had a king platform before, and technically they did fit)... when you go to adjust the bed- for example, raising the head- the mattress will get caught on and wedge up against your headboard. It's kind of difficult to explain- but to keep things simple, I would recommend either 1) Do not use this set up in a square-framed-in platform style bed; 2) If you do, make sure the headboard slants AWAY from the bed (think sleigh fashion), which will allow it room to move; or 3) Purchase a dust ruffle and then if you'd like a head board, go with an individual piece headboard and position your bed a few inches from the wall to allow the bed room to move.

The "massage" mode on this bed is not so much massage as it is just plain and simple vibrations. You can adjust the intensity of the vibrations, and the patterns (think wave-style, head to toe and back). It is kinda nice/therapeutic; but it is too loud to be used when the other person is asleep or relaxing and not really a "massage".

Despite it all- I would buy this setup again in a heartbeat. Love it.

product_title: Target Marketing Systems Pacific Stackable Cabinet
review_headline: Good little cabinets...perfect for small spaces.
review_body:
Purchased this one and the one with the glass front. I assembled it and put it into use yesterday, so this review will focus on the basics. I'll edit in a few months or year when I've put it through the paces of kitchen life.

It is shipped in a large a very heavy box. Well packed. Mine had no broken or missing parts. Instructions and hardware, were included and easy to use (disclamer: I'm very handy). Assembly was very simple. I put together two units and stacked them together into a single unit in under an hour with the occasional assistance of my nine year old son. It was really handy having a second set of hands.
A minor issue is that the frame is not pre-drilled where the back panel screws into it and the tolerances were tight along the top tail. This makes it easy to split the frame at the top. Caution is needed to center the screws on the top rail to avoid this.

As other reviews have mentioned, it is IVORY, not white. If you are looking for a crisp white, this is not it.

The sides of the unit are not panels, they are slats. So the items inside are visible (and potentially accessible) from the side.

Overall, quality seems reasonable for the price. Not high end by any means, but not too cheap looking either. Seems quite sturdy. Simple, functional...

review_headline: Beautiful design, very good quality and excellent customer service
review_body: Very good quality table for the price. The glass is quite heavy and the natural wood is exactly the look I wanted. The assembly directions from the manufacturer are terrible. Just a drawing of the table and no indication of how the legs should be positioned. We were unsure at first whether the rubber pads attached to the table legs should be a barrier between the table and the floor or a barrier between the wood and glass top. I looked up the original Noguchi design and we ultimately put the rubber pads between the wood base and the glass to prevent the glass from sliding. Concord Seating was great to work with. The product came very quickly and packaged extremely well. The were quick to respond to questions and followed up multiple times to ensure I was happy. Definitely above-and-beyond customer service. I'd purchase from them again.

product_title: Walker Edison Soreno 3-Piece Corner Desk
review_headline: Some assembly problems but otherwise a good desk
review_body:
Assembled this desk over the weekend. With the exception of the keyboard drawer, the assembly was very easy. The parts were all clearly labeled and the instructions were self-explanatory. Despite this being a 3-pc desk, the assembly was actually faster than the gaming desk we also bought.

The keyboard drawer doesn't work correctly. If you pull it all the way out, it comes unattached if there is any sort of weight on it. This would probably be okay if you have a light keyboard, but I have a heavy mechanical gaming keyboard. Also, the drawer does not pull out far enough to actually use the keyboard easily. Again, this is probably because of the type of keyboard I am using, as mine is a bit wider than the generic keyboards.

The glass tops just sit on the metal frame. While the desk came with rubber cups for the glass, the only place that has holes for the cups was the keyboard and the center corner, but the center corner only had two holes for the rubber cups and because it also sits on the top of the frame the cups don't even touch the glass. The CPU cart is way too low to the ground to even serve a point. It only holds the CPU about a quarter inch off the ground. Seems pretty pointless to me.

All that said, for my purposes, this was an inexpensive desk that gives me a lot more surface space for work. I was able to set up dual monitors and still have plenty of surface space so I don't feel cramped up. But it isn't so big that it devours the office. It sits nicely in the corner of the office and leaves a lot more space in there than what I had with my old desk.

product_title: Sauder Caraway Etagere Bath Cabinet, Soft White Finish
review_body:
This product is excellent in theory. In reality there are a few flaws:
1. The assembly instructions are quite lacking. The drawings are mediocre and the narrative is confusing.
2. The order for assembly suggested by the instructions isn't really logical and led to us missing a few steps and having to u assemble and backtrack.
3. The back is a piece of cardboard. In and of itself perhaps ok, but if one is to anchor this unit to the wall as suggested, one half the bracket is attached by cardboard and therefore is not very sturdy.
4. I had a lot of trouble with the bottom of the unit, that is the pieces that go around the base and on the floor. It never quite came together in a sturdy way.

That said, I appreciate the design of this unit and the closed cabinet. Once you get through the flaws in instruction the unit is attractive and functional.

product_title: Martin Furniture Carlton TV Stand - Fully Assembled
review_headline: Sturdy and solid but not square.
review_body: Looks just like the picture. Is solid and sturdy, however the unit is not completely square because the doors do not hang evenly despite my carpenter boyfriend's best attempt to adjust the hinges. The left door sticks out beyond the frame a tad and the right one doesn't look straight at all. And there's way more space at the bottom of the right door than the left.There are also a couple nicks on the middle bottom edge of the unit but thankfully they're not noticeable. Considering this came pre-assembled I would have thought it would either not have passed quality assurance, or it would have been fixed prior to packaging. Speaking of packaging, this thing was secured tighter than the Pentagon - it was encased in a frame of wood 2x4's and the carpenter boyfriend had to pry off the wood with a hammer and crow bar. Prefer that to shoddy packaging but may be a problem for the average person to deal with. I know this isn't Ethan Allen, but for over $500 I expected that the doors would at least hang correctly. If it weren't so darn big and difficult to package I'd consider returning it.

product_title: Back Support Belt and Work Support Belt, 1 Unit, Black, Lumbar Back Support
review_body:
I got this because we are moving in a few months and the pre-packing has been killing my back. I've been packing up non-necessities in an attempt to minimize the packing when moving week comes. Unfortunately, it has been unkind to my back. I still have more to go so I needed to do something to help my back out. I got this, hoping that it would make the lifting and moving easier.

First, mu only complaint is the lack of directions for use. Fortunately, google provided me with the instructions needed for how to wear it.

Right from the start I could feel it creating a more firm back. When lifting thing, it feels as if I have actually support right where I need it. It did make doing the work easier.

But really the proof is in the day after. Before using this I would be in pain the next day and I would have knots in my back. I was rough. This actually helped to reduce the pain to the soreness that is supposed to happen.

I am surprised that this did such a good job at helping. It isn't some super magic tool. You won't be able to lift cars and leap tall buildings but it does help make lifting things easier.

Please note: I have received this item at a discount or possibly for free in exchange for my HONEST review. When reviewing I consider the items worth as it pertains to it's full price. This review reflects my honest and genuine review of the product.

product_title: Range Kleen CW6009 Stainless Steel Pot Rack Bookshelf, 12 by 36 by 10-Inch
review_headline: Great option if you want a wall rack.
review_body: I had a hanging pot rack, but decided I would rather have a rack on the wall than the ceiling. After much shopping I decided to give this model from Range Kleen a shot. I'm glad I did. It is actually very simple to put together (two decorative screws that mount the wall brackets to the actual rack). I have to give a lot of credit to whoever designed this thing... The mounting holes are 32" apart, so I found a stud and centered one side on that stud and knew I would hit a stud on the other side as well since my studs are on 16" centers. This seems like something fairly trivial, but when you are hanging expensive pots, pans, skillets, etc., it is great to have the piece of mind that your rack is rock solid with four screw directly into studs. No worry about damaging your cooking ware or your floor since this thing isn't going anywhere!  The Rack itself is a fairly simple design, but very attractive and goes with my kitchen. The stainless matches the other stainless in my kitchen well. Pictures tell the story on that. Out of the box and onto the wall, this rack seems like pretty good quality. I expect it to keep a nice finish, and to last for as long as I need it. Best of all, this frees up cabinet space and looks good doing it! I like it more every time I walk into the kitchen and see it.

product_title: WinkBeds - Mattress For Sale - Best Rated Mattress - Mattress Warehouse - Foam Mattress + AirSprings + Gel Hybrid, 100% CertiPure, Medium/Firm Mattress Like Hotel Mattress
review_body:
**** UPDATED 02-25-2016 ****
I have raised my review to three stars, due to several emails I have received from WinkBed's founder over the last few months, asking if there is anything he could do change my impressions of WinkBed. He and his company are dedicated to making their customers happy, and that is hard to come by in this world. I am satisfied with the other brand of mattress I purchased, and have no wish to change, but I appreciate him contacting me and offering me other options.

If you are interested in Winkbed, don't hesitate to give them a try. Each person's experience is different, and this might end up being the right mattress for you. And if not, I can tell you from experience that they definitely work with you to resolve any issues.

*************** Original Review **************************
I purchased through the WinkBed website (slightly cheaper there), but I wanted to share my review here.

I ordered this mattress based on the reviews done by Sleep Sherpa and Sleepopolis, as well as the Amazon comments. I had tried an all memory foam mattress in the past and didn't like it (too soft and too hot), so I though that this hybrid memory foam over spring/coil mattress might suit my needs. I was looking for a mattress that provided good spinal alignment, pressure point relief, could be used on an adjustable bed frame, and did not sleep hot. After sleeping on this mattress, I'd say that all I got from my requirement list was being usable on the adjustable frame, and not sleeping hot.

I'm a heavier person, and I noticed that I sank into this bed quite a bit. I'm a side sleeper, and each night I ended up in a hammock position with my head and feet higher than my lower torso, which put strain on my lower back. I was waking up every few hours with back pain, and I had sank into the mattress enough that it was difficult to roll out of the "nest" to change sides. After a week,my lower back pain was so bad that I couldn't put my feet on the floor and stand up in the morning. So spinal alignment gets no stars - your experience may be different if you are a lighter person (less than 180 lbs).

Pressure point relief was pretty much non-existent. Sleeping on my side, I definitely felt pressure on my hips, shoulder, and even my rib cage. I'd have soreness in these areas that persisted throughout the morning. I think this may be due to the micro-coils, since they are the layer directly below the memory foam. One thing I noticed was that you could actually hear the micro-coils "sticking" in the mattress - rolling over sounded like painters tape being peeled from the wall. Micro-coils may be touted the next big "thing" in the bedding world ( you see them in $2K mattresses like BeautyRest Black), but for me, it's more hype than anything else. They provide too many pressure points with not enough support, and I won't be buying a bed with micro-coils again.

The reason I give it two stars instead of one/zero is that it did not sleep hot at all, and the responsiveness of their customer service department was excellent. They were very prompt and helpful.

If you are considering this mattress, here are some things to keep in mind:
* This mattress is THICK. I measured 15" from the base to the top seam, plus a little more for the dome/quilting on top. You may need deeper sheets to fit this mattress, and your comforter/duvet may be shorter on the sides than you would like. If you are planning to purchase a new foundation, definitely get a low profile box spring rather than standard. Adjustable bed frames may need to drop down to the smallest set of leg extensions.

* If there are two people sleeping on this mattress, there is a bit of bounce/motion transfer when the second person gets into bed. Not terrible, but noticeable. That is typical with most spring mattresses, though, not necessarily something to do with Winkbed in particular.

* There is an initial memory foam odor. It was strong the first day, and was still faintly detectable a week later. If you are sensitive to chemicals/chemical smells, you might want to look at a different mattress, or air out the mattress in another location for a few days before using. I would also recommend the purchase a mattress encasement to help contain the fumes.

* The extra $99 was a bit much for "white glove" delivery. I paid for that since I didn't have any help to get the mattress from the curb to my bed, but I was not impressed with the delivery people who dropped the bed off. This is a 3rd party that wasn't connected with Winkbed, but the delivery guys were sweaty, smelly, and they pretty much threw it on my frame and walked out. Neither of the men used gloves, and their hands were not clean. If you have anyone that can help carry this mattress in (and it's heavy!) I would skip the extra $99 delivery and go for the free curbside delivery.

* The returns process can be a bit tricky. No fault of Winkbed, though - their customer service is great. But again, they are dependent on 3rd party companies for their white glove delivery and removal service, and depending on where you live, it may take them a while to work out the details. My return took over a week, and when I contacted them about it, they said it was because they had trouble finding someone to come get the mattress. I live within 30 minutes of the capital city, though, so I was surprised it was so difficult for them. Especially since the same company that dropped it off finally came to pick it up. They processed my refund immediately after it was picked up, though, so that part was smooth.

Bottom line - If you think the WinkBed is something you might want to purchase, I'd encourage you to go to the box stores that sells BeautyRest and try out a BeautyRest Black with micro-coils first to see if you like the feel. Lay on it in the same position for at least 15 minutes, and it will give you an idea of how the WinkBed might sleep. If I had done that prior to purchasing, I think I would have made a different decision.o with Winkbed in particular.

If you are sensitive to chemicals/chemical smells, you might want to look at a different mattress, or air out the mattress in another location for a few days before using. I would also recommend the purchase a mattress encasement to help contain the fumes.

* The extra $99 was a bit much for "white glove" delivery. review_headline: Great buy for the price! Looks awesome! Enhances living room ambiance!
review_body:
I bought this couple weeks ago and I am really happy with it! It looks nice and the size is optimum to be a TV stand. At this low price, it's far better than other TV stands if you consider the richness it adds to the living room.
Size: I could just managed to fit a 48 inch LED TV in it. Exact TV measurements are 42.2 x 26.5 x 8 inches. This is the maximum size it would accommodate. May be you can risk unto 43'' wide TV or little under it. Height still has good room.
Assembly: This was a task. It took me almost 3 hours to assemble this with help of one more person. I suggest you must watch the assembly video before you start doing it. It would save you a lot of time and headache of figuring out which piece to be mounted in which direction etc.. But this was only one time task. So for such big furniture piece, it is OK.
Only thing I am giving one star less is that the back panels are not strong enough. I almost broke one.

But overall I am very happy with the decision. I will surely recommend it!

product_title: Handy Living Wood Slat Bed Frame Extra Long Twin
review_headline: Maximum weight supported = 150 lbs or so.
review_body: The metal bed frame is very sturdy, and this was easy to put together and comfortable.  The twin-size is not for a full-size adult though - I estimate a max weight of maybe 150 lbs for the slat layout. I checked reviews for weight references and the reviews indicated it was supposed to be ok for bigger people and/or multiple people - that's not what I found. First night's sleep I was in bed and tried to roll over and 2 of the slats under my bum SMACK hit the floor. When my alarm went off and I reached for it, SMACK went a 3rd slat. The slats didn't break, but they flexed down enough that they slid out of the plastic end holders. I'm not sure if I can get the slats back into the plastic ends - but I can't see taking this apart to try to return it either; it's really not designed to be taken apart. Instead, I will be buying multiple ratchet straps to help hold and support the mattress over the frame. I just can't trust it.

product_title: Sauder Beginnings Chest in Soft White
review_headline: I was kind of disappointed in this
review_body: I was kind of disappointed in this, as most Sauder furniture I've bought has been really good, including a captain's bed that was put in the same room as this chest.  This one is barely any better than the similar chest I bought from Walmart.com and returned to Walmart because of damage/the drawers just didn't work at all.  This one was a bit easier to put together, but had the exact same hardware as the Chinese-made chest from Walmart, and I questioned whether it was actually made by Sauder.  It says it is made in America on the instruction booklet, so I'll take their word for it.  The backing, while having a gap in the center, is actually sturdier than the usual cardboard backing that makes a unit square.  I was happy with the sturdiness of the chest.  We were able to get the drawers working with a bit of adjustment of the front screws inside the drawers.  I was very disappointed by the plastic slides, as several sites clearly stated this chest had metal drawer slides, and I assumed they were the roller type.  I could have kept the Walmart chest with the exact same plastic slides and saved some money.  Well, the cutout on the bottom front is cuter, so I guess this chest is ok.  Just ok, though, compared to other Sauder products.  I wouldn't really recommend it, and don't expect it to last very long.

product_title: Crown Mark Pierce Side Table
review_headline: Not sure what everyone else seems to be talking about...
review_body: When my box containing my table arrived, I'll admit to feeling some trepidation upon opening it after reading further some of the customer reviews that I hadn't read when I purchased it mainly because it fit where I needed it to go. So, I found myself very pleasantly surprised when I saw not the first hint of particleboard, a very smooth, glossy black finish covering the entire table excepting the bottom surface of the bottom shelf, which was painted a lighter black and without the gloss. I am a 'lady of a certain age', so was concerned about being able to assemble it without help... Back when my father and I built furniture, we joined pieces with dowels and pegs, and fitted tongue and groove together. A friend recently assembled a tv table for me that everyone on here gave assurance as being 'simple to do, especially if you've ever put together anything from Ikea'. Well, I hadn't - I'm not at all sure I've ever SEEN anything from Ikea!, and the lock bolts for the legs that he demonstrated to me would still be in the middle of my floor had he not been far more savvy and up to date on the progression of furniture assembly techniques than am I. Yet... this little table was a breeze! From unpacking the box to setting it next to my sofa took under 20 minutes, working entirely alone. The company even included the correct Allen wrench for the main leg screws in the hardware packet, although they had put the washers and lock washers onto each screw in backward order, but that was easily corrected. I read here where  one woman cautioned about the assembly of the bottom shelf possibly needing another pair of hands, and she was correct. I was lucky in that I had a cordless drill/screwdriver handy with the correct sized Phillips head that fit the included screws. But the bottom shelf has nothing to rest it upon while being attached, plus has not even any small starter holes drilled into it to 'start' the attaching screws. So I turned the table upside down, threaded the first screw thru the hole in the leg support, snugged the shelf up to it as tightly as the screw would allow by pushing upward on the shelf from below with my left hand, then very quickly (being sure to drill straight down so it would catch) I set the screw to hold the first corner. Without releasing any of my upward pressure on the shelf, I repeated these steps on the corner diagonal to the one I had just attached. After that it was simply a matter of attaching the other two corners. I did have to back one screw out completely and redrill it, as I had obviously gone in at enough of an angle to miss the shelf entirely. The screws are very short - they have to be, because if they were longer they would come out thru the top of the bottom shelf. Also...for those concerned about the strength of the shelf. I am a big girl...weighing over 200 lbs. As a test, I tried carefully sitting myself onto the top shelf, keeping plenty of weight on my feet while listening for any sound of wood cracking. Not only did it hold my partial weight, I was actually able to sit myself completely onto this little table, with nary a wobble! This is not a requested review, I chose and paid for the product myself,  and in point of fact, I seldom take the time to write product reviews. I just hated seeing this little table get a bad rap. I would definitely  recommend it as a purchase for your own needs, and would also eagerly purchase it again should the need arise. Great value for your money, especially in this day of cardboard 'furniture'!crew thru the hole in the leg support, snugged the shelf up to it as tightly as the screw would allow by pushing upward on the shelf from below with my left hand, then very quickly (being sure to drill straight down so it would catch) I set the screw to hold the first corner. Without releasing any of my upward pressure on the shelf, I repeated these steps on the corner diagonal to the one I had just attached. After that it was simply a matter of attaching the other two corners. I did have to back one screw out completely and redrill it, as I had obviously gone in at enough of an angle to miss the shelf entirely. The screws are very short - they have to be, because if they were longer they would come out thru the top of the bottom shelf. Also...for those concerned about the strength of the shelf. I am a big girl...weighing over 200 lbs. As a test, I tried carefully sitting myself onto the top shelf, keeping plenty of weight on my feet while listening for any sound of wood cracking. Not only did it hold my partial weight, I was actually able to sit myself completely onto this little table, with nary a wobble! This is not a requested review, I chose and paid for the product myself,  and in point of fact, I seldom take the time to write product reviews. I just hated seeing this little table get a bad rap. I would definitely  recommend it as a purchase for your own needs, and would also eagerly purchase it again should the need arise. Great value for your money, especially in this day of cardboard 'furniture'!

product_title: Bush Furniture Buena Vista 16-Cube Bookcase/Room Divider Storage
review_body:
I let my teenage son assemble it because it looked pretty straight-forward. He did pretty well, except he wasn't careful aligning the back panel (which is critical for alignment/squaring). In our effort to undo the poor alignment, we broke the front bottom piece and also noticed the two side panels were slightly warped (?).
I am giving five stars for two reasons:
1. It looks very nice (once it's properly assembled).
2. The customer support from Bush Industries was excellent! As soon as you open the box you see a message "STOP!! If you have damaged or missing parts contact Bush Furniture first...". I didn't think I would need to do this, but after the alignment issue, I called the help number and the polite woman (who spoke English as her native language) quickly had the 4 replacement parts en-route to me under 5 minutes. I received the parts within 2 days all at NO EXPENSE to me.
KUDOS to Bush Furniture.

review_headline: Very cheap. Not as it appears in photo.

Not what I expected. Not what It appears in photos. I'm not sure it's even as described. First red flag. Mattress arrives in a tiny box, maybe 2' by 2' by 3'. What? Yeah the foam is not thick. It's so soft that the whole "mattress" can be rolled up into a tiny box. The 4" mattress can be compressed to about ½" between my fingers. The "gel memory foam" layer is all of about 1/8".

I guess perhaps this is intended for camping? It comes with a nice zip bag that you can roll it up in. But why doesn't it say that? I wouldn't even recommend for camping as its so thin after a while you are basically touching the ground on any heavy body parts. Better use an air mattress.

product_title: DHP 3537496 Parsons Coffee Table
review_headline: Nice little table for the price
review_body:
First, a quick warning: Don't order this table expecting that it will actually be made out of wood - it probably isn't even particle board or compressed wood. As near as I can tell, it is made from some sort of compressed cardboard, with a faux wood laminate on the outer surfaces. That said, it is a very nice little table for the price. I paid around $17, and I recommend holding out for that price (it seems to fluctuate, but usually returns to around $17).

The table is very light, but seems sturdy. The faux wood finish is nice enough that it might pass for the real thing if you weren't looking too closely. Assembly is super-easy. You get a table top with a hole on the bottom of each corner, and 4 legs, each with a big screw on top. 5 minutes tops to put it together.

I have two of these, one on each side of a pair of Ikea chairs, and they are just right to hold books, your drink, or whatever else you want handy while you're relaxing. I wouldn't hesitate to buy another if I needed one.

Obviously this isn't a high end item, and I wasn't expecting it as much, but I was expecting better from a North-American company.  This item is really poorly constructed, simple particle board while the top piece is made from solid wood.  Two pieces broke as I was assembling it and another was shipped defective.  Really poor build quality and usefulness.  The drawers are very shallow, which makes it difficult to store everything I was planning to, it basically serves as overflow for clothes I don't keep in my closet (shorts, t-shirts, underwear, etc).  South Shore, the manufacturer, was shockingly bad at customer service.  I called and left a message immediately after the part broke, which went unanswered.  In all, it took eight days from the part breaking on the day I started setting up the dresser to finish building it.  But, I guess you get what you pay for....

review_body: I love this computer desk! I have mixed feelings about functional glass desks, but this one looks great, has plenty of work space, has a clean simple look, and a raised shelf to keep my desktops off the carpet. I didn't really want drawers or other things that might have added to the weight so this really fit my needs well. I also like that you don't have to install the monitor shelf or keyboard tray. I left the latter off completely. Shipping was much faster than I expected and although there was some damage to the outside of the box, the contents inside were so well packed, none of the actual desk parts (especially the 2 tempered glass desktops which I was most concerned about) were affected. All in all, I'm very satisfied with the purchase.

product_title: Linon Anna Double Bookcase - antique Black
review_headline: Great sturdy shelf, easy to assemble, can be damaged during shipment/manufacturing flaws
review_body: I really like this shelf and it fit my very specific size requirements for the room I put it in. I have built a lot of furniture that I bought online and this was by far the easiest to assemble!  It's very sturdy, not wobbly at all. I like that it came with the side supports already assembled. All you have to do is insert the shelves and bolt them in, then screw in the back X stabilizer.  My only complaint is that I bought two of these and both were damaged in shipment, and one was manufactured wrong. The side support was built so that the shelf cannot fit into the slot. It's not worth it to me to contact the manufacturer and try to get a replacement part. My dad happens to be a wood carver so I had him carve the opening out to fit the shelf.  He used a chisel and sandpaper to shave a little of the wood out.  I was a bit disappointed to see the error in manufacturing considering how much I paid.  The Xs on the sides are purely decorative and not very well built. Two of them popped out while I was assembling the shelf. I learned quickly not to push or pull on them while building the shelf.

product_title: Sleep Innovations Shiloh Memory Foam Mattress
review_headline: Not too hot, not too hard, with a caveat;
review_body:
Somewhere in the reviews, a person recommended buying this Isotonic Structure 6 Zone Memory Foam King Mattress Topper to provide a little extra cushioning. So I figured what the heck? I ordered that too.

We've had our mattress for about a year. My husband bakes when he's sleeping. Our 95 lb and 45 lb dog that insist on sleeping with us are also really hot sleepers. But we all sleep comfortably on the bed with just a ceiling fan on the slowest setting above us, even in the summer.

The topper probably provides a little extra "breathing." But all I know is that this combination is great. We've had regular mattresses for years, and they just aren't comfortable. Firm ones feel like sleeping on the ground. Soft mattresses break down too quickly.

This is the "Goldilocks" mattress. It's just right.

product_title: Anji Mountain Bamboo Roll-Up Chairmat without Lip
review_body:
We purchased the dark cherry version of this mat and, although the first shipment was lost, it was rapidly replaced and the new one arrived in good condition. It has been in place in my office for a little over a month on medium pile carpet. I use a chair that slides on wheels to move from one side of my large, u-shaped desk to the other. The first issue I have had is that the mat shimmies or works its way over to one side of my office over time. As I roll my chair to one side of my desk, the mat slides and bunches up against the wall. As a result, I have to move my chair off of the mat and reposition it several times daily. The mat I got is quite large and that is not a simple thing to do on carpeting. The mat has a felt-type backing, so I assume it would slide and move across a hardwood floor also, although I have not tried it on one.

The second issue, which has started to occur in the last week (approximately 3.5 weeks of wear), is that small slivers of veneer have started to shred off of the mat, exposing whatever the base wood (?) is. As other reviewers have noted, chair wheels do dent the surface, which I think is why the veneer is starting to crack and shred off.

While the mat looks good when first put down, I could not recommend it to anyone at this point, particularly given its price and inability to withstand normal, every day use.

product_title: 2-Pcs Sectional Sofa By Poundex
review_body:
LOVE the couch, HATED the shipping (from Furniture Creations - terrible) - but the couch totally gets 5 stars for me!! I (probably like you) was super freaked out about buying a couch without having sat on it, thinking <i> yikes what if it's terrible??? </i> However, our last couch (that we got for ~$350 on sale) was terrible and we DID sit on it in the store, so... I had very little hope on our "testing out" in person abilities either. Anyway, we decided we wanted something with a little more quality - grey, chaise sectional AND one that could be assembled either way (with moves in our future we want to be able to change the direction to fit new spaces). So, we took the risk and got this one. TOTALLY worth it!! Couch has been in our home for a month. Color is a medium grey - not light, not too dark. It has a microfiber waffle fabric that blends in any stains perfectly - with a dog, hopes for kids, and a love of wine, we wanted something that doesn't show stains very easily. This couch was super easy to assemble. I'm a 23 year old women, average strength/superior intellect, and with a neighbor's help carrying up the stairs to my 3rd story apartment (you read correctly), I assembled it by myself in less than 2 hours AND I know that if we move, I can easily reassemble it the other way because it is pretty straight forward how the pieces work (if I were you, I would not waste money on having it assembled). FYI the two boxes seem small, but the couch builds up to the perfect size. Cushions seem really firm at first, but the support is soooooooo awesome - and they do get a bit less stiff with time. We are just in love with this couch - totally in love.

Shipping nightmare - shipping company was late, tried to deliver without appointment, was super late to scheduled appointment and charged an extra $150 to lift the boxes up the stairs (even though THEY were so late for the delivery that my help had to bail). So I said ABSOLUTELY NOT and got a nice neighbor to help me. I was furious. Bad, bad service. Good thing the couch was so nice that I didn't complain any further. Mya= advice is call, call, call - find out who is shipping your couch and stay in contact with them. Schedule a delivery early and get people to be there for the 4 hour window to help you PLUS maybe 2 extra hours just in case the delivery is late.a nice neighbor to help me. I was furious. review_body: Ok this chair is amazing.  Super quiet motor on the lift and very comfortable without being too squishy.  The seat is wide and a decent depth.  Family members with lower back issues find it comfortable.  It's a good looking chair as well and we went ahead with the white glove delivery considering we live in  a basement apartment and didn't want to worry about hefting it downstairs.  They were courteous and professional.  The only snafu was with delivery, but as this wasn't really a problem with mega motion and they took the time to speak with me personally regarding it, I won't deduct a star.  Just be aware that the delivery time they give on amazon is an estimate and probably wrong.  This is coming directly from the company and if you go with the white glove service they have to coordinate with you and their drivers and what not.  It was about a month before we got the chair but they called the house to set up the delivery appointment and then called again before they actually came the day of delivery.  Which all makes sense and I wouldn't have freaked out if it hadn't been for the estimated delivery on the order after I submitted.  SO just keep in mind this isn't your normal amazon delivery.  It's worth it.

product_title: Avista Sovereign Plus TV Stand
review_headline: The metal sections appeared fine. The amount of damage varied each time
review_body:
I have tried to obtain an undamaged Avista Sovereign Plus TV Stand on three occasions now. On each occasion the outer packaging has been significantly damaged on arrival. I can only assume this is from rough handling in transit or at the warehouse.

On opening the packaging, each of the stands had damage to the wooden front panel. The metal sections appeared fine. The amount of damage varied each time, from small dents and splits, to the corners being snapped and separated. Much of this damage could probably have been prevented by better packaging and more careful handling, although even the corners that were not snapped showed signs of the glue failing and the wooden sections starting to part. See the attached photos of the 3 stands.

I was prepared to given Amazon and Avista the benefit of doubt on the first two occasions, but three damaged items is too much; I recommend you avoid this product.

review_headline: but the quality seemed more like something you'd get if you'd buy a $70 piece ...
review_body:
We bought this hoping it was equivalent to IKEA's cube storage in sturdiness, but were dissatisfied with the quality. Overall, for $180, we were hoping for higher quality that we could use in our kids' rooms for a few years, but the quality seemed more like something you'd get if you'd buy a $70 piece at target to get you through a college apartment.

PROS:
-very easy to assemble, and quick

CONS:
-not very sturdy (for the $ paid; again wanted to use this for a kid's room where they're tougher on furniture, but as a first apartment piece, may be suitable)
-baskets did not fit and slide in very easily; would rub against the edges of the cube
-also 3 bolts on the bottom piece did not fit in exactly as needed; the holes weren't drilled quite as deep as they should have been
-worst of all, there was an AWFUL chemical smell that just permeated the room as we unpacked the box. Even a day or two after assembling, it was still strong enough to give me a headache after being in the room for a few minutes. As soon as we disassembled and put it back into the box with packaging, it dissipated and was back to normal.

product_title: DynastyMattress Luxury 12-Inch w/5 Memory Foam Mattress
review_headline: Off gassing wasn't terrible. Yes there was a chemical sort of plastic ...
review_body:
UPDATE: we received this mattress August 3, our first impressions were good, we were sleeping better & thought we had hit gold for the price, now it's not even 6 months later and both hubby and I are having terrible back pain! There are no noticble indents, however, the " memory" seems to be going. The bed no longer seems to conform to our bodies, causing horrible back pain. WE NO LONGER RECOMMEND!!!

Mattress arrived quickly and once we lugged it inside and got it unboxed it began uncompressing quickly. It did take the full 3 days to get it to reach the stated 12" all over. There was some wave to the edging on one side. I've decided it's not enough of a problem to try and ship back. Off gassing wasn't terrible. Yes there was a chemical sort of plastic odor but nothing unbearable. We've had this mattress about a month now and since the first night hubby and I have been sleeping much better. It will take time to adjust. Husband and I adjusted at different rates, he had a sore back for about a week and a half, me about 5 days. As others have mentioned there definitely is a temperature difference sleeping on this mattress compared to a spring mattress. I noticed this from the first night. It is warmer, we also took suggestions from others and put a cooling topper on. Not sure if it helps as it is still noticeably warmer, and we've never tried sleeping without it. Movement does take getting used to.getting in and out were both awkward and slightly difficult that first week, but we're pros now. Lol overall I'm pleased with this mattress for the price. We're hoping to get about 4-5 comfortable years out of this and will be very impressed if it makes it longer than that.

product_title: Sauder 2-Shelf Bookcase, Select Cherry Finish
review_headline: Hard to put together, not sure i'ss worth the money
review_body:
I'm not the handiest, so let me say the three stars are in reference to the condition of the material and not the overall shelf.

Some of the wood was chipped when I got it out of the box. As I tried to assemble it, the large cardboard backing did not actually cover the shelf squarely. While this was listed as a possibility in the directions, it took longer than I would've liked to try and make the cardboard fit the shelf. I've put a piece of furniture from Target together that was very similar, and it wasn't this difficult. The molding that looks so pretty in the picture has to slide onto the sides and this particular shelf was not capable of sliding all the way. The 'wood' was not carved well enough to fit into the slat, so it took more time.

I was disappointed I had to spend so much money on this product.

All that to say, I did this by myself and it took a while. It looks nice enough (despite the scratches in the wood that were there before I put it together) and it's a good size for the space I needed to fill. It does hold all of my books, but the side molding makes it difficult to place books at extreme edges of the shelf. If I were you, I'd look around Craigslist for a sturdier shelf that is already assembled. I'm not sure I'd buy something from this company again.
