product_title: Garland Rug Value Plush Rug
review_headline: adequate and low priced but beware of substantial off gassing
review_body: This rug has to be judged based on price performance: it is very low priced and of adequate quality, so many will be pleased with the purchase. The thickness is about 3/16 inches, which is a shade thin, but acceptable; no one should characterize this as "plush" though.  The rug comes rolled and sealed in a plastic bag; it rolls out flat and looks good.  I am rating it at 3 stars instead of 4 because after it is unwrapped there is very substantial off gassing--much more than I have ever experienced from any similar product. I placed the rug unrolled in a closed room with an air purifier (with a filter containing a significant amount of granular activated carbon) running on high speed and it still took several days for the VOCs to be cleared out.  If you are at all sensitive to chemical odors and don't have somewhere you can air this out for a significant period of time you will want to purchase a different product.

product_title: DHP 6 inch Coil Futon Mattress with CertiPUR-US certified foam, Merlot
review_headline: Good mattress for sleeping, not so good for folding
review_body:
I needed temporary bed for a couple months, so I bought this mattress and the DHP aiden futon frame. The mattress came in a long rectangular box, that the delivery person had thankfully carried up three flights of stairs for me, there was no way I could have lugged it up myself. I opened it up, and it inflated within a minute. I let it inflate some more and slept on it that night.

Its a very firm mattress. And its near impossible for one person to fold the mattress into a sofa position on the futon frame. Since I'm using it as a bed, it doesn't matter much to me. But if you actually want to be able to fold it, get a thinner mattress. When I did fold it up, which required 2 people, I kept it folded for about an hour so it would be easier to fold in the future. But this just left a crease in the middle of the mattress, which I did not want. So I have not folded it up again.

I have slept on it for about 2 weeks and I like it so far. I put a thin mattress topper on it, because it was initially a little to firm for my taste, but now it feels great.

product_title: Serta Back in Motion Health & Wellness Eco-friendly Bonded Leather Executive Office Chair - Smooth Black
review_headline: Get the 44186 one- NOT this one!
review_body: First thing I can tell you is don't buy this one! Buy the 44186 version. I actually bought that one first for one of our offices, and tried it out before buying another. However, instead of just going going back to my order history and re-ordering - I did a search and came up with this one under Prime and thought it was the same. It's miles from the same. This one feels a lot cheaper in it's construction. But the biggest difference? The large back is held to the seat part by the armrests only! Yes, you heard correctly, by the armrests. The 44186 model connects to the seat itself... so much better engineering. The small part- "back in motion" piece has an L shape connector to the seat. The then seat has an L shape connector to the backrest. On top of that, the reason I liked the chair was it's ability to keep pressure on my lower back. I'm not sure if this is also a difference- actually think it's broken... but I can't "lock" the seat from leaning forward like a rocking chair. The other one definitely locks. So I will be calling their customer service line tomorrow. I'm a bit concerned though as their is a web address you can also use- when I enter the Item # and PO# it tells me there is no match

It's nice to be able to wheel this thing by the stove when we need it.  With the breakfast bar leaf popped out, you've got space to do some serious cooking. review_headline: Nice on your feet, but it's too soft for chair casters.
review_body:
Whatever material is used, I can't see it lastly long without cracking. It's too thin, too soft and too flexible to hold up as far as I'm concerned unless it is used over a very thin indoor/outdoor carpet with no backing to reduce the 'flexing' of the mat.

Dimples are left in the mat for some time after you get out of the chair. While a slight 'indent' could be expected, no where near as much here.

One of the two mats this was to replace is around 10 years old with daily use and there are only a very few hairline cracks (if you can call them that) that I can find. The mat is still very usable and will be elsewhere.

review_body:
I've had this bed for roughly a month now after purchasing for my new apartment and due to stiffness I was having with my previous bed. This is my first memory foam bed, and I can say that it has made a difference in my lower back and neck pain. It's def on the firm side, but I prefer that support and it makes it easy to get out of bed.

The only con I have is that the bed is still a little hot when sleeping during a hot summer night. It's nothing that's deal breaking, and I'm sure it'll be a plus in the colder months, but you might have to turn your AC down a couple extra degrees at night in the summer.

product_title: Jestik TV Wall Mount
review_headline: The metal is not machined so that they will just line up perfectly if you put them next to each other so I recommend using a lar
review_body:
This was a little harder to install than I thought it would be because first you put up one side and then the other. They are not attached to each other but you have to line them up together with a tiny level you give you. The metal is not machined so that they will just line up perfectly if you put them next to each other so I recommend using a larger level to draw a line and then put them up. If you do that they won't have to be exactly next to each other and it will allow you to catch a stud for each one if you need the space to do so.
adequate hardware is supplied but the instructions leave something to be desired.

product_title: GUARDSMAN Finished Leather & Vinyl Cleaner INK REMOVER STICK 1 oz. (Pack of 2)
review_body: I purchased this months ago and just decided to write a review because it has been a blessing.  I had just purchased a new vehicle, my niece had an ink pen and wrote on the arm rest and I thought I was gonna pass out.  I tried all the things, after research everyone said to try, then decided to purchase this.  I prayed and honestly felt that God lead me to make the purchase.  I was counting the days to get it because I didn't want the ink to dry on the arm rest.  Once I got it, I begin to use it with nail polish remover, soap and water and cotton swabs.  I used it every other day applying it to the arm rest using the cotton swab to mix it with the nail polish remover and whipping it off with soap and water.  I could slowly see it fading.  I continued this for over a week and no signs of the marks are on the arm rest.  My sister was like...what happened?  She couldn't find it. I was like, I know right....amazing.  I not only use it on leather but on my clothes. I apply it to the mark and apply soap and water and rub the clothing together and rinse it off and it's gone.  It works on grease stains as well, just apply the same technique.  I don't know about anyone else, but it worked for me.  When you make a purchase like this know your gonna have to put a little effort in it in order for it to work.  There is no magic wand for anything, but a little prayer, elbow grease and effort...and it will do what it says.  I thank Jesus for leading me to make the purchase because it has been such a blessing to me.  Great job guys!!

review_body:
This took a fair amount of time to put together. Nothing super complicated, but your usual IKEA level of assemble. Screwdriver and hammer required. Also, do yourself a favor and put wood glue in the tracks of the bottom of the drawer because it's constantly falling out when I open and close the drawer. That's my only complaint.

I bought this nightstand because I'm tired of always seeing junk gathered on top of my nightstand and being unable to see the clock. I put a small basket underneath and threw all my junk in there and it's nice and neat now. I have two, one on each side of the bed. It is a really beautiful piece of furniture and the price was right. All in all, I probably spent less on two of these than I would have spent in time, gas, and headache from buying IKEA. Not to mention the price was about equivalent to what I wanted and of better build and quality.

product_title: LUCID 12 Inch Gel Memory Foam Mattress - Triple-Layer - 4 Pound Density Ventilated Gel Foam - CertiPUR-US Certified - 25-Year Warranty
review_headline: I feel like a genius for finding this mattress.
review_body:
I had been sleeping on an inner spring mattress with a pillow top. It wasn't all that old, but I was waking up multiple times every night. I thought it must be a normal part of getting older (55). Then I started having a lot of trouble with my arms falling asleep. I went to a cardiologist for this who may have thought I was a nut job...um...it wasn't my heart. However, sleeping in a recliner almost completely eliminated the problem, so I decided it must be my mattress.That's when I started looking. I fully intended to splurge on a latex mattress and was saving up to get the best mattress I could find. After reading a gazillion conflicting opinions on what kind of mattress was best, and getting totally fed up with sleeping in the recliner, I decided to spend (a-lot) less on this King Lucid 12 inch gel memory foam mattress just to see what memory foam was like (and to get the hell out of the recliner). But then, SURPRISE, I got a mattress I am completely satisfied with instead of just an interim solution. I feel certain that if I had spent $2500 more on a mattress, like I was thinking of doing, it wouldn't have been better, or maybe even as good, as this one. Like I read in another review, and it is a good thing to remember, the popular brand is not necessarily the best. The shipping, arrival and set up all went smoothly and as expected with no problems. I let the mattress sit through the day and slept on it the same night. Maybe my sense of smell is defective, but I would not say this mattress SMELLS or ever did smell. It is not as if it made the room smell any different than it ever did. The only thing I noticed was an occasional whiff of an unfamiliar scent that wasn't even really unpleasant. I got that occasional whiff now and then for a couple days, no more than a week. Thats the only negative I can report and I don't think it qualifies as a complaint! I have had it almost 2 months now and I am sleeping through the night again (maybe it is making me younger'). Myarms have quit falling asleep too. I have never once felt too hot while sleeping on it, and we are talking July and August in Georgia. I don't know about you but I have accepted the fact that, more often than not, any major purchase will entail some sort of disappointment. The need for an exchange, a modification, a missing part, inferior quality...but this time I actually got more than I expected and made the perfect purchase right out of the gate. Like...by accident. How cool is that?

I'm going to bed now -yay- and I bet my bed's better than your bed!

product_title: MAXTOMARS Ergonomic Design Arm Stand Computer Elbow Stand Laptop Arm Support Armrest Office Desk Extender Wrist Rest
review_headline: Making My Lower Table Extension Ergonomically Work
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:e1c38f638ed2070d9993de06759abf42]]Up to the point, I have been using my wrist as the support point... now it is the back of my forearm. :)

If you happen to be looking for something that is completely fluid with constant, constant motion - well, perhaps if I oil the joints a touch, it will be - but there is a bit of tactile jerkiness to it when in back-and-forth motion. However, in my application as a relatively static arm rest off the little side table I use as a desk extension, this does the trick admirably. The slight stiffness in motion actually is a bit of a plus, as I personally wouldn't to use one too loose and free with its motion.

The overall flexibility of height and orientation is pretty robust although the maximum height from the arm cradle to the top of the clamp is about 2 1/2 inches and the furthest length with the arm cradle's outside edge to the inside edge of the clamp is along the lines of 13 inches. There is a diagonal screw that keeps the height adjustment, even with me leaning my elbow into the cradle and my full upper weight on it. The table itself, though, isn't the most stable of things ((lol)).

- Discounted product provided for evaluation, yet my thinking here reflects all my personal purchasing decision processes, and hopefully may help clarify if this best meets your own needs and expectations.

product_title: Reverie 7S Adjustable Bed From The Makers Of The Tempurpedic Ergo W/ Bluetooth Option (Queen, With Bluetooth)
review_headline: This Bed Base saved my life!
review_body:
I don’t “hang out” in my bedroom. I don’t read in bed. I don’t watch TV in bed. So, I never really considered the need (or expense) of an adjustable bed frame.

I spent years on a big name, conventional mattress and box spring, that was really never that comfortable. I always woke up sore; never “refreshed”. To “enhance” the situation, I bought a high quality 3” MF topper. That took care of the soreness, but it created a bit of sleep apnea in the process.

Time for a new bed! I went to my local big-box mattress store, and naturally, I fell in love with the most expensive mattress in the store! It was the Tempur Ergo Grand, and its was on a fully adjustable, massaging base. The combo together, was priced at $12,500!!! ($8,500 for the mattress) + ($4,000 for the base)

I wasn’t even considering the base, for the reasons I listed above, but learned that just 2” to 3” of elevation of my upper body, had the promise of reducing/alleviating the sleep apnea.

Still, $12,500! is a lot of money. Research for an equivalent ensued, and I wound up looking at this base, and the Dynasty Mattress 15.5” Grand Atlantis Breeze (also here on Amazon). I am sincerely grateful for all of the previous reviews! Very helpful indeed!

It worked! I feel like a kid again when I wake up! Too old to do cartwheels out of bed, but if I could, I would!

Thanks to Amazon, I have been able to completely replicate the $12,500 bed/base combo, for $2,200.

Notes:

Yes, it really does weigh 200+ pounds! (Queen) I had a strong kid, and a “skateboard” type dolly on hand, and it still gave us a workout.

Very sturdy, and basically ready to go out of the box – just screw the 4 giant feet on it, and put it where it goes. Add the 4 corner mattress keepers, and plug it in – its that simple.

It fit very neatly inside my (free-standing) 4 corner bed frame – which was very important to me. This base also ships with everything you need to attach it to a headboard, if need be, and the base is “minimalistically” attractive on its own.

The motors are very quiet, and the massage aspect is very powerful, but doesn’t “transmit” onto the floor – not sure how they accomplished that.

This whole arrangement (with 100+ pound mattress) and me (280 pounds) is sturdy and silent. This base is rated for 800+ pounds, and I believe it!
The remote is nice, small, simple, and the keys light up!e also ships with everything you need to attach it to a headboard, if need be, and the base is “minimalistically” attractive on its own.

The motors are very quiet, and the massage aspect is very powerful, but doesn’t “transmit” onto the floor – not sure how they accomplished that.

This whole arrangement (with 100+ pound mattress) and me (280 pounds) is sturdy and silent. This base is rated for 800+ pounds, and I believe it!
The remote is nice, small, simple, and the keys light up!

product_title: Natural HomeLogic Laundry Detergent - 50 fl oz
review_headline: Cleans just as well as something that isn't all natural
review_body:
I was worried that a natural detergent wouldn't work very well. However, this is working fine for us. My clothes come out clean and there isn't any residue. My son gets his clothes pretty dirty, but they have been coming out just as clean as they would with our regular detergent.

I have to be careful anytime I try a new detergent because my skin can be pretty sensitive. I had no reaction to this and even the scent was gentle enough to not bother me at all. I love the scent, so I was glad that I didn't react to it.

There are measuring lines inside the cap that help you use the correct amount for your load size. However, I do have a bit of trouble seeing the lines sometimes because my laundry room is a bit dim.

My only complaint is that this leaked during shipment. That could probably be avoided if there were a seal on the top of the bottle underneath the lid.

I received this item at a discount in exchange for my honest review.

product_title: CVSLink CX7F Laptop Desk
review_headline: This laptop desk is fantastic and I'm so very impressed with it
review_body: This laptop desk is fantastic and I'm so very impressed with it! I've been looking for a laptop desk for a while now that I can use around the house in various places. I loved that this particular desk also has a fan built right into it so I wanted to give it a shot. So far I am very satisfied. The desk is very well made, nice quality, and so far quite durable. It is perfectly sized to fit my 15" laptop with room to spare. I love the nice little wrist rest on the right hand side of the desk. It's perfect when you're using a mouse with your laptop or even if you just want a comfortable place to rest your wrist for a minute. The desk is very easy to adjust. I really like that the legs fold into the desk for easy storage and you can simply pull a little lever to pull each leg out for you to use it. It has several height adjustment levels and you can also easily adjust the tilt of the desk to however you like it. The green around the edge of the table adds a nice pop of color to the whole thing. I can use this laptop desk while sitting in bed, on the couch, on the floor, basically anywhere I want! It's really a fantastic laptop table! I received this item at a discount in exchange for my honest review.

product_title: Sauder Palladia Panel TV Stand, Select Cherry Finish
review_body: Well, the finished stand is nice but it took forever to ship.  I kept checking and checking and I was just ready to cancel (wish I had) when it finally shipped - it was well over 3 weeks (might have been 4 weeks), heck, my new tv was sitting here waiting for almost 3 weeks and I ordered it at the same time.  When I received it, the box was torn, taped up, banged up, smashed in, etc.  I should have just call then, but it was so late coming I kept it.  Also, it's very heavy (it's says team lift on the box, over 70 lbs. I guess they don't read)  I almost didn't get it in the house by myself -  I'm a woman.  Putting it together was awful - I mean it has so many pieces, screws, hardware, it took me over an hour just to unpack it and sort it out.  I worked on it 3 1/2 - 4 hours that night trying to put it together by myself because I had a  friend coming the next day to help set up the TV.  Her and her son and his friend ended up finishing the job (another hour and half).  Sadly, there are scratches - probably from shipping - one deep right on top but the TV covers it and the rest aren't too noticeable.  But on the top, the front edge is dented in, in two places.  So disappointing, it was the first thing my daughter noticed when she came and said if it was her, she'd return it.  FedEx is horrible and I'm sorry to say it should have been returned - but how can you do that when it was shipped in a million pieces and you sweat blood putting it together??  Think twice on this deal.

The final screw at the top got stuck with about 1/3 of the screw sticking out, the head had completely stripped and I had to cut the screw out of the wall. The hardware packet is not consistent with what is pictured in the manual, I ended up using whatever screws would work for the final steps of installation. I also ended up just using 2" drywall screws to attach it to the stud, no pilot holes and no broken fasteners. This is a real piece of junk, but, it's cheap.

product_title: Serta Bonded Leather Big & Tall Executive Chair
review_headline: You can get better for the money
review_body:
I am a big guy - about 280 lb and 6'5", so I put lots of stress on office chairs.
My previous chair that I also got from Amazon, similar price, was much better quality than this one. I was primarily attracted by the Serta name, since they make good mattresses - so I decided to give it a shot.
The biggest complaint I have is that I cannot find a position that fits me right - I think there's something wrong with chair geometry and ergonomics. I was expecting that since it is heavily padded it will be more comfortable - but I start getting back pain after just 30 minutes of sitting. This doesn't happen at my work in the office chair there, and it did not happen with my previous chair I got from Amazon. So I end up not using this chair as much - hence the 3 star rating.

So my advice is to shop around - there might be better choices available. I am unable to return this chair because I have moved out of the country so the shipping would be too expensive - but if I could I would return it.

review_headline: Love it! Still Love it after a year!
review_body: I read most of the ratings for this type of mattress. I selected this one based on those comments and the fact my niece had just purchased one. I was worried about the comments about the smell and heat. We have had ours now for over a month and no problems at all. I do not wake up hot and there was NO smell at all. It flattened out in less than 24 hours and we slept on it right away with no problems. My husband is about 165 lbs and I am about 100lbs. So we see very little depressing of the material. We are both over 60 and do not experience heat problems. I read about some people not being able to get in or out of the bed and trouble turning over, we do not have these problems. They should try a waterbed if they think this is hard to move around on the mattress. So for now, it has only been a month, I am really happy with my mattress. August 25/2016: Addition I have had this mattress over a year! No heat problems for either of us, is NOT sagging, it is still as good as they day we opened it! I love it still after a year best purchase ever!

review_headline: It looked like an amazing piece to add to my home
review_body: When I ordered this product I was very excited! It looked like an amazing piece to add to my home! But when I had began to assemble the pieces, I noticed a few choice things that were simply a deal breaker... First, the fabric had loose strings all over the place, and that's never a good sign. It shows me that the quality was lower than my expectation and made from cheap fabric and was poorly made. Secondly, there was a cover underneath the ottoman along with the furniture itself, naturally I was curious and I took a peek. There was my second suprise, there was no support! This worried me on a number of levels. What if my kids were to throw themselves onto the furniture or if we had family over? I wouldn't even want to think how long the weak support on this furniture would last... seeing as how it was already so dainty. Lastly, when I read leather my first thought was good quality, and I couldn't have been more wrong. I took a poke a the "leather" and felt as if I had applied the slightest of pressure it would break! And that was it, my last straw, my deal breakers. I refused to inspect the furniture any more, because I knew it would only disappoint further. So folks, go ahead and try it but don't expect good quality.

Reluctantly, I decided to load the chair back into the crate and take it to my local UPS. I am very disappointed that the quality control in communist China, where it was manufactured, is so lax.

I would pay much more if the chair was manufactured in the USA or North America.

product_title: Furniture of America Laurelle 2-Drawer Nightstand, Dark Oak
review_headline: Perfect size. Maybe slightly darker than the picture
review_body:
It's a night stand. Perfect size. Maybe slightly darker than the picture. YES IT IS PRE-ASSEMBLED!!! Everyone is complaining about the item being too small. I respectfully disagree. Read the product dimensions if you aren't sure, but this nightstand comes only a few inches below my queen bed on box springs and a frame. The frame of my bed is about 8 inches off the ground. This should fit nicely next to any bed, unless your bed is on stilts. Excellent American made quality.

Top drawer fits medicine, condoms, REMOTE CONTROLS, and other small gadgets like a 10 inch iPad..... so if it's too small for you, well I don't know what to tell you, except you are stupid my friend.

Other two drawers are identical to one another, and about double the height of the top drawer. and happen to fit screwdrivers, duct tape, sockets, tools and other items like a toiletry bag or small purse.

If you don't have time to assemble furniture, but still want quality, this is for you.

The handle is a really cheap looking plastic and, though they call it "chrome", it's not very appealing. Most products I have purchase at this price range come with plastic screw covers that fit nicely into the head of the screws. This product however came with giant plastic stickers that were way bigger than the holes and just look silly. Also dust has a tendency to cling to the edges and you can't clean it. product_title: Prepac Floating Desk with Storage
review_headline: Great design and look, but some installation feedback/tips.
review_body:
Definitely love this for our remodel of our daughter's (16) room!
However, piece of advice for anyone purchasing. As others have stated (which btw, thank goodness for feedback and reviews because it helped us as well!), if you are going to have an outlet below the desk, you need to go up 3 inches (in our case) higher for mounting. Also, keep this in mind when choosing a chair. If you need to raise the height of the desk due to an outlet, you will need to have a chair that has an adjustable height as well.
Also, because of some customer feedback that I had read about the wear and tear on the surface, we have put clear contact paper on the desktop surface. Only up to where it meets the shelves so it can be easily replaced when it's worn out and dirty. I've done this on other desks and it really does give it a longer life.
Because of the outlet issue, I give this 4 stars. As for function, definitely a great concept and design. Just

review_headline: I was on an Embrarer 90--a mid-size regional jet (I've been on genuine puddle jumpers so this isn't terribly small) and this was
review_body:
I just bought the international size carry-on at TJ Maxx when I was desperate for a small wheeled carry-on I could be sure would get into the overhead of a regional flight. I was on an Embrarer 90--a mid-size regional jet (I've been on genuine puddle jumpers so this isn't terribly small) and this was still too large to fit wheels out overhead, it did fit comfortably horizontally. I really wish it had an external pocket (which it clearly doesn't) and the only handle is the one at the top making lifting it in and out of the overhead space more awkward than it has to be. My second biggest gripe is that it zips completely opposite for how I expect: wheels must be on your right. I don't know if it's my right-handedness or just me, but I keep orienting it so that the wheels are on my left (because I grip the only handle with my right hand), try to open, realize that's wrong, and flipping it.

Otherwise, it seems solid. Would not buy again for these reasons--I live out of suitcases so these are actually pretty major issues for me. For infrequent travelers looking for something small? Great!

product_title: CVSLink CX7F Laptop Desk
review_headline: Sturdy and modern! Adjusts to almost anyone!
review_body:
I got this product at such a great price that I had to leave an honest review! I got this laptop desk for when I am in any other room except for my office to do work at home. I have had laptop desks before and they were never like this one! This one is fully adjustable and has a fan built-in! This can accommodate any kind of person! It tilts and can be raised or tilted with flip of a button or knob. So one can use it on the floor, bed or couch with no problems.
The feet are wide and sturdy too. This doesn't feel rickety or cheaply made. The color is cute, I love sage green and the design is modern futuristic!
The fan never has to be plugged into a wall! Just plug it into your USB port on your laptop and you are ready to chill out your laptop and keep it from over heating! I guess you can plug it into the wall with an extention cord and a wall charger. The fan is quiet and only runs when connected to a port. There is no on/off switch, but not necessarily needed for such a quiet fan. My old chill pad made noise and the power cord was not built in, so I lose the power cord more times than I care to admit!
There is a cushioned pad for the wrist. The pad is made of silicone and feels good on my wrist, I don't use a mouse with my laptop, but tried it out anyway. There are two tabs to keep the laptop from slipping off when tilted, these hold well and when not in use they fold down to help fold the table flat for storage.
I am very pleased with this laptop table and look forward to using it more in the future. I am going to recommend this product to all my friends and family!

product_title: Coaster Home Furnishings  Mobile Kitchen Trolley Cart with Butcher Block Top - Natural / White
review_headline: A good product at a great price
review_body: First, it is amazing that someone figured out how to pack this entire system into one box. Overall, I and my wife love it. We looked high and low in many stores and on the web, and this is really great.  To assemble, I started by putting all of the hardware into a 12-cup muffin pan that I use for many shop projects.  That made it so easy to become familiar with the parts and to quickly spot that one important but very small piece was missing, and the hand towel bar was scraped and dented. The seller responded quickly by email, but after a week I had not received any replacement in the mail.  I purchased missing hardware for 2 dollars and will repaint the towel bar.  I looked at the instructions carefully, and one needs a sense of humor. A couple of the parts are labeled different ways at different points in the illustrations.  By the way, there are no verbal instructions, but that was not a problem.  What would have helped would be to have stickers on each part with an identifying number. That was done, but for only some of the parts.  I also did a dry run assembly, putting the parts together without any of the hardware, just to make sure I knew what to do.  I laid everything out on the garage floor on top of a tarp, and allowed myself three days, just doing a little at a time.  Everything went very quickly, and the only problem was at the very end, when attempting to install one of the drawers.  The side supporting brackets had buckled out instead of being flush, and the drawer could not fit.  I finally whacked both brackets several times with a rubber mallet and eventually made it fit. The only time I needed a second person was to attach the two doors and to get the whole island from the garage into the kitchen (it weighs 120 pounds!).  I decided that the towel bar would be more useful as a paper towel holder, so sawed a slot into the top of both supporting brackets. It works great.  Overall this is one of the best furniture kits I have ever seen and it is a great value.  I am glad that I did not pay too much attention to internet comments about the assembly process being a nightmare.  I found it to be, except for the drawer, to be well designed, well constructed and easy to assemble, especially if I kept a sense of humor and ignored one or two obvious mis-identifications in the instructions.value.  I am glad that I did not pay too much attention to internet comments about the assembly process being a nightmare.  I found it to be, except for the drawer, to be well designed, well constructed and easy to assemble, especially if I kept a sense of humor and ignored one or two obvious mis-identifications in the instructions.

review_headline: Bang for the buck, HQ, and comfy
review_body:
I upgraded my office furniture and bought this chair as it had a greater amount of 4-5 star reviews than competitors of its price range. Well, this chair feels of high quality even if it is made in China.

Pros: Comfortable forearm padding
Comfortable back support
Comfortable butt support
Easy to assemble (recommend 2 people to assemble the side arms to the seat pad and back pad.
Good vertical adjustment and tilt lock works great.
Makes you feel like a BOSS too!

Cons: It does seem a bit narrow for me. I am 5'8, male, 185lbs, and this chair seems like it wants to restrict me. Its just enough space to fit my wide hip section, but for the really large person, I would not recommend this. Please purchase a really good high dollar exectuive chair if you are big and tall.
Upon opening and assembling, I noticed a noise coming from inside the wheel assembly metal. You know the five spoke base the wheels attach to, well inside those, something seemed to be sliding about and creating small noise. I could not retrieve it, and while it is still stuck inside (what ever it may be, it does not matter to me personally). It sounds like a speck of metal sliding back and forth inside the tubular frame of the base of the chair.

That being said, I made the right investment into this chair.

But not that it is installed, it works well as a bed. It is (still) very hard to fold the frame+mattress, but that is mostly due to the thickness of the mattress and not the frame. Without the mattress, the frame opens and closes easily. It feels sturdy and looks nice.

product_title: DynastyMattress NEW! 15.5-Inch AtlantisBreeze Cool HD Memory Foam GEL Mattress
review_body:
Choosing a new mattress is harder than shopping for a new car! I was sleeping on a big name, uber expensive conventional mattress, which was really never that comfortable. I always woke up sore; never refreshed. In an attempt to “enhance” it, I purchased a high-quality 3” MF topper. It certainly was more comfortable, but with it, came a bit a sleep apnea. I had traded one problem for a different one.

I went to my local “big box” mattress retailer, and naturally, THE most comfortable bed in the store, was the Tempur Ergo Grand, and with its fully adjustable massaging base, was priced at $12,500!!!! They offered a lifetime guarantee, but you would need a lifetime to pay for that bed.

Research for an equivalent ensued, and I wound up looking at this mattress. I am sincerely grateful for all of the previous reviews! Very helpful indeed!

I am on night 3 as I post this, and it is simply amazing – it really is a comparable alternative to the Tempur Ergo Grand, at a fractional percentage of the cost!

To compliment this mattress, I also ordered the Reverie 7S fully adjustable base from Amazon. In short, I have been able to completely replicate the $12,500 bed/base combo, for $2,200.

Notes:

Yes, it really does weigh a 100+ pounds! (Queen) Box was 18” x 18” x 60”

After 3 days, it has taken its full shape, and the off-gassing from the manufacturing process has already subsided. I ran the A/C with the windows open, and that was helpful.

The manufacturer, and these reviews, say “medium-firm” and that is dead-on.

Modern sheets fit it like a glove.

No problem getting on, or off the bed – middle-aged, heavier guy here.

Best sleep I’ve had in years – no regrets.

(pic was taken just moments after letting it loose from its plastic wrapper)(takes about 2 days to reach its full shape)

product_title: VIVA OFFICE High Back Fabric Office Chair with Movable Headrest and Adjustable Armrest
review_body:
Decent chair, but mine had two minor design/manufacturing flaws. The two armrests must be bolted into the seat bottom using the three provided flange bolts that are approximately M6-1.0x20mm in size (for each armrest). One one side, two of the bolts weren't long enough. Had to make a trip to Home Depot to purchase the next length up (M6-1.0x25mm flange bolts). The other armrest didn't have this problem. Problem #1 solved with the slightly longer flange bolts. Problem #2 was ONLY two of the three bolts (for each side) could be used, as the holes drilled into the seat were improperly aligned. However, the armrests hold together well with just the two bolts on each side.

Chair fabric is OK. Neck/head rest pillow merely held in place by a velcro strap, but the pillow easily slides up and down (i.e. - will not stay in place very well). I'm a 5'4" guy, so having the chair down as low as it can go with my feet touching the floor, and the armrests as high as they can go to touch my elbows makes for a near perfect ergonomic fit...there's no room to raise the armrests or lower the seat.

review_body: After reading all the reviews, I purchased this item.  I agree with most of the comments that it takes about 4 hours to put together. I got this about a month after my last chemo treatment and I am not a physically active person, but I was able to put this thing together myself!  It was very heavy and I took the advice in the reviews and assembled in the room where it would be used.  I bought a 6 inch futon and only use it to sleep on but I would recommend a 4 or 5 inch futon because it is too hard to get back to a seating position with the 6 inch.  The top bunk is definitely too close to the ceiling for an adult to sleep.  The ladders hurt my feet when I tried to climb up to the top bunk so I bought a 6 foot ladder to use.  Here is the biggest problem, it wobbles and the bolts that hold the entire bed together are coming loose!  I had to re-tighten every bolt on all corners of the top and bottom!  I am going to contact the company to find out what I can do to make sure it doesn't fall apart!!!  Unless someone has an idea of how to keep it secure, I don't recommend this item and especially not for kids!

product_title: Zinus SC-SBBK-14NT-FR Smartbase Bed Frame Metal, Narrow Twin
review_headline: brutal honesty here...  4 may be high. I'd rate 3.5
review_body: This base was amazing when I took it out of the box. It is lightweight, assembles quickly, and I've moved since I owned it so it takes up very little space during that process. The storage is also great.. But there are several support beams underneath which don't allow you to use all the space... That being said, if you have hard wood floors you may want to go another route... Preciously I had carpet and things were okay.  It DID start squeezing after a few weeks...  I fixed it by tightening the wing nuts...  And squeezing was minimal. On hardwood however if your floor is uneven the squeeking is a definite. Also the rubber covers for the feet make it really easy to slide on hardwood and provide minimal friction.  I remedied this buy jamming cardboard under each leg... But...  The squeezing continues...  What I've found is that the wingnuts may be convenient but are a terrible way to keep this thing securely fastened... There are tiny rubber washers that come with it but they almost disintegrate on your first assembly... I'm currently on Amazon browsing washers to hopefully fix this and will apply an oil or wd40 or something.  I'll probably replace the wing nuts altogether... I've actually had one break off during tightening...

product_title: Reclaimed Wood Look Finish Chrome Snack Side End Table
review_headline: Solid metal construction, but a poor top
review_body:
My biggest complaint with this item is the fake wooden top. It's plastic, and doesn't look even remotely like realistic wood. It rings hollow when rapped or tapped, and has an extremely plastic feel to it. The top has a very grey color to it that doesn't even REMOTELY look like any wood I know, much less reclaimed wood.

The item is easy to construct, although the two screws in the bottom frame-piece and two in the top frame-piece are at the joints. If you tighten them too much, you may cause the joint to separate and cause the item to fail and fall apart. There are only six plastic nubs. Four are used for the feet of the item. Two are used between the top frame-piece and the faux wood panel, but there need to be four here.

If you want a very cheap-looking, very inexpensive side table for a rec room or child's room, this would be fine. For anything lese, I would not recommend it.

product_title: Mission Daybed Frame - Solid Hardwood
review_headline: A well-made set, minimalistic design, easiest assembly
review_body: well-thought through, minimalistic design, my 9 yo has assembled it (as one would play with a toy) with a very minor help (my help was needed to hold large parts suspected and to push down with my grown-up weight). Small things are taken care of - slats do not pop out, having an extra grove on top each, screw driver goes almost horizontally due to an extra slit for it, well-sanded all over, refreshing natural color of unfinished solid wood, flaxen with almost imperceptible greenish hues,  and the wonderful light smell of poplar - note: poplar does not take finish, so you would need to paint it if you need another color, however we do prefer the unfinished solid wood, and we will just wipe it periodically with napkins saturated with a light wood oil - it takes exactly the floor footprint of a twin mattress and does not infringe on the room space - we can sit on it with our grown up weight and play board games, it is very sturdy - hardwood, and an amazing piece of wood-working mechanical engineering (years ago, when I had time, I worked with wood, and I can attest it is a truly professional work, design that goes well with the type of wood used and a quality construction. The screws will need to be tighten in one months, that your kid can do him/herself, just put it in your calendar to remind them. We REALLY like it.

review_headline: I used it today for the 1st time on my bathroom and was happy with the outcome
review_body: I'm all about eco friendly and natural products, and was very impressed with the cleaning power of this bathroom cleaner. I used it today for the 1st time on my bathroom and was happy with the outcome. I sprayed my bathtub and let it sit for a while and then scrubbed with a brush and was surprised to see how easily it was to get some of the soap scum and stains  off my bath tub.The longer you let it stay on, the better it takes away the dirt.  No bleach or ammonia to worry about the fumes harming you. I'm not a big fan of the jasmine smell but love the fact that it cleans wonderfully. I look forward to trying all of their cleaning products since I liked this one so much. I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for my honest review.

product_title: Coaster 3 Piece Dining Set
review_body:
I bought this table set for my very small 420 sqft apartment, and it fits perfectly in the dining room! The materials of the table are wood, and are well put together. The chairs are what require the most assembly, and the directions were a bit confusing at first. The ends of the table fold down easily through bars that are under the table, and stay up with no issue or weird gaps/unevenness. The table is very easy to clean and comes with instructions on the care of the product as well. I purchased the dark cappuccino table and the colors of the wood and upholstery for the chairs are beautiful together. Overall the product looks like it is of good quality and expensive!

Cons:
The table is VERY heavy.
The ties that are stapled under the table to hold the pieces together before you assemble them were difficult for me to remove (pieces are still stuck to the bottom, but not visible).
The chairs are SO uncomfortable if you sit on them for longer than the time you would just spend eating (sometimes I have done my homework at the dining table instead of my desk).

Overall the unit is  Flimsy. adjustable back is not well supported when in the up position it has a lot of give. I had to lean the bench up against the wall  otherwise the back feels like it would just snap. The tufted cushions also had one tuft that had not been properly manufactured at was not pulled down like the other 9 tufted spots on the cushion. Cushion is extremely firm, like most foam, I expect it to get softer with use. The gray fabric is true to color and looks sharp, its just too bad the unit is defective and flimsy. Like most furniture you buy online, your better off going to a furniture store and seeing your options first hand.

product_title: Winsome Nolan Console Table with Drawer
review_body: There are two things to really like about this table, ease of assembly and the fact it made from real wood. I'm not sure what kind of wood this is but it's not press board that I'm certain of. The table is sturdy and well made. I have mind centered on a six foot long wall and it looks great.  The drawer is small, mover for looks than anything but it's big enough for me to store pens, note pads, booklets, phone chargers, batteries etc.  As far as assembly goes it's easy to put together using the included hardware and easy to understand instructions. Some of you might need an extra set of hand securing the bottom shelf but it can be done by yourself if you just take your time. I put my table together in twenty minutes. I actually own all four living room tables in this series and am pleasantly surprised at just how nicely they are made. They're heavy which is a good thing and the packing of assorted parts is very professional as well. This table would look great by itself in an entry hall or wherever you chose to use it. Again it's very well made compared to much of the self assembly furniture we buy these day and I doubt you will be disappointed if you chose to purchase this very nice looking table.

product_title: Queen Bed (Black)
review_headline: Make this a 5-star bed with 1 modification
review_body:
Make this a 5-star bed with 1 simple modification.

Drill the mounting holes all the way through the headboard, get longer bolts with washers and mount the base with the bolts going though the headboard.

This will make sure you base won't fall off the headboard in 6 months.

product_title: Knape & Vogt Side Mount Soft-Close Drawer Slide
review_headline: drawer slides are a pain in the a** and replacing them is never as easy as videos make it out to be
review_body:
Word of advice for folks doing kitchen remodels or installs - get the soft close drawers installed as a part of the process, not after the fact. Because of this shortsightedness on my part, I have spent countless hours watching youtube videos and reading through hardware specs for drawer slides. Basically, drawer slides are a pain in the a** and replacing them is never as easy as videos make it out to be.

These slides require two additional components to function. I find it INCREDIBLY annoying that this company does not have an option to include all 3 components together as a set to save on S&H. Plus, the additional brackets sell as individual items, not as pairs, while the slides sell as pairs. This is an asinine thing, and cost the review one star. Assume that you will pay at least double the cost of the slides to get everything you need for the install.

The install itself is another pain in the a** in that (a) working in a cabinet that is already installed is nigh impossible unless you are the size of a hobbit and as slender and flexible as an elf; (b) there are only 8 screws provided, meaning you either need to buy additional screws to secure the slide or you need to make sure you don't put a lot of load on the drawer; and (c) you need to make sure that the slide is absolutely level before fastening it in place, which is incredibly difficult due to point a.

Once you actually manage to install the slides, the first thing you'll notice is that the pull required to open the drawer is actually pretty high - it's not an easy pull by any means and you have to overcome a fair degree of resistance. The next thing you notice is that you have to push the drawer pretty solidly to get it to close fully. A soft hip tap to close won't do it any more - you just end up with a partially open drawer cause there's insufficient force to cause the soft-close mechanism to engage. This cost the slides another star.

However, when they are installed and when you keep the above two points in mind, the slides work well. I love the soft close mechanism and watching it engage on the closing drawer is great. They do work and they work well. But because of the difficulties above and the lack of consumer-friendly bundling, I rate this as 3 stars.

PS - don't be an idiot like me and measure the length of the drawer to determine the slide length needed. Measure from the front of the cabinet face to the back of the cabinet. I've found that this is typically two inches longer than the length of the drawer. Also as an FYI, the back end of the slide just rests in the bracket so it's OK for the slide to be a bit shorter than the length from front to back since the back bracket is about 4" long.ove two points in mind, the slides work well. I love the soft close mechanism and watching it engage on the closing drawer is great. They do work and they work well. But because of the difficulties above and the lack of consumer-friendly bundling, I rate this as 3 stars. I've found that this is typically two inches longer than the length of the drawer. Also as an FYI, the back end of the slide just rests in the bracket so it's OK for the slide to be a bit shorter than the length from front to back since the back bracket is about 4" long.

It is also VERY tall.  We used our old box-spring and I practically need a ladder to get into bed--LOL!  That will be better when I have time to purchase some bunkie-boards. product_title: South Shore Libra 4-Drawer Dresser
review_headline: Great dresser if you know what to expect
review_body: I purchased this dresser for my new apartment to match my other south shore bedroom pieces. The product was shipped undamaged and with all pieces. Like most box furniture pieces there are always some pieces of lower quality including the drawer bottoms and the backboard (a dense cardboard material). If you expect this like I did you will be satisfied with this dresser. Like my other South Shore pieces they have a very smooth plastic gliders for the drawers that I think are very practical and glide seamlessly. When purchased I intended to replace the dense cardboard-like bottoms of the drawers because the amount of clothes that it was going to hold, I was talked out of it and decided to try using all of the material given and not replace the drawer bottoms, and to my surprise they work perfectly. The one thing I did do in addition to the assembly instructions is apply wood glue to wood joints to increase durability if moved. Overall, this is a great product of great quality for the price. I gave 4 stars because I still think they should provide higher quality drawer bottoms and wood glue (for assembly).

product_title: Winsome Daniel 3 Drawer End Table
review_headline: Compact but spacious. Its great once you put it together ;-)
review_body:
The picture is rather accurate, in fact, it looks prettier in reality. I tried to put it together myself, but couldn't, so I called in professional help- if you can get a couple of friends to help that might work too. But even with all his power tools and stuff, it took him a good hour and a half to put it together. My guess is not everyone will find it easy to assemble, so just keep that in mind before purchasing.

Also get a tube of wood glue, as some dowels may be loose.

During my attempts to assemble it on my own, the components suffered quite a few dings but surprisingly, the finished product had no scratches/paint chips, so I guess the material is resistant to minor damage, which is a good thing.

Finally, this is a handy thing to have as a nightstand or just a chest of drawers in a small apartment. Drawers are rather spacious and sturdy. Overall, I am glad I purchased it. Its good value for the money.

product_title: Convenience Concepts Storage Ottoman with Trays
review_headline: Great quality at a great price
review_body: Love this! The size is not overbearing, the lid is easily raised and safely stays up in place (if you have small kids you will like that), there are 4 vent holes in the bottom, (again with the small kid thing), and the trays really do fit on top and raise nicely with the lid of the ottoman. The Ottoman lid is sturdy enough for teens and adults to sit on. I've witnessed my older teen sitting  on it quite firmly keeping her little brother inside of the ottoman. You see, those vent holes come in handy with older kids as well. And the trays; those look so cute as serving trays in the advertised pictures, but in my house they turned into lap desks for homework as the kids kick their feet up onto the ottoman. The trays hold up well too, no scratches yet! My children aren't as rough as my brothers and I were growing up (thank you universe), but I think this piece of furniture could have handled it!

review_headline: the bed frame was fine for a little while and then the middle support ...

The looks would be 5 stars. It is a classic look but the addition of the cream color on the sides makes it pop! Really really liked the looks. As for the quality, we would give it 1 star. It SEEMED excellent but, the first time we washed it, we followed the washing instructions and the nonslip backing totally peeled off from the rug/runner itself. VERY disappointed as it was then virtually unusable as the backing got all messed up and we ordered it due to needing nonslip backing! Emailed the company's customer service department, waited a week, and received no response whatsoever. Sent it back as a return with Amazon and told them the issues with no issue in returning it. Was very hopeful that this would work out (heck, we wanted to order more in this exact pattern for the rest of the house!) but disappointed with the end result!

product_title: Flash Furniture Contemporary Black Leather soft Recliner/Ottoman with Wrapped Base
review_headline: Nice chair. Easy to assemble. (Update: It may have a weight support factor.)
review_body:
This just came in this afternoon by Federal Express. Box weight was 46 lbs. I pulled the parts out and photographed them. The photos are being uploaded here. Then I assembled the chair and ottoman. Basic tools came with this kit, but I used my own tools. At first, I tighten the bolts and nuts up too tight on the back of the seat, which I realized when the chair would not adjust. After loosing the bolts, the chair adjusts easily. After it was assembled, I also realized that I had left the 2 center posts out of the photos, but I was not going to tear it back down to photograph them.

The chair and ottoman seems solid and comfortable. Looks are in the eyes of the beholder, but looks good to me.

1st impression, I am satisfied with it.

Update. September 11, 2015
I just reduced my rating of this chair by 1 star. I noticed last night that the chair seems to be leaning slightly. I confirmed that thought just now. That lean may have been there all along with me just noticing it. The other thought was that I weigh 300 lbs and I may be too heavy for it. In either case, the fact that it is leaning lowers my rating by 1 star from 5 stars to 4 stars. (If it crashes, then so will my star rating of it.)

We've used it for children of guests when they spend the night, but I'm sure an adult would spend a comfortable night away in this bed too. The only small issue is that when folded the wheels don't roll that easily, but this bed is light enough to pull harder or lift when moving.

review_headline: Very sticky, but edges wear quickly...see pictures.
review_body: I let them choose the color because I only needed these for my unfinished basement steps for practicality, not for looks. I would not recommend doing that if you want these treads for aesthetics and looks because the pattern is random and not consistent from tread to tread (see pics below). The backs of the treads are COMPLETELY covered with stickiness (and it IS sticky), and they haven't moved a bit...so make sure you know where you want them before you place them. After two weeks, the front edges were showing signs of wear (see picture). And as another reviewer mentioned, make sure you place them where you will actually step...many people center them on the step, but you will notice you step closer to the front, not the center.

product_title: Casual Home 176-51 5-Shelf Ladder Bookcase
review_headline: Half-inch gap between supports, plate fit poorly. It's ok, but disappointing.
review_body:
The Casual Home bookcase is very easy to put together -- the included allen wrench puts the shelves to the supports quickly with no problems.

My real complaint was that the supports, which are in two sections, fit together poorly on the back right corner. I expect there to be a bit of variation in simple, cheap furniture like this, but a half-inch gap between the top and bottom parts is too much. Even with a dead blow hammer and as much pressure as I could muster, I could only close the gap halfway.

The plate that connected the two parts (one screw on each side) fit poorly, and the screw holes weren't even close to lining up. The wood split slightly when I attached the plate, which didn't help.

I'm not *too* bothered because this is going in a dark corner and the problems won't show, but I'd planned on buying the corner shelf to go along with it. I'm going to skip that because I'm just not confident that it'll fit together properly.

review_body: I bought this a few months ago and it still stinks. The wood is cheap, and i think the majority of the smell might be coming from the big sheet of particle board that the bed sits on. Speaking of which, that part is really two parts. That is understandable, seeing as how it probably greatly reduces shipping costs and makes getting it places easier. It's a little hard to explain maybe, but when assembling, you have the two boards that you have attached the trim to. The boards have predrilled spots for a hole/peg locking mechanism. First of all, that doesn't work so well. Then, once it is together, it doesn't line up well. IF you are able to get that lined up, the trim doesn't line up. So basically, halfway up your bed the trim  doesn't line up with itself. And sometimes it will split apart and leave a bit of a gap. I can live with that, since we don't really have company in our bedroom. But that toxic smell on the other hand...Unless you can air it out for half a year in a well ventilated room before you use it, I would pass on this bed.

review_headline: This rug color should have read “Tarnished Silver” or Medium Dark Grey
review_body:
This rug color should have read “Tarnished Silver” or Medium Dark Grey
I have several Safavieh wool rugs and know that they are high quality so I was so happy to find this cotton rug for my bath.
I ordered this for my bath which has the colors or sky blue and white (but not bright white-white). I thought “silver” would describe something that I envisioned as newly polished silver. The picture in the description shows the color as predominantly off white or a very light grey. The actual rug is predominantly very dark grey with some white strands.
The rug is shipped in a very tough transparent plastic bag and I could see the rug before I even opened the packaging. When I received the rug I noticed it was predominantly dark grey with some white strands. That combination gave the appearance of striped and bold which is too overpowering for my bath ambiance. The color won’t work for me. I think a better photo that shows the weave in full size and color would better serve Amazon shoppers.
I bought the 2’3’ feet by 6 feet rug and there is no way this could be washed in my washer because it is heavy even before it is wet. Maybe it could be washed at the coin laundry that has heavy duty washers but I don’t have time for that, so I am returning the rug.

product_title: Atlantic Gaming Desk - Not Machine Specific
review_headline: All in all a pretty good desk for the money
review_body: All in all a pretty good desk for the money. Very sturdy, and has plenty of surface are for large keyboards and mouse pads. The monitor riser can accommodate a pretty large monitor, I've got a 27 inch on there with a few inches to spare. Also has some additional features such as: a "charging station" you can set your other electronics on, a small pullout drawer in front, a media/controller holder, a headphone holder, and hilariously, a cup holder. My one huge problem and what kept it from 5 stars is the lack of cable management options. It has a small tray underneath for a surge protector, but thats it. For something labeled a "gaming desk" I would have expected more in that department.

product_title: Dorel Home Products 13-Inch Pillowtop Pocket Coil Mattress
review_body:
Excellent mattress. I bought this to replace a far-too-soft memory foam mattress. I was worried because I do like very soft mattresses, but sleeping on one for 2 years has hurt my lower back. Yet too hard mattresses hurt too. The previous reviews made me decided to give this one a shot, and I'm glad I did!

it is firm, yet the topper makes it soft and you sink in just a little. It really is an odd combination of two feelings, and it works! I'm sleeping way better and my back feels great. I highly recommend this mattress! And the price can't be beat!

Regarding the smell: There was a faint chemical smell when i got it, so I let it air out a bit and diffused some lemon oil over it. Once I put the mattress pad and sheets over it I haven't noticed a thing.

Also, be careful opening the plastic when it is rolled up--Be prepared that it can kind of "explode" open with a loud pop. It did for me, and scared me and the friend that was helping me. It was over in just a second, but it can be startling.

review_body: I had looked for a while, and  this is a nice laptop/work space note ( this laptop table IS CENTERED) which I was looking for, I saw alot of nice tables but the part that rasies up is off to the left or right, for a mouse pad, most show a cup of coffee, bad idea) so if the table is to the left when you raise it, then you are going to have to type on your keyboard off set about 6-7 inches, I cant type that far off center, it would take for ever correcting mistakes, and I already make enough of those without adding something else to deal with, and I also have a 17.3" HP and when the tray is raised any, it almost will catch on the table so it doesnt fall off, but remember I said almost, this table is more for a 15 inch laptop if that is what your need for buying it, but let me tell ya, most of the time I have to keep fighting with the table and hanging on to the pc, and thank God I dont keep coffee near my pc. product_title: FURINNO 11058GYW/BK Oak Turn-S-Tube Wide TV Entertainment Center, Grey/Black
review_body:
A lot of iffy reviews on here made me nervous about ordering this, but I figured, for $28, what's the worst that could happen.

Definitely worked out, though, as its even better than I had hoped for. So many reviews say that its much shorter than they were expecting, but its exactly the right size for my needs, and its surprisingly sturdy--I'll definitely trust my 48" flat screen on it.

The black/expresso color is exactly what I hoped for as well. It matches almost perfectly with my black brown Ikea furniture, and that was definitely a relief.

Assembly was the best part. Took all of about 5 minutes, with no tools, and the instructions are idiot proof.

Definitely a fantastic product for the price, though...don't let the other reviews scare you.

review_headline: It's a great table - love how the whole bin is see-thru
review_body: It's a great table - love how the whole bin is see-thru. My only issue with this is where the plug is located. I think that it should be located in the middle and not connected to the stand so that you could lift the bin out of the stand while still remaining plugged. The way it is set up now, you have to unscrew the plug in order to remove the bin. So, you can't lift the bin out if there is anything in it without having something underneath to catch the contents. This table would be perfection if they could change the location of the plug.

review_headline:
I'm afraid it's not unreasonable to assume the worst. As for the functionality First of all it has an unpleasant chemical odor. I'm not incredibly sensitive to these things, but even I had to take it out of my bedroom to air out for a couple of days before using it. A little disappointing in a product that bills itself as "eco," but I would take that claim with a huge grain of salt, since being made of plant-based oils very likely just means they bulldozed some virgin forest and set up a monoculture plantation. Given that there's no information on the origin of the "plant-based oils," I'm afraid it's not unreasonable to assume the worst.

As for the functionality, I haven't had it for long enough to see if it welds itself to the floor, as other reviewers describe. Honestly, I'm not sure if I want to take the chance.

As others have noted, it's not really cushiony and doesn't adequately support the rug, though to be fair I kind of expected that from the picture. Another minor annoyance is that the actual size is substantially larger than the 5' x 8' size in the description, so if you actually want that size you have to cut it to measure.

We didn't have thousands to spend on ... This was actually a very scary purchase for me to make online sight unseen and no way to try it out before buying. This is my first memory foam mattress purchase. I had spent months researching and going to local stores to see if I even wanted a memory foam. I read review after review on this mattress here on Amazon for months new ones added all the time. I will tell you for owning this mattress for almost a year now. I don't know why I spent sooooo long to order it! My husband and I love it! We didn't have thousands to spend on a new mattress, but wanted something with good quality that would last us for a long time. We got the king size with the 2 free pillows which we also love! I do not think this mattress is too hard at all, as some reviews have said. I have major back and neck issues and I used to wake up every morning in so much pain. The very first morning waking up on this bed and pillow... I didn't want to get up. I was so comfy and no pain! The only issue I had at all was with the delivery from FedEx which I am still upset about. I have 2 entrances to my home that are accessible from my driveway. I came home from work with my 14 year old daughter who has a heart condition and was shocked to see what was lying in the middle of 5 car length driveway. Off to the side next to my trash cans my mattress with only 1/3 of the box the rest of it was exposed and lying in 2 feet of snow! It was no where near either one of my doors that were about 20 feet in either direction away from where I assume the driver kicked the box out of the back of his truck and left it where it landed. My daughter and I pulled off the what was left of the box ( thank goodness it was double wrapped in very heavy gauge plastic) I am not a weakling.. But she and I pushed it up the rest of the driveway and lifted it onto the deck 3 feet and shoved it into the house this thing felt like it was 300 pounds. And to be honest with you I have no idea how much this king size mattress weighs.. But it was extremely heavy. I left it lying in my living room for several hours to warm up as it was only 15 degrees outside and I had no idea how long it had been lying in that frozen snow pile. I immediately called Fedex and filed my complaint. The lady told me in the computer the driver wrote it was delivered to my front door... UMMM NO!!!!!! It wasn't I took several pictures and told her I could send them that minute. She said she would file the complaint and a supervisor would contact me back. To this day.... No one has ever called me! I ended up calling Amazon to let them know as well. They were right there on the spot willing to replace my order. I was grateful but advised them it wasn't necessary as the mattress was lucky for Fedex just fine thank goodness the shipping people packed in 2 layers of very heavy plastic. We did get the mattress unrolled just fine by unrolling it inverted as it is rolled up upside down. And it immediately started to inflate as well as the pillows. I was worried it would take longer cause it was still very cold from being outside even though it had been in the house for at least 4 hours before we opened it. Even though you are suppose to wait the 72 to sleep on it we did not. It was completely inflated fully by bed time. I threw on the new mattress pad we also ordered and have been sleeping great ever since. we have also decided that we are going to order the boxspring test matches as well. As we are still using the old coil spring from our old mattress.. And since we live this mattress so much we want the entire set up. We will be doing this soon. Don't hesitate to order this... It's perfect. Even better than most expensive branded mattresses that we tried out in our local stores. It has kept up its shape and continues to be a wonderful sleep. And one more thing . Unfortunately, even thought i followed the instructions to a T it just dint work out.

The holes that attached the center legs were drilled in the wrong spot and the screws popped right through, leaving ugly particle board holes showing. The dowels were too long, or the holes were not deep enough and when installing the top they lifted the laminate leaving two ugly marks on the top.

The glass doors scrape and don't have an even fit and finish. Upon unpacking the think i tossed the box it came it and quite frankly i would have never been able to get it back in there. It fit like a jig saw puzzle. Once even partially put together you're never getting it back in the original box if you need to return it.

I really wanted to like this, but i guess i got a dud. No way to return it, i mean who has a casket sized box sitting to send it back? So now im stuck with a worthless paper weight i need to break into pieces small enough to take to the dumpster, Huge bummer

review_body: I can't tell you how pleased my wife and I are with this purchase. Exceeded our expectations. Arrived early and superbly packed in sturdy cartons (we bought two) with reinforced tops and sides. The nightstands themselves were buffered with foam and wrapped securely. Not a scratch on them. Yes, as others have said, the drawers are a bit small -- put perfectly adequate for a nightstand. They open and close smoothly and the hardware (the only thing I had to attach and it took less than five minutes) is dark brass and attractive. We looked at similar stands in a couple of discount furniture stores and they were more than twice the price plus the cost of delivery. These appear to be real wood, by the way, not pressed board. Nice satin finish -- and no, they are not finished like Ethan Allen or Thomasville quality, but they don't carry that price tag either. We are having 1/4 inch glass cut to protect the tops (as we do with other fine furniture we have) and they will look great next to our four-poster bed.

product_title: ORE International R597-5 Five Tier Metal Book Rack
review_body:
I'm going to compare this to the standard pressed-sawdust five-shelf bookcases that I have a lot of, and that I would have bought another of if I hadn't bought this.

Pros:
Lightweight!! My pasteboard bookcases are in the 60-70 pound range, and simply trying to move them involves a lot of shoving and "walking" it around. This is light enough I can pick it up and carry it to a new place. Let's not mention buying locally (much cheaper than online for normal bookcases) and hauling things up three flights of stairs to my apartment.
Sturdy. Oh, the normal bookcases I've been buying are sturdy enough, but this is too. I have the two bottom shelves filled with magazines, and it's holding them with no problem.
Easy to assemble. Though not much easier than wood ones, since they use a small allen wrench that can be hard to grip for those of us (average women) without a lot of hand strength.

Cons:
One less shelf. A normal "five-shelf bookcase" actually has six shelves, counting the top. You can't put books up there, but you can put light regular stuff, and I find I miss that.
No adjustable shelves. Most bookcases have at least three adjustable shelves, but this has none. Of course, I rarely use anything but the average shelf height, so it doesn't much bother me.

Despite the missing shelf, I really like this bookcase and I'm going to buy more of them before I think about another heavy fake-wood one.

Note: I bought two; this and [[ASIN:B00J2CIAFE 5 Tier Metal Utility Book Rack Black Finish 13.5" D x 24"W x 64 H"]]. This isn't quite as deep, but it's somewhat sturdier. If you want to store lightweight stuff, there's not much difference, but I'm not sure how the other would handle a full load of books.

We have kids and they scratched the seat cushion with something but the dark color hides the scratches quite well.

The only thing is if you have it inside on hardwood flooring or something similar you will want to place it on a piece of carpet. We didn't at first and small rocks and debri would get under it and it scratched our floor.

product_title: Stina Solid Wood Reversible Stair Way Twin/Full Bunk Bed w/ Drawer, Under Bed Chest, Made in USA
review_headline: Maybe made in America...not American quality
review_body: I sought out an American made bunk bed and it was hard to find because almost nothing is made in America anymore.  Nevertheless, I wanted to support our domestic economy so I bought this one.  The bed may be made in America but if this is the standard of American quality now, it's no wonder we've lost our manufacturing capability to China.  This bed is made by Woodcrest and sold through numerous resellers under different names.  It is the same bed and here is what you need to know:  It IS SOLID WOOD. It DOES NOT COME WITH SLATS. It is reversible but you have to remove the panel from one side and attach it to the other side.  Requires drilling 6 pilot holes. Have to drill pilot holes for all the rails. Horrible instructions, not even for the model bed I purchased. The finish is rough.  It wasn't sanded or varnished properly. Most of the parts are assembled with staples and at every staple there is a hole in the wood with chips of wood flaking off. The drawers are nothing but boxes stapled together instead of using proper joinery. The slides on the drawers are cheaper than the cheapest ones I've ever seen.  Nothing but a piece of plastic over a metal slide.  Not only do they make an annoying noise every time they are moved, they aren't stable.  They are flimsy and not secure.  Mine arrived with damage to one of the drawers (corner broken off), a piece chipped off the stairway, the paneling warped, and the fasteners for the paneling protrude off the surface, creating a danger.  I am disgusted with the quality of this American made furniture and I really regret buying this bed.

"The components of our memory foam products are made in China, but they are Certi-PUR US certified. This means that our products are low emissions for indoor air quality. Our products are also made without formaldehyde, mercury, chlorofluorocarbons, prohibited phthalates, and PBDE flame retardants. Our products have been tested and approved for safety, durability, and performance.
For more information about what this seal of approval says about the safety of our products, please visit www.certipur.com . Please let us know if you have additional questions."

I am not sure why it's not on the questions answered section and how much of it to believe but don't have much choice now.

product_title: 3, 4 or 5 Tier Metal Utility Book Rack Black Finish
review_body:
I'm going to compare this to the standard pressed-sawdust five-shelf bookcases that I have a lot of, and that I would have bought another of if I hadn't bought this.

Pros:
Lightweight!! My pasteboard bookcases are in the 60-70 pound range, and simply trying to move them involves a lot of shoving and "walking" it around. This is light enough I can pick it up and carry it to a new place. Let's not mention buying locally (much cheaper than online for normal bookcases) and hauling things up three flights of stairs to my apartment.
Easy to assemble. Though not much easier than wood ones, since they use a small allen wrench that can be hard to grip for those of us (average women) without a lot of hand strength.

Cons:
One less shelf. A normal "five-shelf bookcase" actually has six shelves, counting the top. You can't put books up there, but you can put light regular stuff, and I find I miss that.
No adjustable shelves. Most bookcases have at least three adjustable shelves, but this has none. Of course, I rarely use anything but the average shelf height, so it doesn't much bother me.

I do worry about the sturdiness, though. When assembling it, I was surprised that the screws didn't seem to want to fully tighten. They just kept turning. I eventually realized it was because I was actually bending the metal rods on the side, flattening them with the pressure from the screws. I stopped there, but I'm a woman of average height, weight, and hand strength. I can't loosen a screw most men have really tightened, and I can't get them that tight either. If _I_ can bend these, everyone else should be really careful.

Note: I bought two; this and [[ASIN:B003G2ZKQ8 ORE International R597-5 Five Tier Metal Book Rack]]. This is a little deeper, but it's not as sturdy (that one has slightly thicker poles and rods, and I couldn't flatten anything with the screws). If you want to store lightweight stuff, there's not much difference, but I'm not sure how this would handle a full load of books. The other is holding magazines well. Given the choice, I'll probably buy the other before I buy this one again. But this is still probably better than a heavy fake-wood one, even with the missing shelf.

i will not be purchasing this type of item again from amazon.
