product_title: Signature Sleep 6-Inch Memory Foam Mattress, Twin
review_body:
This bed was recommended to me by someone I knew. At the time, I even got to borrow theirs and it was soft and felt like a cloud. A few of their family members bought and used the bed, so this was really praised as a good item. After buying this for myself, I can see that there is definite a gap in quality that shows with the price point.
Some people buy this mattress and end up with a perfect solution to what they needed; it's real memory foam and comfortly molds to their shape. Mine, after giving it the proper two days to inflate, is more like a piece of wood. Sure, it sinks in a little bit, but it feels both too firm and unsupportive at the same time. I am waking up in horrendous neck pain at day two. I have a physical job that puts a lot of stress on me, but my previous bed, which was sinking in in the middle and needed replacing, was never putting me in this much pain, even under more stressful situations.
I am not rolling in the dough, but I have already read that others cannot even get their beds returned because of some craziness with the shipping policy. So, can I recommend that this bed is worth it for other people? NO, absolutely not: because it is a gamble.

I will be purchasing a topper, as some others (who claimed that the bed was too firm) have suggested. I was not planning to spend extra, but sometimes bad things just happen to you and you have to fix it before you end up at a doctor to fix your neck.

PS, the plastic smell lasted for over 3 days.

product_title: LUCID 10 Inch Gel Memory Foam Mattress - Dual-Layered - CertiPUR-US Certified - 25-Year Warranty
review_body:
I spent months reading hundreds of reviews about the different foam and gel foam mattresses that are offered on Amazon. I knew that I liked the medium firm feel when I was testing out mattresses. I kept in mind that every mattress may have a different feel, but one reviewer made a great point that you can make a harder mattress softer, but you cannot make a softer mattress harder. I steered clear of the plush, soft, medium soft descriptions. I also researched the difference between a foam vs gel form mattress. According to what I read, I can't remember the source, there was more customer satisfaction with all memory foam mattresses than with the gel foam. As far as the mattress feeling hot, I have a waterproof Sealy Posturepedic mattress cover on it and it's just as hot as our old mattress. The mattress is hard. It is described as medium firm. We like a firmer mattresses, but this mattress so far is reeeeally firm. I put an egg crate mattress pad (we already had it) on it under the mattress cover and it has made it more comfortable. We are a co sleeping family so there is plenty of room for the us and our 4 year old. We've only slept on it for 2 nights, but it can feel the difference in my back and hips. I had less pain waking up this morning. My bones didn't crack. Thus, so far so good.

The delivery was amazing! We live on the 3rd floor of a walk up. I feel sorry for the delivery guy who had to get it up the stairs, but it was super convenient for me. It came a day early. I'm sooooo thankful that I worked from home that day so I could set it up before anyone got home. I'm about 5'2" with shoes, 125lbs, little upper body strength ... But I was able to push the beast of the mattress inside and to the bedroom. I ordered the base that is suggested to go with this mattress and it fit perfectly. I placed a remanent rug on it to support the mattress from "falling" through the spaces to protect the bottom. In total, I had an hour to set up bed frame and mattress before I had to pick up my son from school. I was able to vacuum, set up frame, unroll hella heavy mattress and dress the bed in under an hour. The mattress has a padded bumpy side indicating the bottom. I had to flip it over after it started to expand super quickly. Let me say this again, it is HEAVY! But, I did it. Once flipped over, it expanded to 9 inches within 5 minutes. I checked to make sure the mattress cover was on the right way to ensure we would be sleeping on the memory foam side and not the support side. The mattress cover has a crushed velvet feel. There was a smell, but to my super sensitive nose it was not strong. None the less, I opened the sliding door, turned bathroom fan on and faced oscillating fan to blow the smell out of the room. I also sprinkled baking soda on it and vacuumed it before putting on the mattress pad. When we returned home 6 hours later, the smell was minimal and pretty much gone this morning ( 2 days to air out).

My review is kind of backwards, but I will update it as time goes on. I'm hoping this mattress will last us and more importantly that I won't wake up with body ache anymore. As of day 2, I recommend this mattress. I gave it 4 stars and not 5 because it is really firm and not medium firm as described. But maybe it will soften up as time goes by.and mattress before I had to pick up my son from school. product_title: Milliard Mighty Rollaway Twin Bed with Foam Mattress – Built for Longest Life and Heavy Sleepers – Great for Frequent Guests, Bed & Breakfast Homes, and Commercial Use
review_body:
Milliard Premium Folding Bed
When you get this there is no assembly required other than to screw in the 4 wheel which come with it. Once you put the 4 wheels on you are ready to open it up. It does come with a little wrench to use to make sure you get the wheels on tight enough.
Now to open the bed up is really simple also there is a buckle strap on just one side of the bed all you have to do is unbuckle it and it is ready to be opened up and laid down.
Once you have it down its good to go you can place your sheets, pillow and a blanket on it.
I really love the wooden head board that is connected right to the bed, also the mattress that is on this is a very good thickness with a quilted material around the mattress.
For being a fold away bed it truly is very comfortable to sleep on, which makes a really great bed for when company comes over.
It is very easy to set up and even easier to fold back up for when you are not using it, you just need to remember to buckle it back up so it doesn't end up falling back open.
I would also like to add that when you do fold the bed down there is about an inch of space between the two mattresses but when you are laying on it you can't even tell that the little space is there.
This would be perfect for anyone who is looking for a spare bed, or even if your child is going off to college.
I received this product in exchange for an honest and unbiased review

product_title: Serta Bonded Leather Big & Tall Executive Chair
review_headline: Too difficult to put together and operational handles hard to reach
review_body: I have put together quite a few office chairs all by myself in the past.  This chair required a second person to help and was still extremely difficult.  The problem is that the bottom plate does not easily line up with the plate on the back piece so someone will need to provide considerable force to hold the chair in the right position and not move while you put all four short screws in place.  When your friend moves a bit you will curse at him.  When you are tired of cursing at him you can hold the chair together while he tries to screw it together and he will get his chance to curse at you for moving.  Once you finally get the plates together you may find that you cannot put on one or both of the arms because the plates are not aligned just right.  So you get to do it all over again.  The third time was the charm for me.  You are better off assembling this item with an ex-wife or someone you never want to talk to again.  I am 6'5" and have extremely long arms but I must lean way over in the chair and stretch to reach the controls on the bottom of the chair.  The ability to lock the back in place is essential because the tension knob either doesnt work at all or there is such a slight difference between most resistance and least resistance that I cannot tell the difference.  Fortunately you can lock the back in place in any position, not just the straight up position.  If the screws for the bottom plate were 1/4 inch longer I think it would have been easier to put together and I suspect would result in a stronger, more longer lasting chair.  Because the screws are so short they dont go into the wood very deeply and I suspect these screws will tear out sometime soon, which is the reason I was replacing my old chair in the first place.  If this product turns out to be more durable than I currently imagine I will update this in a year and acknowledge my misgivings.  However in the future I will purchase from a local store where I can easily return something thateither appears too flimsy or too difficult to put together.  If you purchase this chair I strongly suggest you go to Home Depot and get four base plate screws of the same diameter but a bit longer than the factory included screws.  That should make it easier to put the chair together and likely provide more strength to hold the plate onto the bottom of the chair.

product_title: Roundhill Furniture Stina Solid Wood Reversible Stair Way Bunk Bed with Drawer and Under Bed Chest
review_headline: Maybe made in America...not American quality
review_body: I sought out an American made bunk bed and it was hard to find because almost nothing is made in America anymore.  Nevertheless, I wanted to support our domestic economy so I bought this one.  The bed may be made in America but if this is the standard of American quality now, it's no wonder we've lost our manufacturing capability to China.  This bed is made by Woodcrest and sold through numerous resellers under different names.  It is the same bed and here is what you need to know:  It IS SOLID WOOD. It DOES NOT COME WITH SLATS. It is reversible but you have to remove the panel from one side and attach it to the other side.  Requires drilling 6 pilot holes. Have to drill pilot holes for all the rails. Horrible instructions, not even for the model bed I purchased. The finish is rough.  It wasn't sanded or varnished properly. Most of the parts are assembled with staples and at every staple there is a hole in the wood with chips of wood flaking off. The drawers are nothing but boxes stapled together instead of using proper joinery. The slides on the drawers are cheaper than the cheapest ones I've ever seen.  Nothing but a piece of plastic over a metal slide.  Not only do they make an annoying noise every time they are moved, they aren't stable.  They are flimsy and not secure.  Mine arrived with damage to one of the drawers (corner broken off), a piece chipped off the stairway, the paneling warped, and the fasteners for the paneling protrude off the surface, creating a danger.  I am disgusted with the quality of this American made furniture and I really regret buying this bed.

Although there is a stop to keep the drawer from sliding IN too far, there is nothing to prevent it from coming all the way OUT if you open it too far. I did exactly that this morning - the drawer, the steel flatware organizer and about 4 dozen pieces of heavy stainless flatware came crashing down on my shins. I wasn't hurt - scraped shins - but it didn't take much imagination to see how bad it would have been if a small child had done that. And at 27" high, this drawer is well within reach of the average toddler. This is a SERIOUS HAZARD for households with small children.

Since I keep my coffee maker on top of this cart, I think I will just use the drawer to store extra k-cups.

review_body: Quick Overview: looks really nice(pro) great construction and very sturdy(pro) the new models are very well shipped(pro) great customer service(pro) optional keyboard tray(pro) glass moves easily(con)  i purchased this for a nice computer desk because it had everything i wanted. Its a great price but looks nice. The middle supports are great for running wires and for a good foot rest.  The older model ,which is the one i got, came in a really poorly beat up and poorly cared for package. The glass was not packed very well . This resulted in my glass being chipped and cracked in a few places. Do not let this sway you away from buying this because the customer support was fantastic. a few pictures later and they were shipping me a new desk.               NOTE -apparently they do not have spare glass so if this happens its going to be a new desk for you I informed them mine was pretty much stuck together and roughed up . They said i did not have to ship them back my broken one. It was at this point things were very frustrating. The replacement i got was a completely new model. This one was packaged with extreme care.  The box is big and inside its lined with very thick cardboard (that you can reuse around the house) The glass is in a separate box on top of the parts,also in a separate box. I was very impressed. BUT it came with no parts to put it together. SUPER SAD AND MAD! Again i email , and again fantastic service. i assured them i had 3 people look for the parts to no avail. To my surprise they also wont ship just the parts. So yet another new desk for me. This time i shipped it back with a slip they gave me. Picked up in a day. The next desk i got was absolutely perfect. I found the new one had a thinner and better construction and was very pleased when i put it together.  If you buy two and wish to combine them together and feel like you are diy enough . it is possible because thats what i did and it looks amazing.  5 star service 4 star product 3 star shippingGreat purchase! I love a good customer service!  update:2/4/2016  if you lean on the desk the glass moves really easy. i wish they would fix this in a new model. suction cups arent enough. maybe add a metal lip in the back or something. if i figure a solution to fix this out ill update again.

product_title: Handy Living Wood Slat Bed Frame Extra Long Twin
review_body:
We chose this product because of the simplicity and similarity to an IKEA slatted bed that we are very please with. It took only 45 minutes to put this product together, working by myself. IKEA has much better instructions with their merchandise. A few thoughts:
1. Use a socket wrench to assemble. The flanges on several legs had been bent in transport, and straightening them by torquing with the included wrench would have been nearly impossible. The enclosed tools were suboptimal.
2. Loosely assemble the outer metal pieces, and check for square by measuring diagonals before tightening everything up. (Presuming your mattress is rectangular)
3. Every bit of packaging is recyclable, except for two straps that held the slats together, a major consideration for us in buying this product.
4. A mallet would come in handy for putting the plastic pieces in, but lightly tapping with a hammer worked as well.
5. Disassembly to move the bed will be simple. The plastic pieces can be left in place on the rails, while bolts and slats are removed for easy transport.

product_title: Split King Size Leggett & Platt S-Cape Adjustable Beds
review_headline: I will try to update as we begin the journey with our new sleep setup.  Happy to answer any questions!
review_body:
Update 02/26/16. All I can say is WOW! The difference this bed has made in my life is amazing!! By raising the bottom section to the max height it helps to relieve my lower back issues. Simply raising the top makes a huge difference when I start to feel a cold coming on. I guess it helps with the sinus drainage while I sleep? I would highly recommend this to anyone looking for an adjustable bed!
Arrived early! Will update the review after we set it up this weekend and spend some time using it. Purchased it due to severe lower back issues (surgery, injections, etc.) Hoping the ability to change my position while sleeping will allow me to sleep in the bed and not in my chair!
I cannot explain how easy this was! There is a video on YouTube detailing the setup. It took longer to watch the video (5 minutes) than it did to actually set it up. The Beds fit perfectly inside my existing bed frame. You cannot tell that there is anything special about the bed until you see the remote. I have serious lower back issues which injections and surgery have been unable to fix. My nightly routine usually involves waking up at 1 or 2 AM and then sleeping sitting up in my chair in the living room. The first night we slept on our almost 3 year old memory foam mattress and the sleep was incredible! I adjusted the head up a few inches, but elevated my feet about 1.5 feet above my body. WOW!!! I slept better than I have in years! The second night we slept with brand new top of the line Tempur Pedic mattresses we bought the day before. All I can say is that the $2000 I spent on the S-Cape was the best money I have ever spent! Between the S-Cape and the Tempur Pedic I feel like I did in my twenties (47 now). I will try to update this as we continue to live with our new sleep setup. Since you spend 1/3 of your life sleeping, invest the money in sleeping well!! I would be happy to answer any questions you may have

product_title: Classic Brands Cool Gel 12-Inch Ventilated Gel Memory Foam Mattress
review_headline: Baby bear would think this bed was just right!
review_body:
We bought this for our guest room after having bought a king for ourselves. I have had several guests since purchasing and they all loved it. Not too firm, not too soft. I have even used it when my husband's snores were keeping me awake. I do recommend rotating it one time per month, though, just to make sure it would wear evenly. When we turned ours, it did feel different.

I also recommend you carefully read the instruction sheet. It does specifically state that you should not use a heating pad in the bed because it could degrade the foam.

As for the "new car smell" --- it does fade over time. We let this mattress inflate itself from its vacuum packed delivery state and let it air out naturally with no sheets or blankets on it. However, if it really bothers you, you could try putting a mattress pad on before the sheets to add an extra layer between you and the foam smell.

Side note: A king mattress with the same exact specs was over 1,300 dollars at a mattress store that I am not going to name. Our king was just over $500. We saved a lot of money on our king and was were very happy to get it delivered to the house. So much easier than trying to coordinate getting a mattress from a store.

product_title: Nourison Modesto (MDS04) Area Rug
review_headline: Not remotely as pictured - washed out, yellowed colors, and very cheap quality
review_body:
I took a chance ordering this rug, disregarding "you get what you pay for." Knowing that monitors can vary in how they show color, I took care to view this rug on three different devices. On all three, the dark brown appears... dark brown. The tan appears... tan. Likewise the other colors. When it arrived, I actually wondered if I'd been sent the right rug. The dark brown was a medium mud color, and the tan was a yellow beige (VERY yellow). The blues and greens were completely washed out, all leaning toward the very yellow end of the spectrum. What looks like a "cool" brown rug with distinct tan, blue, and green was actually a yellowy-beige wash of blah.

If the wrong colors hadn't decided me, the cheap quality would have. This is the thinnest rug I've seen of this type, even including rugs hanging at Home Depot. It's more of a mat than a rug, on par with the indoor/outdoor woven jute rugs for thickness (but not as dense). I toyed with the idea of living with it for a day to be sure, but the third time walking through the room I couldn't take it. Back it went.

product_title: Lorell LLR53100 Mid-Back Task Chair without Arms, 2.3" Height X 9.8" Width X 34" Length
review_body:
We purchased 3 of these chairs for office use, so sitting 6-7 hours a day, 5 days a week, 50 weeks per year. I believe the chairs have adequate cushion for this kind of use. I like that they are fabric because I think it will hold up longer than the fake leather offered on most chairs. The chairs arrived with quality tools required for assembly. Assembly was easy, a total of 7 bolts. The chair parts seem sturdy.

One thing I don't like is the way the seat back height adjusts. You slowly move it up to the desired position. To reset you lift it all the way up and it drops back down to the bottom. The only problem is that it is a little difficult to get a high setting with out accidentally resetting back to the lowest setting. That being said, with about 30 seconds of fiddling you can set it and forget it. One of the seat back ratchets arrived broken. I've contacted the manufacturer about a replacement.

We've purchased about 25 chairs under $200 over the years, these are towards the top end of the quality spectrum. They don't look at nice as other chairs we have purchased. I would say that these chairs place comfort and quality over appearance, and when you are sitting in a chair for long stretches each day, comfort quickly outweighs good looks.

At first I was apprehensive about purchasing a chair with no arms, but when considering this, I looked around the office and saw that everyone had their arms on the desk, not on arm rests.

product_title: Walker Edison Soreno 3-Piece Corner Desk
review_headline: Looks good, but the crossbar blocks your legs a lot
review_body:
This desk looks great with the glass top and sleek design. If you like a glass/modern look, this is a good choice. I bought this specifically because my old desk had cabinets on the side and a small section for my legs to actually be. I wanted a little more freedom for my legs.

Assembly: It wasn't too difficult, although I had to take a section apart at least three times due to installing it backwards or upside down and not noticing until I hit a point that needed it the other way around. Every piece is labeled and all the items needed are in labeled bags, which is great. No guessing about sizes here. However, the directions leave a tad to be desired only because it is hard to know exactly which side they go together. Sometimes the extra holes face upwards, sometimes downwards. They never explicitly say, just reference the picture. And the pictures are detailed, but easy to mess up in my opinion. Taking it apart and putting it back together wasn't difficult though, albeit frustrating and time consuming. Everything screwed in well and easily to the point that I pretty much could just hand screw everything in and just tighten with the wrench.

Finish: The glass is held together with suction cups which I found a bit surprising, but works pretty well overall. There is a little up and down wiggle to it but pretty much none side to side wiggle, which is great. The glass is heavy and feels sturdy, I even dropped a lamp onto it while setting it up and didn't even seem to scratch it. The desk is a bit on the low side, although it fits my GT Omega racing chair fine. However the keyboard tray would be way too low for me would probably get in the way of my legs. I didn't even bother to assemble it and put it on. I also use the none keyboard tray side since that is the way my old desk was aligned and where my wall mounted monitor is. If you use a laptop this might be a bit low for you as you might have to look down at the screen causing neck strain. The worse part was I had to take off a crossbar at the bottom because I was hitting it with my legs. I'm 5'11 if that helps anyone.

Pros:
Love the glass look
Feels pretty sturdy
Easy to put together with one person and some free time

Cons:
A tad bit small in height
Directions for assembly can be a bit confusing
The crossbar had to be removed because it blocked my legs too much
The glass makes it really difficult to hide wires

product_title: Sleep Master Standing Smart Box Spring, Twin
review_headline: Not the best value for money
review_body: This is not the best value for money. While you can put together the bed, the instructions are far too short to be clear and the design of the bed leaves a lot to be desired. For example, when putting together the side of the bed, you need to screw together parts that fit into each other in a male-female slot fashion. One would expect the screw hole holding the things together to be a round hole so the screw stays in place. Instead, it is a cut in the metal and it is possible to pull the two parts apart even after they are screwed together. Things didn't fit together perfectly at right angles and there was some force required to get the various parts to align together to form the frame. I am sure this introduces stress in the metal frame which is not good for the life of the product. The cover that goes over the frame was shorter than expected and tore at one corner while I was trying to put it on top of the frame. The stands are made of plastic, which in reality looks pretty cheap. It would have been better if these were made of metal. The headboard parts are pretty much useless as I don't think any headboard will fir into the narrow space left between the metal headboard latch and the bed. The slats that go into the frame at the top are all the same size, but two of them were supposed to go into slots at either ends of the bed. These slots lie on the curved corners of the frame and are shorter than other slots. It's a lot of pain and hammering before the slats fir into these smaller slots. product_title: e-Joy® Floor Chair Sofa Home Essential / lovers Folding Sofa a Lazy Man Sofa /Normal Version
review_headline: Fabric completely falling apart after 3 months of use.
review_body:
Update (1/10/16): After using this chair daily for gaming for a couple months, the material covering the chair began ripping at the seams where the squares are sewn on the front. The fiberfill that gave the seat its cushion began coming out all over the place, and is pretty much gone at this point. The only good part of the chair left is the frame, which is basically like the frame of a lawn chair, so it is essentially useless, unless you have sewing experience and want to replace the cover. Even sewing it myself, it would cost me about the same to fix it as it would to just buy a new (better) chair. At this point, I would not recommend purchasing this chair.

I initially received this chair at a discount for my honest, unbiased review; obviously, that has not influenced my opinion or rating in any way.

------------------------------------------------------

I've been looking for a game chair for a while now. I had a bean bag chair, but after a couple months, the beans got squashed, and it's just no good anymore. I don't want to have to keep replacing beans, so I decided to look for something else. That's when I found this chair, and figured I'd give it a try. The internal structure/frame seems pretty sturdy. Once I get it adjusted to the right angle, I usually prop the back up against the bed, but it will still hold me comfortably without being propped up. The foam insert is a little thin at the bottom, and I can still feel the floor, but not in an overly uncomfortable way. One issue I've noticed is that the foam on the inside is a plastic type foam that will probably also get squished over time. The material covering the chair is actually a bit plushy...it feels like a short-napped fleece, not the smooth fabric I was expecting. The cover itself is padded as well, and it unzips, allowing you access to the inside and to remove it for washing.

product_title: Sonax C-813-SCM 35-Inch Wide Component Wall Shelf, White
review_headline: Perfect size and look, installation feels like trial and error
review_body:
So the shelf does exactly what it's supposed to do, but it does have its pros and cons:

PROS:
- The appearance is very professional looking. The frosted white glass is a nice touch compared to other shelves that are clear glass or black.

- The single stud installation is super easy, and the mounting bracket is thin enough to hide easily behind the wall mounted television.

- The double-wide size is perfect for a receiver, PS4, and an iPhone docking station

- The corners are rounded, which is significantly safer than sharp corners given the size and height of the shelf unit.

CONS:
- Have to be honest, and say that the piece that holds the shelf to the mounting bracket seems a little questionable. It's literally two screws holding a plate under tension. And there's no solid bottom to the bracket - so, if the screws weren't tight enough or became loose under any circumstance it seems like the shelf would just slide right off.

- I'm also a little disappointed in the wire hiding system. It was almost impossible to hide wires with the bracket flush with the wall. We had to loosen the bracket, tuck the wires, and then re-tighten screws to keep them behind the wire holders. From there it took some tweaking to make it "perfectly" hidden and connected. Once you get the hang of it, it's not that bad.

- Because of its size and its single stud installation, if you bump/jiggle the unit on either side it has a little bit of wiggle (which makes me a little nervous given the mechanism holding the shelf). But assuming once you hang the shelf you're not moving it significantly it shouldn't be an issue.

I bought this frame when we upsized our guest bed to queen and the standard twin bed frame no longer fit the mattresses (you know the cheapie old frames that have 2 cross bars and 4 wheels but nothing more?). review_headline: I would have liked some extra cams in the smaller size
review_body: The dresser pieces were consolidated and packed neatly, with all hardware included, and it came through the shipping process very well--no significant abrasions to the cardboard packaging and no crushing of the contents, despite being a heavy item.  The dresser was easier to assemble that I expected, given some negative reviews I read in advance.  The main problem I had with assembly was that not all of the cams fit adequately and actually broke when I tried to screw them into place.  I suspect it is because the cam holes themselves were not sufficiently cleaned out and the cams got caught on rougher patches of the carving.  I pushed on through, however, and completed the assembly, with concerns about its overall stability.  (Because of this problem, I would have liked some extra cams in the smaller size, though.)  The final assembly works well, the drawers open and close smoothly, and it appears as pictured.  It looks good in my bedroom and replaces a 5-drawer upright, giving me more room to maneuver.  Generally satisfied.

When mounting the headboard, the particle board broke and we had to rig up something to ensure it wouldn't move. Also, one of the drawers had a bent track and gets stuck every time I open it.  After purchasing this online, I saw a similar one at Costco for less, much better quality, and had buyers remorse. If you don't have access to Costco, this bed might fulfill all of your needs. Just go easy on installation of headboard. For those vertically challenged, you may want to invest  into a step stool for easier access. I didn't have a hard time getting in and out of the bed until I became pregnant. It's comical at times to watch.

review_body: The 2 in 1 Collapsible Trunk Organizer & Cooler is exactly what I needed! This organizer is great for helping me keep everything in order. This Organizer also comes with a soft cooler that fits into one of the compartments! You can use it to keep your milk or cheeses or any other cold purchase cold on the way home from the store! I am really excited to have this and have used it for one purpose or another since I received it. I think that one of the greatest things about this 2 in 1 Collapsible Trunk Organizer & Cooler is that if folds flat easily, so that you can fit other objects into the trunk when you don't necessarily need it! product_title: Coaster Peel Black Computer Desk with Keyboard Tray
review_headline: This was a gamble for me that paid off.
review_body:
So I wrote a poor initial review due to the shipping time. It was stated as sept 1 - 7th, then I got the shipped notification email stating sept 15th. I was a bit mad about that. That would have been about 20 days from the day I ordered it until I got it. It doesn't look like my initial post was even uploaded, or it was removed lol. Anyway, the day after I got the shipped confirmation stating the 15th of sept it shows up...keep in mind that's Aug 28th. I no longer can complain about the shipping, it was extremely fast even though the email stated another week to two weeks.

The desk was pretty well packaged, there was one corner of a part that was a tad crushed...it must have been dropped on that corner. Lucky for me it was minor and it was on the keyboard tray supports back side so its not at all visible. This is a simple desk with a keyboard tray, exactly what I was looking for. Not that many parts to it and assembly was simple. Some of the pre drilled holes needed cleaning, they had some wood bits left in them preventing some of the hardware from seating properly.

All and all for the $ I am pleased with this desk. It replaced a desk a made, poorly mind you, that was very similar in size, this one has about 4" more depth but otherwise is exactly what I was replacing.

Pros:
Adjustable feet for added height - I had to max out the height so my chair would roll under the keyboard tray.
Long keyboard tray to accommodate a mouse & MS natural keyboard.
Lightweight, very reasonable price.
I have my full tower, 32" curved monitor, two desktop speakers and my alarm clock on it. Its small but has plenty of room for my needs...I have very limited space.

Cons:
The keyboard tray with a MS natural keyboard doesn't pull out far enough, the F keys are almost covered by the desks top. I may buy extended slides and swap them out.
The adjustable feet I have maxed out, I could have used another 1/2" of thread on these.4; of thread on these.

review_headline: Surprisingly comfortable. The smell was noticeable
review_body: Surprisingly comfortable.  The smell was noticeable, but not terrible; once I put a sheet on it, I couldn't smell it anymore.  It inflated within 6 hours; I slept on it the night it arrived (I was too darn tired of my temporary air mattress), and I think it was fine.  Though my partner and I both are comparing this to very old mattresses, but I like how this is both firm and soft--somewhere in the middle.  I do like how the stitching pattern is different from most mattresses; I've never liked most mattresses weird diamond patterns, but I really like this one.  Hopefully this holds up well; if I get at least two comfortable years out of it, I'd say it fulfilled its purpose!

product_title: Acme Furniture King Bedroom Collection Roman Empire Cherry Finish 5 Piece Set
review_body: After I ordered this bed, I read a ton of awful reviews of the selling company, Appliances Connection, on multiple websites.  I got so scared of the horror stories literally every person had with them.  I attempted to cancel my order.  The bed came about 3 weeks after I ordered it (Understandable, its a tremendous order).  The shipping company allowed me to inspect each of the 8 boxes for damage and when there was none, I happily signed for it.  The bed is manufactured in Vietnam.  It is a great product for the price.  This bed in something like solid oak or another expensive wood could cost up to 5 times as much.  All the pieces were there including hardware, allen keys and a wrench for assembly.  Me and my dad assembled it in about just over an hour.  The only thing you might want to do is add support beams that actually hold the mattress.  We added one and a sheet of 1" plywood board across the support beams for stability.  If you're used to a platform bed like I was, this will require a box spring to raise the mattress to proper height.  It's a great bed and I'm glad I bought it.  It's tremendous, the detail on all the carving is great and not cheap looking.  I'm glad it wasn't cancelled out of my fear of the tons of reviews I read and overall had a positive buying experience.

review_body: Really solidly-built bed, surprising since it's made in china and not that expensive. Any metal connector is solidly built, and the 'arch' pieces that make up the skeleton of the bed are actually wood, not plastic as I incorrectly assumed they would be. Also, regarding those who had the bed fail, I'm a solid 230, and even with someone else in the bed nothing moves. Tighten the ~30 bolts more, you'll be fine.

With this bed, I sleep like the dead and wake up pain free. That is a first!!! Just the right balance of firm and soft. I used to have a Tempur-Pedic and this mattress is every bit as comfortable!
The frame was simple to set up. I just had to hand tighten a couple of wingnuts and that was it. Frame is sturdy and not squeaky and seems very solid although the metal is pretty light weight.
The mattress expanded almost immediately and was ready to go. I have heard of others complain of a "factory smell" but mine had none.
I still can't believe I got such an amazing bed for such a low price!

review_body: Words cannot express how much I LOVE my new pillow!  This is the first contoured memory foam pillow I've ever gotten so I wasn't sure if I would like it.  The pillow came nicely packaged in a zippered plastic shell (much like a comforter set, in case you want to store it or travel with it).  Also, it has a removable, washable cover on the pillow itself.  I love this feature, as I have bad allergies and am careful to wash my linens in hot water, etc.  It is much different from my usual pillow (I was currently using just a regular pillow).  At first touch, it feels very firm but instantly feels very comfortable as soon as you settle in.  My husband doesn't like this pillow.  But that's okay...now I get to use it full time.  :)  In regards to the cooling gel...I wasn't sure if this is just hype and if it would actually be a "cooling" feature or remain cool.  But I am pleasantly surprised.  My pillow stayed cool and comfy, no issues there.  I can't tell there's any gel in it....just a nice pillow.  In all, I'm so glad I got this pillow.  I'm really picky about pillows, and this one has surpassed my expectations.  Thank you!  I received this item at a discounted price in exchange for an honest review. All opinions are my own.

product_title: Oscar Carpet Stair Tread - Set of 13
review_body: I am very happy with this item.  Here are some hints on installation.  I used ipg indoor carpet tape #9971 and was very happy with it.  I decided to cut out enough pieces of tape for five treads at a time before beginning to adhere the tape to the back of the treads.  So I measured and then cut pieces of tape 1/4 inch shorter than the tread.  Of course you have to allow for the width of the tape to be glued on the ends of the treads.  So the tape on the long sides will be 4 inches shorter than your tread.  Cleaning the steps is very important.  I suggest using TSP which actually etches the surface.  Rinse well.  Dry well.  Once the tread goes down you cannot move it.  So if you are fussy about getting them lined up from the top to the bottom of the stairs, I suggest that you tape a light weight string from the top step to the bottom step along one side of where you want the tread to sit.  Trying to line them up as you go can be problematic and measuring each step is a bother.

The set came in multiple boxes. All of which are labeled on the outside as to what they are. The directions are fairly clear. I recommend putting the full size bed together first. But a benefit of this set is you can set aside the top or bottom if it's not needed yet.

review_headline: Great mattress. I am 28 years old and I ...
review_body: Great mattress. I am 28 years old and I hate to say it but I have never owed a new mattress. Getting ready to buy a tuft and needle took me six months to decide. I read 100s of reviews online for many different mattresses. Everyone was saying great things about the tuft and needle. I hadn't read a bad review for this mattress. I've slept on many different ones and this truly is the best. After 28 years of searching I've found the perfect mattress. I have had in for a month or so and still love every single night of sleep. Everytime I lay down to sleep at night it takes me back to the time I spent at Lake Como. When something brings great memories back you know it's a good thing. Great company, good people and the perfect mattress. I am beyond happy that I could give my money to the right people, to the people who truly produce a true to form product. This company delivers on all that they promise. This is a company you can be proud to support. Almost every company only cares about your money but this one truly cares about you. They want to make you happy and satisfied and they truly come through. The mattress is the most important item in your house and they treat you as the most important person in the world. I would recommend this mattress to anyone and everyone who will listen. If you have the slightest problem they will fix it. They care about you long after you've bought your mattress. Great people, awesome company and a perfect mattress.

product_title: Zinus SC-SBBK-14NT-FR Smartbase Bed Frame Metal, Narrow Twin
review_headline: and it was super easy to assemble
review_body:
I put it up yesterday, and it was super easy to assemble. The Queen sized frame came in two sections you unfold, secure the legs on, then attach the two sections together. The ease of assembly actually blew my mind a little bit, as you need no tools. Everything that needs to be tightened, which is just the front and back legs, and securing the two frames together, all tighten with washers you tighten by hand. I would recommend you wear a thick work glove or use a t shirt or something to pad your fingers as you twist them tight, because it will hurt your fingers trying to tighten them super tight, so you'll get it even tighter with some padding between your fingers and the washer. You want to assemble this frame tightly, metal frames will start to squeak if you do not tighten them up good from the start.

I used a box spring with mine, and so my mattress sits up super high. Not so high it's absolutely ridiculous, but a little ridiculous, yes. I like it though, and it has firmed my mattress up using both the frame and a box spring, which I like a lot. The firmer a mattress the better for me. Storage under the bed now is spacious, and using the bars in the center under the frame have allowed me to store things up high, so I can slide things under them.

A good frame so far, but I do worry about it squeaking in the future since it's a metal frame. Hopefully it stays quiet the way it is now.

product_title: Multiple Colors - Heavy Duty - Light Weight - Metal and Plastic Folding Stool - 400lb Capacity - Exclusively by Blowout Bedding RN# 142035
review_headline: Sturdy, heavy duty, portable, and light weight what else could you ask for in a stool?
review_body:
This little stool is nice and sturdy. I am slightly over 300lbs and it held up with no issues, or serious give when I sat on it. These stools are advertised to hold up to 400lbs which makes them a good purchase for any plus size person such as myself.

The plastic seat is slightly textured for a no slip grip. The legs slightly curve out to give a wider stance making this sturdier than I anticipated. It has a built in handle for easy carrying. The design is compact and it's easy to fold up and put away. Literally you grab the handle and pick up this light weight chair and the legs collapse with the seat part folded neatly on top of the stool's legs.

I will probably keep this in the trunk of my car for those events where we are short on chairs. You never know when you are going to get stuck somewhere and need a chair for a long wait!

If there was anything I would change about this stool is if it's being marketed to hold 400lbs the seat needs to be wider. At 300lbs my rear end is pretty wide, and while this seat provides enough coverage that I'm not uncomfortable if I was closer to 400lbs it might be too narrow.

My final thoughts...? Finally a fold up stool that will stand up to my fat butt!

I received the product mentioned above at a discount, for my honest review, this however did not influence the review of the product. The thoughts and feelings expressed here are 100% my own, after testing out, and trying this item.

product_title: ApexDesk Elite Series 71" W Electric Height Adjustable Standing Desk
review_headline: Very sturdy and lots of table space!
review_body:
I requested this desk for my office at work. We started moving to a paperless system at the end of June which meant that I sat 95% of the day. I hated it and was feeling terrible by the time I got home. I knew that I was going to be moving into an office (from a cubicle) so I asked for a sit stand desk. I had been looking for several months for the one that I thought was reasonably priced but big enough for my papers to be spread out on. The other desks similar to this one that I had found were well over a thousand dollars and there was no way I was going to get approval for that. I almost broke down and went with the Varidesk's that other people in the office had been getting. Now don't get me wrong, those desks are nice and everyone seems to like them; but for the accounting department, I desperately needed my table space.

I needed to be able to have my dual screens, keyboard, mouse, ten key calculator and scanner sitting on my desk with plenty of space left over to organize the Accounts Payable things that I have to scan in every day along with the other paperwork that gets thrown my way. (See attached picture, but ignore the mess, I have only been over here for a week!) I had sent another recommendation for a desk and then saw this one about 2 minutes later. After some research, we decided that this desk was the one. At a price of $599.99 with free shipping, this desk wasn't too much more than the Varidesk that I am looking at on the desk of a co-worker.

That brings me to the construction. This thing is HEAVY, but don't take that as a bad thing! For this price, I was expecting a much cheaper support system and table top. Each leg weighs a lot because of the box tubing, inside of box tubing, inside of box tubing for the extension and the feet are weighted as well. I probably could have put this desk together by myself but it wouldn't have been easy so a male co-worker came in and helped when I had to move it around. Thank goodness, I am stubborn and I don't like asking for help, but it was needed. The support under the table top is also what holds the motors and electrical control box so it is also made of a box tubing (with some open areas for access) and is very sturdy. The table top itself (I purchased the red apple wood and i like it, not too dark and not too light) is over an inch thick and seems to be a pretty good composite material. That thing was heavy also and I definitely would have needed the help to lift it!

Now to the motorized part: this is awesome! I have some very jealous co-workers because they think that this is one that I have to manually raise and lower and then get a nice surprise when I reach over and press the button. The cleaning lady likes it too since she can raise it up and clean under it better. The only problem I see with the lifting and lower ingis that sometimes it isn't consistent, as in, you press the button and it might start to raise and then stop. Sometimes it will start again without having to release the button but other times I have to press it again and again. This isn't a major issue for me but I am pretty easy going so if things like that bother you then you might see what causes the issue in the motor or electronics. Another thing I noticed was that if you move this, make sure to pick it up (two people) on both ends and then set it back down. If you move it by sliding it, you can put the legs in the slightest bind and then your legs will "pop" when moving. We picked it up and let the legs go where they needed to naturally and it has been fine ever since.

Now to my Health: I am overweight with some health issues that we haven't been able to sort out so when I went to the paperless system and stopped moving all together here at work, I started gaining weight. I have been using this desk for one week now (started last Friday) and I can honestly say that I feel a lot better and when I weighed myself thismorning, I had lost 4 lbs without trying. I stand about 5 to 6 hours a day now and listen to music which makes me be-bop a little. I get some funny looks but oh well. I have a mini stepper that I am going to start adding into my daily standing to try and get some more exercise while I am here at work. The fact that I am feeling better already makes me excited for a few months down the road to see where I am at.

I would definitely recommend this desk to anyone thinking about the sit stand option and I know of 3 others in my office that are going to getting one in the next few months. Hopefully I remembered to cover everything I wanted to but if not I can answer your questions.morning, I had lost 4 lbs without trying. I stand about 5 to 6 hours a day now and listen to music which makes me be-bop a little. I get some funny looks but oh well. I have a mini stepper that I am going to start adding into my daily standing to try and get some more exercise while I am here at work. The fact that I am feeling better already makes me excited for a few months down the road to see where I am at.

I would definitely recommend this desk to anyone thinking about the sit stand option and I know of 3 others in my office that are going to getting one in the next few months. Hopefully I remembered to cover everything I wanted to but if not I can answer your questions.

product_title: Office Factor Ergonomic High Back Executive Very Good Quality Nylon Mesh Chair with Flip up Armrest Synchronized Mechanism and Aluminum Base
review_headline: Great chair and outstanding customer service!
review_body:
The chair is really comfortable and breathes well with mesh backing and seat cushion. The folding arms are great for sliding the chair under a desk, freeing up space in small areas when the chair isn't in use. The wheels are smooth and roll on hard surfaces with ease. Assembly was done in under 10 minutes and could have been accomplished without the instructions (required hardware included). Well worth the purchase compared to similar items costing substantially more for the same features.

I had this chair 2 months, then the front cross-support under the bottom snapped (thick plastic), these things happen with chairs that don't have a steel frame. I reached out to the company via email to ask about a replacement part rather than dropping $$ on a completely new chair. Not only did they respond in less than an hour, they asked for a picture of the part to make sure they replaced the correct one and had a new part shipped out to me immediately following my reply, complete with tracking information! I was already really happy with the chair, with the exception of the unfortunate defective part, but the customer service that has backed this chair has made the purchase very satisfying.

review_headline: and this one is by far the best! The scent is awesome (Jasmine Mint)
review_body:
I have used a variety of natural dish soaps, and this one is by far the best!

The scent is awesome (Jasmine Mint)! It has a light, sweet scent. I have had far too many dish soaps that have a generic or citrus scent, and this one is so pleasant to use while doing the dishes which makes the effort a bit more enjoyable!

The ingredients are so much better for you than traditional soaps. If you are careful about what you use on your body/skin, think about when you wash dishes and how much soap you get on your hands. Read the labels and make the switch to Mrs. Meyer's. Forget about putting things like SLS, parabens, phthalates, etc. on your skin - or washing it down the drain and polluting. I also think this is much more gentle on skin compared to soaps that have harsh chemicals in them.

This dish soap is very effective. I have used other natural dish soaps that have disappointed. This has a nice thick consistency, and cuts through grease. It puts some other natural dish soaps to shame, to be honest. I feel very comfortable sharing this dish soap with the rest of my family because its not full of harmful ingredients. I highly recommend this product!

Thank you for the opportunity to review this product at a discount!

review_headline: Actual measured size of my pad is 3ft 10.5in x 5ft 9.5in
review_body: This rug pad arrived rolled up on a thick cardboard cylinder, wrapped in plastic with wire ties on each end. Upon unrolling, there was a faint odor that dissipated quickly. There were no creases or folds due to being shipped rolled which meant no need to weigh down or let it lay out before putting it under my rug. One side is felted, and the other has a rubber matrix that keeps the pad from slipping. I was pleasantly surprised at the thickness of the pad, and it definitely makes a difference under my rug. I have it on a hardwood floor, and the rubber backing keeps my rug from slipping around and the rug doesn't slip on the pad. The rug pad I purchased (4'x6') is a bit smaller than stated. Actual measured size of my pad is 3ft 10.5in x 5ft 9.5in. and you can definitely tell the difference in the padded and unpadded areas when walking on the sides, but its not particularly noticeable just by looking at it. I'm very pleased with the rug pad and it seems to be well made. I just wish it was the full 4'x6'. I received this product for a discounted price in exchange for an honest review.

product_title: Handy Living Wood Slat Bed Frame Extra Long Twin
review_body:
This was easy to put together. We actually bought one for our king and when we got a queen mattress, opted for the queen version of this slat frame because we liked the king one so much.

Pros:
Affordable frame
Easy to put together (we used a rubber mallet, just make sure your aim is true)
No squeaking noises
Feels sturdy.
The vaulted ceiling (from a cat's POV) is awesome. My cats love to lounge under the bed because they can walk without crouching.

Cons
Some slats looked less sturdy (knotty?), but moving them to an area that would receive more stress than another is a work around. So far, none have broken and thus we don't expect. Just as with any bed, jumping up and down like a trampoline is not recommended.

product_title: Altra Porter 55" TV Stand, Black Forest
review_body: Disappointing piece of furniture.  I decided to purchase this item without any reviews (NEVER done this before!), and will never make this mistake again. I looked at the item, which seemed to be good. Read the details, saw that it was made in America, the price was acceptable and figured, why not? I knew the item was going to be unassembled, but OMG so many pegs, locks and screws are required to assemble this!!  The assembly took about 3h doing it by yourself, probably quicker if you have a helper. But several pieces on the stand came scuffed (annoying). Plus each piece has a minimum of a dozen inputs, up to almost 20 connections that need to be made. Inserting the locking mechanisms is incredibly difficult to get at a 90 degree angle, but with enough fidgety and pushing all the pieces come together.  Overall, the TV stand is "ok", but at $150 + hours of assembly + the stand looking like a year of wear and tear after the first day = an unhappy Amazon buyer. In the end, this seems like an inferior product to IKEA, which is just sad.

review_headline: Fabulous looking stools that are super easy to put together!
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:59f43372f04d021725ead0036f0291e0]]Oh where to start?? These chairs are great! First of all, they are so easy to put together! I was able to put them together from start to finish in 7 minutes. I don't think I've EVER put a chair together that fast. The quality is fantastic! The red is a really nice bright red, I've kept my decorating scheme pretty simple with black and pops of color and these definitely pop. I've only had them set up for a few days and I've had two friends over and they raved about how nice they are and how they complement my decor. Overall I'm incredibly pleased with these stools; they were really easy to put together and they look amazing!

I received this product for free in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.

product_title: Cheetah Mounts ALAMB Articulating Arm (15” Extension) TV Wall Mount Bracket for 12-24” TVs and Displays up to VESA 100 and up to 40lbs, Including a 10’ Twisted Veins HDMI Cable
review_headline: Initial reservations resolved by great customer service.
review_body: October update: I was originally disappointed. The mounting plate was too big to fit the recessed mounting holes on either of my two monitors. I needed to find some longer screws to use the mount, but it was worth it given the great price. I posted my experience here (below), and was contacted by the distributor. First, after getting an understanding of my problem, they sent me a full refund for my trouble in having to find longer screws. Second, a few weeks later they contacted me and said that they had addressed the problem and offered a free one for me to try. When I received the new one I found that they had removed the corner edges from the original mounting plate and the new one fits inside the recess on the back of my monitors, performing perfectly without needing the longer screws.  So, I can strongly recommend the product - which is a fantastic deal for the price I originally paid. And I can say that the company has phenomenal customer support if you happen to have a problem.  ---------------------------------------Original Review Below this Line------------------------------------------------------ The name of this is TV monitor mount. Well maybe it should just be TV mount. I have two 24" computer monitors, one from Dell and one from Asus, each has a recessed hole for the mounting plate and the size of the opening is too small for the plate, even though the holes line up.  I will have to try and find some long screws that will work with the greater distance between the plate and the recessed screw holes.

review_headline: I bought 4 of these chairs and the experience so far has been great to the point that I can counter the previous ...
review_body:
Ok, so let me start by saying that I always read the negative reviews before the positive ones when buying a product. I bought 4 of these chairs and the experience so far has been great to the point that I can counter the previous negative comments as follows:

1 - Chairs came securely packaged with no damage whatsoever
2 - They all had Coaster tags and not counterfeits
3 - Assembly was quick (about 30 min for set of 2) and straightforward, only issue was with front leg bolt tightening that was a little slow due to the position of the holes
4 - Chairs look beautiful and seat straight, not wobbling at all but you have to make sure the bolts are fully tightened and doing so in an order (true for all furniture assemblies) not unlike when you tighten your car's wheel lug nuts
5 - Granted, the seat padding is not soft but it doesn't feel bad either, unless you plan on sitting for a looong time at your dinner table

I hope this review will be helpful

product_title: OSP Designs Deluxe Finish Wood Bankers Chair with Wood Seat
review_headline: Shipping too long; assembly instructions were wrong
review_body:
Shipping time was way too long. Assembly instructions were wrong. I'm glad I waited to last to put in the buttons, because I had to loosen the screws for the back to get the arms to align properly. The slot could have been a little wider in the seat back so the screws could align properly. One of the caster sockets was bent so I had to open it up with a tapered shaft to get the caster in. The product had some scratches and dents due to the excessive handing during its excessively long time in shipping.
If you can get through all this by having the tools, the product is strong and attractive. If you need the seat to rock back, don't get this chair. There is an adjustment but it doesn't change anything. It is stiff upright. Fortunately for me, this is OK.
I got the hard seat because my wife will make a cushion for it. This is better than the ones with the thin cushions.

product_title: International Concepts Saddle Seat Stool
review_headline: Solid hardwoods, sturdy, nice sanded finish, but has several significant manufacturing issues.
review_body: Bought this particular stool for use in my glass studio, as it looks very sturdy and scored very high reviews from consumers. Positives:  Product arrived very fast...three days shipping, (without using Amazon Prime) and fully assembled.  High quality hardwoods were used and the sandlng/finish well done. Basically  a sturdy well designed stool, however there are a few exceptions that need to be mentioned. Negatives: Stool has one short leg and does not sit on the floor properly without wobbling (very annoying).  I moved in several differnt rooms and then measured the legs...bingo!  One leg shorter by 1/4".  Fix: put a plastic furniture pad under the defective leg. Another leg has a slight chip on the bottom no biggie as it is not going to be used in a family area, albeit a glass studio. But the most annoying thing of all is that the chair is NOT 24" high, only 23" (measured to the top of the seating area) which is a tad short for my workbench.  Not going to bother to return, as I am sure the freight will be half the cost of the stool.  Will use for "something".  Three star rating due to short leg and short overall stool height versus what was advertised.  Buying another unfinished wood stool from a different manufacturer listed on Amazon and we will se how that goes.

product_title: Global Furniture Clear/Frosted Occasional Coffee Table with Dark Walnut Legs
review_headline: I purchased this due to another reviewer's helpful comments and information...
review_body:
Before purchasing, I had asked another reviewer, Bill, about their experience with the table over time. He assured me that it is holding up well so I took the plunge and made the purchase. After assembly, I must say we are quite pleased.

We are using this as a coffee table in our teenage daughter's bedroom. She has (2) twin beds that are arranged so that they form an L-shaped sectional and the table is centered in that area. This arrangement has really opened up the floor space in her room. She is using the table for her alarm clock, remote control storage, and other bedside sundries and it also provides a place for her to set a drink or snack down when she is watching TV or playing a game.

The metallic uprights that we received are indeed metal, not plastic, as stated in a different review. The disks that are situated between the uprights and glass are plastic which makes sense as they are there to protect the glass from scratching or cracking when putting the table together. Unlike another reviewer's table, ours is definitely not made of cardboard. It is some type of dark laminate over press board, plywood, or ???. When assembling the table, you have to punch through the laminate in order to access the holes for the bolts so the laminate is fairly thin. We particularly like the contrast between the beveled, clear glass table top and the frosted glass, bottom shelf. It is visually quite appealing. Once assembled, the table is definitely sturdy.

Thank you, Bill, for your review and for your help. It is most appreciated.

product_title: Pulaski Sutton Swivel Glider Recliner
review_headline: Really want to love it but...
review_body:
So I searched for months for a rocker recliner and was hesitant about buying online without sitting in it, but for the price and look, I couldn't pass it up.

I have only had it a week and sit in it constantly but I can't speak for the long run. It rocks and swivels with ease. It's also pretty comfortable. The foot rest is definitely a chore to push down and it is tougher to keep the back in a recliner position sometimes. I have to stand up sometime and kick down the footrest with my foot. I am 5"10 and luckily for me I have long legs but someone that might not be as tall would have some trouble reaching the ground to rock comfortabley because I barely do. I fit pretty nicely in it.

The color is more of a cool gray with a blue undertone. Luckily I could still make it work with my baby girls nursery.

I would say I have mixed feelings about this chair because it does have some great qualities like the rocking and swiveling but some not so good issues like the difficulty with pushing down the foot rest. If you are more picky with color that could be a big issue for you too.

For the price I would still say it worked out for me because I didn't want to break the bank and it does what I need it to with a little extra effort.

I would have given it a 3 1/2 stars if I could. It close to 4 but not quite. I rounded up.

Good luck!

product_title: Coaster Fine Furniture 460023 Loft Bed with Workstation, Black Finish
review_headline: Nice bed but damaged in shipping.
review_body:
I would have rated this item a lot higher if not for the fact it was received in damaged condition.

This is a metal frame bed; heavy, strong, and sturdy. I can only imagine the level of negligence in the handling of this product that resulted in the damage to the metal members of the bed. Unfortunately, by the time I unpacked the item to inspect it, the carrier (ABF) was gone. Given the damage to the box (in addition to the challenge I had opening it), there was absolutely no way I could repack the unit, nor did I have the slightest inkling of how to go about arranging shipping the unit back. I contacted Amazon.com and they issued a small refund (less than 10%) for accepting the damaged item. I had to use some rather heavy tools to bend a few structural members back into place. Some are still bent but, luckily, they are not really visible (the metal framework on which the mattress lies sustained the brunt of the damage). Once put together, it looks good and my daughter loves it. The damaged areas are mostly hidden by other structural members and the mattress (although it is easy to see when looking at the underside of the mattress).

In the future, I would probably not order furniture of this nature online again. Dealing with the aftermath of shipping damage is too difficult on an item of this size.

product_title: CVSLink CX7F Laptop Desk
review_headline: This multi-function laptop table is everything I could ask for and I use it every day!!!
review_body: First of all, I was completely skeptical about trying out a product like this because I was worried it would just sit in my closet. However, now that I have it, its all I use when I am on my laptop. I cannot get enough of it. The legs are awesome because you can change the height to whatever you want it to be that is comfortable for you. I got the one with the gray color and I like the way the blue and gray look with the lighter color of the table. This table also has a fan function which is so awesome because there is a USB that plugs right into the laptop from the table and it keeps the bottom from overheating. What an awesome feature to include with this multi-functional table. There is rubber on the right side of the table to help your wrist from not hurting from staying in the same position. The only thing I am concerned about that I would change is the fact that there are clips where my arms normally would rest. The idea of the clips is to keep the laptop from sliding, but I think that the placement could be done better or even something that was more comfortable for my arms to rest there. Also, a side note is that my two year old likes to sit on the ground and color using my table too because it is the perfect height for her. So, it definitely fits the multi-function label perfectly. I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest review.

review_headline: I used to sleep soundly but now i sleep on the floor.
review_body: I don't worry about it collapsing under my substantial weight it was easy to put together and i'd buy it again except there really no need. update 11/28/2015 @ 955pm This frame is nice and all but it has a fatal flaw so to speak and that's the welds that hold it together or should i say the welds that are supposed to hold it together ! I'm a big man this i know but this frame was advertised as heavy duty which it is not . I've had this frame 116 days as of this moment and it's showing signs of bending and some of the metal wires have actually broken their welds  . mind you being a big man i know better than to drop myslef onto my bed  and i'll note i've done absolutely nothing crazy to cause this .  If i had known this would happen i'd have brought it locally and gotten an extended warranty so i could return it to the store. instead i had to contact manju via amazon chat who has arranged for paid shipping and a full refund. only downside is i'll be sleeping on the floor until it's actually processed. which is a problem because as i previously said i'm a big man if i wanted these headaches i'd have just kept my box spring and put it on the floor with my mattress .

NOT WORTH IT IF YOU'RE A GAMER.

I went looking for a mesh chair, and found this one as the highest rated chair that didn't cost $300+ dollars.

After 5 months the right asrm rest ripped in the back where my elbow tends to sit, cause the metal structure dug straight through it.

About a week ago the left are rest started doing the same thing.

and about an hour ago, while resting on the left arm rest while watching a movie, the plastic SNAPPED at the seam, and now with just a bit f pressure I can make the entire arm rest turn 90 degrees.

This is a fine chair if you're using it only semi-regurlarly, but if you're looking for something hardcore. Stay Away.

Now I have to go and buy a whole new chair, and I've only owned this one, 8 months.

product_title: LINENSPA 6 Inch Innerspring Mattress
review_body: I've tried both the LinenSpa mattress and the H_L mattress (also sold on Amazon); both being 6-inch coil-spring mattresses. Both are excellent mattresses that measure 5½ inch mattress height resting on my bed frame. The primary difference between the two is the H_L mattress is more firm--considerably so--to my preference.  The LinenSpa has a lower coil count that results in a medium-soft feel under my 225 lbs; people who weigh less than 200 lbs will probably love the mattress.  I slept well on the mattress but my sore back in the morning tells me more support is needed. The LinenSpa mattress is covered with a quality tear-resistant fabric.  The LinenSpa company answered my email questions which was appreciated much.  People who need a firm mattress or who have back problems will prefer the H_L mattress.

product_title: Natural HomeLogic Eco Friendly Liquid Dish Soap, 24 oz | Powerful & Pure Non-Toxic Cleaning | Plant & Mineral Derived
review_headline: Cleans just as well as the big brand names
review_body: No one in my family has any major sensitivities so I bought this product purely out of curiosity to see if an all natural cleaner could be as tough as the major brands. The product comes from Amazon in a plastic bag which allowed some of the product to leak out of the container. It did not leak out the bag itself but the bag and bottle were coated with the soap. The soap itself cleans well, the consistency is much more watery than the name brand I use but the cleaning power was just as good. It lathered well and after I rinsed the dishes, they felt squeaky clean.  The smell is nice, it is not overpowering or overly citrusy. I like the fact the soap is dye free and plant derived. I feel confident with cleaning my child's bottles, dinnerware, and toys with this soap. I received this product in exchange for an unbiased review.

product_title: Tuft & Needle Mattress
review_headline: Weightless sleep with a nifty beginning!
review_body: Great mattress! It cradles your body perfectly and lets you "hang" there while you sleep. It's also amazing and pulling heat away from your body. When people say that you can't feel people getting into/out of bed it seems hard to believe but I've noticed with the Tuft & Needle mattress that it's true! Also, they say that their best suggestion for what to put this on is a slatted bed frame. I was skeptical at first thinking "won't I feel the slats on my back or side?" but I couldn't have been more wrong. I think the slats help with the breathability. I would buy this mattress again and again plus, the price point is SO worth it. Also, unwrapping this product is THE COOLEST experience ever :)

product_title: Best Price Mattress 8" Memory Foam Mattress + Bed frame Set - No box spring needed
review_body:
Even though Amazon stated that delivery of this bed would take an extra 1-2 days, it arrived in only a few days. I was surprised that it was packed in only 2 boxes. Set-up was very easy. The frame basically just unfolds and the mattress is compressed in a roll. Upon cutting the plastic open, it regained its full shape quickly.

I was very leery about buying a bed online. However, I was pleasantly surprised. I purchased this for a spare room at my parents' home. I have already slept on it a couple nights and it was comfortable. I'm not saying it's as comfortable as my name brand, high dollar memory foam mattress I have at home and I'm not sure how it will hold up over time, but for my needs it is perfect. For a spare bed I highly recommend this!

product_title: Elegant Comfort 1500 Thread Count Egyptian Quality Super Soft Wrinkle Free and Wrinkle Resistant 3-Piece Sheet Set
review_body: There was no invoice in my box.  This company is definitely guilty of cleverly worded false advertising.  "Experience the comfort and soft touch as 1500 thread count 100% EGYPTIAN COTTON". Notice EGYPTIAN COTTON in all caps.  "Soft as 1500 Count"  The sheets are decent for summer but I doubt they will last.  Once you find the tag sewn on the top sheet it says "100% microfiber polyester"  No tags sewn on the fitted sheet or pillowcases which have a blue design down the side, contrary to the plain white in the picture. If they are going to sell microfiber polyester sheets,they should be up front and say so. Amazon needs better control of these outside vendors. And these vendors better know what they are selling.  This affects my attitude toward buying from Amazon.  They have gotten too big for their own good and it's time for some tough competition.

product_title: Big Joe Media Lounger, Wheat
review_headline: Perfect for small apartments that can't fit multiple-person seating
review_body:
My apartment has 28" doors. You can't fit a couch through any doorway. I tried thinking of every alternative I could for 2-person seating... was thinking of a futon, but they seemed so uncomfortable (especially the cheaper ones). This was the best alternative out there. You can fit 2 adults easily on it. You can lounge back like a traditional beanbag, or you can push it against a wall and it's just like a couch--you can really mold it any way you like, and it does a good job of supporting whatever position you want to manipulate it into. I throw a body pillow across the top, throw my feet up on an ottoman, and it's just like a double recliner. It's extremely comfortable, easy to make it fluff up, and it didn't even need the initial "fluff time" of 7 days. It was good to go after several fluffs just out of the box. Yeah, it got much more poofy after it was left to air out and fluff up. But after the reviews I was really dreading having to wait for ages for it to be ready to use, and I was glad I didn't have to wait long. For the price you can't get better 2-person seating/lounging.
I also didn't notice a strong smell, at least not that lasted more than a day.
The only thing I could think of even being slightly put off by is that some of the foam pieces inside are bigger than you might expect--it's not that it's an uncomfortable lumpy, it's more just when you run your hand over it it's not smooth like a beanbag. But I think that's what makes it so supportive in different positions, so I wouldn't change it.

product_title: Poundex Bobkona Ansley Microfiber Accent Chair
review_headline: Looks and feels pricey, but it's not :)
review_body: This chair is perfect- it looks much more expensive than it was, it's lightweight, and was packaged well. The legs screwed on easily in 5 minutes, and there is a zip pouch in the bottom of the chair to store them. The color was what I was looking for- a subdued rusty orange, and the back detail adds a lot to the look.  There were some white spots on the fabric when it arrived, but I scrubbed them off with water, and the marks are not really noticeable- not an overall deal breaker, and not worth the hassle of returning it.  Will see how the chair holds up over time, it' a bit stiff now, but nice and wide, and paired with an ottoman, it makes for a good lounging chair.  I also like that it has a low back and arms- because although the chair is extra wide, it's not super tall, so it's great for my small apartment- I put it in front of my windows and it doesn't block out the light like my old wingback chairs did, but still has a similar style.  At this point I would order another for my living room if I had the space!
