product_title: South Shore 54"/60'' Holland Headboard
review_headline: No, it's not an heriloom Amish-made oak headboard.  It is what it is (particle board).  BUT: It totally met my expectations.
review_body:
The longer detailed reviews here are pretty spot on. I'm going to add additional detail and feedback to help anyone else looking to buy this.

Quality: Some people felt this was 'overpriced' or 'should have gone to ikea'. As long as you know that yes, this IS a particleboard product, I felt it is actually pretty decent. The color matches the online photo pretty well, I'm pleased with the overall look. I had no issue with the quality of the hardware- it's fine.

Assembly: To the folks who had trouble assembling it.. Seriously? The instructions are actually quite clear, and if you lay it all out and TAKE YOUR TIME, it all comes together rather nicely. One person said the 3 screw holes were not there on the backside of board "M". I almost had the same reaction, but then I looked *CLOSE*. They're there-- just hard to see and find. Rub your fingers around, you'll locate them. They're small. The only thing I didn't care for was that the back board (the board that's behind the shelf) is attached to the top, but not attached to the bottom. A small gap showed.. I dealt with this by drilling two pilot holes through the bottom shelf and up into the back board- and used the two long screws in the kit to attach. You need to drill carefully, as the back board is rather narrow. While I do believe the instructions are clear, my only gripe is the diagrams (and font for the text) are SMALL. A bit challenging to see with my slightly aging eyes... Read carefully. Look at the micro diagrams carefully. It's all there. Did I mention TAKE YOUR TIME? Yes, I mean it. It will help. Even doing it slowly, I had it all together in under an hour.

Bed frame: Most or many of you will likely be wishing to attach this to a regular metal bed frame. Depending on your bed frame brackets, I'm guessing that 90% of you will need to drill holes in the headboard for this, like I did. Line up frame to headboard, mark the holes, drill. Supereasy, as it's particleboard.... I used a 5/16" drill bit, and then attached the frame with 1/4-20 x 1.5" hex bolts which you'll need to buy from your local hardware store. Don't forget to use washers. Did I mention it's only particleboard? :-)

Overall: If you have the proper expectations, you'll be pleased with this product. I am. The tiny little shelf is just what I wanted-- I didn't want a super deep shelf (takes up too much space). The tiny shelf is great for my rings, my watch, the remote control for my ceiling light, etc. I wanted something that looks fairly decent, and I didn't want to spend a fortune. I have a daughter in college, so my bank account is almost always empty :-) This is NOT an heirloom piece of furniture that your children will inherit. Maybe some day when I have more money I'll buy something that's a little bigger, deeper, more sturdy, solid oak, etc. But for now, what I got really looks great, it's functional, and it was less than 80 bucks. It's exactly what I expected for the price. Lastly, while you don't need to be a home-improvement expert to assemble this, it does help immensely if you've ever assembled something like this before and/or are a bit handy.. If you're nervous about this, or you're not handy or you have no experience drilling a hole or two- just go grab your boyfriend or your sister's husband or... .... and buy that person a 6-pack of beer for their help :-)

product_title: Multiple Colors - Heavy Duty - Light Weight - Metal and Plastic Folding Stool - 400lb Capacity - Exclusively by Blowout Bedding RN# 142035
review_headline: Lightweight and really DOES hold a lot of weight!
review_body:
This stool is just what I needed! It surprisingly takes quite a lot of searching to find a sturdy, well-made stool that won't break easily, or that isn't a complete rip off to buy. Luckily, that wasn't the case with this stool! It's seriously the best stool - I bought it on a whim, since we were in need of one and figured it wouldn't hurt. I could always return it, right? Well, I'm so glad I picked this stool!

PROS
• Lightweight!! I could easily carry it around and downstairs (keep in mind, I'm quite a small/short person)
• Arrives fully assembled! (I'm not that handy, If I'm honest, as far as using tools go..) So you do not have to worry about putting anything together and risking damaging the product out of your own stupidity.. It's happened to me plenty of times and I feel so awful explaining that I broke it.
• Durable!
• Wasn't damaged at all - comes very well packaged!! Very professional!
• Is a great seat for everyone, even heavier set people. It really does hold the weight!! (I had my friend sit on my lap and together we weigh out to be around 300-ish pounds, if that says anything)
• My cat likes it as well. He's a creature of comfort and enjoys being higher up, and although it isn't "too" high.. it's higher than the floor and therefore he's interested in checking it out.

Overall, I highly recommend this product. It's truly durable and definitely well made to hold a good amount of weight. Definitely five stars and worth the price! Love it!

I received this product at a discount for my honest and unbiased feedback.

product_title: Zinus 14 Inch Elite SmartBase Mattress Foundation / for Big & Tall / Extra Strong Support / Platform Bed Frame / Box Spring Replacement / Sturdy / Quiet Noise Free / Non-Slip, Twin
review_body: Initial thoughts are very positive on this queen size frame after using it for one month. As expected, it is lightweight steel rectangular tube. Don't expect a heavy angle iron bed frame, it is not. Although the tubes are lightweight, the construction seems solid. I had a great delivery experience. The box looked like new, no dents and frame was very clean. Setup took seconds. Simply unfold, position braces and tighten. Everything fit. The bed feels very solid with a combined weight of people and mattress approaching 500lbs. We are using this with a 12" memory foam mattress. No issues with the slats being at slightly different height. Also no detectable sagging of the mattress through the frame openings. We do have a few squeaks upon entering or exiting the bed. Not a big deal really. I'm not sure if it is an actual squeak in the frame or if the feet are moving slightly on the laminate floor as weight is applied. It is most noticeable when the first person enters the bed.  As a side note, we used this frame for one week with our old conventional spring mattress while waiting for the memory foam to arrive. It provided better support to the mattress than the box spring we threw out. It made the old mattress more comfortable for its final week.

My home is very natural with earth tones, granites and wood and this went great with everything. Had a couple issues with the hall table and had to replace 2. First one split right away (I think due to moisture from shipping?) and second one had a very odd knot that created a unpleasing look to me. Even with these issues, they expedited and handled the returns in an extremely fast manner. I got 1 replacement like the next day! They handled it fabulously! The designs themselves...beautiful. Great craftsmanship, solid and very well built. I sanded mine down and did a shiny clear coat. In fact, I have several other pieces in my wishlist that I plan on getting soon to complete my look. I would highly recommend these unfinished pieces at a fraction of the cost. Since then have had many compliments on them. review_headline: Beware of back pain and limb numbness!
review_body: We have officially owned this mattress for one year.  It is hard and does not do well for lower back issues or side sleepers.  Side sleepers are likely to experience limb numbness and joint pain in the shoulders and hips.  I am all about knock offs and saving money when I can but this mattress has resulted in so much loss of sleep.  I literally have to get out of bed to get out of pain.  All this being said if you are a young college kid looking for their first mattress its a cheap deal as long as you have no problems with back pain and are not much of a side sleeper.  I really had hoped that this mattress was going to workout but it was a very sad disappointment.

product_title: Harbor View Computer Desk With Hutch
review_headline: I recommend everyone should do this otherwise you will lose track ...
review_body:
Self-assembly: Prepare yourself, this is a project. I'm a 29 y/o female and I was able to put this together myself in about 6 six hours total. I did need help when it came time to turn the unit over and lift it in place. Other than that, it can be done alone. They provide you with everything you need to assemble it and the instructions are clear. There are a ton of pieces and lots of wood so try not to be overwhelmed when you open everything up. It served me well to sort all of the pieces and label what part they were at the beginning so that I knew what to reach for in each step. I recommend everyone should do this otherwise you will lose track of which piece is what as you use them. There are 31 steps and some steps have 5 steps within them. It's not fun to put this desk together so if you can get someone else to do it for you, do it.

The delivery on this item is a great feature too because you can select when you want the desk delivered down to the three hour window. The delivery service may not bring it in the house for you though. The desk comes in two heavy boxes so you will need two people to move this around.

Once it's assembled, you will love the desk. Looks great against a colored wall. The makers were very smart about the construction of this. Has cutouts in back of where the monitor goes and cutouts for your cords to feed through the desk to the wall. Lots of built-in storage. I love the shelf under the keyboard tray. If you can get past the assembly stage, it's worth the money.

There is a bit of a quicksand feeling since there is no springy/bouncy action when initially sitting or laying on it. I find this more relaxing and comfortable compared to a bouncy spring mattress. review_headline: but the instructions were very clear and the bubble-packed hardware was clearly labeled and easy to ensure the right connector w

I bought the stainless steel top and the island is BEAUTIFUL, sturdy, and just exactly the size as advertised. I did have to glue connection pieces back onto back of drawers as they had come unnailed in shipping, but that was an easy fix with glue and an overnight rest with a clamp. Also, the wheels that came with the island will not lock as advertised -- I will likely replace them as it is important to me that the island stay stationary 98% of the time.
Despite the minor problems, this was a great buy.

review_body: The mobile cutting board is very well made of all solid wood without any particle board.  My wife loves using it as a supplemental work surface. product_title: WinkBeds - Mattress For Sale - Best Rated Mattress - Mattress Warehouse - Foam Mattress + AirSprings + Gel Hybrid, 100% CertiPure, Medium/Firm Mattress Like Hotel Mattress
review_body: 8-27-2015:  New queen-size Wink Bed to be delivered tomorrow.  We ordered it on 8-16-2015 direct from the winkbeds site, a cleverly designed and playful web site.  Excited to finally get rid of "old lumpy."  Will post updates here in the coming days and weeks.  Starting off with 5 stars -- we'll see if that holds.  :-/ 9-26-2015:   (Repeating the comment I made today, before I found out how to edit a review!) I appreciate the commenter of my review posted last month, the day before we received the mattress. I too would be skeptical. Here now is my 28-day review, after having slept on our queen Wink for most of a month. While I am impressed with the high quality of the mattress, I must regretfully report that I will be returning the mattress -- it is too firm for me. It should be noted I am a tall, lanky, middle-aged side sleeper. One of the bed's features is a reinforced border around the edges. That feature made the feel too firm when lying within a foot of the edge. The result was a 'give' that was not uniform across the mattress, making it seem like I was falling toward the softer center when lying on my side. The thought occurred to me that this was a fault of our foundation (non-Wink), but that turned out to be untrue; the foundation is sound. We are grateful for Wink's return policy, and hope this review does not unduly influence others who favor a firmer and therefore healthier mattress. How does one decide how many stars to give in this case? I will end this update with 4 stars, which reflects both how impressed I am with the product and also my regret that it did not suit me.

product_title: Leesa Mattress
review_headline: ... one month in and this mattress has been the best I've tried so far
review_body:
UPDATE: I found an even better mattress for low back pain: Liberty mattress by Amerisleep. Although the Leesa was still one of the better mattresses I've treid
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Original review: Ok it's been one month in and this mattress has been the best I've tried so far. I'm 5"8 145lbs and have been having low/mid back pain for the last 10 years or so. I realized that a lot of my pain was happening by the time I'd wake up in the morning so the mattress was clearly the culprit. The other bed in a box mattresses I tried were tuft and needle and YogaBed. The T&N ended up being too firm for my back (feel free to look my T&N review as well), although my guests that slept on it with me liked it. Also I tried Yogabed which was good but I was sinking more into it than when lying on the Leesa.
This may sound cliche but the Leesa offers the perfect firmness without being too firm. Honestly, I'd give it 4.5 stars because it's much pricier than other brands and it didn't make my morning back pain fully go away, but as of now it's been the best mattress I've tried. Oh and I recommend buying it directly from the manufacturer and looking for coupon codes online. P. S. My Yoga instructor recommended placing a big pillow under my shins when back sleeping. product_title: Safco Products 5245BL Boltless Steel Shelving 36"W x 18"D x 72"H
review_body: I love these shelving units -- they are clean looking & support a fair amount of weight.  I have 2 of them in my spare room for storage.  But, there are several major problems with the units:  (1) Getting one that is not damaged is difficult.  The steel is not very strong and the box it comes in has no padding -- so the units typically arrive bent, scraped and the last one came with open ends and parts missing.  The company does not sell replacement parts.  (2) They are tricky to put together, but secure once assembled.  However,  if you bang too hard with a hammer or rubber mallet they will bend.  (3) There are no "feet" available to set the angle iron on so that it does not cut into your floor.  Since it is a different size than most angle iron, none of the angle iron feet available on line can be used.  Sounds terrible -- but the units really are wonderful if you can get around these problems.  I wish Amazon would double box the units before shipping -- that might help protect them better.  I did contact Safco,  but they do not seem to be interested in fixing these problems themselves.

product_title: Volair Sim Universal Flight or Racing Simulation Cockpit Chassis with Triple Monitor Mounts
review_headline: It's good, but wish the wheel mount was better
review_body:
Let me start by saying that the product is good and I would buy another one. Also Volair's customer support is top notch and very responsive. With regard to the product, I think there are some things that are worth reemphasizing that I think are fair criticisms of this type of enthusiast product. I will also caveat that I haven't tried any other competitors, so maybe this is just state of the art and so be it... but I would like to see these things addressed if there's ever a "Volair Sim 2"

My chief complaint is that I think this sim rig was designed for flight first, and the fact that it happens to work for racing is just a happy accident. The reason I say this is because the mounting point for the wheel is not terribly well reinforced, it has quite a bit of flex in it. I think it will probably never break, but the constant flexing with force feedback is not what I was hoping for. Other bolt on doodads are better but do have a tiny wiggle unless very heavily tightened, so something like a Fantatec Shifter you'll get a little bit of play in it. I think this would be completely fine on a flight sim where for the most part you are being gentle, but competition sim racing can be a violent exercise and I can tell I'm going to be rattling this thing all the time.

Additionally, the adjustment options for the placement of the wheel are somewhat limited. "Closer and Higher" or "Lower and Farther away" are your options. I know a lot of drivers like a close and low wheel, right on the chest, and frankly that's just not possible with this thing unless you are a very specific body dimension (I'm 5'11" and slim). Or possibly just different pedals that sit higher up so you can scoot in closer. With G27 I have to make the choice between perfect wheel and perfect pedal placement. I've tried to split the difference.

Finally, the assembly for this thing is a task. All the other reviews are accurate. You can expect to spend 5-8 hours on this thing, and learn a lot of lessons along the way. The instructions are a little hard to follow and some steps like attaching the seat to the chassis are a downright menace. My most important tool in this assembly was a rubber mallet, because some stuff you just have to beat into place.

Other notes (not all negative, I promise!)

- UPDATE: this comes pre-drilled for the X52 Pro. Very nice to have. I think it even bolts to the center-stick, which means you can have the HOTAS on center and left side, with the racing shifter on the right. Perfect!

- The website claims you need M6 x 10 machine screws to mount the G27 pedals, but those are far too short. Get longer ones and thank me later. I used M6x16 and those seemed to do well.

- The triple monitor mounting is very good. Sturdy, quality, easy.

- The seat on this thing is really nice. Frankly it's worth an entire star on its own. It feels very high quality and once you get all your positions worked out it can be very comfortable5-8 hours on this thing, and learn a lot of lessons along the way. The instructions are a little hard to follow and some steps like attaching the seat to the chassis are a downright menace. My most important tool in this assembly was a rubber mallet, because some stuff you just have to beat into place.

Other notes (not all negative, I promise!)

- UPDATE: this comes pre-drilled for the X52 Pro. Very nice to have. I think it even bolts to the center-stick, which means you can have the HOTAS on center and left side, with the racing shifter on the right. Perfect!

- The website claims you need M6 x 10 machine screws to mount the G27 pedals, but those are far too short. Get longer ones and thank me later. I used M6x16 and those seemed to do well.

- The triple monitor mounting is very good. Sturdy, quality, easy.

- The seat on this thing is really nice. Frankly it's worth an entire star on its own. It feels very high quality and once you get all your positions worked out it can be very comfortable

review_body: Don’t mind the walls, my special needs son likes to color on our walls; luckily it’s just washable. But the room needed to be painted anyways so I thought I might as well let the boys have fun coloring. This bed is awesome; my neighbor and it put this together and only took about half an hour to do. Its like 5 pieces all together. The footboard and headboard have slots on them, and then you just hook on the two white side rails, and you’re set, thats it. Roll-out slats come with some screws, to screw that allow you to tighten, and thats all you do. The mattress you need to buy separate, which we bought these nice foam kids mattresses on Amazon for $90 bucks, and they’re very comfortable. The bed is very sturdy, it can hold my 122 pound weight and both my kids weight combined of almost 100 pounds. The bed has been static tested up to 300 lbs. We got the pirate theme for the headboard, and the remote is so easy to use, but be sure to be standing right next to the bed. Makes a wonderful nightlight. This is a great bed for your little ones to grow into. The rails are adjustable which allow you to add under the bed trundle or open storage. As of now, until we build the other bed, it will remain on hold. But it slides nicely under the bed, and slides out, making sleep overs fun, or if you have a kiddo thats a worm at night, and falls off beds you can use the bottom bed as a catcher. Kids love this bed, we often lay on it, and stare out the window and watch the storms and the neighbors, since we live in a not such a safe area..

product_title: Osaki OS4000 Executive Zero Gravity Massage Chair Recliner Deluxe
review_body: This chair offers plenty of options, two levels of zero gravity, seat vibration, and much more. It comes in four pieces--the main unit, the back, and the two sides. Assembly was easier than I thought it would be, at least after I got the sides on. That was the hardest and most time consuming because a bar seems to be blocking the back screws, You really have to manuever to get those in. The secret is to get the bolt started, then slide the thick portion of the tool that is provided onto the bolt and over the bar. Getting the tool back off after you tighten the bolt is a bit difficult, but once the sides are on, the rest is relatively easy. This is a very heavy chair, though, so you will need someone to help you move it (the base portion at least--that's where most of the weight is located), The remote is a bit complicated--check out YouTube for a tutorial on how to use it. The detachable remote is handy so that you don't have to remove your arm from the arm rest to make adjustments to speed or intensity. This chair is great for people with back problems, or for someone who just likes a good massage.

product_title: Zinus Upholstered Square Stitched Platform Bed
review_body:
Like most of you, I had reservations about ordering a bed online. But like most of the other owners of this bed, I'm so happy that I did. I ordered the button tufted queen size bed frame just in time before they sold out and Lord am I glad I nabbed it in time! I live in a tiny apartment off of my university campus and was worried about how I was going to lug a giant box up 6 floors with no male help (I mean, I'm a strong, independent, Asian woman who don't need no man, but I ain't THAT strong)! Well no worries there because a day before the estimated delivery date, FedEx plopped it right outside my door (bravo FedEx guy). I was also worried that since I was getting one of the last batches of this product, parts of it would be missing or possibly defective. Again, this bed proved me wrong. Everything came tightly packed inside the headboard and nothing seemed missing or out of place. The headboard is beautiful. I love the color and how it's fabric instead of nasty faux leather (ew).

Assembly was relatively easy, but like others have mentioned, the pictures are a mess. I could have put together the bed by myself but, luckily, my roommate came home and decided to help after she saw me struggling with dragging a giant @$$ box across our living room. Unfortunately for her, I ended up letting her do all the work (whoops, sorry Shannon ;p), which again, really wasn't that much work at all. It only took us 30-45 min to put it together.

I have a 10" tuft and needle mattress on it now and there's still a lot of headboard left to see after adding the comforter and pillows. Bed doesn't budge, looks so beautiful, and is 100000000% worth every penny. Even my MOTHER agrees I've made a good decision on this bed (and trust me that lady is VERY hard the please #dragonladiesunite). This is the bed that if I were Oprah Winfrey I would buy everyone one!!

Hopefully it comes back in stock for all of you sorry suckers who missed out on the queen size button tufted bed frame. I'm sure the other colors are just as nice though ;)tton tufted bed frame. I'm sure the other colors are just as nice though ;)

product_title: DHP Emily Chrome Legs
review_body:
All in all with tax, I paid about $180. The sofa looks really nice and yes it is firm to sit and sleep on. I placed 4 18x18 inch decorative pillows on it and it looks fantastic. The futon will be used by an occasional sleepover guest. UPS delivered my box and though heavy can be slowly moved into the house.
Assembly consisted on attaching 2 front slanted legs with 3 bolts each, and 3 additional cylindrical legs (2 for the sides and one for the center) with 4 bolts each. Two different allen wrenches were included for this task. There was nothing else to be done and putting the legs on was a breeze.
I purchased a regular twin bed sheet set and a cheap twin sized foam topper. I think I'm going to buy a second cheap foam topper to make the bed comfortable for an adult. A child would also sleep comfortably. The fitted sheet was taut on the open futon but it was very acceptable. The open futon ('bed mode') is several inches wider than a twin bed.
I had tested other types of futons that were in the $450 price range and the open/close mechanism was very cumbersome (and noisy). By contrast, this bed is really easy to open and close (and no loud noises) !
One final thing. I am 5'6" (66 inches) tall and I fit perfectly on the bed lengthwise with a couple of inches to spare. The futon's length is about 70" but once you put a pillow on one end and put your head on it, you realize that you don't actually take advantage of the full length . So keep that in mind. I love it and am very pleased with the look, the funcion, and the price.

review_headline: Solid bookshelf, great height for a telephone table
review_body:
This is a nicely made shelf. I purchases the "2 narrow" version, because we needed a smallish table to hold our cordless phone base/answering machine. This was the height I wanted, so I decided to give it a try, as the price was right and I've purchased a few other Winsome pieces.

It assembles very easily. I generally use a impact driver with a hex bit, which in this case made the assembly take less than 10 minutes. The shelf looks nice, there was a small ding on the back side of the right leg, but it goes against the wall, so it didn't bother me. I did have to shim one leg very slightly.. I was putting felt on the bottom of the legs anyway, so I just added a thicker piece on the one leg to keep it from wobbling. I did think that was worth docking one star.

All in all, it's a nice shelf and solid for the price, and I'll continue to buy and recommend Winsome products.

product_title: COMPUTER DESK - LEFT OR RIGHT FACING CORNER
review_headline: Very nice desk easy to put together.
review_body:
Very simple to put together and you can swap the sides, there are 4 bolts holding the top downs (2 on file cabinet side and 2 on shelf side). I have put together my fair share of desks and wall unites and I have to say this was easy and well thought out. My only issue is that I wish the parts were labeled better and a better indication of which screws to use. It not impossible to figure out but I did have to take a moment to make sure I was using the correct screw.

When put together it feels solid and looks very nice, I wish it was a little bigger. I have learned from the past that when you put unites like this together be gentle, you don't want to over tighten parts and if you make a mistake gentle un-screw your part. The MDF will hold but if you over tighten you could strip the MDF and your screw will not work.

All-in-all, very nice desk and not problems. We have 2, 24" monitors with a desk phone on the upper part and seem to fit nicely (like I said I wish it was just a bit larger).

product_title: High Back Executive Leather Ergonomic Office Desk Computer Chair O10
review_body: The chair arrived in 2 days instead of the quoted 7 to 10 days.  The shipping box was flimsy and was open when it arrived.  Luckily, the chair was undamaged and there were no missing parts.  Assembly was easy-as-pie using an included picture diagram.  I love this chair.  It's nice to look at.  The faux leather has a nice feel.  It's comfortable, and it tilts back nicely if you want to rock back.  I'm 6 foot tall and it's easy for me to recline; but the shorter you are, the more difficult it will be to make it recline.  A five foot tall female, I know, can not generate enough upper body force to make it recline.  Her 5'8" husband also has trouble making it recline; but both of them are quite thin, which may add to the problem.  For $89 and free shipping, this is a wonderful swivel office chair.  As for longevity, the foam may not maintain support, and the faux leather may wear away, and lord knows what other problems may be expected to develop, but out-of-the-box it's a nice chair.

review_body: Sleep Innovations 10" Gel-Infused Memory Foam mattress is a great trade off from a regular spring mattress.  I had to take some time to get use to the difference, but hubby loves it.  I still get somewhat warm while sleeping, however he reports this isn't a problem for him.  The mattress conforms to your body and returns to its regular form quite nicely.  It took awhile for the mattress to expand once taken out of the box, however I was pleased that it wasn't a pain to get in the house and up the stairs--though it's quite heavy.  There is a slight smell that isn't overbearing, but I have a sensitive nose and still smell traces of it.  I'm sure its from the materials it's made with, but this is my first foam mattress so I'm not quite sure.  It seems to be well made so I'm expecting this to last for a while.

product_title: Lifetime Contemporary Residential Folding Chair
review_headline: Kind of awesome, as folding chairs go
review_body:
These are kind of awesome folding chairs! Lifetime is the manufacturer of the ubiquitous white plastic folding tables you see everywhere - lightweight and sturdy. These folding chairs are equally lightweight and sturdy, and reasonably comfortable for a folding chair. I mean, you're still going to pick a standard chair over a folding chair, given the choice, but if you end up with this folding chair, you shouldn't be miserable.

What makes these particular chairs great is that they fold super flat, to take up the least amount of space imaginable for folding chairs. You can tuck a set of four chairs in the side or back of your closet and still have plenty of closet space left. I'm really impressed.

product_title: Epic Furnishings Stockholm Solid Wood Bookcase Headboard
review_body: Well.  There is much to say about this headboard.  The style is just what I wanted.  Color (walnut) is good but veneer was peeling off the edges before we got the pieces out of the box, which was flimsy, at best.  Priced right for a tight budget.  Assembly, on the other hand, was more than challenging.  Directions clearly state that it takes two people to assemble.  SHOULD state that at least ONE of the two needs to be able to figure out how the piece goes together because the instructions are ridiculous.  Parts list shows screws that are not included and NOT referenced in the instructions as well as parts that ARE included and NOT referenced in the instructions.  Pieces ARE marked but nowhere in the instructions, which consist mostly of photos that are too dark to see clearly and VERY wordy descriptions that are less than helpful, does it say which side should be facing.  Connecting pieces don't lock in place, holes weren't drilled in the right places.  NOTHING on how to attach the finished piece to the bed frame (mine ended up fitting on top of the frame, inside the rails).  Not sure how this less than perfect construction will hold up over time but NEXT time, I'll go to IKEA!

product_title: Modern Office Chair
review_headline: Product Change ... and NOT for the better!
review_body:
I liked this chair so much that after the first time I bought it, I bought a 2nd one. The 2nd chair was a disappointment. My first purchase consisted of a single seat with the backrest and seat already combined. For reasons unknown, the 2nd seat came with a backrest that was separate from the seat. You have to connect it by sliding a metal bracket connected to the backrest under the seat. You then have to screw it into place.

Here's the problem.

The metal bracket is slightly curved and it's configured for four holes. There is NO WAY to connect this bracket to the bottom of the seat because the bracket is curved. The four holes in the bottom of the seat are also not aligned with the holes in the bracket ... so the only way to connect it is to use two holes ... which then means that the backrest will not be flush with the bottom of the seat making it difficult to lean back against when sitting. The fact that I could only use two screws instead of four will most likely also degrade the life of this chair.

I have no idea why the manufacturer went from a seamless one seat with backrest and seat to a two part system that was so badly designed. Did the manufacturer NOT test the new product?

I bought my new chair for work and really hate it. The vertical height (after adjustment) is fine. The seat itself is fine ... but being unable to lean back against the backrest is a royal pain. Rather than go to the trouble of returning it, I will buy a seat pad with a strap but instead of using it as a seat cushion, I'll place it in front of the backrest for added support.

product_title: LUCID 14 Inch Plush Memory Foam Mattress - Ventilated Gel Memory Foam + Bamboo Charcoal Infused Memory Foam - CertiPUR-US Certified - 25-Year Warranty
review_body:
I wanted to love this mattress, however this is what happened. As with everyone, I went to my local mattress store, I wanted a Temper Pedic then realized the prices are $5,000 for kings AND UP ! So as any good bargain hunter will do I came on Amazon and found this mattress. Well reviewed, 20 year warranty, everything I wanted for $800..... I received the mattress and automatically loved it. It does sleep hot and I am in FL, however I put a set of $300 cariloha Resort Style bamboo bed sheets on it ( THEY ARE AMAZING ) and it slept just perfect keeping the house at 75 degrees. However, 20 days into it the matress started to sag in the spot I slept. I weigh 215 lbs and am 5'11. I couldnt believe that after only 20 days this thing was soft on the side I was sleeping. The matress pad on top is AMAZING and I want to get one for the Temper Pedic mattress I am getting. The reality is that this mattress is made with much cheaper foam than a Temper Pedic, thus, even with the warranty it will not last and is not the same quality. I really wanted to love this matress and during week 1 I did. But now after 20 days of sleeping on it I must say that I regretfully must return it and go spend a few grand on a Temper Pedic :(

Trust me when I say that I am saddened to return this mattress.

When you get it .... IT DOES STINK LIKE CHEMICALS. if anyone here says it doesnt, then they must work at Dupont Chemical factory because I had to air it out for 4 days before I slept on it in a room with all the windows open, 2 fans on, and the AC Vent closed. I highly suggest you do the same if you buy one of these.

product_title: High Back Executive Mesh Chair With Leather Inset Seat
review_body: I bought this chair to replace a chair I'd had for 15 years. (That chair's arms were finally cracking and starting to give me blisters.) I took a leap a faith and bought this chair without being able to sit in it or otherwise examine it. My previous chair was some no-name brand from Wal-Mart, and it withstood the test of time for about $39. This chair, on the other hand, was uncomfortable, caused burns on my arms from the unpadded vinyl, and stripped a screw that attaches the left arm to the seat. I bought extra elbow pads to combat the irritating arms. That made my arms rest too high, so I had to buy a seat cushion to raise me up entirely, which was needed anyway since the seat of the chair was so uncomfortable to begin with. 0 of 10, would not buy again.

review_headline: Good looks, but lack of substance givesnit a low score
review_body: Unit looks very nice. Problem being that the Ottoman is basically a frame surrounded by material.  No hard walls at all. Inside walls are a thin felt that backs right to the outer leather material. So if you need something with some wall integrity... this unit won't be what your looking for. The floor of the Ottoman is also a thicker version of the felt material. Which maybe OK to place items in that are light, other wise it would seem to me that there is a risk of the material ripping as the weight rests on the floor, not the frame of the ottoman. A nice looking unit but not solid in anyway. Regrettably mine came damaged with an inner beam broken in the frame and will need to return it. Probably won't reorder as it does not fit my intended use and I go for function over looks on any day.

product_title: AmazonBasics 5-Shelf Shelving Unit on Wheels - Chrome
review_headline: Perfect – I'll go so far as to say LIFE CHANGING!!!
review_body: I'm disabled and live in an apartment specifically built for the handicapped. I've been here for three years but have always found cooking a challenge: simply because my kitchen counter and storage space is so minimal. There's a small space, behind my front door and adjacent to my kitchen and, for the life of me!, I don't know why I never thought that it could be used for storage space... until earlier this week. I searched for "kitchen hutch shelves" and found everything from $150 particle board "shelves" (with a maximum total weight of forty pounds) to $3,000 solid wood shelf hutches. I do not know why I didn't take a look at Amazon first! I found one set of shelves but the were a bit too deep... and then I found this unit. The dimensions were perfect. Our maintenance man assembled the shelves with ease and my caregiver and I began to took the shelves. One shelf even accommodates my microwave oven! I have counter space! I no longer need use my stovetop for food storage!  I'm not, in any way, exaggerating when I say that these shelves have been life changing... last night I was actually able to use my small cutting board and chop vegetables with my chef's knife. I've not been able to do that for years. The shelves are extraordinarily sturdy and the assembly was simple and straightforward. We didn't put the casters on since the shelves will always be stationary. I have been so very pleased with every "AmazonBasics" product that I've purchased – they may be 'basic' but they are always of the very highest quality. I just can't sufficiently express how delighted I am with this shelving unit.

product_title: Bush Furniture Buena Vista Writing Desk
review_headline: Writing this review at this very writing desk
review_body: This item is definitely a good value (under $125 on Amazon). It isn't real wood, but rather veneered particle board. The assembled desk is sturdy and looks really good. It takes a little patience to put together by following the pictogram instructions, but it goes quickly once you get the hang of how the parts work. I had recently put together some "ready-to-assemble" cabinets and the techniques were similar. I used wood glue on the dowel joints and wherever unfinished sides came together, but it wasn't necessary and not recommended if you plan to ever disassemble it. I still think it was worth the price even with a few super tiny blemishes. There were a few light spots at various edges or corners that I touched up with a little dab from a dark furniture touch-up pen with great results. Even up close, the desk has the look and feel of a more expensive piece. Still happy about it.  The drawer design is not that bad other than they could have put another latch mechanism on the right side to satisfy symmetry. Otherwise, the existing latch is plenty strong and the drawer glides smoothly enough that everything works properly. I have no problem pulling the drawer out either by the decorative pull hardware (knobs) or with a hand from under the drawer. The purpose of the latch is so that the front panel can quickly fold down so the drawer can become a keyboard tray, which is how I use it. The drawer would also be perfect for storing a laptop of any size. The tray is sturdy and I do put a little weight on it when resting my hands on it in between typing. I really like that the drawer is deep enough to hold a power strip and a monitor power brick behind my keybord so that my desktop can stay clean. Wires and cables can pass easily from the rear of the drawer.  In my case, the shipping packaging was not great. I realize that this was shipped in the Bush factory packaging, but my desk arrived with the lower rear cross brace slightly damaged. Around 1" of the wood veneer was gouged and lifted on the edge of one panel. Because the damage would be facing a wall and would never be seen, I decided to keep the item rather than go through the hassle of returning it. I will repair it later as I have the ability to do it myself. The packaging would have been fine if it would have been taped tighter using more tape. The tape loosened or otherwise stretched during shipping allowing the contents to shift inside the box. The parts were jumbled up when I removed the styrofoam. I'm sure that this was the cause of the damage. No problem for me, but do thoroughly inspect all your panels before starting to put it together or getting the packing box and foam too out of sorts in case it needs to be packed back up.

product_title: Sleep Innovations Shiloh Memory Foam Mattress
review_body: Ok, so I bought this mattress a couple of weeks ago and some of you may think that it is a bit early to write a review for it, but I felt compelled to do so. I will update it in the future if any opinion I have changes as well. First of all I chose this mattress for several reasons: 1.) Its actually reviewed on www.sleeplikethedead.com with really high ratings that are all broken down into sub ratings. 2.) Reviews are Amazon are for the most part positive. The negative ones seem to be roughly all the same things like, its firm, it smells, it unfolded funny, ect. 3.) The price. It wasn't the cheapest on here and its not the most expensive. It is right in that middle range where quality meets price. And I felt confident that I was buying a well made product. Since having this mattress my girlfriend and I freaking love it. The size is one thing that we couldn't wait for, but we didn't know what to expect when buying offline compared to a mattress shop. Some of the negative reviews were right, it is a bit on the firm side. We decided in a couple months or so we will purchase a ultra plush topper for it. But our sleep is still great, we sleep the entire night through most nights. I wake up well rested and feeling great. I work out a lot and I believe this mattress helps my muscles recover better with the quality of sleep I get and relieved pressure off of pressure points. One negative thing that I kept reading about these memory foam mattresses is difficulties with love making. I can honestly say our passionate times have not been affected whatsoever by this mattress. Yes the bounce of the springs is gone but I guess as long as you are in somewhat healthy shape, you'll be totally fine. Shipping was awesome. I never imagined I'd get a mattress in a box the size of a mini fridge one day. It was pretty heavy, I am sure I looked ridiculous heaving it across my kitchen and tumbling it into the bedroom. Unpacking went smoothly. There was no odor and I slept on it 14 hours after I opened it. This mattress is built well in my opinion. I've walked on it, played with the dog on it and it seriously doesn't move. In my opinion, I see this thing easily lasting 20 years or more and I would not mind sleeping on it for that many years as well.

product_title: Herman Miller Sayl Task Chair: Tilt Limiter - Stationary Seat Depth - Stationary Arms - Standard Carpet Casters - Black Base & Frame
review_headline: Great comfortable chair, just not good for your pants buttons!
review_body:
Herman Miller is famous brand for office equipment. I first learned about the Herman Miller Sayl chair at the University of Florida Marston Science Library. They renovated the library and replace the chairs with these $400+ chair. I really liked the chair every time I studied at the library. I enjoyed the locking tilt. This chair really made me sit taller and straighter. I don't know how to describe it, but you should try it out yourself.

The biggest issue with this chair is that pant pocket buttons can easily get caught in the webbing and the button might get ripped off. The webbing can also make the chair difficult to clean.

The chair comes with a 12 year warranty direct from your reseller. I haven't used the warranty yet, but they might require you to send it in if you bought it online.

This is a great desk chair. Don't go cheap on an item you sit in for many hours on end!

My configuration (not purchased from Amazon):
Fog Base with Studio White Y-Tower
Red Back
Crepe Claret (red) Fabric Seat
Red Armpad
Tilt Limiter (91, 101 or 124 degrees)
Height Adjustable Arms (6.7" to 10.8" from the seat)
Stationary Seat Depth (set at 16")
Non-Adjustable Back Support
Carpet Casters (designed for low to medium-pile carpet)

product_title: Flash Furniture HERCULES Series Black Ladder Back Metal Restaurant Chair - Vinyl Seat
review_headline: Solid chair, good value for the price.
review_body:
I have only one question / complaint about this chair -- why does it ship with the seat not already screwed on to the frame??? I checked and the chair would fit perfectly in the shipping box with the seat installed -- why not install it at the factory? Who knows.......

Oh well, minor inconvenience, I screwed it on with a screwdriver in about 2 minutes, if I could have located my power drill it would have taken 20 seconds. The screws are the proper length so they don't pop out of the side you're going to sit on as someone complained about in an earlier review. As far as aligning the seat, it's not rocket science, just press it as far back as it will go and then eyeball the left and right side so they are about equal. I used a sharpie pen to mark the correct spot for each screw but honestly it's not that hard.

Chair is very sturdy which is what I wanted, my previous wood chairs all broke after a while. The back is comfortable, the wood seat is comfortable, and it's just wide enough for a big guy like me without being extra wide. I would definitely recommend this chair.

review_body: I love this cart.  It added much needed space and shelving to my little kitchen.  It wasn't incredibly difficult to assemble and so far it's proving sturdy. I've had it for over a year now, and it's been through a move.  The only thing is the little wooden nubs that go into the holes to hide screws have fallen out all over the place, but not like that's even a big deal.  It locks into place so it won't move out from under you.  It's a little wobbly so I don't suggest doing too much heavy duty cutting, but all of the features are great. product_title: Ergomotion 400 Series Adjustable Bed Base With Wireless Control and Massage - Twin XL
review_headline: Poor quality motors and poor warranty follow up.  Buyer beware-Avoid this manufacturer unless you can rebuild your own motors.
review_body:
Do not buy the split king-sized adjustable base from Ergomotion that includes Serta and other manufacturers unless they promise in writing to back their product, unless you have extra time and money for repairing or replacing motors. Motors are junk. Even if these motors are under warranty you pay shipping charges and unless you purchase extended warranty, you pay labor or do it yourself to replace them.

I bought my king sized adjustable bed from Bailey's Furniture Store in Alaska and two years after spending $5000.00 one of the motors went bad. They are under warranty, but Ergo-Motion wanted $70.00 to ship one to me via UPS. What could I do? Stuck, I had a replacement shipped.

I installed the replacement motor,(which is shorter than than the original factory motor) and it raises the foot of the bed slower on that side than the factory motor on the other side. It is level at the top or the bottom only.
I called and told both Bailey's Furniture and Ergo-Motion that they sent the wrong motor.
"No we didn't." was the reply. "This is the replacement of the discontinued motor." (That the representative said was replaced due to complaints)

So Bailey's Furniture and Ergo Motion say I need to pay another $70.00 for shipping another replacement so the foot of the bed will raise in tandem again. Why couldn't they have shipped the pair at the same time if they already know the lengths of these motors is different?

It will be cheaper to rebuild the original one...Frustrating- that companies do not want to warranty an expensive bed. Very frustrating

product_title: FURINNO 99940GYW/BK French Oak Basic Bookcase Storage with Bins, 3" x 2", Grey/Black
review_body:
So, I got this item today. Knowing that I had to put it together myself, I got together my trusty tools, grabbed a cup of coffee and sat down to read the instructions to start the assembly. Keep in mind, I have put together several pieces of furniture in my day, so I'm at the semi-pro level at furniture assembly.

I took out each piece and examined them for damage. Everything was great. I then took out the instructions and read on the cover that there are no tools required. This should be a snap. Easy peasey.

I then put the table together in about 5 minutes. All of the pre-drilled holes matched up, so I was pretty psyched. Then I got to the part where it said to screw the screws into the pre-drilled holes. Keep in mind that I was told I would need no tools. They must know what they are talking about.

The screws were nearly impossible to get in without tools, but I mustered through. It took 3 hours, 4 shots of whiskey and earplugs for my kids to block their ears from the language coming out of my mouth...but I did it. Then came the hard part. The dozens of nails to put the back on. That was really difficult without the use of tools...but again...I got through it. My feet have gaping holes from pushing those suckers in, but the table is assembled.

I highly suggest using tools for this project. I think it would be a lot easier than what I went through. All-in-all the table is sturdy, although a bit smaller than I had anticipated. Again, use the tools. So much easier, I'm sure.

product_title: Sleep Innovations 10" Gel-Infused Memory Foam Mattress
review_headline: An okay product. It didn't impress or disappoint me. My perspective is a little different than many customers, though.
review_body:
Three-stars is considered a "negative" review even though it technically means "ok." I have a few issues with this mattress, but it's also important to look at my whole experience.

First, I'm reviewing this not as a paying customer but as someone who got a "free" product to review. That's important because I knew going in that a mattress at this price is not a super-high-end product. If I was a paying customer I would probably have looked for something more expensive. Or if I was paying customer, I would know going in that I'm trying to save money and I'm not going to get a truly amazing product, so my expectations would have been at a reasonable level.

This would be a fine, four-star mattress for a spare bedroom or occasional use. Or if you're on a budget and this is what you can pay, then yes, I think it's a decent product.

I am reviewing it as an actual full-time mattress, as though I truly chose it as a deliberate purchase, and on that score it doesn't quite measure up...but it's not priced that way, either. There's a reason why top-line mattresses are over a thousand dollars and this one is not!

Plus - and even more importantly - mattresses are such a personal item with so many different variables that what I don't like about this one could actually be a benefit to someone else. So it really needs a lot of research and consideration from customers. It's a tough purchase, that's for sure.

The Good:

It unpacks and gains its shape quickly. I noticed no real odor - maybe I'm not that sensitive or just don't care.

It is not hot - and the gel, at least to me, keeps it cool while sleeping on hot nights. Overall, that seemed better without a mattress pad...but not using a pad means the mattress is only going to have a sheet as protection. So maybe I'd alternate using a pad in the winter, but not summer.

It is not uncomfortable. It is low weight and easy to manuever, and if you're used to a big spring mattress you'll be shocked by how much space this suddenly provides up top. It's so much thinner, and I like that.

The Not-So-Good:

It is VERY firm. Maybe too firm. I'm just not sure how well I'm sleeping, and I've given this a few weeks to really settle in. What I notice most is there is no "give" when I roll on my side, and I find myself sleeping on my back.

My girlfriend has been telling me I'm snoring - which I was NOT known for before using this mattress. I'm not sure if that means I'm not getting the support I need, or if I'm actually in a deep sleep. I can't say I feel that refreshed in the morning.

But - it is hard to blame the mattress. I don't feel like it's priced with the expectation of full-time, high-end use. So if I was sleeping in this at a friend's house as their spare bedroom, I wouldn't care at all - in fact, the firmness in that case is better than sleeping in a beat up mattress where everything sinks and shifts. So if you prefer a very firm mattress, I think you'd like this a lot more than me.

I wake up sore in the lower back, and overall creaky. But, in the spring mattress this replaced I felt the same way (that was an old mattress, which is why we tried this one)...but I don't remember the back pain. Granted that might ease up over time as the mattress settles in, etc., but how long? Two months? Six months?

And the snoring, like I said, is new. I didn't snore before - and now it's every night. It's not constant and usually a kick gets me to reset. But still...maybe I'm just getting used to the new shape (update: the snoring disappeared a couple weeks later - or at least my g/f isn't noticing it anymore...but maybe she's sleeping through it? Don't know...).

I wish I could be unequivocal about my feelings, instead of this tepid lean toward a negative feeling. When we got it, I was hoping I would either love or hate it -that would be amazing or unusable. And it's neither. We intend to keep using it (I think she likes it overall a little more than me, but we're on the same page) for at least awhile, but it's not something I'm emotionally committed too. On the other hand, I'm not like "let's put the old one back" either. I can live with it and give it an honest effort for several months more - and I'll update this review if my opinion changes over time.

But I don't feel like it's a long-term solution...I feel like in the spring I'll probably start pricing out "real" mattresses.

Again - this was not a mattress I ever would have purchased. The price is much too low to expect an amazing experience. So I'm reviewing from a different perspective than a true customer. If all I could afford was the price then I'd probably be happier - because I'd be like "hey, this is decent enough for the money." Because it is! And I don't want to sound like I'm spoiled - but the reality is I expect to pay four-figures for a true, long-term mattress...not that I like it, I just expect it.

So it didn't amaze me. It's not bad. It's okay!same page) for at least awhile, but it's not something I'm emotionally committed too. On the other hand, I'm not like "let's put the old one back" either. I can live with it and give it an honest effort for several months more - and I'll update this review if my opinion changes over time. But I don't feel like it's a long-term solution...I feel like in the spring I'll probably start pricing out "real" mattresses. Again - this was not a mattress I ever would have purchased. The price is much too low to expect an amazing experience. So I'm reviewing from a different perspective than a true customer. If all I could afford was the price then I'd probably be happier - because I'd be like "hey, this is decent enough for the money." Because it is! And I don't want to sound like I'm spoiled - but the reality is I expect to pay four-figures for a true, long-term mattress...not that I like it, I just expect it. So it didn't amaze me. It's not bad. It's okay!

product_title: Leesa Mattress
review_headline: We both hate the shopping experience of haggling for a mattress and ...
review_body:
I bought this mattress through the manufacture's website. It came in about a week after being made to order. So far my husband and I are both impressed with the comfort and quality of the mattress.

We replaced a 5 year old Simmons BeautyRest with motion reduction that had two trenches on both sides with a hump in the middle. My husband experienced significant back pain as a result of this mattress. So we had added a 4 inch memory foam topper to the top. That helped somewhat but never truly fixed the problem (but made my sore hips feel marvelous). We both hate the shopping experience of haggling for a mattress and were aware of this new model of purchasing. We were skeptical to say the least but were encouraged by the 100 night trial.

The mattress came in a relatively small box for a King mattress and open to it's full size within half an hour (90% within 5 minutes I'd say). There was very minimal odor (much less than the memory foam topper we had before)My husband really loves the way he sinks in. I would have preferred a little bit more hug but am somewhat light at 5'6 and 125 lbs. Many of the online reviews reveal that lighter people sometimes prefer the Casper while heavier people like my husband 5'10 and 200lbs like the Leesa. Either way it's very supportive. I may still decide to add another couple of inches of memory foam to make me sink in a little more but am waiting to see how age affects the feel since many report it takes a month or two to fully break in.

I actually track my sleep via the Sleep Cycle app and I've seen that I'm staying in a deep sleep longer and I don't wake up feeling sore and unrested.  It isn't too firm and it isn't too soft. review_headline: avoid like the plague if you actually intend to sit
review_body: I've been through four, count 'em, four of these, and on the first three, the height adjust lever didn't work, and on all four the back tilt lever doesn't work. Also, of the first three, on two the seat was tilted forward enough that I was practically falling out of the chair, and one the other one the seat was tilted back so that the front was pushing uncomfortably into my legs. I'm amazed that it seems I'm the only person to have this problem. I got the first two from Amazon directly, the third from United Stationers, and the last from the manufacturer themselves. The first three were returned, and the manufacturer just sent me the fourth for free, so I have no incentive to return it, but even with the back tension loosened all the way, sitting in it for any length of time and using my back to push the back of the chair so it tilts back enough to not shove me off causes me significant back pain. Can use maybe 10 mins at a time. I got a free chair, sure, but I wasted four weeks and still can't use it. Well, on to try to find a better chair with a mesh back and seat, or maybe buy a used Aeron on eBay. I can only imagine that there's a significant manufacturing problem, because it's clear many other people have working chairs. In case you think "hey, everyone else's worked, this guy must be crazy", I basically suggested as much to the manufacturer, and THEY insisted that the chair must be broken.

product_title: Home Styles 5010-94 Woodbridge 2-Tier Kitchen Island, White Finish
review_body:
If I were simply reviewing on functionality and design, this would be 5 stars, easy. It's a lovely piece and will serve us well, and frankly, I love it...but...it's tricky to put together and put power drill into the tools needed. If you've never put together a piece of furniture, beware.

Let me preface, I'm 62 and have put built a LOT of furniture, (love it and am go to for many people I know) both kit and from scratch. Never had probs like this.

Engineering: Clever design, not so good execution. Predrilled holes for cams...mostly fine, but sometimes look like they needed a new drill bit. In two instances on my piece, this compromised the wood. I'll be contacting them for new pieces. The camlock screw holes have some kind of threaded insert that sometimes got painted making them difficult to get in aligned, and this is crucial to proper alignment of this lovely little puzzle. Pilot holes for actual screws are a nightmare. Don't trust them and be ready to put in new ones. They're too shallow, this is hardwood, and you can easily strip the screws trying to get them in, only to discover the alignment is off. The pic is of the drawer. The bottom is supposed to go into that routed groove and as you can see, with the screws going into the pilots, it wasn't going to happen. Fortunately, new pilot holes are easy. The decorative trim between the two units was dreadfully off leaving a big gap (see pic). I'll fix that when I take it apart to paint. The front, drawered unit is tricky to assemble. I'd advise not even beginning to tighten cams until all pieces are in place. An extra set of hands would be useful.

The finish...isn't remotely acceptable to me. Since I always planned to paint it, it's not a prob for me, but if you're planning to put it right into operation... Not only are there some unavoidable gaps that I will want to fill, the finish itself feels and acts more like a thin spray coat of primer. Since my furniture needs to work for a living, I'll be putting a good enamel finish on it. The drawer bottom accepted a spray of red Rustoleum just as is and it dried tight and hard. A good finish...wouldn't let me do that.

On the plus side, it's pretty, very solid, handles some of the awkward to get out of regular cupboards bits like mixers and waffle-irons, and once I get it painted and the casters on, it'll be practically perfect in every way. Oh...and the packaging was amazing....

I'll be contacting them about the replacement parts and will amend this review if I run into any problems. I'm assuming they'll simply replace them and all will be well.living, I'll be putting a good enamel finish on it. The drawer bottom accepted a spray of red Rustoleum just as is and it dried tight and hard. A good finish...wouldn't let me do that.

On the plus side, it's pretty, very solid, handles some of the awkward to get out of regular cupboards bits like mixers and waffle-irons, and once I get it painted and the casters on, it'll be practically perfect in every way. Oh...and the packaging was amazing....

I'll be contacting them about the replacement parts and will amend this review if I run into any problems. I'm assuming they'll simply replace them and all will be well.

product_title: DHP Silver Screen Loft Bed
review_headline: A  good purchase.  Like both bed and desk.
review_body:
Got this and assembled in a couple hours. It is very solid. Most beds have a little jiggle/sway. Those small motions get magnified in a taller structure but it's still no big deal. By comparison, this is much more solid and less squeaky than the ubiquitous stacking wooden beds that many of us had in the 70s.

As with many such projects, it's great to have a cordless drill/screw driver when you are making this. The small shelf in the picture is not there, but the desk is large and really useful (great as a desk and strengthens the structure). As others have indicated, the ladder is a bit uncomfortable. We used foam pipe insulation around it and my daughter thinks it's great. The bed is in a corner, and we also used some of the same kind of foam padding to pad the top corner of the bunk (wrapped around the back corner of the top of one leg). This is because the baseboards keep the corner leg about 3/8 inches away from the corner of the walls. A little padding up top closes that gap and helps stabilize the bed.

*The support bars for the mattress come with clever, strong plastic clips that help minimize noise, vibrations, and movement.
*We painted the black squares on the top rails the same lavender color as my daughter's room. It rally softened the bed's appearance and tied it into the room.
*We used a 5" thick mattress, but after seeing it in place, we would have had no worries with a 6" mattress.

product_title: Zinus Deluxe Faux Leather Upholstered Platform Bed
review_body:
I was really excited about this product when I ordered it. It arrived in a good time frame.

The first thing I noticed was the box was pretty beat up when I got it. As I opened the box and contents of the head baord I noticed one of the wooden peices from the side boards had broken off in transit. The screws used were entirely too short. I replaced all 12 screws with slightly longer ones. That was frustrating and added 30 minutes to the build time because I had to run to the hardware store. Then when I went to screw in the legs to start putting together the bed frame I noticed that the 4 washers it was supposed to come with weren't included so I had to make another trip to the store. At this point I've spent roughly an hour getting parts that were supposed to be included. As I started putting the bed together I noticed it was difficult trying to get the best small allen wrench where it was supposed to go. After getting it out together I put the wooden slats on and 3 are split even before we've put the mattress on it. Were going to have to spend even more money to replace the wooden slats so that they can actually hold a mattress and two adults. I want my money back. Buyer beware.

product_title: ApexDesk Elite Series 71" W Electric Height Adjustable Standing Desk
review_body: 4 and a 1/2 stars!  I have used two other types of more expensive (more than $250) adjustable desks during the last few years.  The construction for the Apex is definitely "on par" with the heavier ones.  The legs and support structure is very (I'd like to say "the same" but I can't, though it is that close) similar to the GeekDesk - minus the shin smacking cross support "bar".  (Some other similarities are wiring, motor/motor whirring sound (maybe even quieter?), legs, motor housing, power box, control adjuster cat5 plug...  it has two, though not sure what the other is for.  Maybe what I should list are the dissimilar characteristics... but since many of us would want the most "bang" for the dollar...).  The desk is HEAVY, and sturdy.  On a scale of 5, and 5 being the easiest, the assembly was a 4 1/2.  Every box has the desk assemble instructions!  With the exception of the "L" shaped locks, the entire desk could have been assembled without the instructions.  I think it had 15 screws and three nuts.  The only hard part was aligning two of the six screws the attach the table/composite to the structure.  Though two people are recommended, an average person can assemble alone - I did.  Only two tools were used: a Philips head screw driver and a needle nosed pliers (to hold the nuts while turning the screws).  So why not 5 stars?  The unit arrived with cosmetic damages.  The hard coatings of the "feet"/base were scuffed/chipped to the metal in four areas.  This isn't painted metal... not like paint on cars anyway.  The box it came in didn't seem damaged at all, so I was very surprised to see such hard scrapes/chipped "feet"/base.  Perhaps the box (three heavy boxes total for the desk) the "feet"/base were in was dropped flat during transit.  Also, one of the (not pictured) screw-in round foot-pads were broken in half; which I super-glued together.  Since the desk will stand on carpet, I do not think it will matter.  None of these I'd call the mfg for - it'd just mean headaches (and no desk) for me longer.  A note to the mfg, the "feet" need more bubble wrap.  BTW, the packaging/boxing were super/professional packing.  I know this sounds contradicting, but perhaps with the exception of the scrapped/chipped "feet" everything else were packed wrapped, snug, secured and very professional.  I've shopped a lot for an adjustable desk.  In the end, I've decided to try the least expensive one for the size.  I'm glad to have found this one.  I'll summit photos of the desk later... and the "feet"/base pics too.

product_title: Altra Parsons Desk with Drawer
review_body:
What can I say. I was looking for vanity tables, but none worked for what I wanted. Many didn't have the space not the qualities I wanted on a vanity table.

I started to look into parsons tables and I found this one. Not only did it have everything I looked for in a vanity table, it was affordable. I liked that it came with a built in drawer and is sturdy to hold my makeup.

It's so easy to assemble. It comes with everything you need to put it all together. I thought I was going to have my husband and put it all together for me, but once I saw I could do it I did it! The instructions are easy to fallow and I liked that the parts are labeled for you, so when reading the instructions you can actually match each part with no trouble.

The only thing why I took a start away is that even though I tightened the bolts tight as they could go the legs of the table are not that well. I will have to ask my husband to look at it and see if he can fix that.

I recommend this product totally 100%.
It does not take much space and it looks amazing!

product_title: Wheaton Reversible Corner Desk in Antique Black
review_body:
This desk proved to come in handy because I like to work remotely on occasion. Although there is not half as much space as my desk in the office, this is good to work from for a day or two - anything longer would probably drive me crazy. I like being able to spread stuff around - and I have papers everywhere.

The desk was delivered in a large box that had to weigh a little over 100lbs - on the side of the box it reads "Mech Lift Only". Of course, being a hero, I lugged it (by hand) to the basement office where I assembled it. Speaking of which, the desk is a little tricky to put together and a lot of patience is required.

Once together, I have to say it's generally a nice looking desk. Although there is not a lot of room to "spread out", its good for a laptop and there is enough storage room for paper and a small printer. Overall, it's a good desk for the price and I find that it works well when I work from home 1 or 2 days a week.

product_title: Walker Edison Soreno 3-Piece Corner Desk
review_headline: Great Desk, but Keep it Clean
review_body:
I've become somewhat a minimalist this year, and this desk fits the lifestyle pretty well- keep it simple, nothing overly fancy and doesn't take up a ridiculous amount of space like other desks tend to. Put together, it has some weight to it but if you're on the move and have to pack it up, the heaviest parts are really the glass so it shouldn't be a problem making a couple of trips to move the glass tops then he frame.

The one I purchased is in black. Black legs, bars, frame and all. Looks great, put together within an hour or so. Once you figure out how to do one side, the other side is a snap. You can remove the corner by removing the screws holding it in place and re-fastening the screws, and end up with two smaller desks or tables. They are a little wobbly this way, so don't put too much stress on them.

You may also be able to buy another desk of this kind and attach that one to the one you already own, I'm not 100% on that but it does look that way. If it works, you have one very big desk to suit your needs.

One issue that seems to be my only one: any light hitting the desk will expose hand and finger prints, so be sure to keep some windex or vinegar handy if that kind of thing bothers you lol.

Either way, it makes for an excellent desk for a laptop user or someone who lives alone and uses it for a desk and table both to save space.

product_title: International Concepts Round Top Stool
review_body:
I needed an 18" stool, and this turned out to be perfect, very stable. It needs to be stained/finished, but the bare wood finish is very good. I just used a piece of 320 grit sandpaper for a final rubdown, then a clean cloth to remove the dust. I like MinWax poly spray, and I used semi-gloss, three coats in one day. The stool looks really good. It now needs 3 days to fully harden the finish.

Interestingly, under the seat there was a sticker that stated "made in North Carolina" but stamped right next to it is "made in Vietnam". No big deal, the stool is robust and well made in any case.

review_headline: This chair would be fine if I could get a replacement arm rest for ...
review_body:
This chair would be fine if I could get a replacement arm rest for it. The one that shipped with it seems striped and will not stay up.

I bought it, assembled it and the arm has not functioned properly every.

All you can do with Amazon is return the chair. I have already assembled it and do not want to assemble a replace or find boxes it will fit assembled.

I simply want a replacement arm. A small request that would cost Amazon and Alera a lot less money than trying to replace the entire chair.

Alera has no phone number at Amazon or on their website for consumers to deal with.

Amazon should not sell the goods of manufacturers who do not offer support and Alera should not sell on Amazon if they will not support the product.

Don't buy it---if it comes defective your only alternative is to disassembly it and repack it and return.

Meanwhile I will simply use the chair with the arm all the way down to remind not to buy items on Amazon that do not list a way to contact the manufacturer.

product_title: Sleep Master Ultima Comfort Memory Foam 6 Inch Mattress
review_body:
Very nice for the price. I am a broke college student and I needed a mattress as the couch/futon I bought was a horrible mistake. This was in my price range and I am glad I bought it. It is firm/soft. I don't know how to explain it other than a perfect (for the price) mix of both. Soft enough to not want to get out of bed in the morning, and contour around you. And firm enough to still give support. It's just right for me.
A lot of people are complaining about how soft/too hard it is. You need to keep in mind mattress comfort is subjective. Everyone is different and has different needs.

As for the longevity, I don't know. I've only had it about two months now. I am still very comfortable and I don't see any sagging. Even if that was happening, I'd just buy another one because they are so cheap. You get what you pay for.

product_title: Homelegance Factory Modern Industrial Style Sofa Table, Rustic Brown
review_body: I bought this for extra storage for linens and clothing. When I opened the box, the wood has the most offensive smell - similar to nail polish only worse. I have asthma and had a reaction within minutes, so I opened up all the windows, put on the fan, and put everything outside immediately. I also left the wood pieces OUTSIDE in a protected area to air out for over a WEEK -- and as of today, it still smells bad. I hesitate to store anything on this shelf that will be close to my skin! I already threw the box away, or else I would return it. I feel so badly for the people that have to work in the factory making this. This wood will not be airing out in my lifetime! I will not be buying anything else from this manufacturer.

The beads in the bottom were  just a very thin layer.  So we got these beads,  and were just able to fit the entire bag into the chair.  Over the course of a month,  it's again,  already, lost over 50% of its volume.  Next I will get scraps of foam and try that. product_title: Sauder Pogo 3-Drawer Chest, Soft White Finish
review_headline: I nice addition to a young teen's room
review_body:
I've assembled (too) many pieces of this kind of furniture, and this one is better than most. For example, the back is the same kind of heavy engineered wood as the rest of it--other furniture often has heavy paperboard backs. The storage bin at the bottom is clever in that it makes the base bigger and the dresser less likely to tip when the drawers are open.

A cordless drill/screwdriver is handy when putting this together. Sometimes you need to use a low-torque setting to avoid over-screwing--you don't want to chew-up the engineered wood.

This was easy to put together, even with a kid "helping."

product_title: CreativeWare Eco Styles Spa Bench
review_headline: perfect compact bench/storage for a small entryway
review_body:
I got this as a little bench for our front entry way- both my daughter and husband were sitting on the floor to pull on their shoes so I figured even though we are kind of tight on space (our front entry goes right into our living room) this little bench would fit perfectly, and it does. It was kind of a pain to assemble as the instructions were pretty useless, but as my husband said "you only have to put it together once..."

Other than it being a hassle to put together, it is very sturdy and looks great. We store shoes on the shelf under the bench, and when the bench isn't used for seating purposes, we can throw our stuff on it when we come in the front door (backpacks, mail, etc.) for a few minutes until we get in and get situated.

If you need a compact bench with a bit of storage for a tight space that looks nice and is sturdy, this is perfect. Just be prepared to spend a little time putting it together.

Highly recommended.

They also probably wouldn't be the best option for greater than average sized people, as they aren't particularly wide. I like the colors (off-white/grey with black legs), and they are very easy to clean -- I just wipe them down with a disposable chlorox disinfecting towel. review_body: The complaint that the chair cover is not stable, that when using the cover, it comes loose and moves around too much is true.  When I put it on the chair it looked great.  But we soon found that the neat fit was soon disrupted by using the chair, sitting in it and moving around.  The neatly fitted piece for the bottom part of the chair comes loose and hangs loosely in front of the chair.  I am going to try to take the arms off the chair and put the cover's fabric tightly between the chair and the arm, and then put the arm back on, hoping to clamp the cover's material so tightly it won't move.  But I may run the risk of simply tearing the fabric without solving my problem.  The implicit promise to fit all chairs doesn't work, but I haven't given up completely.  Even with the loose fabric the chair looks better than it did without it, but I am not sure it was worth the $40 that one pays for it.
