I thought about how cool this would be to use if you know you are going to be going somewhere knowing you will have a long wait in a line. For instance DMV or for Concert or Game tickets.It's so light it isn't a problem to carry. You could very easily hook it up to your backpack to take with you. The one thing that I think would make this even better is to have rubber feet instead of plastic. The plastic make the stool easy to slide, something you don't always want to happen,

product_title: Lifetime Contemporary Residential Folding Chair
review_body:
These lightweight folding chairs from Lifetime are great for helping you accommodate extra guests at your home. If you've ever owned or even browsed Lifetime products, such as their folding tables, you know that their products are thick and durable. These chairs are no exception, however, realize that these are NOT part of their commercial line, so they are intended for light duty use around your home, not regular seating for the general public. The weight capacity on these chairs is 275 lbs, so know who will be sitting in them.

When folded flat, they are fairly compact, making them easy to store, and their plastic bottom legs allow them to stand up without sliding and do not scratch hardwood floors. When unfolded, the chairs have a nice, sturdy seat base and a somewhat reclined seating posture. I found them to be very comfortable. They are lightweight to transport and certainly not noisy like metal folding chairs.

I am very happy with these for what I intend to use them for.

product_title: Flash Furniture Cappuccino Wood Bar Stool with Black Leather Swivel Seat
review_body: Really like these bar stools. Solid wood with nice finish and a real leather seat. We have a counter connecting our kitchen to our living room in our new apartment and these are great.They swivel on a metal caster. The assembly is pretty straight forward but awkward at times given the kind of chair it is and the way the unit is assembled. If you've handled an ikea or prefab furniture assembly before, you'll be fine. This is SOLID wood though. The assembly may be ikea like but the materials are definitely not. Assembly Tips: Don't over tighten the screws . They are pre-drilled and you could strip them. Also, don't tighten each screw completely when you first join the legs to the foot rest and top. lightly connect each until all four legs are connected, then, tighten them up. If you tighten one up leg completely, it won't have as much room to give to work the other screws in. keep it loose but connected until all four legs are connected. I have an extra set of allen keys so my wife and I were able to breeze though assembly. This comes with only one key so it will take a while.

product_title: Natural HomeLogic Bathroom Cleaner -16 fl. oz. Safe, Natural, Effective, Sulfate Free Formula Is Non-Toxic And Fume free. Cleans Without Using Harsh Chemicals And Leaves No Toxic Residue Behind. 100% Plant & Mineral Based, No Artificial Colors Or Fragrances.
review_headline: natural cleaner that so far has passed my mob test
review_body: In our quest to go natural and remove as many harmful chemicals from our live as we can, it is very hard to find products that can clean up messes with today's standards. When  you have 2 kids under the age of 10,  1 dog, 3 cats, a husband and a pool.....you end up with a very messy and icky bathrooms daily!  I used this to clean up one of the bathrooms last night and I was very pleased. I did not have to do a lot of scrubbing, it cleaned up the soap and minerals stains very easily. I was very surprised  as many natural products fall short, and so far this one has not. They can do better in the packaging area, the product was placed in a plastic sip lock bag but the bag was not sealed, nothing spilled from this shipment, but some of the others from the same company did leak as they were shipped the same way in plastic bags that were not sealed.  I did receive this bottle of natural bathroom cleaner at a discounted price, to test it and then provide an honest review. I have been a purchaser with Amazon for over 9 years Thank you very much for taking the time to read my review.

I did have to log onto amazon chat for 20 minutes to get my refund for the second piece. I went to wmt online to order 2 more, which arrived unbroken; however even a couple of these pieces from my reorder were not 100% in good condition. At least fairly easy to build and they look nice side by side with books on them.

Note my 1-star review is because both of these arrived badly damaged. When I finally sourced 2 that weren't broken, I like the product.

product_title: Summit Mountain Wood Audio Cabinet with Adjustable Shelves for Media, Components and Storage, Espresso
review_headline: Product is OK, FEDEX delivery is HORRIBLE!
review_body:
Good product, ideal size for most stereo components. HUGE problem with the shipper FEDEX. They delivered the unit in a box that had obviously broken open--I learned later, after much effort and partial assembly, a major panel was MISSING! Apparently it had fallen out of the broken open box. The box was 'resealed' later, sans bottom panel--impossible to assemble without the bottom panel.
I wrote the supplier directly and they re-shipped another unit and asked me to repack the original unit as best I could for FEDEX to pick up.

Second unit was complete; I assembled, found i needed to 'jerry-rig' a couple of places, augment with my own fasteners in a couple of places, but the unit was functional and the jerry-rigging was not easily visible.

Product is a 4 for that reason, delivery company (FEDEX) rates a '0'--what a sloppy, uncaring system! AWFUL!

review_body: I will preface this with the fact that I can get a migraine from the wrong kind of floral smells, so I was a bit nervous getting the Jasmine scent, but I had nothing to fear. The natural Jasmine and ylang ylang scents make this cleaner a delightful and relaxing smell. It is not overpowering, just fresh and clean smelling. This is a great cleaner for my small bathroom because the close quarters mean I spend a lot of time cleaning the walls to keep the place from smelling. This being all natural makes me more confident that I'm not using something extremely risky to my kids in the name of clean smells. I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

product_title: Royal Anti-Fatigue Comfort Mat - 20 in x 39 in x 3/4 in - Ergonomic Multi Surface, Non-Slip - Waterproof All-Purpose Luxurious Comfort - For Kitchen, Bathroom or Workstations - Black
review_body: I am new to the world of standing desks, but it's clear to me that having a high-quality mat is critical to a successful transition to and long-term sustainability of this work posture. This mat has allowed me to transition immediately to full days of work while standing (I also bought a desktop unit that lifted my monitor and keyboard to proper working height) without any discomfort for feet, legs or back. I make everyone who goes by my office and comments about my new arrangement come and stand on this mat, because the difference is immediately and strikingly obvious. It elicits a lot of "Wow!"s and "Oooh!"s. If you are considering a change to a standing desk (which I also recommend), it's pretty clear that you need something like this to make it feasible. I have not tried other mats, so I can't compare this one to other similar products, but I am very happy with it. The only thing I cannot yet speak to is durability, since I've only been using it for two weeks, but it still looks new at this point.

product_title: Safavieh Vintage Premium Collection VTG158-2220 Transitional Oriental Medallion Blue and Multi Distressed Silky Viscose Area Rug (2' x 3')
review_headline: Thinner than expected but velvety-soft; nice quality
review_body:
At first glance, I will admit I was disappointed. It was much thinner than I expected. I was hoping for the type of rug where the fibers would flow across your fingers, somewhat like a shag rug.

However, after closer inspection, I realized that it was a quality rug with sturdy stitching. The "rug" part can be best described as a very soft, almost silky velvet (do not read that as thick..just velvety-soft). The grey shade was very pretty, and as you sweep your hand across it you can see different shades of grey, almost silvery.

The back is not padded and is the type of rug that would slide along hardwood or tile. I plan on placing a felt pad under the rug to give it a more padded feeling and also to keep it from sliding.

FYI: There is a sticker on the back that states you should vacuum frequently but DO NOT use a brush; use a brushless attachment (perhaps a soft furniture or pet hair removal vacuum attachment?)

Overall, I like the the look and feel of this rug. I think it is very pretty and doesn't resemble the "mass produced, cheap look" of those big box rugs. I am happy with the purchase.

product_title: Natural HomeLogic Laundry Detergent - 50 fl oz
review_headline: All natural cleaning that is just as powerful as anything else on the market but without the chemicals
review_body:
I have always been careful with what kind of laundry soap I use. Things like Tide have pieces of fiberglass in it, to get things cleaner supposedly, but they can wreck your clothes and give you bad skin reactions. So I try to buy only natural laundry soap, but sometimes finding the right kind that actually works can be difficult. I had to give this one a try right off the bat, I absolutely love that it's natural and plant derived. I used only a small amount for a big load and used my normal vinegar as fabric softener to avoid chemicals. I also like putting a few drops of tea tree oil in to help get rid of any smells that may be present with kids and pets in the house. The wash came out smelling amazing! The clothes are just as clean as when I was using the chemical concoction that they sell at the regular store. I can do my laundry without worrying about what chemicals I am exposing my family to, but still getting my laundry nice and clean. Fantastic product and a little goes a long way. I never use a full cap as a small amount does just fine.

*I RECEIVED THIS PRODUCT AT A DISCOUNTED PRICE TO TRY IN EXCHANGE FOR AN HONEST AND UNBIASED REVIEW. EVERYTHING IN THIS REVIEW IS 100% MY OWN AND HAS NOT BEEN INFLUENCED IN ANY WAY

product_title: Mainstays 3-Shelf Bookcase, Black
review_headline: worst of the cheap bookshelves I have owned
review_body: I am a grad student.  I have had many build your own bookshelves, all cheap pieces of crap.  I have very, very low standards.  This book shelf is the biggest piece of crap I have every bought in my entire life.  It is entirely useless.  I can't use it for anything.  It took me a very long time to figure out the instructions, although I did take my time to understand them properly before beginning.  When it came to the actual assembly, everything was fine until it got to the cam screws.  I got the "male" part in just fine, but the "female" part ... the hole for it was incredibly shredded out and it was nigh on impossible to get the two parts of the screw to align.  When I tried to attach the sides to the top and bottom, no matter how hard I tried - how carefully I aligned and how firmly I hammered the two pieces together - I could not get the pieces to attach to one another with any degree of firmness.  If I grab the side piece, I can pull and push it away from the top and bottom.  The only thing keeping the bookcase as a rectangle and not an unfortunate rhombus or trapezoid is the thin cardstock back nailed to the frame.  I'm afraid to put anything on it, afraid to move it even, lest the whole thing fall apart.  A stiff breeze could undo all my work.  Do *not* buy this piece of junk.  Buy another crappy bookshelf; it's guaranteed to be better than this one.

product_title: Ultimate Dreams 13" Gel Memory Foam Mattress
review_body:
This is my first review on Amazon. I am in no way being compensated in any way by anyone for this review. I don’t know anyone at Amazon or at the mattress company. I simply feel the need to get the word out.

I am a 51 year old male. I had a major car accident in 2004 which left me with quite a few different problems. Some the issues are a bad lower back and a less than perfect rotator cuff on my right shoulder. I work hard to stay in shape and eat right because I know it makes it better on my back. I have used a stand up desk since the accident and I’m confident it has positively impacted my back health as well. Throughout the days and evenings my back normally feels pretty good and is a non-factor. The nagging issue I could not get my hands around was the way I slept and how I felt when I woke up.

My wife and I tried many different mattresses in an attempt to find “the right one”. I tend to toss and turn at night trying to find a comfortable position. I always sleep with a pillow between my knees when I’m on my left side and I have pillows under my knees when I’m on my back. I almost never sleep on my right side because I know my shoulder will hurt all day. Long and short, we have really been working for a solution. No matter what we/I did, every morning I would roll out of bed and my back would hurt. I would have to spend 15 minutes every single morning trying to get my back to relax and literally “pop” back into place. Once I heard the pop the pain was relieved and I was ready for the day. Needless to say, even though I did get sleep every night I am confident it wasn’t good sleep. I hope this give you a good idea of my situation.

So, after years of looking into different mattresses, which was an extremely confusing and frustrating process for me, and fighting the urge to buy a crazy expensive foam mattress I came across an independent review of the Ultimate Dreams Dream Foam 13” mattress. I felt the review was not sponsored which was important for me. It said the Dream Foam mattress was comparable to a MUCH more expensive product but was much less costly. Since the Dream Foam bed isn’t for sale at a brick and mortar store the reviewer recommended trying the competitive product. Well, that’s what I did and I absolutely loved it. I laid on it for 15 minutes and was all smiles. I told my wife about it and we decided to give the Dream Foam a try since it was supposed to be very similar.

We want a split king adjustable which ends up pretty darn expensive from my perspective. It was very unnerving for us thinking about spending that kind of money and not being completely sure what we are getting. So we decided to order one of the Dream Foam XL twin mattresses and nothing else…yet. I would sleep on it, if it didn’t work for me my wife could use it and I would order a different style. We would make sure we each had the right mattress before we ordered the adjustable bed.

Well, the mattress arrived yesterday. I got home at 11:30pm from a 5 hour drive which meant my back was already sore. I immediately opened the mattress on the floor next to our bed and watched anxiously as it expanded. I told my wife I was sleeping on it that night. She thought I wouldn’t be able to because of the reported smell associated with new foam mattresses. I am happy to say, the smell of this mattress was minimal and completely manageable. We put a sheet on the mattress and I was laying on it by 12:00. I was fast asleep minutes after I put my head on the pillow. During the night I tried three positions. I started on my back then I rolled over to my left side. I remember waking up around 4:00 thinking how good the bed felt and how good I felt. I decided to give it the ultimate test. I intentionally rolled over on my right side to see how it handled the rotator cuff issues. When I woke up at 6:00 I was still on my right shoulder. I opened my eyes and just laid there. I focused on my right shoulder to see if I felt any pain…NONE. I focused on my back to see if I felt any pain…NONE. I rolled out of bed and stood up and felt NOTHING!! I was really surprised and simply couldn’t be more excited. I had my first pain free morning in literally years which also meant I had my first pain free sleep in years. I am higher than a kite right now. Granted it was only one night but you have to have one before you can have two!

We are going to give the bed a few more nights before we make a decision and order the rest of the items but I feel pretty confident where this is leading. I am a HUGE fan of this product and would highly recommend it. I will probably give a follow up report in a few days to either inflate the enthusiasm or to quell it.

Everyone’s back issue is different so there’s no way of knowing whether or not you will have the same results as me but I sure hope so.

product_title: SoftTiles Kids Foam Playmat- Safari Animals- Premium Nontoxic Interlocking Foam Floor Tiles for Children's Playrooms and Baby Nursery (6.5'x6.5')
review_headline: Great mat for playing on the floor with baby.
review_body:
Update 10/26/2016: Over a year later and this mat has held up beautifully with a very active toddler dragging practically everything across it and two cats clawing it to death. We walk over it constantly because it's still in the living room. In fact, I just ordered another one with different animals so I can add on to the original because my daughter now has a play table and the chair slides too easily over the wood floor. So, the new mat is going to connect to the old one and extend the padded area. For those who say it isn't soft, keep in mind that the softer the tiles are, the shorter their lifespan. And these are plenty soft to handle my knees and the knees of my 65+ year old parents. They look amazing after all this time. We have vacuumed them and washed them with no change in the texture (the only damage they have is from the cats, and even that isn't too bad). They are firmer than other mats, but my daughter has fallen on them A LOT, and while she might bump her head and cry, she isn't hurt. The mat doesn't slide around at all. They aren't completely waterproof at the seams (naturally), but they do slow down any spills. One of my best baby purchases!!!!

Original review:
We have hardwood floors, so I was looking for something to both cushion baby's body when moving around and to cushion me when I'm sitting on the floor playing with her. This has a nice thickness and cushion. It isn't smushy, just has enough give that it's easy on the knees. The colors are vibrant and the tiles lock together extremely well. The size is perfect. Not so big that it won't fit in the center of a room and not so small you can't easily fit several people playing on it at the same time.

I'm not sure why some people experienced an odor, because mine had none. Maybe theirs sat out in the heat?

The only thing I'd love to see improved, and this is just me being very picky (because I love the set), is for the edge pieces to start off with a wider flat part before they begin to taper down. This is because they taper down so quickly that the tips of the large pieces are thicker than the edge pieces, so stick up a bit. Again, this doesn't detract, but in a perfect world, it would be nice for there to be no edges sticking up at all.

I'll update this after a few months to let people know if there has been any effect on the hardwood floors from the tiles sitting on them for extended periods.

As an aside, my cats have loved clawing the pieces, so little holes now exist, but there has been no shredding of the material so far, so no risk of ingestion for baby. But keep in mind if you have cats, chances are they are going to want to "sharpen" their claws on these tiles. :)part before they begin to taper down. This is because they taper down so quickly that the tips of the large pieces are thicker than the edge pieces, so stick up a bit. Again, this doesn't detract, but in a perfect world, it would be nice for there to be no edges sticking up at all.

review_body: I received my computer task chair with tractor seat in vibrant candy heart pink and chrome today, a day earlier than expected.  Both my husband and I agree it looks as though we paid a lot more than we actually did.  It came meticulously packaged with everything needed, all components, tools needed for assembly, as well as extremely simple instructions.  This is the first ever in my lifetime that a set of assembly instructions came with no words just illustrations!  A whole twelve minutes... that's all the time it took my dear sweet husband to do the assembling.  As previously mentioned the packing couldn't be more perfect.  Not a single scratch or dent anywhere.  It's so nice to still find a company with old fashioned values who still take pride in what they do!  The color is a darker shade than candy heart pink but nonetheless it is beautiful and inspiring as stated in an earlier review I read  before making my own purchase.  Its' beautiful lines as well as stunning color can't help but put smiles on our faces.  The tractor seat is extremely comfortable and shaped or should I say molded perfectly to fit ones' bottom. This is coming from a family who already has six other office chairs which are higher priced. The only improvement would be to do the back rest frame in metal but then again we were already aware of that before purchasing by reading the reviews.  We highly recommend this task chair to everyone looking for a super comfortable chair at a great price.  It's already one of our favorites and I might add the best looking too!!!

review_headline: No harsh chemicals, just a clean kitchen!
review_body:
I have a hard time making myself use harsh cleaners, I just end up with skin issues afterwards, but I want to be sure my family is safe from things like salmonella. Natural home logic All purpose cleaner has given me peace of mind, knowing I can get my house clean, but also knowing I don't have to resort to dangerous chemicals in order to do that.I tried it out in the kitchen this morning after breakfast, which is always a mess with little kids. I sprayed it on the table cloth first to see how it would do with a sticky mess there. A few swipes with a wash cloth and it was clean! I moved on to the sink, where I had been doing dishes, and cleaned up the faucet, the inside of the sink and along the counter. It works fantastic! The biggest obstacle is the glass top stove, which it took care of in just a few wipes. The smell is lovely, like grapefruit and orange. The spray bottle worked perfect and I would definitely buy this again.

product_title: Stand Steady Traveler Folding Stand Up Desk
review_body:
This is a stand up desk elevation which folds up for travel.
Materials and workmanship are good and the stand indeed folds up nicely and sets up easily. The height is adjustable in 4 increments and the highest setting fits me (6ft 3inches) nicely on top of a medium height desk.
The base is large enough for a 17inch notebook and bears the weight well. Unfortunately, typing on top of the stand, even while applying only gentle and even downward pressure, turns into a really wobbly affair since the stand is not really solid- this constitutes a major product flaw in my use case.
I also reached out to the customer service of Stand Steady through Amazon to give them a chance to comment on the issue I have with the product but have not heard back in 48hours.

I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest review.

Your happy its here, if you squint your eyes it almost looks good but soon realize it will fall apart...most likely by the end of whatever season or party you purchased it for. I wouldn't trust anything important on this table: food, beverages, Poker game or Thanksgiving turkey etc.

product_title: Home Styles Furniture 5061-66 The Orleans Storage Wine Rack
review_body:
When we received this rack in the mail, the first thing that impressed us was the sheer weight. It is clear the items are of durable quality just by that metric. After unwrapping assembling and using this assessment became even stronger. Several friends have commented on its appearance.

INSTRUCTIONS AND ASSEMBLY:
This was very nicely done.
All the parts were well labeled and nicely wrapped to protect all the surfaces. Stickers were on each part so you know what parts went where. All the hardware was in a bag.
Not only did they show you in wonderful illustrations how things got put together they recommended the orientation of the parts. Sometimes you installed with the rack in different orientations and they were clear to note when this was to happen. They also told you when not to tighten up stuff completely, so it had some play while other things were still being attached.
Also and these means a lot, they included extra hardware. This is a godsend if a part goes ricocheting off somewhere never to be found. I recently put together a very expensive tool that didn’t have a single spare and we lost 30 minutes trying to find a nut we dropped.
The assembly went smoothly and we carted this very solid rack up 8 stairs and I can vouch for fact, the weight was in the rack not the packing.

USAGE:
The beautiful wood on the top, base and small shelves is a nice match to my medium oak dining room. The darkened silver uprights, glass and bottle racks are a wonderful accent. Not too flashy or tacky. All 28 bottles that I have put in it, have a nice tilt and the glasses slide in their holder. Of course the glasse have some play and are not secured. Might take them out when the grandchildren come over, but other than that, I’m content with their fit. Any tighter might cause different issues. I have grasped the rack and shook it to see if there was any play and it was limited only to making my glasses ring. Very little movement was noted. Since I have the unit on carpeting that is most likely where the play came from.

The dimensions are nice fit in my house. 16.5” tall X 38” wide X 41.5” tall. Only you will know what works for you.little movement was noted. Since I have the unit on carpeting that is most likely where the play came from.

The dimensions are nice fit in my house. 16.5” tall X 38” wide X 41.5” tall. Only you will know what works for you.

product_title: Cosco Products 4 Piece Malmo Resin Wicker patio Set - Brown with Teal Cushions
review_headline: For giggles I thought I would work at a good pace to assemble it with my wife holding stuff ...
review_body: Wow some people just have no business buying things that need to be assembled! First off it comes in one compact box because it is a 4 piece set for less than $500 dollars. You do know it has to be manufactured and shipped a few thousand miles for you to get it.. This is why it is in one compact box, not some conspiracy so you can't move or return it. Also My wife is five foot noting -115 lbs and she had no problem getting it into the house. I walked in and saw the box and said this is the huge box the nut jobs wrote about, and it is not 100 lbs. For giggles I thought I would work at a good pace to assemble it with my wife holding stuff or handing me screws from time to time. 60 min flat! To those that took 3 hours, first, lay out matching parts in separate piles. this will in an instant tell you what is what, without the part a,b,c etc second, assemble on your dining room table with a blanket over it makes it much easier. Third if you live in the year 2015 and utilize this technology of buying with a click, get your self a $30 cordless drill and a multi bit set $5 for all you future purchases so that you don't cry impossible assembly in the future. If you use an Allen wrench you are an idiot! Also out of the 40 assembled things I have in my house including a bunch of IKEA stuff the way the screws were packaged and labeled for each part and lined up biggest to smallest was awesome! I wish IKEA did that! Bottom line fantastic look, for a hell of a price and super easy to assemble. BTW to those that were "missing screws you used to long of screws on the back centers ..they were supposed to be for the feet! I'm thinking about getting another set  two more chairs would be nice

product_title: Hands-free Magic Mesh Magnetic Screen Door Curtain Anti-Mosquito/Bug Beige
review_headline: Product so bad, repeat business is not a goal
review_body: This screen came with 8 pieces of velcro fasteners...each measuring approximately one-inch square in size. These were intended to secure edges of sides and tops where they are attached to door frame. There were 7 push-pin tacks...to be used as reinforcement. It is not realistic to use these by themselves because the net, with use, will rip from the door, at the point there is pull on the tacks. I attempted to use pieces of velcro that I already had on hand, but using a glue gun to secure it to the net didn't work well. Very messy. The magnet fasteners that hold the middle  in place...that is supposed to fall back into place after passing through the doorway...simply fell off the net curtain as it was handled. They did not remain on it when put back into place. At $8, it was not worth returning, and it certainly wasn't worth the time and effort I put into it to get it to work. The only reason I went to the trouble, was that the flies, coming into my place were driving me crazy. This was a piece of crap. The inclusion of attachments did not appear to be a mistake. There is no intent by the manufacturer or seller to obtain repeat business. Bottom line: scam.

product_title: Wheaton Reversible Corner Desk in Antique Black
review_body:
We just moved my Mother into new Mother-in-law quarters here at my house and we needed to get her a new desk that would fit into a smaller space than she was used to. We thought this corner desk would be perfect. It also matched with other pieces of her furniture that are black as well.

It came in a huge, heavy box. We actually had to use a dolly to get it into the house. Assembly is definitely required but is still fairly easy and straightforward. The desk is reversible and can be assembled with the drawers on either side.

It has a printer shelf which allows you to put papers underneath it.

There are two drawers. One drawer is for storage while you can hang files in the other drawer. There are also two cubby holes above the drawers.

This is better suited for a laptop instead of a full-sized regular computer because it doesn’t have a keyboard tray. Some people don’t mind putting the keyboard on the desk itself but I personally prefer the keyboard tray to save desktop space.

The desk is pretty for a computer desk. It isn’t fine wood but I think the colors look handsome together.

review_headline: DON'T WASTE YOUR TIME AND MONEY!
review_body: This is a total waste of money. First off, it's not cherry, or cinnamon, it's almost black. Secondly, it's cheap particle board with plastic veneer, and even worse the backing isn't wood or particle board, but a printed piece of cardboard. Assembly is a nightmare, the instructions are poorly written and also instruct you to put the hinges on the door before attaching to the unit. This doesn't work.  Also instructions tell you to mount this onto wall before attaching door. So then you're stuck with it.  The description reads resistant to stains, scratches and humidity... It shows literally very single fingerprint. And it scratches very easily. Also the veneer was already bubbled upon arrival. The pegs used to hold up the adjustable shelves show. The hives are extremely difficult to adjust to level the door, and even after leveling the door through hinge adjustment, the door will not lie flat. Don't waste your money. Grateful for amazon's amazing customer service which gave me a refund after I explained the problems with this item, but will never get back the hours of frustration and time wasted with this hunk of garbage.

product_title: Alera SW504818BL Industrial Heavy-Duty Wire Shelving Starter Kit, 4-Shelf, 48w x 18d x 72h, Black
review_body:
These are a very solid set of shelves. I thought that the packaging was only fair (while moving the box, I could hear the hardware rattling around, and the styrofoam packing had gotten crushed during shipping), but when I took inventory, everything was there and in good shape. This can either be built as one large unit or two smaller units (the package includes hardware for either). I opted for a single tall unit - which means that you must attach the bottom and top halves of each upright pole. They use a screw-in metal connector for this which is quite sturdy and solid. The shelves are held in place with plastic keepers that fit into grooves on the uprights (it's sturdier than it sounds), and extra plastic keepers were supplied. The bottom of the poles have levelers (there are extra levelers supplied for a two unit configuration), but you can unscrew these and put in replacement wheels instead (not supplied, but the instructions are provided). There are also some extra pieces in the package that can be used to attach the shelves to a wall for extra stability.

I put this together by myself, but it's a heavy unit, and there were a couple times that I wished I had a helper or third hand. The instructions are complete but minimal - I found that I had to figure out for myself the best way to juggle four poles, 8 plastic bits per shelf, and the shelves themselves.

product_title: South Shore Furniture Cosmos Collection Twin Mates Bed Box
review_headline: Good bed though would go better quality next time.
review_body:
The bed quality is about what we expected for the cost. It took my husband and I about 2 hours to put it together. The directions were mostly pictures so there is some deciphering that needs to be done. Luckily we did it with only 1 thing that we had to go back and fix (and it was an easy one). The drawers initially did not close flush against the bed but once the mattress was placed on they closed perfectly fine so that might be a weigh distribution issue? I'm not really sure. Thankfully this bed was bought for my 12 year old so I don't need to worry about him jumping on the bed and such; would not recommend for younger children who may jump as I'm not sure I would trust the bed board that holds the mattress.

When I asked my 12 year old he said that it was very comfortable and he loves it (he had picked it out). Of course a majority of that comfort is from the mattress but as the one sleeping in it he said that he is very happy with it.

SO while we are not dissatisfied with the product (it's only been up 3 days), in the future I would probably buy a more expensive wooden piece of furniture instead.

product_title: Heart of the Kitchen Cart
review_body:
PATIENCE, PATIENCE, PATIENCE!!!!!!!!!! I am an engineer and while I was able to follow the scant direction, IT TAKES INTUITION! Lay ALL the parts out and FAMILIARIZE yourself with EACH PART. DRY FIT together first. Read directions SLOWLY. DO NOT try to do it all at once. GO SLOW. It will come out great BUT you need to know your limitations. MOST people CAN do this. IT IS INTIMIDATING coming out of the box. WAY TOO MANY PIECES. The instructions assume professional assembly which MOST PEOPLE ARE NOT! I can't emphasize enough, study all the parts FIRST. Have a large area to work. Take some white glue and glue the joints as you go. Don't use too much. It may take a day or two. In the end you will have a nice piece. I would recommend an oak or maple stain to darken the pine to a richer finish.

UPDATE Use glue on all joints. What I have found was even after being tightened, the joints were still wobbly. Also some hardware may e missing so count everything out. The more I got into this the more I realized how sucky the directions were. Also I recommend a nice stain and then poly fiI also had to modify the drawer slides by removing one inch from the slide to allow the drawer to properly close. Overall it is still a nice piece. I did not use the casters and opted to use a felt strip on the bottom. It is more stable.

review_body: Awesome piece of furniture. As other reviewers have stated - and as the description says - the whole thing comes packaged in the headboard, but to me that is not where the brilliance of the design ends. This bed arrived on time - I carried it upstairs myself (female - but I work out). I opened it and it came with a tiny bag consisting of two screws and the allen wrench you can use (we have a drill - recommend) to put it together. The two screws are for if you mess up any of the others already included in all the places they need to be. My husband is an engineer - a good one at that - and his comments on 'flat packaging design' being some of the most impressive designed pieces is true. I would recommend this bed to any and everyone out there looking for something stylish, sturdy, and affordable. This fit the bill. It is for our guest room - we combined it with a foam mattress from another retailer (O) and it has made for a great addition to our home. Go for it!!

product_title: Tuft & Needle Mattress
review_body: My husband and I were waking up with lower back pain and shoulder pain off and on for over a year, and we thought perhaps the 10 year old spring mattress could be the culprit. We looked at several online beds, and since Tuft & Needle has a showroom in Phoenix, only two hours away, that seemed the best place to start. The showroom was very busy, and we tested a mattress in a private room with a very low key salesperson. Impressed, we ordered. Two weeks of using the mattress confirmed that our old bed was hurting us, and the new T&N mattress has been like floating on air. I am 5'6", 116 pounds, but I have really wide hips. The way the foam moves, my hips can slightly sink in but my back stays straight. Perfect. And hubby's tossing and turning doesn't wake me anymore.

product_title: Flash Furniture HERCULES Series Big & Tall 400 lb. Rated Swivel Task Chair with Adjustable Arms
review_headline: Great value and good construction for the price
review_body:
I assembled the chair, but, yeah, it takes some effort to get the back joined to the seat, as you have to apply lateral pressure - they're both padded pretty well, so you have to press the back bracket towards the front of the seat while getting the bolts into place. Other than that, though, assembly is straightforward, and the only tool you need (a hex wrench) is provided.
The chair is wide enough to be comfortable, and the armrests are spacious. The base is welded steel throughout, all the way to the casters, and rolling in this chair across a hardwood floor is a pleasure. The seat's quite comfortable, and the waterfall padding does help. The back's cushy and, for us shorter, wider folks, provides suitable support.
The chair provides seat height, armrest height, and tilt with tilt tension adjustments. It does not have a back height adjustment (which is going to present a problem for tall folks - I'd recommend this chair if you're 6' or less, but no taller than that) or seat angle adjustment, however.
If you don't need the features of an executive chair, but you do need the reassurance of a chair meant to support heavier people, this is a pretty good purchase.

review_headline: Fantastic extra space for my desk !

I bought this for my desk - it sits cross-wise across the corner of the desk and hangs out on three sides -- effectively adding extra space plus another shelf. Laptop sits on top and is connected to large monitor and wireless keyboard -- so this configuration still allows direct access to the laptop when needed. Lots of space on the under shelf then for all sorts of desk needs. Don't spring for "assembly:" it takes less than 5 minutes (large twist on screws come with the posts - you don't even need tools to assemble it) - it just all twists together. I don't have a nice pull out drawer on my desk, so I ordered one for the bottom shelf - and there is still room to sit stuff on top of that. Space between the two shelves is just under 8". Amazon has all sorts of separate drawers you can order -- but I bought this one:

product_title: Twin Loft Bed with Desk
review_headline: Best use of space with generous sized desk
review_body:
We've only had the bed for a week or so, will loop back and re-review later. This was a big leap - ordering furniture from Amazon that we want to last for years... I'm very happy with the quality, and everything is exactly as described. My daughter has a very long/narrow bedroom, and with window placement, finding the right furniture was a challenge. Based on measurements, this bed looked ideal.

What I really like:
- Feels like solid wood, quality equivalent of most other children's furniture we've purchased - not flimsy or plywood-like
- When assembled, feels very secure and solid
- Desk is largest I was able to find for a loft bed of this size - it's something she'll be able to use for years to come, and having ample desk space was a key factor in selection
- Efficient use of space
- Built in dresser provides great extra storage, and drawers feel heavy and durable

Only drawbacks:
- Delivery in 5-6 boxes on a pallet, so a lot of packaging to deal with and boxes to get into place to start assembly; BUT, free shipping with Prime
- DIY assembly - just finding the time to put it all together; assembly wasn't that difficult or time-consuming, but dealing with unpacking all the boxes in the right order took time too

product_title: Tuft & Needle Mattress
review_body:
Used to have a queen sized pillow top which made too much noise and had a lot of motion transfer. After weeks of research I decided on a Tuft & Needle mattress. I was debating getting a Casper mattress but the king sized was $200 more expensive than Tuft and several reviews about the Tuft mattress stated it was more firm than the Casper. This was a no brainier!
Ordered the mattress directly from the Tuft & Needke website (not Amazon) on Monday morning , 9 am and it was delivered to my front door in a box on Wednesday the same week at 1:30 pm. Do the math, that's quicker than Amazon ! Plus the Tuft website is very informative and super user friendly.
The mattress at first didn't fit on the king sized box spring I have; it was too small. Give it some time to inflate after opening, overnight it for perfectly. This mattress is firm but not too much and very comfortable!
Now I sleep through the night no problem and when the pregnant wife gets up at night I never hear it !
Zero motion transfer or noise, wish I bought this before as its half the price of a similar big name mattress like Sealy or Simmons! Don't waste your time with that and get a tuft n Needle mattress now ! You won't regret it!
My only concern about this mattress is the test of time as this is a newer company and I'm not sure how long the mattress will hold up. However at $750 with zero shipping or tax, it's totally worth it!

review_body: The company I used was great- rerouted it several states away for no extra charge when mistakenly delivered to my previous address (my fault). As for the actual product, it is as would be expected for price. Not very sturdy; I think it is made of really hard-pressed styrofoam type product- no wood involved. Each arm is held on at two points. Not for a house with rambunctious kids or pets. We (2 adults) have had it for a week and already something popped on the back when my husband leaned back (stretching - no more strenuous than you would expect a couch to be able to handle). It's very firm (personally I like that) - if you want a cushy couch, this is like sitting on the floor if the floor was covered with a plush carpet. Was missing a screw to put it together but wasn't too terrible to put together. Plus side- it is long enough for a person to sleep on and if you like a firm mattress would be OK for a few nights. This will suffice for us as we are in this location for one year and wanted a couch that would last that long - but don't plan to move it with us. But if you want something to last any longer than that, dig a little deeper into your pocket. I can't complain about Superior Importers customer service though - they were fabulous.  UPDATE - another couch was just delivered to my house? I only ordered this one... the one that was delivered was one that was on my wish list but I never ordered it and was never charged for it, so I'm confused. Don't know if that mixup was on Amazon's end, or Superior Importer's end.

product_title: Signature Design by Ashley Larkinhurst Sofa, Earth
review_body:
I love this! I made the decision to go with this fabric after a lot of research. We have been through 2 sets of expensive leather furniture in the past 22 years. With the prices I paid for it, I was disappointed with how it held up. Both sets looked well worn within 5 years. We have 2 dogs that are allowed on our furniture. They scratch the leather. My husband also sits in the same spot on the couch every day, wearing out just that individual cushion. This is perfect! The fabric hold ups to the dogs, does not scratch. The cushions not only are flippable, they can also be switched around, in order to provide even wear.

Update: We have now owned this couch and the matching loveseat for over 2 years. It has held up perfectly! It still looks new. Any spot has wiped off with a damp cloth. I can't believe what I paid for this great quality.

As I've been shopping for a long time for the perfect replacement, I actually spoke to the salesman at Ashley. He stated it is one of their most popular sofas on the floor.

The color is kind of a warm taupe. It blends with the colonial yellow on my walls and the cool taupe brick of my fireplace. It reminds me of an old worn bomber jacket worn by the airforce 50 years ago.

The pillows are a nice extra! They reverse of the print side is the leather look fabric in a nice diamond pattern - very expensive looking.

This is the best! I'm thrilled to find it at this wonderful price, too - in store it would have been considerably more expensive.

product_title: Sleep Innovations Shiloh Memory Foam Mattress
review_body:
How desperately I wanted to like this mattress.

We can talk about firmness and temperature, but what really matters is: how does it affect the quality of my waking life? The answer is: most days, my back is sore when I get up, and I am in general more lethargic which is probably due to poor quality sleep.

If I had to pinpoint a reason, it would be the HEAT. I call this thing the frying pan. I learned on the first night to not use a down comforter (something I used year round with our Beautyrest). I bought a thin cotton blanket, and even that is too warm: many nights I wake up drenched in sweat; other nights I simply find that I have soaked the pillow (sometimes two of them). This can't be good for deep sleep.

Apparently, this is a problem for *some* people with *all* memory foam mattresses, even the expensive ones. (Judging from the reviews here, I'm guessing we are a small minority of the population.) In my hours of online research, I learned that there is no simple fix for dealing with the heat. There are plenty of long forum threads on the topic, with solutions ranging from expensive sleepwear to expensive wool mattress pads to... keeping the windows open or the A/C on all night. I tried the cheapest recommendation, which was to sleep *above* the down comforter so it insulates me from the mattress. That works pretty well at keeping the heat down--though nowhere near as cool as springs were--but is so thick along with the fitted sheet that it defeats the whole memory foam thing. Feels more like a futon pad.

I was hoping that in the ten years since my last mattress purchase, our civilization would have transcended the unpleasant experience of setting foot inside a mattress store (why are they all like visiting a car dealership?), and that may be the case with one of the many mail-order mattress companies out there--but it wasn't with this mattress. I'm not willing to buy another foam mattress sight unseen, so it's back to springs for me.springs for me.

product_title: Big Joe Large Fuf in Comfort Suede, Black Onyx
review_headline: it was poor quality and incredibly uncomfortable to sit or lay down ...
review_body: We ordered this for my mother to have as extra seating/sleeping when my aunt came to visit her a few weeks back.  What a joke.  After allowing it to expand to full size, my mother sat on it and immediately sunk straight down to the floor.  Also, some of the foam that filled the bag was covered in hard pieces that poked you when you sat on it.  Overall, it was poor quality and incredibly uncomfortable to sit or lay down on.  Thankfully, Amazon was understanding and allowed us to return it; however, finding a box that would fit this monstrosity was impossible, even after Amazon refunded an additional amount to buy a box large enough to return it in.  We bought the biggest box that we could find - still a no go.  After fighting to try and get this thing in to a giant box, we called Amazon and asked if it was alright if we just removed some of the foam that was inside of it.  They gave us permission to do this, and after removing a LARGE portion of the foam, we were able to finally get it to fit in the box to return it.  I am attaching pictures of the foam that we had to remove (to give an idea of how much we actually had to remove to return it, as well as to let people know what is actually inside), as well as a picture showing how lumpy it was even after it had been sat on several times.  So, 1 star for the product, but 5 stars for Amazon Customer Service.

review_body:
I looked for a long time for the right shelving to host my large Blu-Ray / DVD collection. My family room is in the basement and has carpet on cement. The free-standing racks that I've used up to now, while they do their job, were always a hazard as they tended to be unstable unless anchored to a wall. In addition, they were hard to vacuum around. These wall mounted shelves from Prepac are ideal. I bought two units and was able to assemble and hang both in about four hours. Assembly was very easy, all parts were included and they look fantastic on the walls.

The only reason this is not five star is that the backing of the shelves was made of cardboard and was rather difficult to attach. With that one exception, these units are well made and versatile. I'll probably buy more.

product_title: Boss Black "No Tools Required" Executive Leather Chair
review_body:
I am 6'5" 275lbs (svelte like a gazelle), I ordered this char a little over a year ago and it has finally given out completely. After about two months the hydraulic piston gave out so I have our maintenance department fix it so it was at max height and held there. Then a month or so later the back broke, it would just swing back pivoting in the middle. Then the wheels started to break apart into pieces. Finally the the cheap plastic fins that the wheels plug into gave out which sent me head first to the floor (I got pinned between my desk and the wall, and was saved by a passing co-worker who only saw feet in the air and came in to help me up). While all this was happening the chairs "leather" was pealing off the arms and the back.

I have to say, for the year I had it, it was very comfortable, and looked much more expensive than it was. If this chair held up better I would give it 5 stars without hesitation.

product_title: South Shore Vito Collection 6-Drawer Double Dresser
review_body: This was by far the worst piece of furniture I've ever purchased! I am 9 months pregnant and I had no problem helping my husband putting together our crib and changing table. This piece of furniture however, was impossible! Granted I should have anticipated the price reflect the quality in some aspects but damn this stuff is crap! The box came in good shape, the materials looked pretty good on first inspection. Once we got to the hardware I started getting worried, hardly any screws. Even with our reservations we decided to do our best, with our baby due any day we really had no choice. Things weren't staying in place, holes were either too big or too small it was a mess. The final straw was when things were finally starting to take shape and then out of no where one of the anchors in the front corner rips our of place and it's ruined! We were so frustrated, such a waste of time! Thank god for good Amazon customer service. We didn't even bother calling the manufacturer. Needless to say we will be returning it! Please don't ware your time or money!

review_headline: If you like to be swallowed up by the bed this mattress ...
review_body:
i bought this mattress in the full size a few years ago. It is very supportive but yet a memory foam feel. It has not lost its support at all after years of nightly sleep. If you like to be swallowed up by the bed this mattress isn't for you. I however like it. And plan to purchase a second one for another bed today. I've used it on ikea frames and wood futon frames all with the same support and comfort.

It comes in a box all rolled up - you open the plastic packaging unroll it and it poofs up very very quickly. The box however is big and heavy so be ready to have a helper handy if you're not a hoss.

I would suggest getting a mattress protector - the raspberry velour cover does not come off - and if you have a little one have an accident on the mattress it's quite the process to descent it. A mattress protector was a must after one accident.

product_title: Homeplus Storage Cabinet
review_headline: Good value, and good laminate furniture.
review_body:
Huge package. Think 137 pounds (at least package billed at 137 pounds by the shipping company). So, if you live alone, you need to get creative to get this into your home, especially if you have a townhouse with stairs.

It's MDF with laminate, there are no solid wood parts, so if you have a thing for veneers or solid wood, this isn't it. If it was solid wood it'd probably be a lot heavier.

Laminate is good quality, and all pieces match in color. The instruction manual is full, fluent English and has very clear part labeling and instructions. I'm very technical and handy, and it took me roughly 2 hours to finish.

There are some parts where it would definitely be easier to have a 2nd person (holding the door while you mount it). If you're a small person, you may have some trouble lifting it by yourself after assembly. The shelves and swing-out door are good design to allow less digging around the back of the cabinet to find that thing you need.

product_title: Linon Hunter Storage Bench
review_headline: And in a 3rd spot it looks like something came into contact with the wood finish before ...
review_body: 3 stars on assumption that I get a non-broken unit.  Mine came busted.  One of the pre-set wooden dowels was punched all the way thru the wood, lifting and splintering the outside finished side.  Another wooden down was broken in half.  And in a 3rd spot it looks like something came into contact with the wood finish before it was dry and peeled off a good 2x2 inch chunk.  Smack in the center of the chair railing, so just about as noticeable a spot as you could be.  Overall was happy with the wood quality, but the finish was on the cheap side.  Not entirely smooth or even, on the thick side on edges.  And the bottom board for the chest is def. on the thin side.  When a replacement arrives I'm going to create a replacement out of 1/2 plywood and probably add a support or two.  Update: 9/2/2015 - so far do not have the item.  It was shipped but never made it to us.  The "system" says we refused delivery and it was heading back to the shipper.  However, we never refused shipment.  We were home both times the delivery driver came out.  His computer said he had the package, but it was not in his truck.  Either time.  He was pretty pissed that "they" (whomever that is) didn't laod / loaded to the wrong truck twice.  Amazon is trying again.  We'll see....

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
An array of bonded leather swatches, in various colors and patterns.

Bonded leather, also called reconstituted leather or blended leather, is a term used for a man-made upholstery material made as a layered structure of a fiber or paper backer, a pulp made from shredded leather, and a polyurethane coating which is embossed with a leather-like texture. Related products, bicast leather or coated leather, are made by splitting, shaving, or grinding leather to reduce its thickness, and then laminating it.

product_title: Zinus Memory Foam 6 Inch Green Tea Mattress, Narrow Twin / Cot Size / RV Bunk / Guest Bed Replacement / 30" x 75"
review_body:
Stats....
Firmness: 2/5 (5 being firmest)
Support: 2/5 (5 being best postural support)
Cooling: 2/5 (5 being coolest)
Initial Smell: 4/5 (5 being most pungent)
Long Term Smell: 0/5 (5 being most pungent)
Author's Height/Weight: 6'2" 185lbs

This bed had a lot of promise, but I cannot in good conscience give it higher than a 2/5 overall. The bed arrived within 2 weeks as it was not prime eligible. It would be worth having a friend help you carry the mattress to your room as it arrives rolled up in a long box and is quite heavy. You simply remove the mattress from the box and cut away the plastic compression wrap, then let it expand; mine was almost completely expanded within 1hr and done within 4hrs. My room is 11'x12' and smelled for roughly 1.5 days (the first half day of which it smelled quite strongly of chemicals) so it would be preferable to open this in your garage and let it sit a few days first. Since those first few days, the smell has been completely eradicated. As far as long term use, the postural support is awful. Your butt will sink into the center of the bed while your legs and head are propped up, which becomes especially uncomfortable when lying on your side. Strangely, I would only rank this mattress as medium firmness, but the actual density is very poor. It is worth noting that the quality of the bed has remained constant over the last 6mo, so at least it has not grown more uncomfortable. I will be pawning this mattress on craigslist when I move to a new apartment.

product_title: Tuft & Needle Mattress
review_headline: Buy the mattress and thank me later!
review_body:
The entire process couldn't have gone any better. The website simplified it in a way that I could relate with what they were trying to do. Which is to make a great product, reasonable priced, and shopping for it without the headache of being sucked into the massive buying process that exist today. I would probably rather go shop for a used car than a mattress. If I didn't buy from T&N I would gone to Costco and bought. But I saw the reviews, I saw the 100 day trial no questions asked, and believed in them and gave it go. I didn't even consult with my wife, I just pulled the trigger and bought it. Today I look like a hero to my wife and I find myself evangelizing to others about how great it sleeps and easy it was to shop.

The actual mattress is firm, but soft at the same time. I can sleep on my back and holds well, but if I choose to roll over on my side it's soft enough to allow without hurting your shoulder. It's also very cool to sleep on, I don't sweat at all and I weigh 180.

Buy the mattress and thank me later.

And by the way, the customer service is outstanding. The founder (so they said) emailed me shortly after my purchase and before it arrived to my house. I actually responded back thinking it was a templated email, but I was wrong. He responded to back to my email and we made small talk. Those little things can make all the differences.

Again, buy the mattress, it won't disappoint.

product_title: Safavieh Lyndhurst Collection LNH552-1291 Traditional Floral Ivory and Multi Area Rug
review_headline: Ivory? Never in a million years....
review_body:
Due to the size and unusual shape of a room, I was having difficulty identifying an appropriate rug available locally that would suit. I turned to Amazon for help and I was so excited to find this one available in ivory, as that's the base color I was seeking. It was with high anticipation that I awaited delivery, only to be utterly disappointed when it arrived. Tan, coffee, paper bag, or mocha would all be apt color descriptors, but never in a million years could this rug be classified as ivory. What a complete letdown! Needless to say, it's going back; too bad, since it otherwise seems like a nice rug.

As an aid for others, I've included two photos of a corner of the rug comparing its purported "ivory" color with two different true shades of ivory. The first photo is of the rug next to a dark ivory drape, and the second sets it between a light ivory sweater and a Starbucks Mocha Frappucino.

product_title: Lorell 4-Shelf Panel Bookcase, 36 by 12 by 48-Inch, Cherry
review_body: Bookcases are great and gorgeous. Very solid. Purchased two. One arrived fine. The other arrived with concealed damage. Attempted to get damaged top replaced as the rest was intact and it was mainly built but it proved quite arduous with the supplier as supposedly the manufacturer was not responsive. After various expectations set by them for resolution failing I engaged Amazon and a full return of the damaged unit was arranged. Unfortunately the supplier refused to do an advance replacement, particularly as I had been awaiting resolution over 1.5 weeks, and it wasn't until they had confirmation of its return by their carrier that a replacement shipped. The new one arrived in pristine condition after roughly another week passed. Glad that hassle is done, but again the units themselves are quite lovely, solid and work perfectly in our home library.

product_title: Tuft & Needle Mattress
review_body: This is a fantastic mattress. I've used a box spring for years and was initially worried about the switch to a firmer foam mattress. I'd even had bad experiences with firm foam mattresses resulting in hip bruising in the past (I am a side-sleeper). But this mattress is the perfect combination of firm and soft- my back and shoulders are no longer tense when I wake up in the morning, and I can comfortably sleep on my side. This mattress also does not retain too much heat and remains cool and comfortable through even the hottest nights. Love, love, love this mattress! I bought through the Tuft&Needle website, and the mattress arrived promptly and was very easy to move into my new apartment. Great quality mattress, excellent customer service, fantastic buy all around.

product_title: Brentwood Home Cypress Mattress, Bamboo Derived Rayon Cover, Gel Memory Foam, Made in USA
review_body:
Received this mattress today in King and was a little worried with some of the reviews. I unpacked it and it immediately started to expand and take shape. I'd say within 2 minutes it was 90% there. The corners are still a little dented but it hasn't even been an hour yet so I'm confident it's going to turn out nice.

I'm coming from an old single sided Queen pillow top that I bought as my first real bed about 7 years ago. This thing already has me excited, it's soo comfortable. I don't know how people said it's really firm, it feels nice and soft to me. I'm about 190lbs and it feels just right. I can maybe see if you're 110lbs that it would feel firm but I don't know what Memory Foam mattress wouldn't.

I have not noticed ANY smell and it literally just came out of the package. The cover it comes with is very nice, even though I'll be putting a waterproof one on top(kids).

The only reason I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 is because it's not a true King size. King is 76" wide X 80" long and after pulling the corners out tight this one is going to measure right at 72-73" wide by 80" long. So it's going to end up normal King length but only Cal King width. That's not a huge issue for me since It's still going to be 12-13 inches wider than what I'm used to but it is something to be aware of, especially since others have noted the same.

All in all I don't think you can beat this thing for the price!

product_title: Lifetime Contemporary Residential Folding Chair
review_body: I picked up these chairs to use as seating for events. The chairs are sturdy and lightweight, and they fold flat and stack together easily. The seat height is good -- not too low like on some chairs. They feel more substantial than a typical folding chair. The plastic tips on the legs keep them from sliding on the floor and scraping/marking the floor.  The seats aren't padded, but they are contoured, making them pretty comfortable.  The only negative for me is the color of the seat and seat back gives them a dirty look, specifically there are grey/dusty looking streaks in the material. In general, however, they are good quality, practical chairs.  Lifetime also makes a "commercial" folding chair with an "all-weather finish" that is sometimes priced similarly to these chairs on Amazon, so you may want to check those out and see if they better suit your needs. [[ASIN:B0074HYTOA Lifetime 80187 Classic Commercial Folding Chair, 4 Pack]]

Absolutely awful workmen ship. The pieces in the side panel should have been glued down with wood glue. Another big con I noticed in several reviews was the finish was too thin and the surface of the table top scratches easily. They are all right about that! Once of mine got badly scratched within a few days. Was this worth the $84 I spent (for each!)? Absolutely not. But it was a gamble I took and paid the price. However, I am still happy with the look of the end tables. As far as appearance, I honestly love them. Also the baskets are much darker than they appear in the picture. Looking at other reviews and taking my 2 orders into consideration, it seems to be hit or miss. Good luck.

So I bought this because of the great reviews and the fact that my best friend got one. The one my friend got was amazing, soft but good support, and perfect for those who sleep on their back or sides. I was so excited when it finally arrived, but from there everything was a disappointment. Overall, if you get a non-defective product, it should work out great. If you have to return it for any reason, good luck cause it's gonna cost you extra.

Product Review:
I cut it out of the box and air sealed packaging, allow it to sit on a solid flat surface for 24 hrs, and it expanded about 80%. I had no idea what had gone wrong. I continued to let it air hoping that it just needed extra time to expand. Two weeks later and still nothing. The mattress had expanded more in the middle than the sides; I did try to sleep on it but I kept on slipping off every time I shifted in my sleep.

Refund/Return Review:
I contacted the manufacturer to see what I could do to get a refund/return. You can contact Dreamfoam by email or phone, they have an awesome customer service team. However, because I bought the product from Amazon, they don't provide refunds or facilitate returns.
When I tried to return the mattress via the Amazon online option, I had no idea how to get the mattress shipped back. The mattress would no longer fit in the box it arrived in. Amazon will pay for the shipping costs but not the container. A box to fit the mattress would cost about $50. I called Amazon and explained the situation. They made a one-time exception and gave me a refund without requiring me to send the mattress back. Which was really kind of them and saved me a huge hassle.

Final Verdict:
I'm going to buy direct from Dreamfoam, that way it's covered by their warranty.

review_headline: Best foam and with no to little scent!
review_body:
Just love this foam filling!!! I am VERY sensitive to scents and this did NOT smell, at ALL! the ONLY time it had ANY scent, was when I washed it and dried it on HOT (in a pillow I made) , and even then it only had a kind of off scent for a very short time. In fact, the pillow looked better after I washed and dried it (stuffing wise, seemed to balance out my stuffing job). I have used this to re-stuff the lumbar part of an old recliner and it has worked beautifully! It has been 5 months since I re-stuffed the chair, and it still acts like day 1! It hasn't stayed compressed or anything, it just looks like the chair was always the way it should have been. I am stuffing dog beds with it, little pillows, anything that needs a little bounce or padding! When I run out, I am definitely buying this again! It comes in a big fabric square that is lined with a plastic bag full of VERY compressed little pieces of shredded foam filling.if you only need a little bit of filling the FIRST time you use it, DO NOT open it all the way up or you will have a really hard time getting it closed again! (although you could STILL close the inner plastic bag to keep it sealed). The zipper runs over the top and down one side of it. The zipper works well and the fabric is really sturdy for keeping all the foam in. It's kind of like having block shaped (hard) bean bag waiting to fill your foam needs at a moments notice!

I would HIGHLY recommend this product!

product_title: eHemco Kitchen Island Cart Natural Wood Top with White Base
review_headline: Sturdy little cart that assembles easily
review_body:
Nice little cart. Took me exactly 90 minutes to put it together (I work slow). The instructions are pictures only (no narrative) but they were quite clear and easy to follow. The parts are nicely packaged and clearly labeled/numbered in the order in which you assemble them - a welcome touch for people like me who get lost easily putting together furniture. Nothing was missing. The wheels are heavy duty and move smoothly. Both the door and drawer operate easily and are nicely aligned.

Now for a few nitpicks:

~ A couple of the wood pieces were rough and had flaws. This wasn't a big deal, as fortunately the flaws were in places you won't see.
~ The wheels were not bagged and left some black marks on the back cabinet panel. The panels are reversible, so I placed the marked side of the panel so that it faced the inside of the cabinet and won't be seen when the door is closed.
~ The door and drawer handles are very lightweight and cheap-feeling. I will probably replace them with something sturdier from the hardware store.
~ IMPORTANT: Make sure you have all screw holes lined up PERFECTLY with the screws before tightening. If you're off by just a fraction, the wood will split. I had this happen on a couple of pieces and had to remove the screws, realign the parts and try again. You'll know you're lined up properly if you don't feel a lot of resistance when you start turning the screw. Use a flashlight if necessary to ensure the holes are aligned.
~ And speaking of the screws, do NOT use a power drill/driver to assemble this unit. Use a manual ratcheting screwdriver. The wood is fairly soft and it seemed like a couple of the little screws stripped their holes.
~ When assembling the side pieces, don't fully tighten the screws until you have inserted the side panels. You need a little wiggle room to make sure the panels seat properly.

Overall, the finished product is nice and sturdy and warrants four stars, but I don't know that I'd use it for a large microwave or other heavy appliance. I'm just using mine to display a small wine rack on top, and keeping paper plates, cups and napkins in the bottom cabinet.

product_title: Cool-Living Stand Up Desk made of Light Weight Aluminum
review_headline: Decent desk, poor internal mechanism, tools not included.
review_body:
This was purchased at my office. As mentioned elsewhere, they do not provide the necessary allen wrench to build this. Fortunately I had a set on hand. After finishing the build, I tried to use the crank for the first time and most of the teeth stripped off the gear, rendering it unable to raise or lower. I discovered the problem only after disassembling everything to look inside and found all the gear teeth broken off.

Fortunately, I investigated and found that an allen wrench (differently sized than that needed to build the desk itself) can be inserted directly into the main mechanism on the side of the desk (behind one of the silvery plastic covers). I was able to manually engage the mechanism in that way and get the desk up to appropriate height. However, that isn't as feasible for frequent raising and lowering.

The desk itself is solid and well built, which is why I have given two stars. The lack of provided tools and the non-functioning gear handle were a big problem, however.

product_title: CVSLink CX7F Laptop Desk
review_headline: This product is nice and overall I like it
review_body:
This product is nice and overall I like it. Lets start with what I like about it. The table is extremely adjustable, the legs can go up and down and the table itself tilts for your personal setting. There are clips towards the front of the of the table to stop it from from falling off if tilted forward. There is a rubber wrist support on the area for your mouse which is great and I love it I use it often. The last thing about this table is the built in fan, it charges off your laptop and the fan is super quite which I love.
Now to the things that I don't really like about it. The clips that stop your laptop from falling forward ( at least for me) are right where I put my hands to type so my wrist is right on them ( I don't use them often anyway but could still be an issue.) Not that its really needed but you can't have a mouse pad on it so if your table gets dirty (mine did I have a two little ones) your mouse is going to get grimy as well. The leg under the fan doesn't always lock when you close them. Now that doesn't mean that it just falls open but my toddler can easily grab it and pull it down. The last thing about it is there are no clips on the backside of the table to hold the laptop from falling back ( I like my laptop angled back just slightly.)
Now I will say that overall I like this table I and I will get a lot of use out of it. I was given a discount on this to give my honest opinion of it.

product_title: Ultimate Dreams Crazy Quilt 7 inch TriZone Mattress
review_body: Absolutely what I needed!  These look just like twin mattresses, in nicely-made quilted covers,  feel just like real mattresses--very comfortable and thick--but are lightweight.  PERFECT for guests, because they are so comfortable, and are then easy to stack on top of each other when you aren't using them. And they are made in the U.S.!  If you have room for an extra twin bed, you can stack these mattresses for when you need them.  I got the TWIN sized ones because they take up the least room when I don't have guests.  Today I took  my inflatable queen-sized mattress, which worked very well the only time I used it but was not as comfortable as the DreamFoam, to Goodwill.  First I ordered two of these DreamFoam twin mattresses, and then, after they were here and I could see that they were great, I ordered three more. So I have five.  When I had a house full of guests a few weeks ago, these mattresses were WONDERFUL!  Comfortable to sleep on,  odorless, easy to stack to make more room for kids to play during the day.   The quilted mattress covers they come in are very nice and well made, and, contrary to what some have said in the comments here, these mattresses were identical to each other, uniformly excellent quality.  I am very sensitive to odors, and have not smelled any odor from the DreamFoam.  When the mattresses are delivered, all of the air has been compressed out of the foam and they are in some kind of very tough shrink wrap.  In just a short time after being unwrapped, they expand, and are nice and thick.

The feel/texture is a lot rougher than I expected, which might be okay for outdoor spaces but I was expecting something softer from the images. You definitely wouldn't want young children running on it barefoot as it might scratch them. The bottom is a bit slippery on the floor so you would needed a rug pad or place something heavy on top like a coffee table. The main reason I gave it two stars however is that mine came with the entire length of the short edges folded about 1.5-2" and glued to the back! Yes, glued! You can see the glue sticking out along the corners. In the advertised image there is a white/beige border all along the edges. Mine however only has borders on the long edges. product_title: Inval AM-B223 Armoire, Espresso-Wengue
review_headline: Adequate for price, but not great
review_body:
As other reviewers noted: this is a bear to assemble. The large, heavy box was delivered just to my doorstep. My adult son and I opened it and carried pieces separately upstairs in order to assemble it.

The instructions are just visual and need to be scanned very carefully before starting. Separate and count all the many screws (lots of sizes), nails, other hardware parts.

Just putting on the hardware took me 3 hrs. Without an electric drill/screwdriver it would have been impossible. For several places where you need to insert screws, there are no pre-drilled holes, and that was a real problem. I carefully marked the spots with silver marker to see it against the dark stain, and then drilled small holes. This was particularly hard when lining up the hinges.

Once all the hardware parts were on, the assembly of the pieces only took another hour - and definitely requires 2 people.

This is made of very hard particle board that has been stained. It scratches easily, edges break too. In the end we got it all together and the doors line up, etc. It holds most of my husband's casual clothing, so it works for now.

But it is not as nice looking as the photo and will just be a temporary piece for us. We moved to a smaller, century old townhouse in the city where there is limited closet/storage space. In the future I will look for a more solid piece of furniture.

product_title: Classic Brands Europa Wood Slat and Metal Platform Bed Frame
review_body:
I plan on moving within a few months and didn't want to invest too much on a new bed frame. So this seemed perfect and had high reviews. But... don't do it.
The first night I slept on it then woke up I realized the middle leg started to tilt. I figured I didn't tighten it enough (which is really difficult with the type of screws it uses anyway) so I tightened it thinking it would be okay. It was NOT OKAY! Every time I sat on the bed the leg would shift, every morning I would have to readjust. The plastic corners kept coming out of place. This bed was a mess!
I was going to deal with a few months of tilting legs but then right before laying down I sat on the bed and the wooden slats slipped out of their slots and down I went. I fixed it even though all I wanted to do was sleep, but I was anxious all night that the bed was going to crumble beneath me.
Sure enough, within a week, I was asleep and then the slats came loose again and the mattress dipped down.
The next morning I dismantled everything, packed it up, and scheduled a time for return and refund.
NOT WORTH THE HASSLE!
