product_title: Signature Design by Ashley Callum Chairside End Table
review_headline: Very happy after a long search
review_body:
I had been looking around for a more contemporary replacement for a pair of glass & ‘brass’ end tables I’d had around since the 80’s, which were looking very sad. I liked the clean lines and interesting design and thought that I’d try one. The price seemed very good and if there was something wrong with it I could return it without too much trouble. After receiving and assembling the first one I ordered a second one the next day.

The material is a decent veneer on a fairly heavy substrate. Completely assembled, it has a good weight and will not topple easily, which is a good thing since I have cats. It comes well packaged and each piece is clearly marked corresponding to the numbering in the assembly instructions. The instructions are all graphic and easy to follow. The one little nit that I have to pick is that the screws, or bolts, used in the assembly have round heads and are designed for use with a small Allen wrench, which is supplied. I found the fit of the Allen wrench into the head of each bolt to be a bit problematic and made for slow going so I used a small pair of pliers to more quickly grasp and turn the bolts into place. I would save the Allen wrench for the last couple of turns in order to torque each bolt down tightly. In all, it took about an hour to assemble the first table, maybe about 40 minutes for the second one. It also helps if you pre-treat the bolts and their slots with a bit of lubricant like WD40.

It’s not built to the tolerances of, say, Thomasville or Henredon but once it’s together it’s very solid and tight, looks very good and at a good price. I would buy another if I needed one and can recommend this unit based on my experiences.

product_title: Legacy Decor Soild Wood Bookshelf
review_body: I love the bookcase.  HOWEVER -- and a BIG HOWEVER, the screws that were included weren't correct.  I assembled the bookcase as I went along, so I didn't realize the mistake until only the top was left to attach.  Not wanting to undo my assembly, and thinking that I could get four screws, I threw away the packing -- I mean four screws are so much smaller and lighter than the bookcase, right?  Ha!  I'm not sure which utopia I thought I was in.  The seller won't replace the screws because I obtained the bookcase through Amazon and not through them.  Another thought:  the screws become tight at different depths so that some are quite recessed and other are flush w/the surface of the wood.  The recessed screws are unsightly, but I don't think my students will notice.  The bookcase will serve the purpose for which I bought it, so I will look at a couple of local hardware stores for replacements or buy some strong wood glue.  I will not ever buy again from this seller again either directly or through Amazon because of their unwillingness to correct a problem created by a mistake that was theirs

product_title: Headrest for Herman Miller Aeron Chair by Engineered Now
review_headline: Great! (Once I Macgyvered it a bit)
review_body:
I have a Herman Miller Areon Chair size A (for us shorties!) and this is just too lose. to tighten it enough with the alan wrench is impossible because the bolt hits the plastic and can't go any farther. because of this, it won't just completely fall off, but it can easily slide to the side and then fall off. So my solution was to take 2 XL binder clips and put them on either side to keep if from sliding to the side. So now it won't slide off, but it jiggles loundly when i move my chair because it's not tight.. so then i took a small stack of post its and put it in between the clamp on the headrest and my chair so it would be tight. since doing that, it's perfect! (this possibly could have been solved with a shorter bolt, but I work in an office.. with office supplies.. so i went that route)

it adjusts perfectly to where i want it, (forward/back, up/down, tilt) I can easily re-adjust it if i'm sitting a little different during the day, and it looks like it came with my chair. I'm thinking it's probably made for the standard size B chair so maybe that's why mine was lose? who knows. but i do love it.

It's press board with a laminate, so I shouldn't be terribly surprised, but I wanted to let others know exactly what they're getting. My computer runs a little hot and has to have an extra fan to ventilate it inside the cabinet. As a result of that heat, the adhesive between the press board and the laminated surface on the front of the shelf has denatured and come up. Everything fits together well over all, and I'm happy with it. Lots of working space for my personal computer with dual monitors and either an iPad or laptop on the other side.

product_title: LEGGET AND PLATT Performance Adjustable Bed Base, Wireless, Massage, Wall Hugger, S-Cape, King
review_headline: The worst $2,000 ever spent, worthless customer service, terrible technology - do NOT buy if you expect it to work!!!!!
review_body: If I could give this less than 1 star, I would.  We have owned this base for 2 years, this month.  In that two years, EVERY SINGLE COMPONENT of this base has been replaced TWICE.  Yes, you've read that correctly, TWICE.  We have called L&P the manufacturer of this bed no fewer than 30x in the two years, to have them walk us through the ridiculously awkward, cumbersome and overly complicated process of programming the remotes to operate the bed because it continuously loses programming making the bed non-functional.  We purchased the bed from a local, well respected, chain mattress company.  However, after multiple warranty calls by the L&P repair personnel without permanent fixes to the constant loss of programing and failures, we told L&P that we wanted our money back.  No other product we've ever owned, has been this unreliable and problematic.  The supervisor at L&P told us to try one more exchange and if that didn't work, they would investigate a refund for us.  We've now had 3 more calls to customer service for reprogramming and failures.  On our last attempt, not fewer than 3 days ago, the Customer Service rep was not only rude when I asked to be finally provided the refund we were promised, but she became combative, stating that "Leggett and Platt didn't get our money."  I responded by reminding her that, in fact, they did - just not directly, so it shouldn't matter - they can just refund the money to the retailer who is then able to provide us a credit to purchase another platform that works.  She refused, but I insisted that she have a supervisor contact me subsequent to another reprogram session.  As yet, that call has yet to be received.  Meanwhile, the bed has now failed catastrophically, almost leaving my disabled wife without a bed - it failed in an almost upright position and wouldn't respond to any attempts to lower, including the emergency lower buttons on the motor controls themselves.  Now, after an hour of call attempts to customer service, they are unreachable, with a message stating "They are experiencing extremely high call volume and to call back later" at which point they hang up.  STAY AWAY FROM THIS COMPANY - THEY ARE AWFUL AND THEIR DESIGNS ARE UNRELIABLE, ANTIQUATED AND TERRIBLE.  This is NOT $2,000 worth of technology or service.e, they are unreachable, with a message stating "They are experiencing extremely high call volume and to call back later" at which point they hang up.  STAY AWAY FROM THIS COMPANY - THEY ARE AWFUL AND THEIR DESIGNS ARE UNRELIABLE, ANTIQUATED AND TERRIBLE.  This is NOT $2,000 worth of technology or service.

product_title: Mylex 47.5 Inch Bookcase
review_headline: Inconsistent quality, 1st one was great, 2nd and 3rd inferior
review_body: The first shelf I received was pretty good. The delivery was super quick. I received the item about three days after I ordered it (total $36 and free shipping). The instructions were fairly simple but screwing by hand required a bit of force for someone my size. The back is made out of cardboard but I didn't mind since the price was low. I also wanted a book shelf that wasn't too heavy but was sturdy, so something in the 35-45lbs range. This fit the description. Since I liked the first one, I ordered two more, especially since the price dropped to $30 with free shipping. I probably shouldn't have however. The second shelf was damaged/dented along an edge (minor damage but noticeable). The hole slots for the screws were much messier and the cardboard back wasn't wide enough to nail it securely against the wood. The board needed to be a good 1/2" wider. I had to hammer in the nail slanted towards the edge to that it wouldn't show through from the back of the shelf. Also one of the nails was missing for both the 2nd and 3rd shelves, but this wasn't a big deal since I had my own nails.

product_title: Flash Furniture Mid-Back Swivel Task Chair with Flip-Up Arms
review_body: Received the chair yesterday. At first, the chair felt comfortable for the latter half of the day. The second day I noticed pain from the sciatic nerve. I thought maybe it was just my nerve so I swapped chairs and within an hour it went away. I tried using the chair again and it came back. From what I noticed, the cushion flattens out extremely quick. You are left sitting on the plastic. I saw a comment on here from a 275lb guy and thought this was the chair for me. I'm 230, 6-2 and this chair is not comfortable. If you are below 200lb, it may be great for you but anyone over 6' will tower in this chair and anyone around my weight will bottom out on the plastic. I'm returning it and looking for a better chair.

I had help from my husband, but you might be able to put this together by yourself if you're really handy.  I was able to fit my crockpot and breadmaker on the bottom shelves, but I'm not sure I would put anything suuuuuper heavy on the top shelves.  Right now, I've got my cookbooks on one of the top shelves, and some plants on the other.  It looks really great in my kitchen, and the wooden shelf is a nice cherry color.

product_title: Sliding Door Inlaid Glass Mission Multimedia Cabinet (MS-700 Series)
review_headline: Best solution for a large video collection!
review_body: We ended up buying two of these cabinets for our DVD collection, and it was a nice color match to an existing cabinet we were placing them next to. I bought the first one, planning to check out the color match, ease of assembly and quality of materials before buying the second one. However the first one arrived (way ahead of schedule) with damage to one of the back panels, obviously caused by the carrier. It would have been a very difficult part to replace, so I did a satisfactory repair to it myself and once the cabinet was filled the repair isn't visible. Amazon worked with me to make an adjustment for the damage. The quality of the materials is excellent, with the doors, top and bottom being hardwood, and the sides, center piece and shelves being laminated high-density particle board. I used wood glue on all the pegs during assembly and this cabinet is rock solid. When I ordered the second one, it too arrived earlier than the anticipated delivery window, this time without damage. I assembled it in about an hour. As we are only storing DVD and BluRay disks, we only used 12 of the 18 shelves for each cabinet. My only wish is that it had been available in a taller size, but that's just my configuration issue. If you buy it from one of the sellers who have it for about $250 it's a good price.

product_title: Sleep Master 5" MyEuro Foam Mattress
review_body:
This is a fantastic mattress! I got the queen size to use for guests and wow, I was impressed. It's very firm and supportive. Soft enough but not springy. Lightweight but keeps its shape incredibly well. Some have posted that it doesn't even need a box spring on bed with slats such as metal bunk beds. I haven't tried that myself but it is plenty thick. The package is pretty amazing it come vacuum stuffed into a bag. I was able to work it out of the draw string bag without ripping the bag (I was hoping to reuse it). But after I let the air in, it expanded to impressive proportions, so there is no humanly possible way to get it back in. (I guess I just need another purpose for the bag.). I will probably get a mattress bag for it from the sleep shop when I move next. Until then, my guests and I are enjoying this mattress!

5 Stars!

Then the screws that mount the metal and wood to the bottom of the mailbox are way to long so we had to go buy the right one of those. Then the bolts to mount the mailbox to the stand are just tightening bolts and the thread on the stand stripped after about 5 turns. So we are going to have to drill holes in the top of the stand to make it more sturdy. Honestly its not worth $200 but is does look nice now that its up.

review_headline: The best bed I've ever slept on!
review_body: Let me start this review off by saying that this is the first "new" mattress I've ever owned because my parents have always been in the lodging business so I've only gotten box springs that were in storage. I also travel a lot so I've spent a lot of time on different beds around the world from pull-out couches to $7,000 tempur-pedic GrandBed. I ordered the full size of this bed for $379.00 it arrived in about 4 days in a large round box. Let me also mention that when it was delivered I was not at home so it sat in the pouring faint for almost 2 hours. When I came home I was afraid that my new bed was ruined from the rain. But, pleasantly to my surprise it was only the box and a little bit of the strong outer plastic that was wet. When I fend through 2 more layers of strong vacuum sealed plastic I laid it downstairs and let it air out for a little under 24 hour. Then I brought it upstairs at laid on it. It was firmer than I expected and was kind of pissed that they would sell such a firm mattress. But, after about a week it softened up a lot and now almost a month after its to a very good firmness. I would highly recommend this bed to everyone!

product_title: Artesia TV Stand
review_body:
It’s nice to have choices when it comes to TV stands. A quick search on Amazon reveals at least 285 pages. With so many options, now one has to decide on the color, what materials it’s made out of, will it fit in the consigned area? Is within my budget? And are replacement parts easy to acquire if missing or broken? Oy Vey!

My journey from start to finish was not without several annoying bumps along the way. As all the parts were laid out in advance to make sure nothing was missing, the first roadblock happened. The two rear back braces or panels (part #7) were missing. A call to the company was made (which had a call center in California), and the representative was very apologetic and said he would have replacements sent right away at no cost. If they truly were sorry they would have FED-EX’d them overnight or the very least 2nd day air. Five business days later the missing pieces arrived and assemby of the unit began.

And then the second road block happened. The Allen screws used to bolt the top glass to the supporting frame were too short. The size given was ¼ x ¾ inch, when it should have been ¼ x 1 inch. With the size included in the box, the bolts would only rotate into its designated holes at around 3 or 4 thread rotations. This could pose a potential hazard that could cause damage to the TV or person if bumped or moved. A trip to the local Lowes and Home Depot hardware stores did not stock what was needed, but luckily there happen to be a specialized nuts and bolts shop several miles away that had what was needed for a few dollars.

A few minor things to point out; the instruction illustrations are very small, and larger print would have been nice. The two bottom glass shelves use suction cups to hold them in place, so be careful to ensure the shelves are flush with the back braces before lying against the suction cups. They are near impossible to remove. Having two people to assemble this unit makes constructing it much easier.

In all, assembly time was fairly quick, taking into account breaks and interruptions. About 1-2 hrs. The Studio Designs 50701 Calico Designs Artesia TV Stand 58-Inch is good fit for the area I’m using it in, and with its sleek/modern upscale look for around $200.00 makes a nice addition to any home.time was fairly quick, taking into account breaks and interruptions. About 1-2 hrs. The Studio Designs 50701 Calico Designs Artesia TV Stand 58-Inch is good fit for the area I’m using it in, and with its sleek/modern upscale look for around $200.00 makes a nice addition to any home.

product_title: Crown Mark Pierce Side Table
review_body:
We have been using this as a little table for a keyboard and mouse for our kids to temporarily use a computer for the past couple of months. Previously, I had a cheap side table that was half the width (same depth) but it wasn't long enough for the keyboard itself so we couldn't put the mouse on there easily. This particular table ended up absolutely perfect for this use. It's pretty sturdy because the kids put their feet on the bottom shelf all the time and sometimes stand on it. My kids are young and light, so kids that are older could possibly break the bottom piece and so could heavy objects. (I fully expect that if my kids don't stop standing on the bottom shelf that it may break at some point.)

Although side tables such as these are not normally made to be used in this fashion, I am completely happy with it. Since we are using it as a desk type replacement, I don't expect it to look extremely professional. The edges of the table have been very easily worn down with very little use so I would never use this later for anything else. However, if it isn't going to be touched a lot then it looks nice enough to display some light objects on it.

The biggest problem we have with this is that not everything lined up correctly. So, we ended up needing to use additional tools that should never have been needed. There are cheaper options out there but not usually at our local stores so this was a good enough option for us.

review_body:
UPDATED REVIEW!
We've had these chairs for 3 months and one is completely broken and another one is cracked. I'm a small girl, there is no reason 90 pounds should cause this to happen. I personally feel we got defective chairs because our other two are holding up wonderfully. It is really unfortunate that our dining area went from high class to now half broken. I am not sure that I will replace these chairs with more alike. I may just get different chairs and keep the remaining two as accent chair in my home.... I don't want to waste any more cash on something that won't even last a year. Very disappointed. 3 months....
Still love them, I just don't know what to do at this point.

-August review-
I can't even find words to explain how amazing these chairs are! For starters- shipping was WORTH every penny. Usually I only buy big items that ship free. I paid 60 bucks for standard shipping and received the chairs in 3 days (from the time I placed my order to the time they ended up on my doorstep) These chairs are absolutely perfect and the highest quality I've seen for the price. They came throughly packages, with no damages. They make my dining room look absolutely flawless. Surprisingly comfortable for being acrylic! They fit both my husbands and my body perfectly. Great addition to our home. I purchased these because I thought they'd be super easy to clean with our two children, and yet still fit my high-end taste. I was totally right. Highly recommend these chairs to anyone, absolutely anyone. They are perfect!

product_title: Black Vasari Corner Flat Panel Plasma / LCD TV Console
review_headline: Worth the effort to put it together
review_body:
Took me about 2 hours to put this together, mainly because I really struggled to get the front panel of the top piece to connect to the top. The plastic "pegs" that are used to connect them are SUPER hard to push into the peg holes provided! That part alone took me 20 minutes, and even still, the two pieces are not flush together. I get that they don't want it to fall out, but it shouldn't be THAT hard to put the two pieces together! Make sure you read the directions carefully and note which sides of the pieces are the front vs the back!

Other than that, this is the PERFECT corner unit. Plenty of storage space, and our 40' TV fits beautifully on it :)

product_title: William's Home Furnishing Rocking Chair
review_headline: You get what you pay for...
review_body: 5 stars for comfort...2 for sloppy manufacturing, packing and directions. The chair took way longer to assemble than it should have because there were no written directions, only a hard to see parts' drawing. This chair should have been better protected in its shipping box because the tips of both rocker legs were smashed. The fabric was poorly attached to the base of the seat and back with fraying pieces and lose staples. The long and short is that you get what you pay for and I bought the cheapest of the offerings for the same chair. I will sand the rocker tips and already removed the staples. The frayed fabric is hidden. I really like sitting in this chair because I need a firm back and seat. So I will keep it as it is hidden in a back TV room. You get what you pay for and this is all I wanted to pay.

It fits lots of toys, more than I expected being that it is fairly shallow in depth but the length makes up for it.  I feel it is very sturdy to sit on and could withstand a fair amount of weight no problem.  I would not trust heavy items in the storage part as the bottom is pretty flimsy but if you want a trunk for clothes, linens or toys it is just fine.  Other reviews said the feet were plastic but mine are wood cut from blocks and stained.  The method of attachment for the legs is good and solid, I have no problems sliding my bench around on the floor but I do have it on finished concrete not carpet.  The color is nice, exactly what I expected from the pictures, dark but still brown and looks great with my dark walnut furniture.  I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 because of the fact that it is pleather, I knew that when ordering and is what i wanted as I was not looking to buy a piece to last decades but more like 4 or 5 years.  I think by the look and feel of it I can expect that kind of life out of it as long as it is well cared for before it starts to look like a cheap piece of furniture.  Overall I am very happy with this bench and recommend it.

product_title: Camden County Five Shelf Bookcase
review_headline: sturdy, and attractive bookcase for something that's made of ...
review_body: This is a good-sized, affordable, sturdy, and attractive bookcase for something that's made of particle board. However, when I opened the box, there were three damaged pieces. Two shelves had about 1 inch sections of the "wood-toned" coating scraped off the edges. One piece had a bigger chunk missing. Since it would have been a lot of trouble to return something so huge and heavy (and it's necessary to destroy the box to open it), I put it together anyway. It was easy to assemble - about half an hour for a mom with help from a 14-year-old boy, only a screwdriver and hammer needed. The prior reviewer complained about three unsightly holes on the underside of the top of the bookcase. The bag of parts includes three plastic plug/covers. Once you install those, the holes are not a problem.

product_title: Alera Merix Series Mesh Big/Tall Mid-Back Swivel/Tilt Chair - Black
review_headline: Keeps Me Free of Sore Hips!
review_body:
My sore hips from my other bariatric office chair are already feeling better using this chair. I'm not great at putting things together, but this was very easy. The only trick was that you need to not tighten the bottom plate until after you slip the chair back piece under it. If you do tighten it, the metal for the back won't fit under. Not a big deal...but since the directions are pictures only it's easy to miss for novice assemblers like me.

I'm SOOOO excited that this chair is allowing me to sit for long lengths of time already without my hips hurting. It sits flat so I don't feel thrown-forward, the "bounce" is good (especially for a heavy person) and time will tell if it holds-up...but if it doesn't, I'll amend my review. So far it's great and I'm glad I read the reviews on all of the chairs as this one had consistently better reviews than the other chairs in it's category, and they seem well-deserved at this point!

review_headline: Seems like a sturdy stand for my 40inch lcd
review_body: Seems like a sturdy stand for my 40inch lcd. They need to better package. The two polls holding up the TV has scratches on it most likely from vibrations during shipment. Looks like they packaged the poles within the bottom portion of the stand which had sharp edges. There was a sort of plastic strip on the sharp edges but it looks like that came undone during shipping so it caused the scratches on the poles. Also according to the instructions, the component tray stand has bracket mounts that clamps on to the lower portion of the poles with bolts. The bolts were not long enough so you can only mount it on the upper portion of the poles which were slightly thinner. The stand rolls well and is stable.

review_body: Simply brilliant.  I assembled this unit solo and the instructions were well written and easy to understand (unlike those from the yellow and blue, big box retailer ;-)  The casters make this a truly functional piece of furniture, The way it transforms from a credenza/console looking table to a craft table is what I love the most and had to have it.  The wood finish is of excellent quality and the shelves and door bins are more than adequate and strong.  I sew regularly/daily so mine is more open than closed. review_body: I recently decided to re-decorate my entire bedroom. I searched high and low for an affordable, open faced, white nightstand, and I finally found this one. product_title: Arctic Dreams 10" Cooling Gel Mattress Made in the USA
review_body: After trying almost every other mattress available out there, I decided to give this Arctic Dreams Memory Foam mattress a try. I must say it is the most comfortable bed I have slept on yet. Not to mention the cheapest! We have been through Sertas, Simmons, and even had a Sleep Number bed that we spent hundreds of dollars on but they all hurt our backs. This is the first memory foam mattress we have purchased and I am so glad we did. I wish we would have found this years ago. It arrived by FedEx in a large box. It was vacuum sealed and rolled up. I couldn't believe a queen mattress fit inside such a small box but it was very heavy. After I placed it on my bed and started unrolling and cutting plastic, it started taking shape. Within ten minutes, it was in full form. It is like sleeping on a cloud. You cannot tell when the other person is moving in bed and there are no springs to make noise. Even though I can't see where there is any cooling effect, it really is an amazing mattress. I would highly recommend this mattress to anyone! I received this product in exchange for my unbiased opinions.

product_title: Zinus Viscolatex 10-Inch Memory Foam Mattress
review_body:
I have not tried out a memory foam mattress in years. The last time that I did I was left with a not so favorable impression of them. I remember it feeling more like lying on wet sand than a bed. I was pleasantly surprised by this Zinus viscolatex foam mattress.

We got the twin size for a guest room (and child's use in future). It arrived compressed and rolled in a 18"x18"x41" box (see photo). After unpacking and unrolling I expected a strong off-gassing odor, but that was not the case. There was very little odor and it was not really unpleasant since the foam in this mattress is infused with green tea and coal. It seemed to expand to full depth pretty quickly but waited a day before trying it out anyway. In the meantime, I noticed that the mattress is covered in an attractive looking cover. The cover is zippered and is made of three different materials for the bottom, sides and top. It protects and keeps the foam clean sans sheets and makes the mattress look good right out of the box.

The mattress is on the firmer side while still being comfortable. As I indicated, when I first tried it I was impressed with it because it felt better than I was expecting since I always much preferred spring mattresses. This Zinus mattress felt closer to the feeling of a spring mattress than any other foam mattresses that I had tried in the past. It provides good support and seems to have a slight bit of bounciness to it. We've already had an overnight guest sleep on it (two days after receiving letting it fully expand) who sleeps on a memory foam at home. She said that this mattress was more comfortable than her own and enjoyed a comfortable night's sleep.

As with every foam mattress, there is very little support on it's edges. If you sit or lie on the edge, you will sink in deep, as expected.

Overall this Zinus mattress represents a very good value and offers a lot of convenience for a mattress purchase. Even as a spring mattress lover, this is a foam mattress that I could sleep on. The twin size that I have would be an excellent choice for a child's room or small guest room.ress lover, this is a foam mattress that I could sleep on. The twin size that I have would be an excellent choice for a child's room or small guest room.

product_title: Lang Furniture Special 5-Drawer Chest with Pewter Hardware with Roller Glides, 16 by 24 by 44-Inch, Black
review_body:
Not sure how/why this got such good reviews from other people. But this thing showed up basically in pieces. Scratches on every surface. Broken rails, drawers, bottom fascia. And honestly I would just blame FedEx or whatever for damaging it, but the box wasn't damaged. Then I saw the tiny little staples they use for attaching the drawer rails to the inside of the unit. These staples are a half a step up from regular staples you'd use to attach two pieces of paper together. I would be interested in hearing the opinions a year or two down the road from all the 5-star review folks. I would bet my bank account that something broke on this thing. I really wanted to believe that I could buy a decent piece of furniture that is made in America for under $150... unfortunately I was wrong.
I brought it back to UPS today, expecting my refund soon.

It's kind of like a box of chocolates with this bed, you never know what you're gonna get, cause they don't tell you what color! So if you like surprises order this bed! Other than the colors being completely off, the bed seemed to good enough quality, except the slats are flimsy and seriosuly rest in a free standing piece of wood with 3 support legs ... It's the strangest piece of furniture I've ever seen. Worse than any flimsy Ikea piece. The bed however, does not crack and creak like our old one after my dad put it together wrong, so it will suffice. We now have a bed with a black headboard and all LILAC/purple sides. It's like an 80s bed  from the Earth Girls Are Easy set. Buyer beware, but so far it's doing its job, and we are still alive.

product_title: Elegant Home Fashion Vera 2-Door Floor Cabinet
review_headline: Mediocre quality, but attractive if you can use it
review_body:
Mine came with a nasty gash on one side of the top even though there was no damage to the packaging. This was clearly a defect that it left the factory with. But we needed it in a hurry and it was far too impractical to repack it for return, so we painted over the defect and just made do.

The main problem is poor construction quality. The design is actually quite attractive and it's a nice, functional piece. But the tolerances aren't wonderful (a notch or two below typical IKEA construction) and there's very good chance that you won't be able to assemble it correctly, whether because of the poor tolerances or a missing or defective part.

At this level of quality, I feel that the piece is overpriced.

product_title: Sleep Master MyEuro Smartbase/Wooden Slats Mattress Foundation
review_headline: Good quality, even if a little utilitarian looking.
review_body:
I put together this frame by myself, it probably took close to an hour going pretty steady. It Was not difficult to assemble, there are just a lot of pieces. It came with everything needed to assemble (just an Allen wrench). I was able to wedge all the slats into the plastic ends without an trouble and without a tool. Overall it was pretty straightforward.

We are using this as a base under a 9" memory foam mattress which it works well for. The height clearance allows us to store rolling suitcases underneath it. I also like that it is only as wide and long as the actual mattress so it saves space in our small room.

The base does seem very stable even with both of us moving around, and we aren't light people. One leg or area has a very slight creak to it but it's very slight and only on one corner. I could probably apply some oil and stop it.

My only complaint with the base is it's not particularly visually appealing, but then I knew that from pictures before ordering. It is a very basic frame. Also because of some of the legs being located in the middle of the length of the frame instead of at the corners I have stubbed my toes on them. The edges are rounded and smooth so it wasn't too bad, but all the same the legs are right there at the edge of the bed just waiting for my sad toes.

product_title: DreamFoam Mattress Ultimate Dreams Latex Mattress
review_headline: Two inches may not seem like a lot
review_body:
The mattress does not match up to its description. I ordered a queen mattress, the dimensions of which are listed as 60" by 80". The mattress, fully unfolded and with plenty of time to expand, measures true in length, but the width measures slightly less than 58". Two inches may not seem like a lot, but it is definitely noticeable. The bed looks and feels smaller than a standard queen. Because the mattress is too narrow, it does not fill out the bed frame. I know the mattress had time to properly expand because right after I set the bed up, my wife and I left for a two week vacation.

On the positive side, it is comfortable, made in the USA, convenient and seems to be constructed well. I only wish the product details had been accurate.

product_title: Heritage Hill Five Shelf Open Bookcase 71" H
review_headline: Very pleasant to build, if you are Ramsey Snow
review_body:
This was a very pleasant build - if your definition of pleasant is the seventh circle of hell.
Firstly, all the screws and small bits came in one bag. Not a good start, but hey all the parts were there.
Secondly, the directions are absolutely terrible. it does not differentiate from which side is the front or back, so it is up to you to find out to see where the holes are in order to fit the front boarder frames.
That is of course if the "front" holes were consistent between parts.... such the bottom and the middle shelves that you build into the frame for structural integrity, had one set of holes facing one way and another the other way... there is no permutation of front and back switch upside down inside out that would let me install this thing correctly according to the directions.
Fourthly, the parts themselves are not precise. there are gaps and there are holes that are not even alighted with each other.
Fifthly, i had to drill my own holes on one of the basis for the two sides because IT WAS MISSING HOLES. so much for tool less
Sixthly, these screws are coated in so much crap my magnetic screwdrivers would not hold on to them/
Finally, related to the sixth these screws strip so easily you would be able to find them in Magic Mike XXL

I hope who ever made the instructions gets paper cuts the rest of their lives every time they touch paper.

product_title: Queen Size Bed Frame Rail with Headboard & Footboard Attachments 5-legs and Glides
review_body:
I don't generally review products, but based on the other reviews I felt that I needed to contribute my experience. When I first received this product, three of the legs were missing. I contacted the seller to indicate that pieces were missing and asked that they send me, in addition to the minuscule piece of paper that vaguely outlined in one image how the parts go together, a more complete list of what I should be looking for in case something else was not included as well. I was referred back to my slip. We received the additional legs, but they differed slightly from the ones originally included. My husband and I put it together this weekend.

First, the instructions continued to be problematic as they aren't actually instructions, simply a picture. The second red flag, after the missing parts and the replacement parts that were slightly different, was that the legs were slightly bent, and the joints seemed very insecure. The third was that the screws bolts that were to hold the middle beam in place barely connected enough to screw. The paint was scratched all over as though it had been returned before. The end beams are connected in the middle with one bracket that doesn't actually secure or screw into them at all, but is simply tightened by an L screw to secure them over lapping. This makes it nearly impossibly to square the frame solidly.

We were skeptical, but in good faith, put our box spring and mattress on top. It was wobbling simply with the weight of the mattress. My very svelte husband sat down and laid back as the joints swayed looking like they were about to snap. We considered trying to lower the feet for a lower center of gravity, but it was clear that it was not the feet that were necessarily insecure but the very cheaply put together joints. We looked underneath and the middle foot was already cocked off to the side. Obviously if jointed properly it shouldn't be able to do that. It would have snapped in two months, which really isn't acceptable and is a safety concern with us expecting a baby soon. Careening and collapsing mattresses aren't exactly child safe.

I just felt people should be warned about buying this product, and to be wary of which vendor is selling and what their return policy is, as my normally expedient Amazon experience has turned into quite a nuisance in addition to wasted money. I am returning and incurring the cost myself as something this shoddy and unstable is useless to me.

product_title: DynastyMattress New Cool Breeze 12-Inch Gel Memory Foam Mattress
review_headline: I figured worse case it would be a guest bed
review_body: I was hesitant to purchase a mattress via the internet (who in their right mind does THAT?). But I was in crunch mode and had off loaded a mattress we purchased that we were told was a King, (so I purchased sheets, frame bedspread etc) to find out it was a California King. So I needed a new mattress and fast. With the mostly rave reviews, I figured worse case it would be a guest bed. My bed arrived as described in a narrow box looking like a Little Debbie swiss miss roll. My 6 year old and I got it inside and into the bedroom. We followed the instructions and realized we had put it on upside down. It was already filling out as the seals were all removed. So with him guiding the mattress and me doing the heavy lifting, we were able to rotate/flip it. Mind you, I also am recovering from birth and have 3 annoying cats who just had to see what was going on. I figured after that, I had earned a drink. So I finished getting the bed ready with my newly purchased sheets, pillows, bedding etc and slept the best I had in a long time. product_title: Lifetime Contemporary Residential Folding Chair
review_headline: OK for LIGHT DUTY occasional use
review_body:
These are very light duty chairs. I am an engineer, and I can see that these were built to attempt to lower the cost. I would say that these are not worth more than $20 per chair, given that they are very weak riveted connections. They are not built for comfort, as they are completely flat, making them cheaper to manufacture, but also this allows them to fold very flat for storage. These are good for occasional short term use. You will not set these up in an auditorium setting as they are too small and uncomfortable for prolonged use. DO NOT supply these for obese people, as you may end up needing to use your homeowner's insurance if the connections fail. The stated loading of 275 lbs is based upon a static load. If you sit hard onto the chair, or try to stand on the chair to do work (not a safe use of the chair), you may be in for an accident.
Beside all of the aforementioned negatives, these are GREAT for keeping in a closet and taking out when you have a large group of company.

product_title: Extra Large Heavy Duty Office Chair Casters 4" Nylon Twin Wheel - Ideal for Carpet Set of 5
review_headline: My carpet and pad is really thick so these wheels did help after tightening the expansion ring on wheel stem.
review_body:
Well I didn't think they fit but when I took the metal expansion-ring off the end of one, it went right up in socket, was too loose and fell out . That told me the stem would fit and not hurt the socket but to tighten the ring up---rings weren't closed up enough, real loose which 'they' made the stem too wide. After using a pair of channel locks to tighten up ring and put vaseline on both socket and stem, still had to slightly drive them up in socket. Expansion ring still really worked as I hope I don't have to remove them. My carpet and pad is really thick so these wheels did help. I can live with the slight bog down as before COULDN'T MOVE AT ALL I'm 5' 110lbs so maybe not ENOUGH weight to roll chair but it is better.
Company sent them out pronto and good packaging.

The second one assembled has a side to side 12 degree tilt due to the base-hole being off center. After a couple months of use I developed scoliosis and hip disintegration requiring hip replacement surgery. During the operation they discovered I'd developed severe flat-ass-itia. This is caused from putting a disproportionate amount of weight on my left buttock. I'd just completed my collagen injection therapy when the tragic knee-hitting-chin accident mentioned above occurred.

Seriously, these are very horrible chairs. The chairs are as stated above, but I didn't really lose teeth, develop scoliosis, endure collagen injections in my ass, have my hip replaced, or get stuck for 11 days. Everything else is true . . . well I'm not 6'10" either.

review_headline: Decent mattress, especially for the price
review_body:
I ordered this mattress in Queen size, after reading about 200 or more various mattress reviews, as I had previously ordered the twin size for my daughter's bed, and was moderately happy with it. And I am moderately happy with this one, too. I made the transition from a memory foam mattress, as I started reading that memory foam can cause back, neck, hip, and shoulder pain, of which I have all. After 6 years on a memory foam and about 5 previous on a major-name number air mattress, it definitely took some getting used to sleeping on it. I also added a plush mattress pad/cover, which is super-soft, but doesn't do much to soften the feel of the mattress itself, and a 2 in memory foam mattress topper, which has helped a lot in the comfort level, especially when first laying down.
Beware of the super-bounciness of this mattress, especially if you're coming off of memory foam, and that the edges don't really have much support, so if you lay too close to the edge, you'll feel like you're about to roll off.

product_title: The Original Gorilla Grip (TM) FELT + RUBBER Area Rug Pad, Made In USA, 2x4, 2x8, 3x5, 4x6, 5x7, 5x8, 6x9, 8x10, 8x11, 9x12, 12x15, Extra Thick, Hypoallergenic, Hard Floor Protector, 20 Year Guarantee
review_headline: Crazy grip strength and amazing quality.
review_body:
So there are many different rug pads online, almost too many to choose from. This was the dilemma that I faced, way to many different options. Want thick, thin, with grip, without grip, green certified, folded or unfolded?

Glad that I went to amazon to find what seems like the prefect pad for me. I have three 8x10 rugs over porcelain tile that needed pads. There were just so many choices and all around the same price point. I ordered what had a fair amount of reviews and this is how i ended up purchasing the gorilla grip brand on rug pads. I ordered the 1/4 inch pad with the latex grip. My inexpensive rugs now feel as though they were thousands of dollars. So plush that i can easily fall asleep on the floor directly.

They do not shed felt, they grip like crazy and provide a really luxurious cushioning effect. The pad came completely rolled wroth no folded edges. Other competitors may say that they come rolled but may have started the roll with a slight fold that is sometimes almost impossible to get rid of and your rig may tend to want to lift on that folded edge. This pad was completely rolled,clean and did not wreak of any harsh chemicals or materials.

If you are thinking about ordering, why haven't you hit the"add to cart" button already? The grip helps the rug stay put. It took three people to get the rug to move to reposition worth the rug pad.

product_title: Merax Racing Chair Home Office Chair
review_headline: Was worried about it being too big. It was fine.
review_body:
I'm 5ft 2in and I was initially worried when ordering this that it would be too big because of the reviews. However that fear was alleviated when I assembled it, it wasn't difficult. The chair is perfectly fine. It makes you sit a bit weird but to be fair, it's ergonomic and I've never had an ergonomic chair. I hope it'll help my posture. The only problem I have is because it's so tall, it makes it so Ican't peddle my little desk peddler so easily, but that's okay, I can still peddle. I just have to scoot forward. However from a sitting along perspective, it's great. I'm an artist and wanted something that would make it so I don't end up with bad posture over hours of drawing. I believe I made the right decision. At my height, the tip top of the chair reaches up so I can lean the back of my head over the neck pillow, or I think it's a neck pillow.
Either way, I guess it's a good size, if you'r nervous as a short person, go to the store and find a high back chair and plop yourself in. It was the same height as all the other high back chairs, maybe a tiny bit shorter because it's designed to fit with the human torso and head. The recline feature is a nice add on too.

While I was assembling it, it seemed sturdy enough, althoug hgetting all the bolts to wiggle into place in harmony with each other took a minute or two at some points. I just didn't want to mess it up.
Either way, tall people thinking it was too big for short people, you were wrong. The only problem is my toes touch the ground and not much else. All the same, I can stand up without doing anything ridiculous.

review_body: We needed a new office chair and decided to purchase this one. Unfortunately, the chair was way too big (height-wise) for the little office room we were using it in. The good news is that their three cats absolutely love this chair and take turns sharing it. The bad news is that the chair is always in use, and it's not them using it!

product_title: Crosley Furniture Cambridge Cuisine Kitchen Island
review_body:
This is frankly the worst built piece of furniture I've purchased in a long time.

The trim around the door and drawer panels was cut too short, so there's a 1/4" gap at all the corners. Those come pre-assembled, so someone built that ugliness and said yep, ship it anyway. You can actually see the gaps in the picture on the product page, so it's not even just this one unit.

The predrilled holes for attaching the drawer face were in the wrong location, so the drawer hit the surrounding frame and wouldn't close. I somewhat fixed that by drilling new pilot holes, but without widening the slot for the drawer bottom as well, it still rubs the top when opening and closing.

The cams for assembling the larger pieces are cheap, and the result is that it's not sturdy and wobbles side to side.

It's a shame, because the legs, top, and side towel rods are all solid, and it could have been great if they spent a few more dollars on the assembly hardware and some quality control. As it is, it's a complete ripoff for what they're charging.

The only reason I'm not taking it apart to send back is that the dimensions are perfect for what I need. If you have some flexibility, buy something from a different manufacturer.

review_headline: Perfect for an eat in kitchen.
review_body:
Great table, works great in my eat in kitchen. I ordered the table only -- I wanted round stools so I bought those separate, but it works great. It was easy to assemble, took me about 35 minutes by myself. It feels nice, seems sturdy, has little tiny leveling feet to eliminate any rocking on an uneven floor. The top seems pretty durable, it's only been a couple weeks but we're not gentle with it and there are no dings or scratches or anything.

I like that it's counter height, makes for a nice alternative to the regular dining room table, lets me roll my kids Boon high chairs right up to the table so they can be part of the meal and not feel separated. Also when the kitchen is full, it makes for a nice alternate work surface.

The base is narrow enough to be able to tuck chairs in, but still solid and sturdy. The top is very much a Cherry color and the base is a very yellow based white, like antiqued or off white which is sometimes deceptive in the pictures. Overall, it's great and I'm happy with it.

My husband took possession of the bed, moving the TV directly in front of it and setting up his game console… I might never see him again. He loves the built-in massage. And a bed with a remote control? He is in hog heaven.

Features that are worth mentioning:
• You can elevate your feet, lift your head and adjust your back all while receiving a gentle body massage
• The Powerlift motor has a weight capacity of up to 700-pounds that can elevate the head up to a 59-degree angle and feet up to a 45-degree angle, providing a wide range of motion.
• Wallhugger technology moves the bed back as the head is elevated
• 4-inch locking caster legs make it easy for vacuuming or moving the base when needed.

product_title: Furniture of America Garrett Twin Over Full Bunk Bed, Gunmetal and Chrome Finish
review_headline: Love this bed! Looks and works great!  Assembly process was awful.
review_body:
Awesome bed. Kids (young teens) love it (a lot)!

Pros:
-- Looks nice
-- Easy to make the bed
-- Not flimsy like many models
-- Feels quite strong

Cons:
-- ASSEMBLY: was a real pain assembling. You may want someone helping you (hint hint). Directions were not so helpful, parts were poorly labeled. I firmly believe that not every bolt hole was cut with precision (needed a hammer in a couple areas).
-- The 4 rods that sit near the top of the "X" shaped legs (each end of bed) are noisy. I simply added silicone (clear) and its now QUITE, no noise, no metal banging and no creaking sounds at all.
-- The small metal rungs on the ladder are not the most pleasant to the feet but our youngest has not complained. Foam would make a nice addition (as long as it does not spin or slip).

Note: while this bed seems to be very strong. I recommend reminding the kids to get in the bed gently because a nice 'impact' (not weight alone) could easily bed the metal mattress supports and then it would be all over. As long as you take care getting in and out (I mean, NO Jumping or hard drops into bed, should have NO issues).

At the end of the day: It looks GREAT!, we all love the design, easy to use, has been the kids favorite bed so far! We would buy again (but would not look forward to assembly (lol)).

product_title: Coaster Furniture Computer Desk - Silver
review_headline: EZ Assembly, functional, just what I wanted
review_body:
Very well packed. If you had parts broken or bent, go after the carrier. There wasn't room in the packaging for any of the components to move around and every corner had a very strong corner cover element. I mean all of the way down the front sides of the box, the back sides, across the front and back tops and across the front and back bottoms.
Assembly was a one person task and took about 30 minutes. While you will need to provide your own Phillips screwdriver, the Hex key and the "wrench" were included.
So, all put together, not a scratch on it, it looks nice, the keyboard shelf operates well, it is small - which is what I wanted, and holds the weight of my HP-AIO okay. I did notice a small problem with shaking that worried me for a bit at first. Then I turned the Blue Oyster Cult down and the shaking went away - and the upstairs neighbors stopped yelling, too.
All in all, this is a great Ittle cart and I feel the price/performance ratio to be very good. The finish is a slightly mottled silver-gray with a little bit of a sheen to it. Actually, I was hoping for a littke less gloss to the finish so I wouldn't have to dust as often...
NOTE: If you have your own tools, use a 1/2" open end wrench - even pliers and a little care would be easier than the included wrench. I also found a ratcheting screwdriver with changeable bits to be a big help as I don't like using hex keys if I can avoid it, so I used a 5/32" hex bit in my ratcheting screwdriver. (A 4mm would have probably been better; I was just being lazy and so I didn't go get my full set of tools.) Unless you have an electric driver/drill with a good clutch, resist the urge to use it, because it's so easy to strip self-assembly furniture. And remember to wait two weeks and then re-check all fasteners. (Standard rule of assembling anything. Not saying I remember...)

product_title: Kore Wobble Office Chair - Standing Desk Stool, Task Chair, Perfect for Active Sitting, Better than a Balance Ball for Office - Everyday - Black Leather-Like
review_body: Fantastic chair!! I already had a sit/stand desk, with a treadmill underneath and no extra room for a typical office chair. I love the treadmill but you can only walk for so long. Typically when I wanted to sit I would go put my laptop on a desk tray and sit on the couch. Well I recently have been going to a chiropractor and learned how bad this has been for me!! My posture is horrible and I'm starting to get a reverse bend in my neck (yikes!). He has something similar in his office for exercises before your adjustment so I thought, why not get something I can use myself everyday. I have been using it for a couple of weeks and I can see a real difference in my posture! It is easy to move so I can walk on the treadmill and put back when I'm ready to sit. I will tell you - it takes a bit of getting used to! My back was sore for the first week with my muscles getting used to the new movements and position, but now I can sit for much longer periods of time and am fine. I highly recommend this for your back health!

review_headline: Well made, easy to assemble, comfortable.  What the Dr. ordered
review_body:
I purchased this couch specifically because my new space is EXTREMELY small, and I wanted something I could cozy up with someone with to watch a movie, but without sacrificing comfort or space to move around in the room. Because it has no arms, all of the width can be used for your tush and that of your companion.

Been using it for a few days, this loveseat has done the trick. Ships almost completely assembled, like 6 screws to attach the headrest to the seat, and then screw on the legs and that's it. The cushions are pretty "cushy", not rigid, so you feel like you are in a living room, not an Ikea catalog (no knock on Ikea stuff, but my experience with small couches and loveseats from there are that they are built for functionality and looks rather than comfort).

Bottom line: at this price ($230 and free shipping, Aug 2015), I would certainly purchase this again and get a 2nd one if I had the space.

product_title: Crosley Furniture Brennan Entryway Storage Bench and Hanging Shelf Set - White
review_headline: Good Product and Value but Requires Extra Work
review_body:
I selected this model over a few other similar Entryway Shelves available on Amazon. It was not the cheapest option, but I have found in my experience with "do it yourself" assembly furniture, the material used is very important to the quality. This one is hard wood (and quite heavy, read more about potential issues hanging it later), which I felt would be worth the extra money.

Overall building it was quite easy, however I did encounter a few problems. Many of the Philips head locking anchors to construct it would not tighten down and kept falling out of their holes. Because of this I used some clear caulking to hold them in place once tightened down. The packaging includes 3M caps which go over the screws, so the caulking doesn't show. Even with this a few of the anchors didn't hold very tight so there were gaps showing between the top piece and shelves. For this I used some white caulking to fill in the gaps and it looks great!

Other reviews mentioned the weight being a problem. The kit comes with plastic anchors designed to hang it from drywall. As others mention, they are NOT strong enough and I would recommend instead using EZ Ancors (which are metal and press from the back on the drwall) to keep it braced to the wall better:

http://www.homedepot.com/p/E-Z-Ancor-Toggle-Lock-100-lb-2-1-2-in-Phillips-Zinc-Plated-Alloy-Flat-Head-Self-Drilling-Drywall-Anchors-2-Pack-10006/100111355

So again, it is very heavy, however I did hang it by myself. What I did was trace the outline of the shelf and ledge bar on a large piece of paper. I marked where the screw holes would be, then hung the paper on the wall level and marked the holes in the wall. I screwed in the metal anchors, lifted it by myself and screwed in the anchors one at a time. It looks great, but it does take a fair amount of work. If you are up for doing a little extra work and are handy it could be a great choice. Otherwise, there may be better options.

product_title: Skyline Furniture Velvet Tufted Full Wingback Headboard, Peacock
review_headline: I ordered this headboard for my new house. The ...
review_body:
I ordered this headboard for my new house. The first time I ordered this, it was sitting on my front porch of the house that I have not taken possession yet, I had to pay a mover to store it for me for 2 weeks until I moved in. Keep in mind, The description says it usually takes 3-5 weeks to ship. I have now paid 150 dollars in storage and pickup fee for this item that was "left on the front porch". Since I had a storage unit, I decided to bring a few boxes out so my friends did not have to bust there backs helping me move on Sep. 1. When I looked at the item, I discovered that it was NOT what was pictured, but a flat headboard, NOT wingbacked!
Now, I have a replacement headboard that is coming TOMORROW! Another 100 dollars in moving fees and storage and my confidence that it will be the one in the picture is LOW to say the least. So far, this headboard has cost me 250 dollars in storage and pickup fees. Beware when ordering this item! it will be on your porch the next day and might not even be the one you ordered.

product_title: Altra Dietz Laptop Computer Cart
review_headline: Great for my needs, not perfect for extended typing.
review_body:
Update: Fixed the wobble: I found a board in the shed about the width of the other leg, cut one end at the same angle as the desk, painted it cherry and bam! No more wobble at all.
I read all the negative reviews and though they do have a point, but for my use, this works, and I like it. If it doesn't hold up over time I'll update my review.
Pros:
*price is right
*easy assembly
*looks nice
*Allows me to adjust my chair high enough that my legs are at a 90 degree fold which is much more comfortable than having chair too low at my regular desk.
*Having my screen at eye level and tilted really helps my neck, especially since I can't type without looking at the keyboard.
Cons:
*Yes, a little wobbly
*not easy to adjust height if you will regularly want to do so.

To address some of the wobble concerns, the individual components are sturdy, where the desk part slips into the base is where the wobble comes from. I took a plastic "wobble wedge" (available on Amazon) and secured it in the gap, not a perfect fix, but improved the situation. Use real tools to tighten all the bolts and screws, not the tools included in package.
I also used a common plastic door jam to wedge under the uneven wheel.
I do data entry on a calendar, I type for 30 seconds at a time in between calls. When my hands are on the computer, I try to keep the heels of my hands steady, too much hand motion will create a slight wobble. If you are using this for a business where you type long emails or are a student writing papers, you might want to invest in something sturdier. I've seen ones in stores for $130 that are no better than this one.

There are a couple areas where the finish has chipped away and the brown/yellow particle board underneath were showing. Depending on where these are, you could probably get these pieces replaced if you were so inclined. Too much work for use given I purchased this for my kids' room at the cabin and wasn't expecting anything fancy. The drawer runners are plastic, but they seem to work okay. The back of the cabinet is a thin flimsy piece you nail on the back, which is typical for this particle board furniture. If you are expecting a typical made-in-china product with some small flaws you will be happy with your purchase. If you are expecting a nice piece that looks like white painted wooden furniture, you will not be happy with your purchase.

This was a perfect in between. Also I was very concerned with having the memory foam get hot but it hasn't been a big problem, seems just like a normal spring bed temperature. I have slept on it now for 2 months and everything seems still good. It may be a little soft for my liking just because I am used to firm beds but still very comfortable! My boyfriend and I sleep on it and it has not sank or anything. He is about 180 lbs and I am 135 lbs. It does sink when you sit on the edge of the bed however. product_title: Harbor View 5-Drawer Chest
review_headline: 1 - It arrived early and in good shape 2 - it is not solid wood
review_body:
I was very worried about ordering this chest of drawers due to the price being so low, but the dimensions were exactly what we needed to fit in a nook in the bedroom. I ordered and crossed my fingers.

1 - It arrived early and in good shape
2 - it is not solid wood, and you should not expect it to be for $230. I actually found the quality to be well above average for this price point.
3 - It takes a long time to assemble and is quite heavy. BUT, the instructions were good and clear. And the product (for me) went together without any odd gaps or broken pieces. Definitely assemble this on carpet or a rug, and vacuum first as to not scratch the finish.
4 - It looks good and fits. Comparable products in solid wood were in the $700 range at a minimum, so I feel like this was a pretty good value.

So, if you are on a budget and don't mind spending a few hours putting it together, I think this is a decent piece of furniture at a low price. And that makes me happy.

product_title: Dorel Home Products Full Loft Bed
review_body: For the price you cannot do better.  It took me and a friend about 4 hours to put together (but we qualify as senior citizens).  The instructions are easy and I will say what has been said before a.) make sure you read the instructions all the way before you begin, and b) do not tighten the screws tight until you are done.  We had to loosen a few times so things would line up before it sunk in.  My ceiling is 8 ft and it works.  I cannot sit up on bed, but plenty of room when laying down.  I put an 8 in mattress on it and it sleeps like a dream.  I have my computer desk, printer, table and chest in the space under the bed and have plenty of room.  I worried the finish would scratch but it is solid and sturdy and not a problem.  The bed does wobble when you climb ladder.  I am sure it could be braced if it bothers you, but it is more of a sway, no feeling of not being solid.  I did put the foam on the ladder to pad (it would hurt to climb without it) and I have a small step stool for last step (otherwise the ladder is a little too straight for balance).  Those two problems and work arounds are my only complaints.  And, for space saving I don't think you want the ladder sticking out in the room.

product_title: Dream Pro Restore Gel-Infused Memory Foam Mattress
review_body:
I’ve had my Dream Pro mattress for a week now, and I think I can now safely give it two thumbs up! This is my first foam mattress, so I had some hesitation adopting this new technology. My previous mattress was an expensive box-spring that was about eight years old, and I could no longer get an uninterrupted night’s sleep on it, tossing and turning due to the discomfort from pressure points. (hip, knee, shoulder). The foam does take some getting used to, as it’s a different “feel.” There’s no springiness to it, it’s more of a settling-in sensation. It’s firm, and then the mattress conforms to your shape. As a result, there’s less moving around trying to find a comfortable position; the mattress adjusts its comfort to your position. The other nice thing is that I can hardly tell if my wife is moving. It doesn’t transmit motion like a conventional mattress.
The deciding factor, though, is that in the morning, I don’t want to get out of bed! I’m so comfortable and cozy that I’m tempted to hit that snooze button, rather than leave my bed. I’m very happy that I got my Dream Pro!

review_body: Outstanding desk! The wood desk top is very sturdy which I loved. I was worried it would have been light and weak. I plan on finding a stand to put three monitors on it, and will let others know how that goes, but for now I have a 29 inch LG and it works great. I love the cup holder which can be moved to any leg. Speaker mounts are nice, keeping them off the desk and out of the way. I don't know who still buys cd's anymore. I guess I could use the cad rack for the occasional dvd I buy, but I could do without that part. Love the controller and headset mounts. The drawer is a basket and has a small container for small stuff like pens and whatnot. The charging station on the left will hold three large phones, or one large tablet. Underneath and on the back of the desk is a basket you can use for your surge protector. It will not hold larger battery backup units. All in all a good desk for a gaming computer. Even has plenty of room for school work or being an adult and looking at bills. Perfect for college students. But seriously folks, it's got a cup holder! Murica.

product_title: Rolland Office Chair Gas Lift Cylinder – Universal Size Fit All - Heavy Duty
review_body:
On September 3, 2013, I purchased the Lexmod Edge Office chair here on amazon ( http://amzn.com/B005WVID9M ). Within about six to eight months, the chair started sinking on me - sitting there, the gas cylinder would just drop an inch or so, then again a little while later, until it bottomed out. The chair was cheap, but it still was annoying that it couldn't go a year without a fairly significant functional problem. I finally gave in and looked here on amazon for a replacement gas lift cylinder.

I purchased this cylinder August 5, 2014. Just a bit over a year ago. I waited this long so that I could really see if this was of good quality or not. I can say that it has never once faltered. I can set the chair at whatever height I like, and it'll stay there, reliably.

I'm really pleased. The price is very low, and the quality is very high. Impossible to beat that combination.

product_title: Cosco Hazel Kids 4 Shelf Bookcase Espresso
review_body:
After winning my war on the styrofoam, with our deep and creepy wall to wall carpet, I could finally start assembling the shelf. Letting you know right now, if you have wall to wall carpets, like many Americans still do, specially in rental apartments, don't assemble it on the carpet, it may get you frustrated when it keeps sticking to the cracks.
Altho some of the parts where marked wrong, the instructions provided good images, and was very easy to follow. The back panel is fastened with 28 tiny screws, so an electrical screwdriver/drill is recommended, as I used a crappy screwdriver, and cursed more like a sailor who have just stubbed her toe... The finished product is beautiful and sturdy. It has some scratches here and there, and a huge one I see they have tried to cover up, but you can barely see it. It also comes with a screw so you can fasten it to the wall.
This really made my daughters room look so much more personal and cozy now, I love it! And the price is awesome!

product_title: Modway Edge Office Chair
review_body: The majority of my reviews tend to be in the four to five star range because I consider myself to be a well informed consumer who researches most of the products I purchase.  But now and then greed gets the better of me and I would make an impulse buy solely based on a greatly discounted retail price tag.  This chair is one of those buys (offered durning a Lightning Deal) and as some of the other reviews state it has a major flaw.  Not all of the four bolt holes used to attach the backrest to the frame does not line up.  You can use the top two but the backrest will be wobbly and eventually loosing the top bolts.  The difficult solution to fix this problem is to read drill the bottom hole to attach the pieces using self tapping screws with a little epoxy glue.  The easiest solution is to buy a better chair.

review_headline: Don't Waste Your Money! You Get What You Pay For!
review_body: Wood on the table top is extremely flimsy, and mine came with one board not solidly fastened down. And I'm pretty sure that the top hasn't been coated with a sealant. Additionally, the metal table legs were not bent evenly at the midpoint where they are supposed to be secured with an iron piece and three bolts and nuts. In my case the bolts didn't even emerge through the holes enough to attach a nut, much less tighten it enough to secure it. I am trying to remedy the situation by buying longer bolts for the mid-point but I'm worried it will cause the table to be tilted. I'll soon find out. Don't waste your money! Invest in something that'll make it out of the box and through the assembly process.

product_title: High Back Executive Leather Ergonomic Office Desk Computer Chair O10
review_headline: Great for the price, but only lasted a year.
review_body: I've owned this chair since march of 2014. The only reason I'm here now is because I'm shopping for a new chair. I wont deny that this chair was great for the first 2-3 months. After the first 3 months the chair was permanently tilted to the right. I weigh around 230 pounds. The recline was broken from there on out. It was due to the cheap plastic material the body of the chair is made out of. My weight caused the screws to bend the material. It's advertised for 250 pounds but I would say 200 pounds maximum. The cushions lasted much longer than 3 months, I can;t say how long without guessing however. The cushions (even the arm rest cushions) have probably been flat since I hit the 7 month point. I've owned it for just over a year and they've been flat for a very long time. For the price it is a decent chair. I will say that if you're looking for a chair that will last you need to up your budget.

product_title: Roundhill Furniture Belledica Metal Bed Set with Headboard
review_body: As desperate as i was to order a new bed, since my old one broke, i honestly should have gone with a better brand. First off all this thing is nearly impossible to put together right the first time. Having included 1 page of instructions that is merely 3 indecipherable pictures, it would be natural to put the frame together wrong. That is, not knowing which screws go where and when to not tighten them all the way to let other screws in, confusing right? absolutely. Another thing that bothered me was the incredibly flat wrench that came with it (pictured). It's nearly impossible to use as i ended up having to use my socket set. Strangely enough the nuts would not fit in any of my sockets,Metric and standard, which merely added to the headache of putting this monstrosity together. Additionally, the black metal thing that came with it weared out after tightening 1 screw which of course made it harder to tighten all 12 screws. I've had the bed for about 4 months now and it squeaks terribly, which is sad because my old one, of 12+ years, never made a sound. Overall i am very disappointed in the quality of this product. and i advise anyone who is considering looking for a new bed frame to do yourself a favor and stay away from this.

product_title: Chill Sack Memory Foam Bean Bag Lounger, 6-Feet
review_body:
First and foremost, I've been looking into purchasing a large bean bag chair for the past few months. I was lucky enough to receive a discount on this product in exchange for an honest review. When you see the price tag of items like this, they tend to make you hesitant to purchase. However, after seeing how the chair was packaged and seeing the overall quality, I would've purchased this for the retail price.

When it says 7.5 feet, they aren't joking. This bean bag chair is HUGE! We chose the chocolate brown cover and my children actually call it our ho-ho couch since it looks like a giant ho-ho. When you open the box, the foam is compressed into a block with tape and plastic wrap. I thought they did a really good job packaging it to ensure the foam didn't expand during shipping. The foam is encased in a liner and was really easy to fluff up. The cover is made of a nice suede and looked very nice.

As for comfort, I'm in love with this thing. It's so comfortable and o now have somewhere, other than my bed, to snuggle and lounge around with my kids. In fact, since we received this, my children are constantly on it together. It's quite heavy, so when I stand it up to fluff it and flip it, my husband typically helps.

The foam is extremely soft and fluffs up nicely. My husband is a bigger guy and typically doesn't care for things like bean bag chairs, but even he was pleased with the quality and comfort of this bean bag chair.

Pros:
Quality
Comfort
Size
The effort put into packaging/shipping the item

The only con I have is the weight of the item, which is no fault of the manufacturer. It clearly states how much the chair weighs and I don't see how it could be made to weigh less, but it's just a little difficult to pick up or move.

Finally, I was really impressed that my chair was shipped and received well before the estimated arrival date. In fact, my chair was received before the estimated date it was supposed to be shipped. Receiving my chair early was an added bonus! I highly recommend this chair and the seller!

product_title: Chill Sack Memory Foam Bean Bag Lounger, 6-Feet
review_body:
I have wanted one of these for some time now, and I am very satisfied with my purchase. I refer to it as my nest, and my cats think it also belongs to them. The bean bag came in the shipping box, with plastic wrapped tightly around the tan fabric casing that contained the foam inside. I pulled away the plastic around the beanbag, and it was already starting to poof out. I let it go for an hour or two, and then put the cover on it (very nice cover by the way). Then I turned and kneaded at it - repeatedly/alternating - and then settled on it a few times. The cover does not attract/hold a lot of pet hair as I had feared. I have slept on it two nights in a row, my cats love it and frequently claim it as their own, and my sofa has been neglected. My only recommendation is that you make sure your rotate and fluff it frequently (based on how much you sit in it). The foam can settle a bit when you sit in the same spot on it for hours on end, so just give it some fluff.

It is very large, like a twin bed. If you don't want something that big, I recommend one of the smaller versions. I included a picture with this review, and hope it helps you to get a good idea of the size (excuse the mess, I just moved). I obtained this item at a discounted price in exchange for my honest review.

product_title: Home Dynamix Royalty Collection Area Rugs
review_headline: Great for boosting around in an Aeron chair!
review_body: I found this rug while searching for a way to protect the new tile floor in my home office; I didn't want to use one of those typical, vinyl, "condom like" floor protectors that you see everywhere (and that I'd always be rolling off of anyway) and so I decided to go for a medium sized rug instead.  I got stuck on this one cause my office is all neutral colors and I'm a sucker for earth tones, anyway ... I was concerned about the thickness of the rug or that it might slide around as I boosted around over it in my beloved Herman Miller Aeron Chair (I do a lot of "boosting") and so I also ordered a Gorilla Grip Non-slip Rug Pad to place underneath it (cause the reviews of the Gorilla pad just can't be denied) ...  And so now I'm a few days in to using the rug and can say I love it.  Really, it's perfect for what I wanted it for (boosting around in my Aeron chair while not destroying my new flooring) ...  It was a little tricky getting the Gorilla pad in place and then getting the rug installed perfectly over it but after a couple tries I discovered that the best way to do this was to first stretch the Gorilla pad out flat in the precise place where I wanted the rug to lie and the roll the rug up into a perfect tube and then unroll the rug over the Gorilla pad.  It's working great and at only about twice the price of those hideous vinyl Chair Condom(tm)'s? I think it's going to work really kick ass as a floor protector in my office/workstation space.  The chair rolls over the rug/pad combo without disturbing the placement in the slightest.  It's awesome and I'm stoked that I took the chance on the rug (also the Gorilla pad).  Sure my constant "boosting" might wear the rug out in a few years but that's totally okay with me ... if the price is the same three years from now? I'll gladly buy another one.  Necessary details:  -the rug shipped rolled up neatly and unrolled just as neatly; corners stayed flared for a few minutes but quickly flattened out. No problems at all with the shipping.  -the colors are 100% true to the Amazon photos  -the rug measures just about a half inch think; it is not a very heavy rug but still lays nice and flat (again, I have several furniture items resting on it so keep that in mind.  ...  All in all? Stoked on the purchase. Great looking rug and works great with my Aeron chair casters (albeit, with a really nice rug pad underneath).  :-)
