product_title: The Original GORILLA GRIP Area Rug Pad, Made In USA, Available in Many Sizes
review_headline: Gorilla Grip..Finders...Keepers.  A fantastic rug gripper!
review_body: Gorilla Grip is a terrific product.  This was the first time I had used this rug gripper but it won't be the last.  It is a keeper for me and let me tell you why.  I purchased a new rug that would be used in a heavy traffic area.  The rug manufacturer recommended a rug gripper and had their brand listed which was over double what I was expecting to pay.  I did my research and found "Gorilla Grip".  It is a family owned company that cares.  If you are not satisfied...now or for any reason later,  they will replace or refund your money.  Companies just don't make that kind of deal these days.  The product is a keeper.  It was so easy to put down and cut (it comes in some perfect sizes).  My rug was 2 foot shorter than the gripper so I easily cut it down and saved that piece to cut in half for two wood chair pad grippers.  Gorilla Grip holds very tight to my hardwood flooring and creates a safe, non-slip cling.  This is a nice thicker but supple rug gripper.  Some of the other grippers were just too light weight to do a good job and just would bunch up under the rug.  I have Gorilla Grip on my Amazon wish list now and it will be the only rug gripper I will ever purchase.  Finders - keepers, please try Gorilla Grip...I highly recommend it!

product_title: Simpli Home Warm Shaker Low Storage Cabinet
review_body: Recently we purchased this cabinet.  After all is said and done, we do like it.  However, putting it together was not a good experience.  I wouldn't recommend this to anyone who doesn't have some experience making things with wood or putting  furniture together.  So glad we had our son and daughter-in-law to help out and they even had trouble.  All the pre-drilled holes for the top of the cabinet were drilled in the wrong place and the top would not fit on.  We ended up having to drill more holes in the correct places in order to put this cabinet together.  The instructions leave a lot to be desired and, as I said, if you don't have some experience, you are going to be in trouble.  We did get it together after about 3 hours. I am happy with it and it is a very nice looking piece of furniture.  My son said the next time I am thinking of ordering  something to be put together, call him and he will pay me so I can go out and buy it already assembled.

product_title: Modern Diamond Gray Button Tufted Upholstered Padded Square Queen Platform Bed with Headboard - Includes Modhaus Living Pen
review_body:
This is the worst product I have ever purchased. The fact that Amazon continues to list products that are constructed as poorly as this one makes me question my desire to ever purchase these big ticket items from them ever again. This product is absolutely not worth the price. To say you get what you pay for would be giving this bed too much credit. Do yourself a favor and buy literally any other product with your money.

I received and constructed the bed within a few days, and that process was easy enough. However, the first night I slept on it, the wooden slats feel out and the legs on the middle beam broke, leading the bed to completely collapse. The legs and screws were bent and the middle metal beam was also bent completely beyond repair. This was after one night. I tried bending everything back into place but the entire structure of the bed was broken.

Beyond that the size of the bed itself is too big, so your mattress and box spring will look small as they don't fill the incorrectly-sized space.

This is a great bed to buy if you like sleeping on the floor and throwing away your bed.

review_headline: That one was easy to assemble by following the directions
review_body:
I got the longer bookcase, too. That one was easy to assemble by following the directions. This one went up even faster (and without the need to read the directions) because it was exactly the same as the longer bookcase. As with the longer one, I noticed that the finish on this bookcase is not perfect. There are blemishes. And this bookcase has an odd smell, just like the longer bookcase did. I imagine it will wear off in time. With the longer one, I noticed that I couldn't put very heavy books on it (it started to bow the shelf), so that it is something I will keep in mind with this one. (I think I'll be able to put my hardcover books on this one, because it's got shorter shelves.)

All in all, you get what you pay for. These bookcases don't look too bad in person, they assemble easily, and they do pretty much what I need them to, for a fairly inexpensive price, so I think they're okay. (At least until I am better able to afford some bookcases that are solid wood and far more expensive.)

My husband wanted to switch out the bedframes from one room to another and wanted me to help (when it originally took two big moving guys to do). After getting scraped on my leg by the L shape bracket while trying to move the heavy, 7ft tall headboard, I stormed out to Bed, Bath and Beyond and picked up one of these EX Moves. I came back and threw it in his direction and said get it ready while I get a fresh band-aid, and I'll be there in a minute...well, I came back upstairs and he had moved it himself. He said this thing was so easy. The lifter thing that comes with it is the best thing, there is absolutely no stress of trying to lift something to fit the sliders under the legs. I've even used it to move smaller recliners on carpet myself using this Ez Moves. This is definitely one of my best As Seen on TV purchases.

product_title: Arctic Dreams 10" Cooling Gel Mattress Made in the USA
review_headline: The cooling gel kept my husband stay cool and from sweating
review_body:
My husband and I replace out king mattress every 4-5 years. Our previous mattresses were all spring mattresses and this is our first memory foam mattress with cooling gel. We didn’t know what to expect other than we were going to be getting a new one. My husband had complained occasionally how his back would hurt or he didn’t get a well-rested sleep on our old mattress. So that when we figure we needed to get a new one. We were planning on getting another spring mattress but we decided to try this one because of the cooling gel effect.

My husband get hot and burn up when he sleep. But it the opposite for me, I get cold and need his body heat to stay warm. When the mattress arrive, it came in a big brown box probably about 5’ feet high and 2’ wide. Don’t let the size fool you; this is heavy. I got home before my husband and I was lucky enough to even get it inside my house. I tried to get it up the stair myself but I learned real quick that it wasn’t going to happen. So ladies, PLEASE wait for your husband because this thing is heavy.

Once we got the mattress out of the box, it was seal and vacuum tight in a plastic bag that is wrap over and over like 7x. We set it on our bed frame and started to unroll from there. Once the plastic is ripped open, the mattress quickly began to expand. In just about 5 minutes, it had fully expanded into a full size mattress. The top of the mattress is white quilt fabric while the bottom part is gray. This way you don’t have to confuse yourself which side is which.

We lay on the mattress and we can instantly feel the difference between our old spring mattress and this memory foam. The biggest thing is that we didn’t feel the metal spring and our body didn’t sink in. We slept like a baby that night and woke up refresh. The cool gel kept my husband from burning up and from sweating at night. We couldn’t make a better replacement choice for our mattress. Thank you Dreamfoam bedding for making such a great mattress for us. I highly recommend this mattress- you won’t regret it. It is extremely comfortable and for the price it’s a seal!!

*Received this product at a discounted price for an exchange for an honest review.making such a great mattress for us. I highly recommend this mattress- you won’t regret it. It is extremely comfortable and for the price it’s a seal!!

My Mom can get it to recline easily but does not have enough strength to revert it back to the sitting upright position, thus leaving her "stuck" in the chair. She had a recliner chair prior to this and had no problem operating it back and forth. She says she loves this chair and that it's very comfy.  I hope the handle loosens as time goes on so that she can use the chair not only for sitting but also so that she can safely recline.

This is also going to come in really handy for the next time we go to the parade in town since it is so easy to put up and down and comes with the carrying case.

product_title: Wine Cart With Glass Rack, Drawer, Holds 9 Bottles By Winsome Wood
review_headline: Not perfect, but great for cramped spaces
review_body:
I purchased this locally about three years ago and it has held up nicely. At 15 x 15 inches it takes up little space and will hold nine 750ml bottles of wine. The drawer is a nice touch for accessories like a corkscrew and other small implements (I also keep coasters in mine). Assembly was a snap. I am fairly experienced at whipping unassembled furniture together so I didn't bother to look at the instructions and had the cart together in less than twenty minutes.

Wood quality is OK. There are natural blemishes that practically guarantee that no two carts are going to look identical - but that is a good thing. I loved the countersunk holes and plugs to hide the screws that hold this together. I recently purchased a bamboo cart for another room and the screw heads were exposed. So bravo for attention to small details.

One of the reasons why I subtracted a star is the drawer will cock when sliding in and out. That is a function of looser tolerances that I suspect were on purpose so that it would work in both dry climates and humid environments. Do carefully examine the photo at the top of this page because it shows that the sides of the cart do not completely enclose the drawer. This is not an issue for a casual look, but looks out of place in more formal settings.

Also be aware that the glass holders will actually only hold a total of nine glasses unless you want to risk the fourth glass in each of the three slots falling out or only partially fitting. Another factor is the stemware quality. Cheaper glasses are more apt to fit because they has smaller bases and are overall thinner. For example the glasses from the [[ASIN:B005KPGDUG Arc International Luminarc Cachet White Wine Glass]] set fit perfectly (although you are only going to comfortably fit nine total into this cart's glass slots.)

Overall this is a great solution for cramped spaces. It's attractive in a shabby sort of way (the sides of the drawers and loose fit), but for the price you are getting a functional wine rack that is made of real wood.t for the price you are getting a functional wine rack that is made of real wood.

review_headline: I can't say enough how much I like this desk
review_body:
I can't say enough how much I like this desk. This thing's fantastic. If/when we ever move out of this house we're taking this with us, and if it gets messed up in transit, I'm getting another one.

Assembly does take some time, and that's to be expected with a desk that has this many pieces to put together. The boards aren't marked with label stickers, but the instructions are pretty good about showing you what piece is what. there's not too many ways you can screw up assembly.

The finish looks good in black and the fact that the shelves on each side can be removed entirely is a nice touch.

This desk is almost a steal at the price. I use it as a computer desk, and have a seperate side/end table to hold the printer and computer tower. You might be able to fit a small tower or mini-pc on the desk but a full tower for gaming is going to need a separate stand. It's perfect for laptops or tablets. I can see how this can be used for other purposes like a vanity with a mirror and lights mounted on the top.

product_title: Homelegance Aven Upholstered Platform Bed In Black Bi-Cast Vinyl
review_body:
The bed looks good. It feels sturdy and is easy to assemble if you have a bit-driver or drill with screwdriver attachments. The vinyl covering is decent quality and not plastic-y. The footboard is odd, as mentioned in other reviews. It sticks out from the end of the bed and is very short. I don't mind the short part because I don't like footboards that extend above the mattress. Since it is dark in color and very short, it's possibly a tripping hazard when you walk around the foot of the bed in the dark. Overall, this is almost a good product at a fair price. However, there were some unacceptable and neglectful mistakes of packaging (specific to my bed) and relating to the manufacture (in general.)

1) Product arrived with a large sliver of wood piercing/protruding through the vinyl footboard. This was not concealable as it is right in the middle of the outward facing side. There was no damage to the packaging corresponding to this area, so it's hard to imagine that it was not packed that way... And it would have been impossible to not notice. See attached photos. Frankly, it's comical...

2) During assembly, I found that one of the screen holes in the footboard, which has a metal liner, had NO threads so the screw could not be inserted.

3) To keep the feet from rotating around the single screw that attaches each of them, there are two wooden dowels for each of the four feet. Wooden dowels should be inserted into pre-drilled holes that have a bottom to them. These don't. The holes go all the way through a wooden board. They can easily fall all the way through the hole and disappear into the hollow interior. Once inside, there is no way to retrieve them without disassembling the footboard. There are no spares in the box. This is something that can be dealt with if you have a good drill and don't mind a trip to the hardware store to buy a few more thick screws...

4) There are zero spare screws or dowels in the box. I often find that there is at least one spare with assemble-it-yourself furniture.

I contacted the manufacturer via email, but noted on their website that they do no talk to customers and are wholesale only. As expected, I received no reply. I requested replacement of the footboard from Amazon, but I don't know if they will do a partial replacement. I really don't want to disassemble and re-pack this entire thing, but the hole in the vinyl is unacceptable... Will update once return is complete.

product_title: Zinus Deluxe Faux Leather Upholstered Platform Bed
review_headline: Parts were awful and of poor build.  but can be used.
review_body:
I agree with most of the reviews with low star numbers. For those with 4-5 stars, I'm not sure what they were smoking.
To start off, the parts were kept in the large head board and zipped up with a weak, poor quality cloth. When my husband lifted the head board facing up, the weight of the parts ripped through the cloth. In addition, I am missing the 4 washers for the 4 legs.
Many of the metal parts were soldered on very poorly, several important sections were soldered on crooked, with different thickness on the same joint. I hammered the metal parts in order to fit the pieces that do not align to make them fit. I am shocked as to how poorly it can be done.

One of the most difficult part to put together was the sides. Each side consists of 2 pieces that hooks on to the headboards on both ends and in the middle, hooks onto two screws of the middle horizontal metal bar. The distance of the 2 screw does not align with the length of the side pieces. We got it in by turning the side pieces out ward to line them up then simultaneously push down to hook on the screws and hammering these pieces in.

I'm giving it 2 stars as once you put it together, you can't see from the outside how low quality this product really is, it actually looks fine and, you can actually use it.

product_title: Perfect Cloud Atlas Gel-Plus 10-Inch Memory Foam Mattress - Amazon Exclusive Model Featuring New Gel Cool Visco - 10 Year Hassle-Free Warranty
review_headline: Please do not buy this mattress, even if you're not pickyk
review_body:
After giving it one final try last night, I can confidently say this is the worst mattress I've ever slept on. I'm NOT a picky person, either. I'll get great sleep on a military cot or even an airbed (which I now must defer to for the time being). Thankfully Amazon has rectified the situation and so this review has nothing to do with the extraordinary service that Amazon has provided.

Among the main issues with this mattress:

1. It is too wide. It bulges in the bottom foam section, meaning I have to stuff it into my bed frame for it to fit. It looks awful this way.
2. The mattress is not 10". It is more like 9 and a quarter inches.
2. The smell left me nauseous and practically ill for a few days
3. It traps an insane amount of heat, which doesn't make any sense considering it's specifically designed to do exactly the opposite

Comfort-wise:

1. I've awoken every morning to lovely back pain which I've never experienced before
2. It's such a soft mattress that there's the sensation that there's nothing below you, which might be good for some folks. For me, it meant the horrible feeling of sinking into an abyss.
3. This memory foam doesn't compare at all to any floor models found in stores. It's like it's not even memory foam there's that big of a difference.

Anyway, I hope this is helpful to someone. Please just don't buy this, and save yourself the trouble. I actually had to take a day off of work because I slept so poorly on this mattress 2 days in a row. Don't let that happen to you and just suck it up and buy a mattress at a store where you'll know if it works for you or not. Do not gamble with sleep -- it's a third of your life!

product_title: Signature Sleep 6-Inch Memory Foam Mattress, Twin
review_headline: READ ME - As Good As It Gets!
review_body:
This is my first review and I decided to make it a bit more extensive than it needs to be so, here it goes.

When I first moved out of my parent's place for I college, I needed a bed.
I first got a spring mattress (this one to be exact: Signature Sleep Contour 8 Inch Twin Mattress) on Amazon and it was amazing to watch it inflate in front of my eyes. Being an inpatient 18 year old, I did not find the floor very comfortable so I slept on the mattress about 20 hours in (DO NOT DO THIS). It was a great for a few days but then, I noticed that the bed slated to one side. At first, I thought it was just me, adjusting to a new bed; however, I was terribly wrong. I reread the instructions and the reviews of many others and realized my mistake. I ordered another one and let it sit for a full 72 hours and it was a bit more than satisfactory for around three to four months.

Now that we have the background story out of the way, I went over to a friend's house and she had this amazing memory foam bed. I had the best night of my life and slept like a rock. The morning after, I asked her how much the bed was and where she got it. To my amazement, She got the mattress for ONLY $150 MORE than my spring mattress AND it was on Amazon as well. Being a broke college student, I didn't have the money at the time but, I was able to get enough to buy the same exact mattress about a month later. The mattress came two days later (to all the college students out there, you can get Amazon Prime for six months free! Hop on that deal!) and I went through the same procedure for the third time. Open the packaging, cut the outer layer of plastic and then finally, I cut open the inner plastic layer. The mattress inflates and comes to life and for the next year, I've been looking forward to sleeping in my comfortable bed. It has held up in shape and firmness and I could not be anymore satisfied. Don't get me wrong, this is not your thousand dollar Tenpur-Pedic mattress and for you bigger people (I'm 5'8, 145 pounds), it may not last you as long. But, because of how much money you are saving, you could potentially replace this mattress every year and still save money compared to buying the big brand names.

Fast forward a bit and, I bought this mattress again after I transferred schools and could not take my old mattress with me. I never, ever write reviews but I feel like this mattress deserves it. For a mere four hundred dollars, you could potentially be having many great nights of sleep. Never again will I cheap out on a $150~ box spring mattress and I firmly believe I will be buying this mattress over and over again.

One last thing I would like to mention, many reviews are not giving this mattress the justice it deserves. They are lowering a star or two just because the mattress "didn't come on time" or something of the sort. We should not be reviewing the shipping process but instead, we should be reviewing the experience the item has provided. If you are reading this review to decide whether you wish to buy this mattress, I highly suggest you go for it. BUT, MAKE SURE TO LET IT SIT FOR AT LEAST 48 HOURS. THIS GIVES THE MATTRESS AMPLE TIME TO INFLATE TO ITS MAXIMUM HEIGHT. Don't make the same mistake that I made with my old box spring mattress.

product_title: DynastyMattress 10-inch Cool Gel Memory Foam Mattress-Twin Size
review_headline: Took some getting used to but I'm happy I bought it.
review_body: I have had this mattress for over a year and I wanted to get the experience in before I left a comment. The mattress was shipped rolled up in a box. It took about a full day to fully expand and I didn't encounter any funny smells or anything. It has a nice soft cover but I still put another mattress cover over it as keeping it "properly protected" is required for the warranty. My initial impressions were that the mattress was just tooooooo hard. I wanted firm but I didn't expect to have arm and shoulder pains if I slept on my side or neck pains if I slept on my back. I had gotten so used to sleeping on my couch that I don't think my body knew how to act in this new environment. After a few days of breaking it in I started to adjust to it and have really enjoyed it so far! I hate to get into a bed and feel like I'm sinking in it so this mattress is ideal for me. I have even moved to a new place since I originally received this mattress and it has survived the move and held up pretty well. It still feels like a brand new mattress (perhaps a wee bit softer). I haven't experienced any memory indentions nor have I had the need to rotate or flip the mattress. It also does a good job of keeping the bed cool. Now they could have kept the free pillow. That thing is heavy and never seemed to fit into any sort of shape. It was a nice freebie so I won't complain about that. So if you're looking for a nice FIRM mattress you've come to the right place. I would suggest you invest in a good mattress pad.

product_title: Venture Horizon Thin Man Pantry Cabinet White
review_body:
As expected, it's made of compressed wood. It ok on hard surfaces, but not on carpet. It's not very sturdy. Do not put too much weight on the bottom shelf the top two shelves, because when you pull on the handle with a lot of weight on the bottom shelf, it will resist movement on the bottom and rock the rest of the shelves on top and the connecting pegs will start to loosen as the cheap glue starts to fail. When there is more weight on the shelf above than on the shelf below, it will put even more strain on the cheap glue and wood pegs.

Once I put some screws between the pegs on each shelf, it does not have that wobble anymore, and works fine now. It is not worth the $129 I spent on it. Spend a little more money and get a higher quality shelves, it's worth it.

Its a little too firm for me and so far Ive woken up with more back pain than my last spring mattress but my body probably just needs to adjust to it. I did wake up last night extremely hot and sweaty, even with the gel infused top layer the mattress retains quite a bit of body heat. I will update my review/stars once I get used to it.

UPDATE: Ok, Ive had this mattress for another week and I'm adding a star because I'm liking it more and more. My body has adjusted I think and no more pain. Very comfortable and I'm sleeping great. Only disappointment now is noticing the price dropped $80 in the two weeks since I bought it. Very discouraging but what can you do? For less than $370 this is a no-brainer - buy it!

review_headline: American craftmanship should be better than this
review_body: When I was looking at dressers the "Made in America" label caught my eye which is why I decided to but this dresser. I get the dresser home and see that the drawer guide track hardware is mounted to the outsides of the drawers and the insides of the dresser with pneumatic staples when it should have been screwed together so it doesn't loosen up. Almost all of the drawer guide tracks are loose and shake around and not tight before I even put anything in an drawers. Once the drawers are filled up the drawer guide tracks will loosen up even more with use. Some of the staples were backed out enough that the drawers would catch when trying to close the drawer. At some point I will have to take all the drawers back out, pilot drill all blind holes, and put screws in myself to fix it. This is a disappointment before I even start using the dresser. American craftsmanship is better than this.

product_title: 100% Latex Mattress Topper - No Fillers - Reversible with 2 Firmnesses, Parent
review_body: it would seem they have fixed the 'fuzz balls' some reviewers have reported. this product does not shed anything and is made extremely well. the pictures showing uneven and poorly drilled holes are not representative of the latex topper we received. the topper is cut perfectly and the holes are drilled well and straight. the manufacturing quality issues appear to have been fixed.  they should take new pictures of the pad for their Amazon listing, as the current photos makes it look like the surface is uneven. its like an optical illusion because of the wavy pattern the ridges are made in. it looks a little like the surface is uneven with deep valleys, but actually the ridges are very shallow and the surface is completely flat with no deep valleys, only the shallow ridges... under a mildly padded mattress protector/pad you would never even feel the ridges. the pad came with paperwork stating that the pad is actually 3 different firmness's - Full wave, ultra plush side @ 14 ILD - Soft pressure relief center, 3.75 lb density @ 19 ILD - and 5lb density firm support side @ 25 ILD. although you can clearly see only two layers... sleeps cool and feels very buoyant. i think it could be a little too firm for those who want a pillow top or similarly plush surface.  i can see this topper either adding some firmness to an overly soft mattress, or providing a little more softness to a firm mattress.

product_title: Warren Contemporary Style Coffee Bean Finish Buffet Cabinet
review_headline: Great piece, perfect for a liquor cabinet.
review_body:
Great piece, once assembled it does not have the typically cheap look of flat pack furniture, i.e. it's not obviously flat-pack like some cheaper units.
Assembly was straight forward, taking a little more than an hour for my wife and I. I should preface this by saying that we have a lot of experience assembling flat-pack furniture together so we are quite efficient. It was not a particularity hard piece to assemble compared to some other pieces we have done. The instructions could be more clear in places. We were able to figure it out easily based on our experience, but just take your time and it should go together in under two hours. I appreciated that a small tube of wood glue was included, with the opening the exact size of the pegs meant to be glued. This made gluing, a notoriously messy procedure, easy and clean. The glue will add permanence and stability absent from other flat-pack furniture.
All the pieces went together nice and flush; all the pre-drilled holes were where they should be. The cabinet door hinges have two adjustment screws that make fine tuning their operation a breeze.
The pieces are made mostly of composite plywood with a dark wood veneer that looks rather realistic. Most flat-pack stuff is the bendy particle board, but this stuff has more structure too it, making the finished piece nice and sturdy.
Very satisfied with its use as a liquor cabinet.

couple of things to highlight however: the rug is slightly thin but that didn't bother me. The rug comes with a chemical odor or some sort of an oily odor, but that was just the packaging and the odor disappeared couple of hours later. Lastly, the rug was packaged so tightly and it wouldn't stay "flat" on the floor. I had to use my imagination, and i used a mattress to force it back flat.

In overall, i didn't mind those inconveniences as i was saving over 200 dollars for a rug of this size. The color was also a plus as i was not able to find it anywhere in a similar price. I would recommend the rug to a friend.

product_title: Kings Brand Furniture Modern Fabric Klik Klak Futon Bed Sleeper Sofa with Adjustable Back, Beige
review_body:
For the price, you can't really expect much more.
It's a decent sofa, good for sitting in a small room where a standard 6ft+ futon would be too crowded. It will sit three small people or two large people comfortably. The cushion itself feels cheap - like if you sat on it too hard it would deflate. It feels like a pocket of air under the seat, not a foam cushion or something more comfortable. It can fold back like a regular futon would, though at just under 5ft not many people will be able to sleep comfortably on it overnight.

Mine came with a few tears in the underside fabric of the sofa. Nothing that hinders the operation, but it's a clear sign that quality and perfection aren't what you're getting. I just set the sofa up and forgot about it.

Generally, it holds up. It's great for when I have people over and we just watch some shows or play games, where it's accompanied by my $60 coffee table from Target. Functionally, I would give it 3 stars - but at ~$160 can't really expect much more.

product_title: Jofran Oval End Table in Ellipse Cherry Finish
review_body:
The style of the table fits in nicely with our contemporary furniture and is overall a good value. The assembly instructions include a list of all parts and pictures of how it goes together with the parts clearly labelled, and they were easy to follow but took a bit of time with 12 bolts to screw in. You must take care not to over tighten the bolts or they will pull out the threaded inserts that they screw in to.

I ordered two tables, and one of the boxes had been packaged with an extra piece of cardboard wrapped around the side to cover up significant damage to the box, which appears to have been done by the original manufacturer. Unfortunately one of the table legs was also damaged. I received very good service from the shipper, who offered either a 15% discount or to ship a replacement table. Since this was going into a room with all new furniture, I opted for the replacement table which arrived promptly and undamaged.

product_title: Multiple Colors - Heavy Duty - Light Weight - Metal and Plastic Folding Stool - 400lb Capacity - Exclusively by Blowout Bedding RN# 142035
review_headline: This little stool proved to be a sturdy workhorse!!
review_body:
This stool is AMAZING! I was surprised and thrilled that this stool comes fully assembled!! This is a huge advantage for someone like me, who is all thumbs! To look at it, it doesn't look like it can hold 400 pounds but after putting it to the test, this little stool proved to be a sturdy workhorse!! Having all that weight on it and this stool stood its ground, didn't crumble in the least!

I got mine in black and I was very pleased that the seat area is a nice textured surface. I really love that the handle is built into the seat. It was so easy to unfold into a seat, grab it by the handle and instantly it folded flat again. The handle makes it convenient to carry as well as it being super lightweight.

I plan on keeping this stool in my car, as we often go to outdoor concerts and firework shows where there is standing room only. Now I have my little stool I can take with me. I can also use it as extra seating around the house!

I highly recommend this little black stool! It is just awesome and highly efficient!

Disclaimer - I received this item for my honest and unbiased review. All opinions are my own based on personal experience

review_body:
This is the sturdiest bed frame I've had in a long time. It's solid construction makes it great for adults or kids. I assembled it by myself in under 2 hours, I'm a tiny 5'0" woman. Came with the tools needed to assemble so no scrambling for wrenches or drivers. Only complaint is that very few hang curtains will fit this bed and to add or change them the bars need to be unscrewed, not sure they make hooks large enough for it either- mine from my last bed didn't fit so it's likely I will need new curtains which I was hoping not to do.

Over all, speedy delivery- 3 days early. Came with all parts and the tools needed to assemble. Solid construction. Not a quick solo build but possible. Good product at a great price point. Would reccomend to others.

And no, sadly, I was no paid or sent product to write this, just happy with the product.

review_headline: Great for adding additional space to my kitchen and looks amazing!!!
review_body:
I got this for my new place that had a bit smaller kitchen and I needed some more space. This thing was great for this. I put this on the edge of the kitchen bar it added a lot of extra space for my kitchen stuff. The thing was super high quality and was surprisingly easy to put together. I got it together with little problem and it looks amazing! It really adds to my kitchen. The extendable top is really nice since I can keep it down and only put it up when needed which is the exact width (with it down) as the end of my kitchen bar). The drawers are really nice and the extra space at the bottom gives me more drawer space than my small kitchen came with. I do not really drink wine so I did not need the wine holders, but turned them into extra cabinet space so I can store stuff in them like small kitchen items.

In the end this is super high quality and added so much extra space to my kitchen and looks amazing in my kitchen. I am super happy with this and highly recommend it!!!

I can think of nothing worse than being unable to get comfortable in your bed so my husband and I ordered this. It's perfect for him. He rests well, sleeps like a baby and it's not showing any issues at all. There was no smell at all and even though the bed is thick, he is able to use the hospital bed controls to sit up a bit in bed with no problem. He doesn't sit ALL the way up but if he had to, I think it would still work.
My husband and I liked this so much we're getting a full sized one for our little trailer.

I have a lot of arthritis going on in the ol' lower back/entire spine region and I wasn't a bent up mess while putting it together. The pieces are mostly light and fit together with ease, the top I did need help with because it's long and a little heavy for my out of shape self.
Highly recommend and I'm in the process of saving up my bonus points on a credit card so I can get me one too!
One thing I will caution, CAREFULLY read the directions for the drawer slides.. this was a serious pain in the keister for me until I figured out what they were trying to tell me.. read at least three times before attempting to put the drawer assembly together..
Oh.. and the door hinges.. those you will need to position just right also.. I had to loosen/tighten/loosen before I found the right adjustment for them, and it's perfect now, he loves it, I feel like I won Father's Day 2015 with this desk!

review_body: This desk is exactly what I wanted. review_headline: Sleep is good. This mattress is awesome.
review_body:
Had less than great expectations when looking at this. We had been looking at and laying on all manner of $4,000-plus options and we delayed our purchase because, well, $4,000!?!

Pop off the plastic and it expands in minutes, not 24 hours as some have said. Corners are crisp and not rounded. No odors after just a few minutes (I guess some was contained from being in a bag). It is fairly firm compared to our former foam topper, but after several nights we sleep like a stone as this is really just the right firmness for support. Doesn't transfer movements when someone gets up. Lots of good things to say.

product_title: T1006 Cream Green Burgundy Multi Variation Oriental Area Rug Carpet
review_headline: Beautiful Color - Pics Don't Do It Justice
review_body: I bought the purple rug for my light lilac bedroom - all of a sudden I went from, "oh, what a pretty room" to "WOW" within a second of laying it on the floor.  It brought the whole room to life.  The pics just don't do it justice, the purple is a vibrant color and it is so well made that it doesn't need padding; not even on hardwood floors.  The other plus is the feel of the carpet, it is so soft that it is a joy to walk across. I've added a pic that might give one a better view of the color, but it also doesn't encompass the real rich color.  The rug seems to be well made, time will tell of course, but I have bought enough rugs in my lifetime to spot one that's going to fall apart easily - this isn't one of them, I expect to be enjoying this rug for years.  For the price this is a steal.  Shipping was impressive; it came sooner than expected and was securely wrapped in high quality plastic with the ends reinforced. Overall I am extremely pleased and would recommend it to a friend.

Ten Year Review:

The turn-buckles that link together the corners of this type of platform bed begin to pull out of the holes into which they have been inserted. There is no way to "fix" this problem except to add metal L supports or bracing on the inside of the frame. The bed is basically kaput. The problem is caused by turning over at night, too much jolly activity, etc. Ten years is a good run, but the bed is limited.

product_title: Lifetime Contemporary Residential Folding Chair
review_headline: A Chair For The Whole Behind
review_body:
The seat is a lot larger than folding chairs I had purchased many years ago. These measure roughly 15" deep and 16" wide. There is no part of my behind hanging off the edges since everything fits on the main surface. The seat is big enough that even when I wish to slouch on the chair, which pushes your rear more forward in the seat, there is still solid surface underneath to support.

There is a slight dip in the plastic toward the backside of the seat so it feels somewhat like molded seating. Due to the dip, your rear will tend to slide to the back of the seat whether you want it to or not. It's comfortable to sit in, but I do prefer a more flat surface that makes it easier to sit on the edge of the seat without sliding back. Because you're somewhat made to sit in the back of the seat, it can be slightly difficult for shorter people and children to keep their feet on the ground if that is what they want.

There was no wobble to the legs when sitting. Everything felt secure and stable. The leg ends had good grip on my hardwood floors. They didn't scoot around unintentionally when people got on and off the chairs. The legs are nicely unobtrusive. The front legs are well behind where the front of the seat is so when moving the chairs around, the legs do not tend to be a hindrance bumping into other furniture.

review_headline: Beautiful end table for a minimalist livingroom!
review_body:
This table is beautiful and looks exactly as it is shown in photos, maybe even better. For a reproduction piece, it definitely looks like it's worth more than the price. I was concerned the base would be too glossy, but it's just right and looks great next to my dark gray sectional.

The only downside was that my package was missing the screws and washers which are required to connect the top to the base. I contacted Amazon, and since the product was out of stock, they offered to either have me return it for a full refund, or give me a partial refund for the missing pieces. Gotta love that Amazon service! I opted for the partial refund and found the screws I needed at a local hardware store. (For reference, it requires 3 screws - 6mm x 25mm and 3 washers, and since it's underneath the table, the type of bolt & head of the screws can vary since no one can see it anyway. I used a Philips/Flat head one though.)

the rotation feature makes squeaks later on, but nothing a lubricant can't fix if you get one from the dollar store for 2$ or go with whatever you like.

Would I buy it again? Ehhh No, not real leather.

Is it comfortable? Well ya, I play games with it almost everyday so I don't see an issue besides the squeaks.

product_title: 32"L HALL CONSOLE ACCENT TABLE
review_headline: Make sure you hire a handyman, difficult to assemble
review_body:
This is a beautiful piece of furniture and looks as beautiful when you see it as on the website. However, there are several
caution flags to be aware of:

(I) this is NOT easy to assemble AT ALL. I have assembled many bookcases and all sorts of furniture, but I could not
assemble this by myself. The instructions are NOT great and there are about 75-100 pieces of nails etc that you have to
put together to get this assembled.

(ii) When I couldn't assemble this, I contacted the seller to see if I could purchase the option on the website to have someone
assemble for me. They never addressed that in the email back to me, simply advised me to hire a handyman. We sent several
emails back and forth and when I couldn't get a handyman I decided to return it. The seller won't give you a return
label so you have to pay the $30+ dollars to ship it back, which is really not worth it, after paying more than $90 + (price plus shipping) to get it
in the first place.

(iii)I finally went on craigslist and found a local handyman who came out and assembled it for $90

(iv) if you are a carpenter and very handy with tools, you can probably figure it out. But if you aren't, this is really difficult to put
together. I am surprised that other people haven't commented on this on the reviews.

The table, however, is absolutely beautiful once assembled.

product_title: DHP Modern Metal Framed Industrial Canopy Bed Frame, Queen, Gray
review_body:
Dents. Scratches. More dents. I don't know where to begin. It would be steady to blame this on the shipper, but the box was pretty clear of damage. Two of the four major posts in the package were significantly dented. There is even huge glob of paint that is smeared as though it was packaged before it had the opportunity to dry. I can see the steel under neath. 3 of the four posts end caps are completly lifted. I wish i could upload pics. I had to stop mid way of assembly once I opened the posts package and saw the poorly damaged posts. I have reached out to DHP and am awaiting a response.

The packages was 100+ lbs so have a friend.
The color is a middle tone grey, not as dark as the photos: think Bugs Bunny.

I would not order again. It's appears to be sturdy but poorly crafted.

product_title: Best Price Mattress 6-Inch Memory Foam Mattress, Twin
review_body:
This Mattress played with me emotions a little, but now I love it.

When I first got it, I was super excited to lay down. I rolled it out of the packaging and let it be for a few hours. Upon first lay, I thought it was too firm, but I thought it would lighten up overnight. It didn't! I woke up super sore. I cursed this mattress, the manufacturers, and all the people who reviewed this product with happy words.

I thought maybe one nights rest wasn't enough to judge a new mattress and hoped that it was just my body getting use to it's awesomeness. When I purchased this mattress I also purchased a different cover for it. I got one that was waterproof and all that jazz, just in case. It didn't arrive at the same time as my mattress because it was out of stock. Around the time that I was cursing the mattress, my new cover arrive. I thought I might as well give it a try before I burn the mattress for wronging me in such a way.

I removed the cover that came with the mattress and oh man was that the best idea I ever had!! Immediately, the mattress plumped up like it was taking a breath of fresh air. I slid on my new cover like a dream and the mattress welcomed all the extra room. It was an immediate transformation. The mattress was still firm, but it was no longer stiff. When I laid down, I felt the mattress wrap around me like it should. I don't know what the deal with that cover was, but it was like they took a size 16 girl and stuffed her in a size 12. It wasn't her fault. And now that she has a cover that fits her body type, I am in love!!

Trust me, remove that cover. If you feel like the mattress isn't giving you all you want, it's the cover's fault. The mattress now is my favorite and I am so glad that I found it!!

product_title: Charleston-2 Platform Bed Frame - Solid Hardwood
review_headline: 5 stars but be prepared to stain/finish it
review_body:
First thing, this product is the nomad bed [[ASIN:B000KV4MKS Nomad Solid Hardwood Platform Bed Frame - Queen Size]] but with an additional headboard. Also comes with some longer bolts to attach the headboard to the bed frame, replacing the regular bed frame bolts on that end (so don't build the bed frame with the regular bolts like I did). The twin sizes don't have the "gap in the middle" issue from other reviews as they are just one set of slats.

It's thick, solid wood for a particle-board price, shipped to your door, and it's well cut and drilled so it fits together no problem. So five stars for that, easily.

The only downside is that the wood is unfinished and *looks* unfinished. The company says most of their customers leave it natural and I'm neither handy nor picky, so I thought I would too. But it looked too raw and naked even for me. I had to go out and get some [[ASIN:B000RNNF2K Minwax 63025 Minwax Water Based Satin Polyurethane, 1 Quart]] for it, and now it looks good. But that was an extra $40 for supplies and took more than a day. Account for that in your decision whether to buy it.

product_title: Catskill Butcher Block Island with Raised Panel Doors and Drop Leaf
review_headline: Wanted to love it but broken and missing parts made this a project none of us have time for.
review_body:
I really wanted to love this butcher block island. It was the perfect size, color, made in USA, awesome! Unfortunately, it arrived to us seemingly perfect, and after investing an hour into unpacking and putting it together, we found that not only was one of the doors broken but also it was missing all 6 handles, and who knows what else that we hadn't discovered yet. There is a big sign that comes with the materials stating DON'T RETURN THIS if things are broken or missing. To me, this reads as them knowing that they frequently are producing products broken or missing parts, which is unacceptable. We are building this Saturday, so I can't call them until Monday, and best case they'll have my parts to me by end of Wednesday. Meanwhile, I don't have the space to leave this half built, nor the time to waste. I am so disappointed that I couldn't get this done on the afternoon I blocked off for it. I knew that replacing the parts would turn this into a 1 week project, something I am not interested in.

Amazon is awesome as usual and will pick this up and refund me. Amazon cannot be blamed for missing parts or broken parts (before or during shipping).

I give the product 2 stars instead of 1 because I'm confident that if this is built with all parts present and unbroken it is likely a great product.

I am going to buy a butcher block island pre-assembled at a local furniture store for a little more $$$ but a lot less time and phone calls.

product_title: Bestar Hampton Corner Computer Desk
review_headline: An excellent desk with some assembly intensive work.
review_body:
This desk is not an easy assemble, and that is because it is a huge desk. I had one similar that after 12 years and four moves started falling apart. It was a matter of time before it dumped everything I owned on the floor.

The manufacture of that desk no longer exists, I'm guessing these guys picked them up and made some minor changes as it was very similar.

First The Bad: That nice little pop up stand for your computer/display? there isn't a single freaking hole between it and the little nooks underneath it. No running of cables, no anything without you having to destroy the desk by drilling with a hole saw through it. It's 2015 and yes a lot of things are winless, but come on.

There are four screws that are just a tiny bit different form a bunch of others. You not discovering this till almost completely assembled is pretty rage inducing as there is no way to get to them without complete disassembly. These aren't 'screw it' screws either, they are the screws that hold the center piece of the desk in. and give it the rigidity.

The Good: It's a huge desk. You could easily put three separate computers on it. One in the middle, and one on each end. I have a 27" iMac in the center, and an Alienware X51 mk 2 with a 29" display on the right. There is a laptop going on the left side. Still tons of room

The indifferent: yes, it's hard to put together as the pieces are big and the box is heavy. With one other person though you can knock it out in a few hours. We got it upstairs by just opening the box downstairs and carrying pieces up. You could probably carry it up, but unless you work out why hurt yourself.

product_title: Serta RTA Palisades Collection Bonded Leather Loveseat
review_headline: A good couch but with a few downsides
review_body:
I really wish I could give this couch 5 stars, but after a few months of use, it has had some downsides.

First, the positive aspects:

It got here fast and was easy to put together. My husband and I had it up and in place in less than an hour. We read some previous reviews and had the covers ready for the cushions before they expanded all the way. I can see it causing you issues if you let the cushions "inflate" all the way before putting them in the covers.

This couch is also relatively shallow, but that's what we wanted in or house and looked for while shopping. My husband is 5'7" and I'm 5'4", and we've actually had a really hard time finding a couch that fits our smaller frames. This couch, however, is perfect for us.

We both also have lower back problems, and this couch has actually helped us a lot. There's not enough room to lean back in it too far, so it forces us both to have better posture. We've both experienced fewer back problems since purchasing this couch.

If you are taller or want a couch you can really lounge on, this might not be the couch for you. It is relatively small, especially compared to the giant couches you find in furniture stores.

Now the negatives:

The back of the couch looks terrible. The Velcro doesn't go down all the way on the sides, so the fabric isn't secure all the way down. If this part of our couch showed, I would tack it down or put more Velcro on the back, but ours is against a wall. It is, however, a pretty cheap couch, so I had anticipated a few lower quality aspects.

It also had a very strong smell when it arrived. We opened the windows, and this smell went away in less than 24 hours. It just smells like a cheap, new pair of shoes. I would not put it together in a room with no ventilation. It would have been an awful 24 hours if we did not have a window in the living room.

After a few months of pretty heavy use, the bottom cushions are still really springy and the couch is not "dipping" anywhere in the seat area. However, the cushions you lean back against are a different story. They have gotten slouchier over the months, and we are constantly picking them up and trying to beat them back into shape.

However, I do have to say that the couch we had before this was a $900 couch, and it had the same problem after a few months, so I'm not sure this is an easily avoidable problem with any couch.

Last but not least, the biggest negative is that there seems to be a gap in the middle of one of our arm rests. The fabric is there, but there is no frame in one spot that is about 2x2 inches. This is only on one side, so I think this might just be a flaw in the couch we received. It does seem, however, that some other reviewers have had similar quality issues with this couch (screw holes in pieces not lining up during assembly, funky leg pieces, etc.) which leads me to believe that the construction of the couch itself is pretty cheap. This one issue isn't a huge deal, and the couch itself is still comfortable, but in the end I did give this couch 4 stars because this is a flaw (and one that my husband gripes about constantly).

In the end, I think this is a pretty good couch for the price. No, it's not a perfect couch, and you should probably expect a small defect or two if you order it, but it is pretty comfortable and sturdy for the price. We have had lots of people over since we got it who are so surprised at how cheap it was and that it came in a box from Amazon, so I take that as an indicator that this is a pretty good deal. The fabric is nice and so is the shape. If you think it will work for your purposes, I think it is worth taking the plunge.the bottom cushions are still really springy and the couch is not "dipping" anywhere in the seat area. However, the cushions you lean back against are a different story. They have gotten slouchier over the months, and we are constantly picking them up and trying to beat them back into shape.

However, I do have to say that the couch we had before this was a $900 couch, and it had the same problem after a few months, so I'm not sure this is an easily avoidable problem with any couch.

Last but not least, the biggest negative is that there seems to be a gap in the middle of one of our arm rests. The fabric is there, but there is no frame in one spot that is about 2x2 inches. This is only on one side, so I think this might just be a flaw in the couch we received. It does seem, however, that some other reviewers have had similar quality issues with this couch (screw holes in pieces not lining up during assembly, funky leg pieces, etc.) which leads me to believe that the construction of the couch itself is pretty cheap. This one issue isn't a huge deal, and the couch itself is still comfortable, but in the end I did give this couch 4 stars because this is a flaw (and one that my husband gripes about constantly).

In the end, I think this is a pretty good couch for the price. No, it's not a perfect couch, and you should probably expect a small defect or two if you order it, but it is pretty comfortable and sturdy for the price. We have had lots of people over since we got it who are so surprised at how cheap it was and that it came in a box from Amazon, so I take that as an indicator that this is a pretty good deal. The fabric is nice and so is the shape. If you think it will work for your purposes, I think it is worth taking the plunge.

product_title: Flash Furniture Mid-Back Mesh Multifunction Executive Swivel Chair with Adjustable Arms
review_headline: For the price this chair is quite good. I've had it for only about a month ...
review_body:
For the price this chair is quite good. I've had it for only about a month though, so not sure about long term durability. The mesh back does well with keeping cool. I haven't had an issue with mine stretching out yet like others have mentioned. Only time will tell. The adjustable arms are a little tall for going under desks even at the lowest setting, but are about right for resting your forearm although they don't necessarily need to be installed at all if so desired. The arm rests are made out of a rubbery foam material which seem to be holding up fine, but for those that are rough with their chairs, they will tear up at some point. The seat is cushy enough for me, and the contours are just fine. I do like all the adjustments, so I can fine tune my seating position. That was what drew me to this chair in the first place. The height adjustment is a little high at the lowest setting though. It's not a problem for me (6'1"), but I can see where it could be for those who are shorter. I was a little worried that the plastic base would be kind of weak (as opposed to a metal base), but it doesn't seem to be an issue at all. The instructions aren't great (not horrible either), but there really isn't much to it. If you can read and follow instructions, it won't be a problem for most. The best part of all is that it's silent. No squeaky squeaky like my old chair!

Pros:
Holy adjustable, Batman!
Mesh back
Comfy contoured seat
Relatively easy to put together if you can read and follow instructions

Cons:
A little tall at lowest seat height setting may be an issue for some
Arm rests at lowest setting are a little high, too

review_body: This cart turned out great!  We bought this for my daughter's dorm room so she would have a microwave and coffee cart with storage for some dry goods and utensils.  It looks great, has great functionality, perfect size, and the wheel locks actually work.  We got the black and took me just over an hour to assemble. A few tips on installation. If everything doesn't fit exactly right or seems tight when closing doors etc - loosen up the screws just a bit in the vicinity of the tightness.  I ended up loosening several  then made sure it was square - cinched screws back up starting at the bottom and worked toward the top.  The doors worked and lined up perfectly.  The other tip is make sure you pay attention to the parts - they were labeled well and the manufacturer includes 1 spare of every type of screw needed.  I would definitely recommend this product.  I saw a similar product in a home store that was cheaper and assembled but its quality its materiels were not as good as the Home Styles Cuisine Cart.  We even used command strips to mount a surge strip to the underside of the surface top because the 3 foot power cords that come with microwave ovens and coffee makers were too short to reach the wall outlet in her dorm room.

product_title: South Shore Furniture, Basic Collection, Queen Platform Bed with Moulding 60", Natural Maple
review_headline: Not bad for the price. Mine needed a little extra elbow grease.
review_body: It's cheap so I got this as an experiment on whether or not I like platform beds without breaking the bank.  First, this thing is borderline too big to ship via UPS.  It's is packaged well against bumps, but since it's long, it's susceptible to bending and cracking of the long MDF(particleboard) pieces.  That's what happened to me.  Two of the four matress slats were cracked but I worked out a partial refund with Amazon and I went to Lowes and got a piece of MDF to make my own slats. It was either that or ship the whole heavy ass thing back. The partial refund was the better option for me.  After cutting the replacement MDF to size and drilling the holes and slots in the new MDF that matched the original, I was able to put it together with ease.  For how cheap it is, it is sturdy and it does look halfway decent.  And yeah, platform beds are great with people with bad backs.  I'll probably upgrade to something nicer when we move in a year or two, but for now piece is working nicely.

review_headline: Solid bed with beautiful clean lines and nice fabric.
review_body:
This bed in my opinion is Beautiful! It looks much more expensive than it is. It has a very clean look which is exactly what I was looking for. It was very easy top put together and it is solid...no creaks or squeaks when I move around in bed. No need for a box spring so if your in the market for a new mattress, the savings of not having to purchase a box spring for your new mattress practically pays for the bed!
The delivery was a nightmare but Amazon rejected my review that included the reason I would never order another item that was going to be delivered by CEVA delivery company.
I'm still giving it 5 stars because the delivery problems had nothing to do with the quality of the bed. The bed is really 5 stars and Amazon went above and beyond to try to help me so I would also give them 5+ stars. I hope the woman who helped me reads this because I really do appreciate all of her efforts to help out.
All in all I Highly recommend this bed. The fabric is beautiful and the bed is well made and in the end I am very happy I bought it. It was also very easy to assemble but very heavy so I had to open the box outside and carry the pieces in one at a time because the box for the king size bed weighs over 120 lbs. The box was damaged during delivery but it was double boxed so the inside box was perfect and so was the bed.

She felt completely ripped off. I felt kind of sorry for her. Ok, I admit, I can notice a slight difference (I feel hers is a bit softer, comfier) but it is a minimal difference, not equivalent to the price differential at all. This mattress has nothing to envy to those thousend-dollars mattresses. Maybe the cotton wrap is slightly cheaper but just put a mattress cover and youre good. This mattress is not hot at all, it feels perfectly fine, just like a normal mattress. Also it had no smells when opened... 100% odor free. I dont know what people are talking about a weird smell, theres no smell? I'm really happy with this product. If youre looking for a smart choice this is it man. Hands down. product_title: All Cotton Futon Mattress Size: Full, Thickness: 8"
review_headline: Lasted less than a year under regular use
review_body:
Ordered this mattress a year ago. I used it as my primary mattress, not as a sofa or guest bed. It is a lot of work to maintain. I regularly flipped the mattress top to bottom & side to side, along with shaking/fluffing it on a regular basis. All suggestions from the manufacturer. I also would change what part of the mattress I rested on; switching between sides & middle. My own idea to spread out the pressure exerted on the cotton fill.

About 6 weeks ago, a dip in the center got to the point where no matter how much I fluffed the mattress, it would compress back down within a couple of hours of going to bed. I emailed the manufacturer, who after viewing some photos, declared this was normal wear & tear. I disagree that a product maintained to manufacturer standards should be like this after a year. They are currently reviewing another set of photos that highlight the amount of compression to decide if this is a warranty issue (2 attached).

The bed was good while it lasted & probably would still be good for someone using it as an occasional bed. However, Gold Bond is supposed to be one of the better traditional futon companies (intended for regular use) & it has definitely failed in that regard for me.

product_title: International Concepts Mission Solid Wood Lift Top Coffee Table
review_headline: Good Well Designed and Solid Table
review_body:
The table arrived well packaged for it's size and weight. The shipping company hand trucked the box into my garage where I could un-pack the table parts and dispose of a large amount of cardboard. The table is an import from Viet Nam and is made from a hardwood that I couldn't identify. After doing some research on the internet, turns out that the wood is from overly mature rubber trees in old rubber plantations that have become unproductive after 30 or so years. These plantations use to be bulldozed and burned but now, the trees/wood are being utilized for furniture manufacture and export. The wood looks somewhat like a cross between teak and mahogany, lightly porous and lightly colored like pine. Large pieces such as the table top are glued panels of smaller cuts of lumber. The pieces are well sanded on the exposed sides of the table.

After sanding all the table pieces with 320 grit using my 1/4 sheet pad sander, I applied 2 coats of Minwax stain which produced a uniform and rich finish. Some commenters have complained about an uneven stain finish. Minwax has always been my stain of choice and has always produced good results. I used multiple coats of fast drying Poly satin which worked OK as I brushed it on and rubbed out each coat with 0000 steel wool. I used a can of spray poly for my final coat. I think if I had to do it again, I would use Deft brush and spray lacquer because it's faster drying and easier to rub out between coats.

What I like about the table:
- Well designed; bolts together and is solid
- I really liked the spring loaded table top which lifts up and can be used like a large TV tray. The weight of the table top keeps it flush against the rest of the table
- The table fit together well; no issues
What I didn't like about the table:
- I took one star off for this issue: the table is glued together with what looks like epoxy glue. Great glue; water resistant and strong. However, if theglue gets on other surfaces, it only shows up after the sanding and staining process. I spent some time re-sanding and re-staining the 2 leg structures. Some of this was done twice and I still didn't get all of the glue off. Fortunately, most of the glue was on the inside of the legs and didn't show from the outside.

Overall, I like the table and would buy another piece of furniture from this manufacture. It's solid wood and not veneer coated engineered wood from other countries like China. If your environmentally minded, you have the satisfaction of using lumber from trees that use to be slash and burned.

product_title: Coaster Rimini Euro Faux Leather Glider Recliner and Ottoman Set in Brown
review_headline: Thumped from the start and squeaks
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:1d829003223c38d3fc8e81293eea92b0]][UPDATE 12/2016]
Feel free to read my original review and updates below, but I want to boil this down at the start with the outcome: DO NOT PURCHASE THIS CHAIR. The first one failed where the base connects to the pole of the chair. The metal literally began tearing away from the chair because the chair pole was loose and pushing against the chair base. They actually sent us a replacement chair, and from the first time we sat in it, it had a bump in its rocking motion, and it began squeaking within a month. Since then, the chair now makes extra squeaking noises while rocking, and the handle that keeps the back of the chair from moving causes a catch in the rocking motion. This chair is a total and complete disaster. After two chairs, both with significant problems, we are VERY frustrated and 100% unsatisfied.

[ORIGINAL REVIEW]
I have waited a year to post a review of this chair. It had a sort of "thump" in its motion since the beginning, but I wanted to see how it held up. Sad to say, it has not held up well at all.

The thump hasn't left the chair. You can feel the thump or jerk in the motion while rocking, and it often jars my wife or I while trying to rock our baby to sleep. How frustrating. Within the last month, the chair now developed a horrible squeak. I could hear it from another room, through two doors, when my wife was rocking our baby to sleep. She said she could barely think with all the racket from the chair. Well, today, I got under the chair and tried to find where the squeak was coming from.

I loosened and used lubricant around all the bolts. Didn't fix it. I removed the bolt from the bottom of the base and lubricated all around, even on the ball bearings I could see there. Didn't fix it. It sounds like the squeaking is coming from the very middle of the chair, not from the arms that connect the chair to the base. So I dripped lubricant onto the middle axle deal and turned the chair all around. Didn't fix it.

I've run out of places to lubricate, and the chair still squeaks horribly. I am SO frustrated with this thing. Feels like a waste of over two hundred dollars.

I've contacted Coaster Furniture, but the one year warranty expired two months ago for me, so I'm sure they will just say "sorry." I will update my review when I hear back from them.

[UPDATE 10/2/2015]
The chair actually broke. I hadn't checked the bottom shaft where the chair connects to the base for a couple months, but suddenly, the chair started thumping even worse than it was. I turned the chair over and immediately noticed that the metal at the base of the chair had actually started to break because the "thump" was actually the pole shifting slightly inside the shaft the whole time! I have attached a picture and video of the damage. My wife is small, so it's not like she was rocking this thing like crazy. This is just from normal use of the chair. I contacted Coaster, and they have agreed to handle the situation to our satisfaction. We have yet to finalize this arrangement, but the fact that they agreed at least says a lot about what their customer service is willing to do. If they follow through, I will be very happy with Coaster Furniture's customer service.

[UPDATE 10/12/2015]
Coaster Furniture followed through on the arrangement, and they replaced the chair. I'm relieved. The rep I worked with was nice. It took them awhile to get things worked out, but they did finally follow through. Here's hoping we don't have any more problems with the chair.

[UPDATE 11/30/2015]
The replacement chair now has the exact same thump in its motion as the first chair. A handyman friend took the cover piece off the bottom of the chair and noticed that the base pole of the chair had bad welds, which kept the base from being sturdy. The replacement has also developed a squeak almost exactly like the first chair did, but this time, it only took a month. I emailed the support rep and left a voicemail for him, and never received word back. SO FRUSTRATED with Coaster Furniture. Very poor quality products. We had to move this chair out of the baby's room and move a different one in because of the squeak.oicemail for him, and never received word back. SO FRUSTRATED with Coaster Furniture. Very poor quality products. We had to move this chair out of the baby's room and move a different one in because of the squeak.

review_headline: Can't imagine a better folding chair
review_body: For folding chairs, these are actually amazingly comfortable.  EDIT: Having used a couple of these for about 2 years now, I'm still impressed by them (probably more surprisingly good than any other product I can think of). Not only are they actually really comfortable, but they're surprisingly durable. I got a cat last year that loves scratching the fabric on these chairs - I was afraid the chair would be shredded in no time, but in fact I can barely tell that he's been scratching at it on a daily basis for several months. It's held up as well or better than my actual, expensive furniture.  I originally bought these as temporary kitchen chairs after I'd moved and had no real furniture yet, but I still use them around the house quite often. This chair is actually more stable and solid than the wooden ones that came with my dining set - the screws on those loosen and wobble slightly if I stand on them, but I feel completely secure standing on one of these (I'm a 180 lb. guy for reference).

product_title: Lifetime Contemporary Residential Folding Chair
review_headline: Not your standard steel folding chairs
review_body:
These blow molded chairs from Lifetime are extremely nice and light. They are light and well built. The granite whitish color is pretty and the plastic nature makes them super easy to clean.

PROS
- Light weight - anyone can carry them
- Fold very flat -- The four fold into a stack about five to six inches thick
- Blow molded plastic is extremely durable and easy to clean
- Very sturdy -- can hold a full size adult easily
- The powder coated legs are very sturdy and strong
- The plastic tips won't mar wood floors

CONS
- I did have a problem with my set in that one of the foot plastic pieces was missing. The box was pretty beaten up when it arrived so I don't know if it was lost in transport or if it's a factory defect. I'm going to contact the vendor to see if I can get a replacement piece and post to see how easy or hard it was to deal with them (so I only have 3 out of 4 functional chairs --- although I could order some plastic covers for these chairs from Amazon for the feet). My base expectation is that I get 4 out of 4 working chairs, if I can't get that, I'll have to drop it a star or two in the near future, if I can't get it to 4 out of 4 but I don't want to knock it now because sometimes things happen in transport and I don't want to be unfair to Lifetime -- they are Great Chairs and deserve 5 stars.

I initially ordered this bed on the 3rd of August and on day of scheduled delivery the package came up lost and they could not locate it moving. They were kind enough to reissue a replacement bed for me along with a 20% refund back to my acct for this inconvence it caused me. I ended up getting my bed on the 20th of August.

I also bought a service on Amazon from NYC Professional Installions for $57.99 to assemble my bed. I recommend this service as they come and literally build your entire bed In under an hour.

You WILL NOT regret at all!!!!!!!

product_title: Sauder Edge Water Panel TV Stand, Estate Black Finish
review_body:
The quality is great for the price. It was fun to put together. Took me < 2 hrs to put together (1 person)

If you're looking for a small, nice-looking stand (or a storage desk), this is it! If you enjoy putting things together, it will be an added bonus. I would consider myself an intermediate and it took me about 2 hours to complete. I did have to undo a couple items (my mistake), but I caught them early on. There is a video online, but I found the instruction booklet to be sufficient. It looks nice (I posted a photo) and I use it as a printer/router stand. The storage is not bad to store a few items to keep out of view. There was a small crack, but I covered it up with the printer. Having stickers included (matching the wood) would've been nice!

Overall, it's a great buy and looks great! I'm already looking at other matching furniture by Sauder! Great job guys!

PROS:
* Inexpensive
* Looks nice
* Storage is not bad
* Not too bulky

CONS:
* Crack on top piece of wood (should include stickers to cover up cracks)
* Instructions could be a bit better

review_headline: soft but firm. Will begin sagging in a few months
review_body: I bought this last week to replace a 'Mattress Factory' bed that I've had for 7 years and was just too firm. This mattress is soft enough that I no longer have pressure points and pinched nerves from laying in one spot too long, but is still firm enough to provide great support. I should have done this years ago!  3/5/16 I am editing this review to say that the mattress is already sagging and will be lucky to last a year before I have to replace it. I knew the 'warranty' was worthless before I bought it since you have to return the mattress at your own expense and they have lots of 'qualifiers' to prevent having to honor claims. I've rotated the mattress 4-5 times as suggested and the depression down the middle keeps getting worse. I try to sleep on opposite sides of the bed, but I have a queen size mattress so I shouldn't have to sleep in an 18" slice on one edge.   Thankfully it wasn't very expensive. This is my first time sleeping on a memory foam mattress and I love it, but I will definitely be shopping for a higher quality replacement very shortly.
