review_headline: With a little DIY, you too can have a great looking desk for half the price, thats made out of real wood!!!!
review_body:
First off, this is a great minimalist desk. It looks very clean and modern, but also classic and simple. Because of that its almost suited for any style. Its made from Malaysian Rubber trees, which naturally produce Latex. While it is from another country, the trees are only cut down after they stop producing, so atleast your not getting some unknown hard wood out of the Amazon rainforest.... The wood has the density similar to maple and will hold up well for a lifetime of use if taken care of.

As far as the condition it came in: It came in a large box, about 60 pounds. The legs were wrapped pretty well, but there was a few nicks and scratches in the wood. I think Fedex, could have been a little gentler with the package but it could have been packed with a little more care. Especially about the corners. The left front corner on the top was smashed in slightly, and I had to sand it down. It is slightly noticeable. Between sanding and painting I pretty much took care of all the scratches. Always sand!!!!!

Here is how I finished it: Prep is the most important part. I spend a few hours sanding, wood puttying and generally looking it over. I then taped up edges and other places I didn't want paint. I painted all the legs separate from the top. I did a few layers of paint and then a final layer of clear polyacrylic. Staining was a little bit trickier. I retaped the other way this time doubling up the tape. With extra coverage because stain is much faster moving then paint. I then did two lightish layers of stain, it really soaked in the first coat. Then applied a layer of polyurethane let dry, then smoothed with steel wool. I did that 4 more times slowly building a smooth durable finish. I went through the extra trouble of layering in an attempt to help make the wood more durable. Though, if you add to many layers it can chip off, thats also why its important to create an adhesion layer with sanding or steel wool.

I'm really happy with how it turned out. I used an Valspar off white (I don't remember the name) and Kona stain for the top. I spent about $150 all said and done. It was a fun project, and wasn't hard. Just took patience. If you've never done something like this, maybe try staining the underside first and seeing how it comes out. Also, if you really don't know. The internet is your friend.

Updated April 2016
Still holding up really well, a nick or two here and there but still looks sharp. The finish has also held well. I've noticed I have inspired many others to finish their desks similarly to mine. I feel honored.

Update February 2017
Couldn't be happier with this desk. It still looks great, I sit at it everyday for hours. Its finish has held up well too. I'm really glad I took on this project. One thing to keep in mind about the desk is its size. Its really only good for one Monitor. It could handle two, but not big ones. I still have a similar setup as to the second picture. The only difference being a pair of bookshelf speakers, and a small DAC/Amp combo. Not much room for anything else.) and Kona stain for the top. I spent about $150 all said and done. It was a fun project, and wasn't hard. Just took patience.

Updated April 2016
Still holding up really well, a nick or two here and there but still looks sharp. The finish has also held well.

Update February 2017
Couldn't be happier with this desk. I still looks great, I sit at it everyday for hours. Its finish has held up well too. I'm really glad I took on this project. One thing to keep in mind about the desk is its size. Its really only good for one Monitor. It could handle two, but not big ones. I still have a similar setup as to the second picture. The only difference being a pair of bookshelf speakers, and a small DAC/Amp combo. Not much room for anything else.

review_headline: Z-Line Cyrus desk is perfect for home office!
review_body: I love the desk, the clean, open look, the moveability.  An added bonus--my house cats won't jump onto the glass top because of reflections of nearby items.  Other reviewers had difficulty removing glass shavings.  I used the sticky side of tape to remove the visible pieces, then a non-scratching scrubber sponge to pick up the rest, and a quick finish with glass cleaner.  (Discard the sponge.)  And for folks who might hesitate to buy because of not wanting the top level, I didn't install it and the desk is NOT compromised in any way.  Just add small washers (o-rings) or felt pads at the back corners when inserting the screws into the side frames, so the glass doesn't get scratched.  Also, the portion of back panel that extends up above the glass top acts as a backstop for my monitor, in the event a cat does jump up because they like to rub on and lean against the monitor.  Assembly was easy, the instructions were clear, but it definitely takes two people.  All in all, I couldn't be more pleased with the desk.

product_title: Zinus Deluxe Faux Leather Upholstered Platform Bed
review_body:
The arrived earlier than I expected and that's what save it from a 2-star rating.
The good:
-The bed was a snap to put together and I did it in less than 45 mins while taking breaks.
-The bed looks great. It looks like a more expensive bed.
-The box is sturdy. There is no rocking, it's level. The legs are space and give it the right amount of stability.
The bad:
One of the supports for the slats, which supports the mattress, which supports my 270lbs of sleeping mass, would not screw into the premade holes. 3 came attached, but one was loose. I attached it with the screws provided, rolled the slats out, attached them to the top with the velcro.
At 1am the support failed and the right facing corner of the mattress collapsed (that's where my head lay).
I reattached to support with 4 longer screws (3 are provided) and while I was up I did the other 3 supports as well.
No problems since.
My advice is to make sure ALL 4 slat-supports are securely attached to the sides. If in doubt get longer screws.
Not a bad bed for the $$$...there just may be an issue in prefab.

product_title: Brooklyn Bedding Mattress
review_body:
We live at 8,500 feet, and the mattress completely decompressed within minutes, probably due to the high altitude. I’m guessing that those at sea level might find it takes longer to decompress. I was able to put mattress pad and sheets on it immediately, and we were able to sleep on it that night. There was no smell whatsoever, and I am exceedingly sensitive to smells.

Our previous mattress had been a medium-firm innerspring which had gotten progressively firmer as it aged, developing peaks and valleys that caused pain. We replaced it near the end of its warranty period because I was having persistent pain at pressure points like hips, knees, elbows, and shoulders. We are both fairly small people and that meant we needed more padding than we felt a Medium mattress would provide.

I really wanted a latex mattress because they are considered the most durable and are not heat sensitive. I definitely did not want another innerspring, and I didn’t like the reviews that stated Memory Foam was heat sensitive as we keep our house very cool in the winter. I wanted a mattress that would give continual comfort that didn’t vary with the room temperature. Per Mario, a soft mattress would be best for our situation.

The choices came down to Ikea, DreamFoam, The Love Bed, and Brooklyn Bedding. I eliminated Ikea from consideration because it seemed to come only in one choice of firmness, was considerably more expensive, had poorer ratings, and shipping was $200. DreamFoam had slightly lower ratings than both the Love Bed and Brooklyn Bedding. What was particularly nice, though, about DreamFoam, the Love Bed, and Brooklyn Bedding was that the manufacturer would vary the construction based on the degree of firmness you wanted. From reading reviews of many mattresses, it is obvious that one man’s firm is another man’s soft. The online video showing how the mattress is constructed helped us decide this was the mattress we wanted, and the difference in the latex layers led us to choose Brooklyn Bedding over the Love Bed.

Going from a medium-firm to soft was an adjustment that did not happen immediately. The first few nights on the BME took getting used to the different feel, but it was extremely comfortable. Now after 1 week on the soft Brooklyn Bedding Queen, we are very happy with our choice. Waking up without joint pain is wonderful, and sleeping soundly throughout the night gives us much more energy throughout the day. The only disappointment was that we didn’t get the pillows others received.

One tip. The instructions for set up are INSIDE the plastic sheeting that compresses the mattress! You find them as your mattress is unrolling and reinflating before your very eyes. I had read the setup instructions online, so this wasn’t a problem, but it might be better to have them outside the wrapped mattress for those who didn’t think ahead.

We bought it from the manufacturer's website and got 5% off plus free shipping.

review_headline: Well built BUT not for a person 5' 11" or taller.....
review_body:
The chair assembled easy, has nice look, durable materials and construction but unfortunately it wasn't made for a tall person even though the tilt is adjustable. I am 5' 11" and my butt hangs over the back of seat (feels like circulation getting cut off by private parts) and my knees go over the knee pad so the pressure is on my shins which does not feel good at all. I think it would be a comfortable kneeling chair for a much shorter person.....maybe 5' 8"?

I didn't want to go through the hassle of packaging and return expenses so I just kept it. I guess since it is not good to sit (or stand) in the same position for long periods of time, I decided to keep it since I have to stand up before my butt and legs start getting uncomfortable. I have an adjustable stand up desk too so this is holding until I find one that feels great for my height.
It's relatively small and light it doesn't take up much room. I tried using a pillow for the butt area but it didn't help.
I will be looking too purchase another one that fits my size. So I will update if I find anything that is suitable for my height.
